00054 var NetworkManager = (function NetworkManagerClosure() {
00055 
00056   var OK_RESPONSE = 200;
00057   var PARTIAL_CONTENT_RESPONSE = 206;
00058 
00059   function NetworkManager(url, args) {
00060     this.url = url;
00061     args = args || {};
00062     this.httpHeaders = args.httpHeaders || {};
00063     this.getXhr = args.getXhr ||
00064       function NetworkManager_getXhr() {
00065         return new XMLHttpRequest({ mozSystem: true });
00066       };
00067 
00068     this.currXhrId = 0;
00069     this.pendingRequests = {};
00070     this.loadedRequests = {};
00071   }
00072 
00073   function getArrayBuffer(xhr) {
00074     var data = (xhr.mozResponseArrayBuffer || xhr.mozResponse ||
00075                 xhr.responseArrayBuffer || xhr.response);
00076     if (typeof data !== 'string') {
00077       return data;
00078     }
00079     var length = data.length;
00080     var buffer = new Uint8Array(length);
00081     for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
00082       buffer[i] = data.charCodeAt(i) & 0xFF;
00083     }
00084     return buffer;
00085   }
00086 
00087   NetworkManager.prototype = {
00088     requestRange: function NetworkManager_requestRange(begin, end, listeners) {
00089       var args = {
00090         begin: begin,
00091         end: end
00092       };
00093       for (var prop in listeners) {
00094         args[prop] = listeners[prop];
00095       }
00096       return this.request(args);
00097     },
00098 
00099     requestFull: function NetworkManager_requestRange(listeners) {
00100       return this.request(listeners);
00101     },
00102 
00103     request: function NetworkManager_requestRange(args) {
00104       var xhr = this.getXhr();
00105       var xhrId = this.currXhrId++;
00106       var pendingRequest = this.pendingRequests[xhrId] = {
00107         xhr: xhr
00108       };
00109 
00110       xhr.open('GET', this.url);
00111       for (var property in this.httpHeaders) {
00112         var value = this.httpHeaders[property];
00113         if (typeof value === 'undefined') {
00114           continue;
00115         }
00116         xhr.setRequestHeader(property, value);
00117       }
00118       if ('begin' in args && 'end' in args) {
00119         var rangeStr = args.begin + '-' + (args.end - 1);
00120         xhr.setRequestHeader('Range', 'bytes=' + rangeStr);
00121         pendingRequest.expectedStatus = 206;
00122       } else {
00123         pendingRequest.expectedStatus = 200;
00124       }
00125 
00126       xhr.mozResponseType = xhr.responseType = 'arraybuffer';
00127 
00128       if (args.onProgress) {
00129         xhr.onprogress = args.onProgress;
00130       }
00131       if (args.onError) {
00132         xhr.onerror = function(evt) {
00133           args.onError(xhr.status);
00134         };
00135       }
00136       xhr.onreadystatechange = this.onStateChange.bind(this, xhrId);
00137 
00138       pendingRequest.onHeadersReceived = args.onHeadersReceived;
00139       pendingRequest.onDone = args.onDone;
00140       pendingRequest.onError = args.onError;
00141 
00142       xhr.send(null);
00143 
00144       return xhrId;
00145     },
00146 
00147     onStateChange: function NetworkManager_onStateChange(xhrId, evt) {
00148       var pendingRequest = this.pendingRequests[xhrId];
00149       if (!pendingRequest) {
00150         // Maybe abortRequest was called...
00151         return;
00152       }
00153 
00154       var xhr = pendingRequest.xhr;
00155       if (xhr.readyState >= 2 && pendingRequest.onHeadersReceived) {
00156         pendingRequest.onHeadersReceived();
00157         delete pendingRequest.onHeadersReceived;
00158       }
00159 
00160       if (xhr.readyState !== 4) {
00161         return;
00162       }
00163 
00164       if (!(xhrId in this.pendingRequests)) {
00165         // The XHR request might have been aborted in onHeadersReceived()
00166         // callback, in which case we should abort request
00167         return;
00168       }
00169 
00170       delete this.pendingRequests[xhrId];
00171 
00172       // success status == 0 can be on ftp, file and other protocols
00173       if (xhr.status === 0 && /^https?:/i.test(this.url)) {
00174         if (pendingRequest.onError) {
00175           pendingRequest.onError(xhr.status);
00176         }
00177         return;
00178       }
00179       var xhrStatus = xhr.status || OK_RESPONSE;
00180 
00181       // From http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec14.html#sec14.35.2:
00182       // "A server MAY ignore the Range header". This means it's possible to
00183       // get a 200 rather than a 206 response from a range request.
00184       var ok_response_on_range_request =
00185           xhrStatus === OK_RESPONSE &&
00186           pendingRequest.expectedStatus === PARTIAL_CONTENT_RESPONSE;
00187 
00188       if (!ok_response_on_range_request &&
00189           xhrStatus !== pendingRequest.expectedStatus) {
00190         if (pendingRequest.onError) {
00191           pendingRequest.onError(xhr.status);
00192         }
00193         return;
00194       }
00195 
00196       this.loadedRequests[xhrId] = true;
00197 
00198       var chunk = getArrayBuffer(xhr);
00199       if (xhrStatus === PARTIAL_CONTENT_RESPONSE) {
00200         var rangeHeader = xhr.getResponseHeader('Content-Range');
00201         var matches = /bytes (\d+)-(\d+)\/(\d+)/.exec(rangeHeader);
00202         var begin = parseInt(matches[1], 10);
00203         pendingRequest.onDone({
00204           begin: begin,
00205           chunk: chunk
00206         });
00207       } else {
00208         pendingRequest.onDone({
00209           begin: 0,
00210           chunk: chunk
00211         });
00212       }
00213     },
00214 
00215     hasPendingRequests: function NetworkManager_hasPendingRequests() {
00216       for (var xhrId in this.pendingRequests) {
00217         return true;
00218       }
00219       return false;
00220     },
00221 
00222     getRequestXhr: function NetworkManager_getXhr(xhrId) {
00223       return this.pendingRequests[xhrId].xhr;
00224     },
00225 
00226     isPendingRequest: function NetworkManager_isPendingRequest(xhrId) {
00227       return xhrId in this.pendingRequests;
00228     },
00229 
00230     isLoadedRequest: function NetworkManager_isLoadedRequest(xhrId) {
00231       return xhrId in this.loadedRequests;
00232     },
00233 
00234     abortAllRequests: function NetworkManager_abortAllRequests() {
00235       for (var xhrId in this.pendingRequests) {
00236         this.abortRequest(xhrId | 0);
00237       }
00238     },
00239 
00240     abortRequest: function NetworkManager_abortRequest(xhrId) {
00241       var xhr = this.pendingRequests[xhrId].xhr;
00242       delete this.pendingRequests[xhrId];
00243       xhr.abort();
00244     }
00245   };
00246 
00247   return NetworkManager;
00248 })();

00252 var ChunkedStream = (function ChunkedStreamClosure() {
00253   function ChunkedStream(length, chunkSize, manager) {
00254     this.bytes = new Uint8Array(length);
00255     this.start = 0;
00256     this.pos = 0;
00257     this.end = length;
00258     this.chunkSize = chunkSize;
00259     this.loadedChunks = [];
00260     this.numChunksLoaded = 0;
00261     this.numChunks = Math.ceil(length / chunkSize);
00262     this.manager = manager;
00263   }
00264 
00265   // required methods for a stream. if a particular stream does not
00266   // implement these, an error should be thrown
00267   ChunkedStream.prototype = {
00268 
00269     getMissingChunks: function ChunkedStream_getMissingChunks() {
00270       var chunks = [];
00271       for (var chunk = 0, n = this.numChunks; chunk < n; ++chunk) {
00272         if (!(chunk in this.loadedChunks)) {
00273           chunks.push(chunk);
00274         }
00275       }
00276       return chunks;
00277     },
00278 
00279     getBaseStreams: function ChunkedStream_getBaseStreams() {
00280       return [this];
00281     },
00282 
00283     allChunksLoaded: function ChunkedStream_allChunksLoaded() {
00284       return this.numChunksLoaded === this.numChunks;
00285     },
00286 
00287     onReceiveData: function(begin, chunk) {
00288       var end = begin + chunk.byteLength;
00289 
00290       assert(begin % this.chunkSize === 0, 'Bad begin offset: ' + begin);
00291       // Using this.length is inaccurate here since this.start can be moved
00292       // See ChunkedStream.moveStart()
00293       var length = this.bytes.length;
00294       assert(end % this.chunkSize === 0 || end === length,
00295         'Bad end offset: ' + end);
00296 
00297       this.bytes.set(new Uint8Array(chunk), begin);
00298       var chunkSize = this.chunkSize;
00299       var beginChunk = Math.floor(begin / chunkSize);
00300       var endChunk = Math.floor((end - 1) / chunkSize) + 1;
00301 
00302       for (var chunk = beginChunk; chunk < endChunk; ++chunk) {
00303         if (!(chunk in this.loadedChunks)) {
00304           this.loadedChunks[chunk] = true;
00305           ++this.numChunksLoaded;
00306         }
00307       }
00308     },
00309 
00310     ensureRange: function ChunkedStream_ensureRange(begin, end) {
00311       if (begin >= end) {
00312         return;
00313       }
00314 
00315       var chunkSize = this.chunkSize;
00316       var beginChunk = Math.floor(begin / chunkSize);
00317       var endChunk = Math.floor((end - 1) / chunkSize) + 1;
00318       for (var chunk = beginChunk; chunk < endChunk; ++chunk) {
00319         if (!(chunk in this.loadedChunks)) {
00320           throw new MissingDataException(begin, end);
00321         }
00322       }
00323     },
00324 
00325     nextEmptyChunk: function ChunkedStream_nextEmptyChunk(beginChunk) {
00326       for (var chunk = beginChunk, n = this.numChunks; chunk < n; ++chunk) {
00327         if (!(chunk in this.loadedChunks)) {
00328           return chunk;
00329         }
00330       }
00331       // Wrap around to beginning
00332       for (var chunk = 0; chunk < beginChunk; ++chunk) {
00333         if (!(chunk in this.loadedChunks)) {
00334           return chunk;
00335         }
00336       }
00337       return null;
00338     },
00339 
00340     hasChunk: function ChunkedStream_hasChunk(chunk) {
00341       return chunk in this.loadedChunks;
00342     },
00343 
00344     get length() {
00345       return this.end - this.start;
00346     },
00347 
00348     getByte: function ChunkedStream_getByte() {
00349       var pos = this.pos;
00350       if (pos >= this.end) {
00351         return -1;
00352       }
00353       this.ensureRange(pos, pos + 1);
00354       return this.bytes[this.pos++];
00355     },
00356 
00357     // returns subarray of original buffer
00358     // should only be read
00359     getBytes: function ChunkedStream_getBytes(length) {
00360       var bytes = this.bytes;
00361       var pos = this.pos;
00362       var strEnd = this.end;
00363 
00364       if (!length) {
00365         this.ensureRange(pos, strEnd);
00366         return bytes.subarray(pos, strEnd);
00367       }
00368 
00369       var end = pos + length;
00370       if (end > strEnd)
00371         end = strEnd;
00372       this.ensureRange(pos, end);
00373 
00374       this.pos = end;
00375       return bytes.subarray(pos, end);
00376     },
00377 
00378     peekBytes: function ChunkedStream_peekBytes(length) {
00379       var bytes = this.getBytes(length);
00380       this.pos -= bytes.length;
00381       return bytes;
00382     },
00383 
00384     getByteRange: function ChunkedStream_getBytes(begin, end) {
00385       this.ensureRange(begin, end);
00386       return this.bytes.subarray(begin, end);
00387     },
00388 
00389     skip: function ChunkedStream_skip(n) {
00390       if (!n)
00391         n = 1;
00392       this.pos += n;
00393     },
00394 
00395     reset: function ChunkedStream_reset() {
00396       this.pos = this.start;
00397     },
00398 
00399     moveStart: function ChunkedStream_moveStart() {
00400       this.start = this.pos;
00401     },
00402 
00403     makeSubStream: function ChunkedStream_makeSubStream(start, length, dict) {
00404       function ChunkedStreamSubstream() {}
00405       ChunkedStreamSubstream.prototype = Object.create(this);
00406       ChunkedStreamSubstream.prototype.getMissingChunks = function() {
00407         var chunkSize = this.chunkSize;
00408         var beginChunk = Math.floor(this.start / chunkSize);
00409         var endChunk = Math.floor((this.end - 1) / chunkSize) + 1;
00410         var missingChunks = [];
00411         for (var chunk = beginChunk; chunk < endChunk; ++chunk) {
00412           if (!(chunk in this.loadedChunks)) {
00413             missingChunks.push(chunk);
00414           }
00415         }
00416         return missingChunks;
00417       };
00418       var subStream = new ChunkedStreamSubstream();
00419       subStream.pos = subStream.start = start;
00420       subStream.end = start + length || this.end;
00421       subStream.dict = dict;
00422       return subStream;
00423     },
00424 
00425     isStream: true
00426   };
00427 
00428   return ChunkedStream;
00429 })();

00431 var ChunkedStreamManager = (function ChunkedStreamManagerClosure() {

00433   function ChunkedStreamManager(length, chunkSize, url, args) {
00434     var self = this;
00435     this.stream = new ChunkedStream(length, chunkSize, this);
00436     this.length = length;
00437     this.chunkSize = chunkSize;
00438     this.url = url;
00439     this.disableAutoFetch = args.disableAutoFetch;
00440     var msgHandler = this.msgHandler = args.msgHandler;
00441 
00442     if (args.chunkedViewerLoading) {
00443       msgHandler.on('OnDataRange', this.onReceiveData.bind(this));
00444       msgHandler.on('OnDataProgress', this.onProgress.bind(this));
00445       this.sendRequest = function ChunkedStreamManager_sendRequest(begin, end) {
00446         msgHandler.send('RequestDataRange', { begin: begin, end: end });
00447       };
00448     } else {
00449 
00450       var getXhr = function getXhr() {
00451         return new XMLHttpRequest({ mozSystem: true });
00452       };
00453       this.networkManager = new NetworkManager(this.url, {
00454         getXhr: getXhr,
00455         httpHeaders: args.httpHeaders
00456       });
00457       this.sendRequest = function ChunkedStreamManager_sendRequest(begin, end) {
00458         this.networkManager.requestRange(begin, end, {
00459           onDone: this.onReceiveData.bind(this),
00460           onProgress: this.onProgress.bind(this)
00461         });
00462       };
00463     }
00464 
00465     this.currRequestId = 0;
00466 
00467     this.chunksNeededByRequest = {};
00468     this.requestsByChunk = {};
00469     this.callbacksByRequest = {};
00470 
00471     this.loadedStream = new Promise();
00472   }
00473 
00474   ChunkedStreamManager.prototype = {
00475 
00476     onLoadedStream: function ChunkedStreamManager_getLoadedStream() {
00477       return this.loadedStream;
00478     },
00479 
00480     // Get all the chunks that are not yet loaded and groups them into
00481     // contiguous ranges to load in as few requests as possible
00482     requestAllChunks: function ChunkedStreamManager_requestAllChunks() {
00483       var missingChunks = this.stream.getMissingChunks();
00484       this.requestChunks(missingChunks);
00485       return this.loadedStream;
00486     },
00487 
00488     requestChunks: function ChunkedStreamManager_requestChunks(chunks,
00489                                                                callback) {
00490       var requestId = this.currRequestId++;
00491 
00492       var chunksNeeded;
00493       this.chunksNeededByRequest[requestId] = chunksNeeded = {};
00494       for (var i = 0, ii = chunks.length; i < ii; i++) {
00495         if (!this.stream.hasChunk(chunks[i])) {
00496           chunksNeeded[chunks[i]] = true;
00497         }
00498       }
00499 
00500       if (isEmptyObj(chunksNeeded)) {
00501         if (callback) {
00502           callback();
00503         }
00504         return;
00505       }
00506 
00507       this.callbacksByRequest[requestId] = callback;
00508 
00509       var chunksToRequest = [];
00510       for (var chunk in chunksNeeded) {
00511         chunk = chunk | 0;
00512         if (!(chunk in this.requestsByChunk)) {
00513           this.requestsByChunk[chunk] = [];
00514           chunksToRequest.push(chunk);
00515         }
00516         this.requestsByChunk[chunk].push(requestId);
00517       }
00518 
00519       if (!chunksToRequest.length) {
00520         return;
00521       }
00522 
00523       var groupedChunksToRequest = this.groupChunks(chunksToRequest);
00524 
00525       for (var i = 0; i < groupedChunksToRequest.length; ++i) {
00526         var groupedChunk = groupedChunksToRequest[i];
00527         var begin = groupedChunk.beginChunk * this.chunkSize;
00528         var end = Math.min(groupedChunk.endChunk * this.chunkSize, this.length);
00529         this.sendRequest(begin, end);
00530       }
00531     },
00532 
00533     getStream: function ChunkedStreamManager_getStream() {
00534       return this.stream;
00535     },
00536 
00537     // Loads any chunks in the requested range that are not yet loaded
00538     requestRange: function ChunkedStreamManager_requestRange(
00539                       begin, end, callback) {
00540 
00541       end = Math.min(end, this.length);
00542 
00543       var beginChunk = this.getBeginChunk(begin);
00544       var endChunk = this.getEndChunk(end);
00545 
00546       var chunks = [];
00547       for (var chunk = beginChunk; chunk < endChunk; ++chunk) {
00548         chunks.push(chunk);
00549       }
00550 
00551       this.requestChunks(chunks, callback);
00552     },
00553 
00554     requestRanges: function ChunkedStreamManager_requestRanges(ranges,
00555                                                                callback) {
00556       ranges = ranges || [];
00557       var chunksToRequest = [];
00558 
00559       for (var i = 0; i < ranges.length; i++) {
00560         var beginChunk = this.getBeginChunk(ranges[i].begin);
00561         var endChunk = this.getEndChunk(ranges[i].end);
00562         for (var chunk = beginChunk; chunk < endChunk; ++chunk) {
00563           if (chunksToRequest.indexOf(chunk) < 0) {
00564             chunksToRequest.push(chunk);
00565           }
00566         }
00567       }
00568 
00569       chunksToRequest.sort(function(a, b) { return a - b; });
00570       this.requestChunks(chunksToRequest, callback);
00571     },
00572 
00573     // Groups a sorted array of chunks into as few continguous larger
00574     // chunks as possible
00575     groupChunks: function ChunkedStreamManager_groupChunks(chunks) {
00576       var groupedChunks = [];
00577       var beginChunk;
00578       var prevChunk;
00579       for (var i = 0; i < chunks.length; ++i) {
00580         var chunk = chunks[i];
00581 
00582         if (!beginChunk) {
00583           beginChunk = chunk;
00584         }
00585 
00586         if (prevChunk && prevChunk + 1 !== chunk) {
00587           groupedChunks.push({
00588             beginChunk: beginChunk, endChunk: prevChunk + 1});
00589           beginChunk = chunk;
00590         }
00591         if (i + 1 === chunks.length) {
00592           groupedChunks.push({
00593             beginChunk: beginChunk, endChunk: chunk + 1});
00594         }
00595 
00596         prevChunk = chunk;
00597       }
00598       return groupedChunks;
00599     },
00600 
00601     onProgress: function ChunkedStreamManager_onProgress(args) {
00602       var bytesLoaded = this.stream.numChunksLoaded * this.chunkSize +
00603                         args.loaded;
00604       this.msgHandler.send('DocProgress', {
00605         loaded: bytesLoaded,
00606         total: this.length
00607       });
00608     },
00609 
00610     onReceiveData: function ChunkedStreamManager_onReceiveData(args) {
00611       var chunk = args.chunk;
00612       var begin = args.begin;
00613       var end = begin + chunk.byteLength;
00614 
00615       var beginChunk = this.getBeginChunk(begin);
00616       var endChunk = this.getEndChunk(end);
00617 
00618       this.stream.onReceiveData(begin, chunk);
00619       if (this.stream.allChunksLoaded()) {
00620         this.loadedStream.resolve(this.stream);
00621       }
00622 
00623       var loadedRequests = [];
00624       for (var chunk = beginChunk; chunk < endChunk; ++chunk) {
00625 
00626         // The server might return more chunks than requested
00627         var requestIds = this.requestsByChunk[chunk] || [];
00628         delete this.requestsByChunk[chunk];
00629 
00630         for (var i = 0; i < requestIds.length; ++i) {
00631           var requestId = requestIds[i];
00632           var chunksNeeded = this.chunksNeededByRequest[requestId];
00633           if (chunk in chunksNeeded) {
00634             delete chunksNeeded[chunk];
00635           }
00636 
00637           if (!isEmptyObj(chunksNeeded)) {
00638             continue;
00639           }
00640 
00641           loadedRequests.push(requestId);
00642         }
00643       }
00644 
00645       // If there are no pending requests, automatically fetch the next
00646       // unfetched chunk of the PDF
00647       if (!this.disableAutoFetch && isEmptyObj(this.requestsByChunk)) {
00648         var nextEmptyChunk;
00649         if (this.stream.numChunksLoaded === 1) {
00650           // This is a special optimization so that after fetching the first
00651           // chunk, rather than fetching the second chunk, we fetch the last
00652           // chunk.
00653           var lastChunk = this.stream.numChunks - 1;
00654           if (!this.stream.hasChunk(lastChunk)) {
00655             nextEmptyChunk = lastChunk;
00656           }
00657         } else {
00658           nextEmptyChunk = this.stream.nextEmptyChunk(endChunk);
00659         }
00660         if (isInt(nextEmptyChunk)) {
00661           this.requestChunks([nextEmptyChunk]);
00662         }
00663       }
00664 
00665       for (var i = 0; i < loadedRequests.length; ++i) {
00666         var requestId = loadedRequests[i];
00667         var callback = this.callbacksByRequest[requestId];
00668         delete this.callbacksByRequest[requestId];
00669         if (callback) {
00670           callback();
00671         }
00672       }
00673 
00674       this.msgHandler.send('DocProgress', {
00675         loaded: this.stream.numChunksLoaded * this.chunkSize,
00676         total: this.length
00677       });
00678     },
00679 
00680     getBeginChunk: function ChunkedStreamManager_getBeginChunk(begin) {
00681       var chunk = Math.floor(begin / this.chunkSize);
00682       return chunk;
00683     },
00684 
00685     getEndChunk: function ChunkedStreamManager_getEndChunk(end) {
00686       if (end % this.chunkSize === 0) {
00687         return end / this.chunkSize;
00688       }
00689 
00690       // 0 -> 0
00691       // 1 -> 1
00692       // 99 -> 1
00693       // 100 -> 1
00694       // 101 -> 2
00695       var chunk = Math.floor((end - 1) / this.chunkSize) + 1;
00696       return chunk;
00697     }
00698   };
00699 
00700   return ChunkedStreamManager;
00701 })();

00900 var Page = (function PageClosure() {
00901 
00902   function Page(pdfManager, xref, pageIndex, pageDict, ref) {
00903     this.pdfManager = pdfManager;
00904     this.pageIndex = pageIndex;
00905     this.pageDict = pageDict;
00906     this.xref = xref;
00907     this.ref = ref;
00908     this.idCounters = {
00909       obj: 0
00910     };
00911     this.resourcesPromise = null;
00912   }
00913 
00914   Page.prototype = {
00915     getPageProp: function Page_getPageProp(key) {
00916       return this.pageDict.get(key);
00917     },
00918     inheritPageProp: function Page_inheritPageProp(key) {
00919       var dict = this.pageDict;
00920       var obj = dict.get(key);
00921       while (obj === undefined) {
00922         dict = dict.get('Parent');
00923         if (!dict)
00924           break;
00925         obj = dict.get(key);
00926       }
00927       return obj;
00928     },
00929     get content() {
00930       return this.getPageProp('Contents');
00931     },
00932     get resources() {
00933       return shadow(this, 'resources', this.inheritPageProp('Resources'));
00934     },
00935     get mediaBox() {
00936       var obj = this.inheritPageProp('MediaBox');
00937       // Reset invalid media box to letter size.
00938       if (!isArray(obj) || obj.length !== 4)
00939         obj = [0, 0, 612, 792];
00940       return shadow(this, 'mediaBox', obj);
00941     },
00942     get view() {
00943       var mediaBox = this.mediaBox;
00944       var cropBox = this.inheritPageProp('CropBox');
00945       if (!isArray(cropBox) || cropBox.length !== 4)
00946         return shadow(this, 'view', mediaBox);
00947 
00948       // From the spec, 6th ed., p.963:
00949       // "The crop, bleed, trim, and art boxes should not ordinarily
00950       // extend beyond the boundaries of the media box. If they do, they are
00951       // effectively reduced to their intersection with the media box."
00952       cropBox = Util.intersect(cropBox, mediaBox);
00953       if (!cropBox)
00954         return shadow(this, 'view', mediaBox);
00955 
00956       return shadow(this, 'view', cropBox);
00957     },
00958     get annotationRefs() {
00959       return shadow(this, 'annotationRefs', this.inheritPageProp('Annots'));
00960     },
00961     get rotate() {
00962       var rotate = this.inheritPageProp('Rotate') || 0;
00963       // Normalize rotation so it's a multiple of 90 and between 0 and 270
00964       if (rotate % 90 !== 0) {
00965         rotate = 0;
00966       } else if (rotate >= 360) {
00967         rotate = rotate % 360;
00968       } else if (rotate < 0) {
00969         // The spec doesn't cover negatives, assume its counterclockwise
00970         // rotation. The following is the other implementation of modulo.
00971         rotate = ((rotate % 360) + 360) % 360;
00972       }
00973       return shadow(this, 'rotate', rotate);
00974     },
00975     getContentStream: function Page_getContentStream() {
00976       var content = this.content;
00977       var stream;
00978       if (isArray(content)) {
00979         // fetching items
00980         var xref = this.xref;
00981         var i, n = content.length;
00982         var streams = [];
00983         for (i = 0; i < n; ++i)
00984           streams.push(xref.fetchIfRef(content[i]));
00985         stream = new StreamsSequenceStream(streams);
00986       } else if (isStream(content)) {
00987         stream = content;
00988       } else {
00989         // replacing non-existent page content with empty one
00990         stream = new NullStream();
00991       }
00992       return stream;
00993     },
00994     loadResources: function(keys) {
00995       if (!this.resourcesPromise) {
00996         // TODO: add async inheritPageProp and remove this.
00997         this.resourcesPromise = this.pdfManager.ensure(this, 'resources');
00998       }
00999       var promise = new Promise();
01000       this.resourcesPromise.then(function resourceSuccess() {
01001         var objectLoader = new ObjectLoader(this.resources.map,
01002                                             keys,
01003                                             this.xref);
01004         objectLoader.load().then(function objectLoaderSuccess() {
01005           promise.resolve();
01006         });
01007       }.bind(this));
01008       return promise;
01009     },
01010     getOperatorList: function Page_getOperatorList(handler) {
01011       var self = this;
01012       var promise = new Promise();
01013 
01014       function reject(e) {
01015         promise.reject(e);
01016       }
01017 
01018       var pageListPromise = new Promise();
01019 
01020       var pdfManager = this.pdfManager;
01021       var contentStreamPromise = pdfManager.ensure(this, 'getContentStream',
01022                                                    []);
01023       var resourcesPromise = this.loadResources([
01024         'ExtGState',
01025         'ColorSpace',
01026         'Pattern',
01027         'Shading',
01028         'XObject',
01029         'Font',
01030         // ProcSet
01031         // Properties
01032       ]);
01033 
01034       var partialEvaluator = new PartialEvaluator(
01035             pdfManager, this.xref, handler,
01036             this.pageIndex, 'p' + this.pageIndex + '_',
01037             this.idCounters);
01038 
01039       var dataPromises = Promise.all(
01040           [contentStreamPromise, resourcesPromise], reject);
01041       dataPromises.then(function(data) {
01042         var contentStream = data[0];
01043 
01044         partialEvaluator.getOperatorList(contentStream, self.resources).then(
01045           function(data) {
01046             pageListPromise.resolve(data);
01047           },
01048           reject
01049         );
01050       });
01051 
01052       var annotationsPromise = pdfManager.ensure(this, 'annotations');
01053       Promise.all([pageListPromise, annotationsPromise]).then(function(datas) {
01054         var pageData = datas[0];
01055         var pageQueue = pageData.queue;
01056         var annotations = datas[1];
01057 
01058         if (annotations.length === 0) {
01059           PartialEvaluator.optimizeQueue(pageQueue);
01060           promise.resolve(pageData);
01061           return;
01062         }
01063 
01064         var dependencies = pageData.dependencies;
01065         var annotationsReadyPromise = Annotation.appendToOperatorList(
01066           annotations, pageQueue, pdfManager, dependencies, partialEvaluator);
01067         annotationsReadyPromise.then(function () {
01068           PartialEvaluator.optimizeQueue(pageQueue);
01069 
01070           promise.resolve(pageData);
01071         }, reject);
01072       }, reject);
01073 
01074       return promise;
01075     },
01076     extractTextContent: function Page_extractTextContent() {
01077       var handler = {
01078         on: function nullHandlerOn() {},
01079         send: function nullHandlerSend() {}
01080       };
01081 
01082       var self = this;
01083 
01084       var textContentPromise = new Promise();
01085 
01086       var pdfManager = this.pdfManager;
01087       var contentStreamPromise = pdfManager.ensure(this, 'getContentStream',
01088                                                    []);
01089 
01090       var resourcesPromise = this.loadResources([
01091         'ExtGState',
01092         'XObject',
01093         'Font'
01094       ]);
01095 
01096       var dataPromises = Promise.all([contentStreamPromise,
01097                                       resourcesPromise]);
01098       dataPromises.then(function(data) {
01099         var contentStream = data[0];
01100         var partialEvaluator = new PartialEvaluator(
01101               pdfManager, self.xref, handler,
01102               self.pageIndex, 'p' + self.pageIndex + '_',
01103               self.idCounters);
01104 
01105         partialEvaluator.getTextContent(
01106             contentStream, self.resources).then(function(bidiTexts) {
01107           textContentPromise.resolve({
01108             bidiTexts: bidiTexts
01109           });
01110         });
01111       });
01112 
01113       return textContentPromise;
01114     },
01115 
01116     getAnnotationsData: function Page_getAnnotationsData() {
01117       var annotations = this.annotations;
01118       var annotationsData = [];
01119       for (var i = 0, n = annotations.length; i < n; ++i) {
01120         annotationsData.push(annotations[i].getData());
01121       }
01122       return annotationsData;
01123     },
01124 
01125     get annotations() {
01126       var annotations = [];
01127       var annotationRefs = this.annotationRefs || [];
01128       for (var i = 0, n = annotationRefs.length; i < n; ++i) {
01129         var annotationRef = annotationRefs[i];
01130         var annotation = Annotation.fromRef(this.xref, annotationRef);
01131         if (annotation) {
01132           annotations.push(annotation);
01133         }
01134       }
01135       return shadow(this, 'annotations', annotations);
01136     }
01137   };
01138 
01139   return Page;
01140 })();

01149 var PDFDocument = (function PDFDocumentClosure() {
01150   function PDFDocument(pdfManager, arg, password) {
01151     if (isStream(arg))
01152       init.call(this, pdfManager, arg, password);
01153     else if (isArrayBuffer(arg))
01154       init.call(this, pdfManager, new Stream(arg), password);
01155     else
01156       error('PDFDocument: Unknown argument type');
01157   }
01158 
01159   function init(pdfManager, stream, password) {
01160     assertWellFormed(stream.length > 0, 'stream must have data');
01161     this.pdfManager = pdfManager;
01162     this.stream = stream;
01163     var xref = new XRef(this.stream, password, pdfManager);
01164     this.xref = xref;
01165   }
01166 
01167   function find(stream, needle, limit, backwards) {
01168     var pos = stream.pos;
01169     var end = stream.end;
01170     var str = '';
01171     if (pos + limit > end)
01172       limit = end - pos;
01173     for (var n = 0; n < limit; ++n)
01174       str += String.fromCharCode(stream.getByte());
01175     stream.pos = pos;
01176     var index = backwards ? str.lastIndexOf(needle) : str.indexOf(needle);
01177     if (index == -1)
01178       return false; /* not found */
01179     stream.pos += index;
01180     return true; /* found */
01181   }
01182 
01183   var DocumentInfoValidators = {
01184     get entries() {
01185       // Lazily build this since all the validation functions below are not
01186       // defined until after this file loads.
01187       return shadow(this, 'entries', {
01188         Title: isString,
01189         Author: isString,
01190         Subject: isString,
01191         Keywords: isString,
01192         Creator: isString,
01193         Producer: isString,
01194         CreationDate: isString,
01195         ModDate: isString,
01196         Trapped: isName
01197       });
01198     }
01199   };
01200 
01201   PDFDocument.prototype = {
01202     parse: function PDFDocument_parse(recoveryMode) {
01203       this.setup(recoveryMode);
01204       this.acroForm = this.catalog.catDict.get('AcroForm');
01205     },
01206 
01207     get linearization() {
01208       var length = this.stream.length;
01209       var linearization = false;
01210       if (length) {
01211         try {
01212           linearization = new Linearization(this.stream);
01213           if (linearization.length != length) {
01214             linearization = false;
01215           }
01216         } catch (err) {
01217           if (err instanceof MissingDataException) {
01218             throw err;
01219           }
01220 
01221           info('The linearization data is not available ' +
01222                'or unreadable PDF data is found');
01223           linearization = false;
01224         }
01225       }
01226       // shadow the prototype getter with a data property
01227       return shadow(this, 'linearization', linearization);
01228     },
01229     get startXRef() {
01230       var stream = this.stream;
01231       var startXRef = 0;
01232       var linearization = this.linearization;
01233       if (linearization) {
01234         // Find end of first obj.
01235         stream.reset();
01236         if (find(stream, 'endobj', 1024))
01237           startXRef = stream.pos + 6;
01238       } else {
01239         // Find startxref by jumping backward from the end of the file.
01240         var step = 1024;
01241         var found = false, pos = stream.end;
01242         while (!found && pos > 0) {
01243           pos -= step - 'startxref'.length;
01244           if (pos < 0)
01245             pos = 0;
01246           stream.pos = pos;
01247           found = find(stream, 'startxref', step, true);
01248         }
01249         if (found) {
01250           stream.skip(9);
01251           var ch;
01252           do {
01253             ch = stream.getByte();
01254           } while (Lexer.isSpace(ch));
01255           var str = '';
01256           while (ch >= 0x20 && ch <= 0x39) { // < '9'
01257             str += String.fromCharCode(ch);
01258             ch = stream.getByte();
01259           }
01260           startXRef = parseInt(str, 10);
01261           if (isNaN(startXRef))
01262             startXRef = 0;
01263         }
01264       }
01265       // shadow the prototype getter with a data property
01266       return shadow(this, 'startXRef', startXRef);
01267     },
01268     get mainXRefEntriesOffset() {
01269       var mainXRefEntriesOffset = 0;
01270       var linearization = this.linearization;
01271       if (linearization)
01272         mainXRefEntriesOffset = linearization.mainXRefEntriesOffset;
01273       // shadow the prototype getter with a data property
01274       return shadow(this, 'mainXRefEntriesOffset', mainXRefEntriesOffset);
01275     },
01276     // Find the header, remove leading garbage and setup the stream
01277     // starting from the header.
01278     checkHeader: function PDFDocument_checkHeader() {
01279       var stream = this.stream;
01280       stream.reset();
01281       if (find(stream, '%PDF-', 1024)) {
01282         // Found the header, trim off any garbage before it.
01283         stream.moveStart();
01284         // Reading file format version
01285         var MAX_VERSION_LENGTH = 12;
01286         var version = '', ch;
01287         while ((ch = stream.getByte()) > 0x20) { // SPACE
01288           if (version.length >= MAX_VERSION_LENGTH) {
01289             break;
01290           }
01291           version += String.fromCharCode(ch);
01292         }
01293         // removing "%PDF-"-prefix
01294         this.pdfFormatVersion = version.substring(5);
01295         return;
01296       }
01297       // May not be a PDF file, continue anyway.
01298     },
01299     parseStartXRef: function PDFDocument_parseStartXRef() {
01300       var startXRef = this.startXRef;
01301       this.xref.setStartXRef(startXRef);
01302     },
01303     setup: function PDFDocument_setup(recoveryMode) {
01304       this.xref.parse(recoveryMode);
01305       this.catalog = new Catalog(this.pdfManager, this.xref);
01306     },
01307     get numPages() {
01308       var linearization = this.linearization;
01309       var num = linearization ? linearization.numPages : this.catalog.numPages;
01310       // shadow the prototype getter
01311       return shadow(this, 'numPages', num);
01312     },
01313     get documentInfo() {
01314       var docInfo = {
01315         PDFFormatVersion: this.pdfFormatVersion,
01316         IsAcroFormPresent: !!this.acroForm
01317       };
01318       if (this.xref.trailer.has('Info')) {
01319         var infoDict = this.xref.trailer.get('Info');
01320 
01321         var validEntries = DocumentInfoValidators.entries;
01322         // Only fill the document info with valid entries from the spec.
01323         for (var key in validEntries) {
01324           if (infoDict.has(key)) {
01325             var value = infoDict.get(key);
01326             // Make sure the value conforms to the spec.
01327             if (validEntries[key](value)) {
01328               docInfo[key] = typeof value !== 'string' ? value :
01329                              stringToPDFString(value);
01330             } else {
01331               info('Bad value in document info for "' + key + '"');
01332             }
01333           }
01334         }
01335       }
01336       return shadow(this, 'documentInfo', docInfo);
01337     },
01338     get fingerprint() {
01339       var xref = this.xref, fileID;
01340       if (xref.trailer.has('ID')) {
01341         fileID = '';
01342         var id = xref.trailer.get('ID')[0];
01343         id.split('').forEach(function(el) {
01344           fileID += Number(el.charCodeAt(0)).toString(16);
01345         });
01346       } else {
01347         // If we got no fileID, then we generate one,
01348         // from the first 100 bytes of PDF
01349         var data = this.stream.bytes.subarray(0, 100);
01350         var hash = calculateMD5(data, 0, data.length);
01351         fileID = '';
01352         for (var i = 0, length = hash.length; i < length; i++) {
01353           fileID += Number(hash[i]).toString(16);
01354         }
01355       }
01356 
01357       return shadow(this, 'fingerprint', fileID);
01358     },
01359 
01360     traversePages: function PDFDocument_traversePages() {
01361       this.catalog.traversePages();
01362     },
01363 
01364     getPage: function PDFDocument_getPage(pageIndex) {
01365       return this.catalog.getPage(pageIndex);
01366     }
01367   };
01368 
01369   return PDFDocument;
01370 })();

01373 
01374 // Use only for debugging purposes. This should not be used in any code that is
01375 // in mozilla master.
01376 var log = (function() {
01377   if ('console' in globalScope && 'log' in globalScope['console']) {
01378     return globalScope['console']['log'].bind(globalScope['console']);
01379   } else {
01380     return function nop() {
01381     };
01382   }

01385 // A notice for devs that will not trigger the fallback UI.  These are good
01386 // for things that are helpful to devs, such as warning that Workers were
01387 // disabled, which is important to devs but not end users.
01388 function info(msg) {
01389   if (verbosity >= INFOS) {
01390     log('Info: ' + msg);
01391     PDFJS.LogManager.notify('info', msg);
01392   }
01393 }

01395 // Non-fatal warnings that should trigger the fallback UI.
01396 function warn(msg) {
01397   if (verbosity >= WARNINGS) {
01398     log('Warning: ' + msg);
01399     PDFJS.LogManager.notify('warn', msg);
01400   }
01401 }

01403 // Fatal errors that should trigger the fallback UI and halt execution by
01404 // throwing an exception.
01405 function error(msg) {
01406   // If multiple arguments were passed, pass them all to the log function.
01407   if (arguments.length > 1) {
01408     var logArguments = ['Error:'];
01409     logArguments.push.apply(logArguments, arguments);
01410     log.apply(null, logArguments);
01411     // Join the arguments into a single string for the lines below.
01412     msg = [].join.call(arguments, ' ');
01413   } else {
01414     log('Error: ' + msg);
01415   }
01416   log(backtrace());
01417   PDFJS.LogManager.notify('error', msg);
01418   throw new Error(msg);
01419 }
01420 
01421 // Missing features that should trigger the fallback UI.
01422 function TODO(what) {
01423   warn('TODO: ' + what);
01424 }

01426 function backtrace() {
01427   try {
01428     throw new Error();
01429   } catch (e) {
01430     return e.stack ? e.stack.split('\n').slice(2).join('\n') : '';
01431   }
01432 }
01433 
01434 function assert(cond, msg) {
01435   if (!cond)
01436     error(msg);
01437 }

01439 // Combines two URLs. The baseUrl shall be absolute URL. If the url is an
01440 // absolute URL, it will be returned as is.
01441 function combineUrl(baseUrl, url) {
01442   if (!url)
01443     return baseUrl;
01444   if (url.indexOf(':') >= 0)
01445     return url;
01446   if (url.charAt(0) == '/') {
01447     // absolute path
01448     var i = baseUrl.indexOf('://');
01449     i = baseUrl.indexOf('/', i + 3);
01450     return baseUrl.substring(0, i) + url;
01451   } else {
01452     // relative path
01453     var pathLength = baseUrl.length, i;
01454     i = baseUrl.lastIndexOf('#');
01455     pathLength = i >= 0 ? i : pathLength;
01456     i = baseUrl.lastIndexOf('?', pathLength);
01457     pathLength = i >= 0 ? i : pathLength;
01458     var prefixLength = baseUrl.lastIndexOf('/', pathLength);
01459     return baseUrl.substring(0, prefixLength + 1) + url;
01460   }
01461 }
01462 
01463 // Validates if URL is safe and allowed, e.g. to avoid XSS.
01464 function isValidUrl(url, allowRelative) {
01465   if (!url) {
01466     return false;
01467   }
01468   var colon = url.indexOf(':');
01469   if (colon < 0) {
01470     return allowRelative;
01471   }
01472   var protocol = url.substr(0, colon);
01473   switch (protocol) {
01474     case 'http':
01475     case 'https':
01476     case 'ftp':
01477     case 'mailto':
01478       return true;
01479     default:
01480       return false;
01481   }
01482 }
01483 PDFJS.isValidUrl = isValidUrl;

01485 // In a well-formed PDF, |cond| holds.  If it doesn't, subsequent
01486 // behavior is undefined.
01487 function assertWellFormed(cond, msg) {
01488   if (!cond)
01489     error(msg);
01490 }

01492 var LogManager = PDFJS.LogManager = (function LogManagerClosure() {
01493   var loggers = [];
01494   return {
01495     addLogger: function logManager_addLogger(logger) {
01496       loggers.push(logger);
01497     },
01498     notify: function(type, message) {
01499       for (var i = 0, ii = loggers.length; i < ii; i++) {
01500         var logger = loggers[i];
01501         if (logger[type])
01502           logger[type](message);
01503       }
01504     }
01505   };

01508 function shadow(obj, prop, value) {

01512                                      writable: false });
01513   return value;

01610 function bytesToString(bytes) {
01611   var str = '';
01612   var length = bytes.length;
01613   for (var n = 0; n < length; ++n)
01614     str += String.fromCharCode(bytes[n]);
01615   return str;
01616 }
01617 
01618 function stringToBytes(str) {
01619   var length = str.length;
01620   var bytes = new Uint8Array(length);
01621   for (var n = 0; n < length; ++n)
01622     bytes[n] = str.charCodeAt(n) & 0xFF;
01623   return bytes;
01624 }

01628 var Util = PDFJS.Util = (function UtilClosure() {
01629   function Util() {}
01630 
01631   Util.makeCssRgb = function Util_makeCssRgb(rgb) {
01632     return 'rgb(' + rgb[0] + ',' + rgb[1] + ',' + rgb[2] + ')';
01633   };
01634 
01635   Util.makeCssCmyk = function Util_makeCssCmyk(cmyk) {
01636     var cs = new DeviceCmykCS();
01637     Util.makeCssCmyk = function makeCssCmyk(cmyk) {
01638       var rgb = cs.getRgb(cmyk, 0);
01639       return Util.makeCssRgb(rgb);
01640     };
01641     return Util.makeCssCmyk(cmyk);
01642   };
01643 
01644   // Concatenates two transformation matrices together and returns the result.
01645   Util.transform = function Util_transform(m1, m2) {
01646     return [
01647       m1[0] * m2[0] + m1[2] * m2[1],
01648       m1[1] * m2[0] + m1[3] * m2[1],
01649       m1[0] * m2[2] + m1[2] * m2[3],
01650       m1[1] * m2[2] + m1[3] * m2[3],
01651       m1[0] * m2[4] + m1[2] * m2[5] + m1[4],
01652       m1[1] * m2[4] + m1[3] * m2[5] + m1[5]
01653     ];
01654   };
01655 
01656   // For 2d affine transforms
01657   Util.applyTransform = function Util_applyTransform(p, m) {
01658     var xt = p[0] * m[0] + p[1] * m[2] + m[4];
01659     var yt = p[0] * m[1] + p[1] * m[3] + m[5];
01660     return [xt, yt];
01661   };
01662 
01663   Util.applyInverseTransform = function Util_applyInverseTransform(p, m) {
01664     var d = m[0] * m[3] - m[1] * m[2];
01665     var xt = (p[0] * m[3] - p[1] * m[2] + m[2] * m[5] - m[4] * m[3]) / d;
01666     var yt = (-p[0] * m[1] + p[1] * m[0] + m[4] * m[1] - m[5] * m[0]) / d;
01667     return [xt, yt];
01668   };
01669 
01670   // Applies the transform to the rectangle and finds the minimum axially
01671   // aligned bounding box.
01672   Util.getAxialAlignedBoundingBox =
01673     function Util_getAxialAlignedBoundingBox(r, m) {
01674 
01675     var p1 = Util.applyTransform(r, m);
01676     var p2 = Util.applyTransform(r.slice(2, 4), m);
01677     var p3 = Util.applyTransform([r[0], r[3]], m);
01678     var p4 = Util.applyTransform([r[2], r[1]], m);
01679     return [
01680       Math.min(p1[0], p2[0], p3[0], p4[0]),
01681       Math.min(p1[1], p2[1], p3[1], p4[1]),
01682       Math.max(p1[0], p2[0], p3[0], p4[0]),
01683       Math.max(p1[1], p2[1], p3[1], p4[1])
01684     ];
01685   };
01686 
01687   Util.inverseTransform = function Util_inverseTransform(m) {
01688     var d = m[0] * m[3] - m[1] * m[2];
01689     return [m[3] / d, -m[1] / d, -m[2] / d, m[0] / d,
01690       (m[2] * m[5] - m[4] * m[3]) / d, (m[4] * m[1] - m[5] * m[0]) / d];
01691   };
01692 
01693   // Apply a generic 3d matrix M on a 3-vector v:
01694   //   | a b c |   | X |
01695   //   | d e f | x | Y |
01696   //   | g h i |   | Z |
01697   // M is assumed to be serialized as [a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h,i],
01698   // with v as [X,Y,Z]
01699   Util.apply3dTransform = function Util_apply3dTransform(m, v) {
01700     return [
01701       m[0] * v[0] + m[1] * v[1] + m[2] * v[2],
01702       m[3] * v[0] + m[4] * v[1] + m[5] * v[2],
01703       m[6] * v[0] + m[7] * v[1] + m[8] * v[2]
01704     ];
01705   };
01706 
01707   // This calculation uses Singular Value Decomposition.
01708   // The SVD can be represented with formula A = USV. We are interested in the
01709   // matrix S here because it represents the scale values.
01710   Util.singularValueDecompose2dScale =
01711     function Util_singularValueDecompose2dScale(m) {
01712 
01713     var transpose = [m[0], m[2], m[1], m[3]];
01714 
01715     // Multiply matrix m with its transpose.
01716     var a = m[0] * transpose[0] + m[1] * transpose[2];
01717     var b = m[0] * transpose[1] + m[1] * transpose[3];
01718     var c = m[2] * transpose[0] + m[3] * transpose[2];
01719     var d = m[2] * transpose[1] + m[3] * transpose[3];
01720 
01721     // Solve the second degree polynomial to get roots.
01722     var first = (a + d) / 2;
01723     var second = Math.sqrt((a + d) * (a + d) - 4 * (a * d - c * b)) / 2;
01724     var sx = first + second || 1;
01725     var sy = first - second || 1;
01726 
01727     // Scale values are the square roots of the eigenvalues.
01728     return [Math.sqrt(sx), Math.sqrt(sy)];
01729   };
01730 
01731   // Normalize rectangle rect=[x1, y1, x2, y2] so that (x1,y1) < (x2,y2)
01732   // For coordinate systems whose origin lies in the bottom-left, this
01733   // means normalization to (BL,TR) ordering. For systems with origin in the
01734   // top-left, this means (TL,BR) ordering.
01735   Util.normalizeRect = function Util_normalizeRect(rect) {
01736     var r = rect.slice(0); // clone rect
01737     if (rect[0] > rect[2]) {
01738       r[0] = rect[2];
01739       r[2] = rect[0];
01740     }
01741     if (rect[1] > rect[3]) {
01742       r[1] = rect[3];
01743       r[3] = rect[1];
01744     }
01745     return r;
01746   };
01747 
01748   // Returns a rectangle [x1, y1, x2, y2] corresponding to the
01749   // intersection of rect1 and rect2. If no intersection, returns 'false'
01750   // The rectangle coordinates of rect1, rect2 should be [x1, y1, x2, y2]
01751   Util.intersect = function Util_intersect(rect1, rect2) {
01752     function compare(a, b) {
01753       return a - b;
01754     }
01755 
01756     // Order points along the axes
01757     var orderedX = [rect1[0], rect1[2], rect2[0], rect2[2]].sort(compare),
01758         orderedY = [rect1[1], rect1[3], rect2[1], rect2[3]].sort(compare),
01759         result = [];
01760 
01761     rect1 = Util.normalizeRect(rect1);
01762     rect2 = Util.normalizeRect(rect2);
01763 
01764     // X: first and second points belong to different rectangles?
01765     if ((orderedX[0] === rect1[0] && orderedX[1] === rect2[0]) ||
01766         (orderedX[0] === rect2[0] && orderedX[1] === rect1[0])) {
01767       // Intersection must be between second and third points
01768       result[0] = orderedX[1];
01769       result[2] = orderedX[2];
01770     } else {
01771       return false;
01772     }
01773 
01774     // Y: first and second points belong to different rectangles?
01775     if ((orderedY[0] === rect1[1] && orderedY[1] === rect2[1]) ||
01776         (orderedY[0] === rect2[1] && orderedY[1] === rect1[1])) {
01777       // Intersection must be between second and third points
01778       result[1] = orderedY[1];
01779       result[3] = orderedY[2];
01780     } else {
01781       return false;
01782     }
01783 
01784     return result;
01785   };
01786 
01787   Util.sign = function Util_sign(num) {
01788     return num < 0 ? -1 : 1;
01789   };
01790 
01791   // TODO(mack): Rename appendToArray

01793     Array.prototype.push.apply(arr1, arr2);
01794   };
01795 
01796   Util.prependToArray = function concatenateToArray(arr1, arr2) {
01797     Array.prototype.unshift.apply(arr1, arr2);
01798   };

01800   Util.extendObj = function extendObj(obj1, obj2) {
01801     for (var key in obj2) {
01802       obj1[key] = obj2[key];
01803     }
01804   };

01806   Util.getInheritableProperty = function Util_getInheritableProperty(dict,
01807                                                                      name) {
01808     while (dict && !dict.has(name)) {
01809       dict = dict.get('Parent');
01810     }
01811     if (!dict) {
01812       return null;
01813     }
01814     return dict.get(name);
01815   };

01817   Util.inherit = function Util_inherit(sub, base, prototype) {
01818     sub.prototype = Object.create(base.prototype);
01819     sub.prototype.constructor = sub;
01820     for (var prop in prototype) {
01821       sub.prototype[prop] = prototype[prop];
01822     }
01823   };

01828 var PageViewport = PDFJS.PageViewport = (function PageViewportClosure() {
01829   function PageViewport(viewBox, scale, rotation, offsetX, offsetY, dontFlip) {
01830     this.viewBox = viewBox;
01831     this.scale = scale;
01832     this.rotation = rotation;
01833     this.offsetX = offsetX;
01834     this.offsetY = offsetY;
01835 
01836     // creating transform to convert pdf coordinate system to the normal
01837     // canvas like coordinates taking in account scale and rotation
01838     var centerX = (viewBox[2] + viewBox[0]) / 2;
01839     var centerY = (viewBox[3] + viewBox[1]) / 2;
01840     var rotateA, rotateB, rotateC, rotateD;
01841     rotation = rotation % 360;
01842     rotation = rotation < 0 ? rotation + 360 : rotation;
01843     switch (rotation) {
01844       case 180:
01845         rotateA = -1; rotateB = 0; rotateC = 0; rotateD = 1;
01846         break;
01847       case 90:
01848         rotateA = 0; rotateB = 1; rotateC = 1; rotateD = 0;
01849         break;
01850       case 270:
01851         rotateA = 0; rotateB = -1; rotateC = -1; rotateD = 0;
01852         break;
01853       //case 0:
01854       default:
01855         rotateA = 1; rotateB = 0; rotateC = 0; rotateD = -1;
01856         break;
01857     }
01858 
01859     if (dontFlip) {
01860       rotateC = -rotateC; rotateD = -rotateD;
01861     }
01862 
01863     var offsetCanvasX, offsetCanvasY;
01864     var width, height;
01865     if (rotateA === 0) {
01866       offsetCanvasX = Math.abs(centerY - viewBox[1]) * scale + offsetX;
01867       offsetCanvasY = Math.abs(centerX - viewBox[0]) * scale + offsetY;
01868       width = Math.abs(viewBox[3] - viewBox[1]) * scale;
01869       height = Math.abs(viewBox[2] - viewBox[0]) * scale;
01870     } else {
01871       offsetCanvasX = Math.abs(centerX - viewBox[0]) * scale + offsetX;
01872       offsetCanvasY = Math.abs(centerY - viewBox[1]) * scale + offsetY;
01873       width = Math.abs(viewBox[2] - viewBox[0]) * scale;
01874       height = Math.abs(viewBox[3] - viewBox[1]) * scale;
01875     }
01876     // creating transform for the following operations:
01877     // translate(-centerX, -centerY), rotate and flip vertically,
01878     // scale, and translate(offsetCanvasX, offsetCanvasY)
01879     this.transform = [
01880       rotateA * scale,
01881       rotateB * scale,
01882       rotateC * scale,
01883       rotateD * scale,
01884       offsetCanvasX - rotateA * scale * centerX - rotateC * scale * centerY,
01885       offsetCanvasY - rotateB * scale * centerX - rotateD * scale * centerY
01886     ];
01887 
01888     this.width = width;
01889     this.height = height;
01890     this.fontScale = scale;
01891   }
01892   PageViewport.prototype = {
01893     clone: function PageViewPort_clone(args) {
01894       args = args || {};
01895       var scale = 'scale' in args ? args.scale : this.scale;
01896       var rotation = 'rotation' in args ? args.rotation : this.rotation;
01897       return new PageViewport(this.viewBox.slice(), scale, rotation,
01898                               this.offsetX, this.offsetY, args.dontFlip);
01899     },
01900     convertToViewportPoint: function PageViewport_convertToViewportPoint(x, y) {
01901       return Util.applyTransform([x, y], this.transform);
01902     },
01903     convertToViewportRectangle:
01904       function PageViewport_convertToViewportRectangle(rect) {
01905       var tl = Util.applyTransform([rect[0], rect[1]], this.transform);
01906       var br = Util.applyTransform([rect[2], rect[3]], this.transform);
01907       return [tl[0], tl[1], br[0], br[1]];
01908     },
01909     convertToPdfPoint: function PageViewport_convertToPdfPoint(x, y) {
01910       return Util.applyInverseTransform([x, y], this.transform);
01911     }
01912   };
01913   return PageViewport;
01914 })();

01928 function stringToPDFString(str) {
01929   var i, n = str.length, str2 = '';
01930   if (str[0] === '\xFE' && str[1] === '\xFF') {
01931     // UTF16BE BOM
01932     for (i = 2; i < n; i += 2)
01933       str2 += String.fromCharCode(
01934         (str.charCodeAt(i) << 8) | str.charCodeAt(i + 1));
01935   } else {
01936     for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
01937       var code = PDFStringTranslateTable[str.charCodeAt(i)];
01938       str2 += code ? String.fromCharCode(code) : str.charAt(i);
01939     }
01940   }
01941   return str2;
01942 }

01944 function stringToUTF8String(str) {
01945   return decodeURIComponent(escape(str));
01946 }

01959 function isInt(v) {
01960   return typeof v == 'number' && ((v | 0) == v);
01961 }

01983 function isDict(v, type) {
01984   if (!(v instanceof Dict)) {
01985     return false;
01986   }
01987   if (!type) {
01988     return true;
01989   }
01990   var dictType = v.get('Type');
01991   return isName(dictType) && dictType.name == type;
01992 }

01998 function isStream(v) {
01999   return typeof v == 'object' && v !== null && v !== undefined &&
02000          ('getBytes' in v);
02001 }

02003 function isArrayBuffer(v) {
02004   return typeof v == 'object' && v !== null && v !== undefined &&
02005          ('byteLength' in v);
02006 }

02012 function isPDFFunction(v) {
02013   var fnDict;
02014   if (typeof v != 'object')
02015     return false;
02016   else if (isDict(v))
02017     fnDict = v;
02018   else if (isStream(v))
02019     fnDict = v.dict;
02020   else
02021     return false;
02022   return fnDict.has('FunctionType');
02023 }

02034 var Promise = PDFJS.Promise = (function PromiseClosure() {
02035   var STATUS_PENDING = 0;
02036   var STATUS_RESOLVED = 1;
02037   var STATUS_REJECTED = 2;
02038 
02039   // In an attempt to avoid silent exceptions, unhandled rejections are
02040   // tracked and if they aren't handled in a certain amount of time an
02041   // error is logged.
02042   var REJECTION_TIMEOUT = 500;
02043 
02044   var HandlerManager = {
02045     handlers: [],
02046     running: false,
02047     unhandledRejections: [],
02048     pendingRejectionCheck: false,
02049 
02050     scheduleHandlers: function scheduleHandlers(promise) {
02051       if (promise._status == STATUS_PENDING) {
02052         return;
02053       }
02054 
02055       this.handlers = this.handlers.concat(promise._handlers);
02056       promise._handlers = [];
02057 
02058       if (this.running) {
02059         return;
02060       }
02061       this.running = true;
02062 
02063       setTimeout(this.runHandlers.bind(this), 0);
02064     },
02065 
02066     runHandlers: function runHandlers() {
02067       while (this.handlers.length > 0) {
02068         var handler = this.handlers.shift();
02069 
02070         var nextStatus = handler.thisPromise._status;
02071         var nextValue = handler.thisPromise._value;
02072 
02073         try {
02074           if (nextStatus === STATUS_RESOLVED) {
02075             if (typeof(handler.onResolve) == 'function') {
02076               nextValue = handler.onResolve(nextValue);
02077             }
02078           } else if (typeof(handler.onReject) === 'function') {
02079               nextValue = handler.onReject(nextValue);
02080               nextStatus = STATUS_RESOLVED;
02081 
02082               if (handler.thisPromise._unhandledRejection) {
02083                 this.removeUnhandeledRejection(handler.thisPromise);
02084               }
02085           }
02086         } catch (ex) {
02087           nextStatus = STATUS_REJECTED;
02088           nextValue = ex;
02089         }
02090 
02091         handler.nextPromise._updateStatus(nextStatus, nextValue);
02092       }
02093 
02094       this.running = false;
02095     },
02096 
02097     addUnhandledRejection: function addUnhandledRejection(promise) {
02098       this.unhandledRejections.push({
02099         promise: promise,
02100         time: Date.now()
02101       });
02102       this.scheduleRejectionCheck();
02103     },
02104 
02105     removeUnhandeledRejection: function removeUnhandeledRejection(promise) {
02106       promise._unhandledRejection = false;
02107       for (var i = 0; i < this.unhandledRejections.length; i++) {
02108         if (this.unhandledRejections[i].promise === promise) {
02109           this.unhandledRejections.splice(i);
02110           i--;
02111         }
02112       }
02113     },
02114 
02115     scheduleRejectionCheck: function scheduleRejectionCheck() {
02116       if (this.pendingRejectionCheck) {
02117         return;
02118       }
02119       this.pendingRejectionCheck = true;
02120       setTimeout(function rejectionCheck() {
02121         this.pendingRejectionCheck = false;
02122         var now = Date.now();
02123         for (var i = 0; i < this.unhandledRejections.length; i++) {
02124           if (now - this.unhandledRejections[i].time > REJECTION_TIMEOUT) {
02125             warn('Unhandled rejection: ' +
02126                  this.unhandledRejections[i].promise._value);
02127             this.unhandledRejections.splice(i);
02128             i--;
02129           }
02130         }
02131         if (this.unhandledRejections.length) {
02132           this.scheduleRejectionCheck();
02133         }
02134       }.bind(this), REJECTION_TIMEOUT);
02135     }
02136   };
02137 
02138   function Promise() {
02139     this._status = STATUS_PENDING;
02140     this._handlers = [];
02141   }
02148   Promise.all = function Promise_all(promises) {
02149     var deferred = new Promise();
02150     var unresolved = promises.length;
02151     var results = [];
02152     if (unresolved === 0) {
02153       deferred.resolve(results);
02154       return deferred;
02155     }
02156     function reject(reason) {
02157       if (deferred._status === STATUS_REJECTED) {
02158         return;
02159       }
02160       results = [];
02161       deferred.reject(reason);
02162     }
02163     for (var i = 0, ii = promises.length; i < ii; ++i) {
02164       var promise = promises[i];
02165       promise.then((function(i) {
02166         return function(value) {
02167           if (deferred._status === STATUS_REJECTED) {
02168             return;
02169           }
02170           results[i] = value;
02171           unresolved--;
02172           if (unresolved === 0)
02173             deferred.resolve(results);
02174         };
02175       })(i), reject);
02176     }
02177     return deferred;
02178   };
02179 
02180   Promise.prototype = {
02181     _status: null,
02182     _value: null,
02183     _handlers: null,
02184     _unhandledRejection: null,
02185 
02186     _updateStatus: function Promise__updateStatus(status, value) {
02187       if (this._status === STATUS_RESOLVED ||
02188           this._status === STATUS_REJECTED) {
02189         return;
02190       }
02191 
02192       if (status == STATUS_RESOLVED &&
02193           value && typeof(value.then) === 'function') {
02194         value.then(this._updateStatus.bind(this, STATUS_RESOLVED),
02195                    this._updateStatus.bind(this, STATUS_REJECTED));
02196         return;
02197       }
02198 
02199       this._status = status;
02200       this._value = value;
02201 
02202       if (status === STATUS_REJECTED && this._handlers.length === 0) {
02203         this._unhandledRejection = true;
02204         HandlerManager.addUnhandledRejection(this);
02205       }
02206 
02207       HandlerManager.scheduleHandlers(this);
02208     },
02209 
02210     get isResolved() {
02211       return this._status === STATUS_RESOLVED;
02212     },
02213 
02214     get isRejected() {
02215       return this._status === STATUS_REJECTED;
02216     },
02217 
02218     resolve: function Promise_resolve(value) {
02219       this._updateStatus(STATUS_RESOLVED, value);
02220     },
02221 
02222     reject: function Promise_reject(reason) {
02223       this._updateStatus(STATUS_REJECTED, reason);
02224     },
02225 
02226     then: function Promise_then(onResolve, onReject) {
02227       var nextPromise = new Promise();
02228       this._handlers.push({
02229         thisPromise: this,
02230         onResolve: onResolve,
02231         onReject: onReject,
02232         nextPromise: nextPromise
02233       });
02234       HandlerManager.scheduleHandlers(this);
02235       return nextPromise;
02236     }
02237   };
02238 
02239   return Promise;
02240 })();

02242 var StatTimer = (function StatTimerClosure() {
02243   function rpad(str, pad, length) {
02244     while (str.length < length)
02245       str += pad;
02246     return str;
02247   }
02248   function StatTimer() {
02249     this.started = {};
02250     this.times = [];
02251     this.enabled = true;
02252   }
02253   StatTimer.prototype = {
02254     time: function StatTimer_time(name) {
02255       if (!this.enabled)
02256         return;
02257       if (name in this.started)
02258         throw 'Timer is already running for ' + name;
02259       this.started[name] = Date.now();
02260     },
02261     timeEnd: function StatTimer_timeEnd(name) {
02262       if (!this.enabled)
02263         return;
02264       if (!(name in this.started))
02265         throw 'Timer has not been started for ' + name;
02266       this.times.push({
02267         'name': name,
02268         'start': this.started[name],
02269         'end': Date.now()
02270       });
02271       // Remove timer from started so it can be called again.
02272       delete this.started[name];
02273     },
02274     toString: function StatTimer_toString() {
02275       var times = this.times;
02276       var out = '';
02277       // Find the longest name for padding purposes.
02278       var longest = 0;
02279       for (var i = 0, ii = times.length; i < ii; ++i) {
02280         var name = times[i]['name'];
02281         if (name.length > longest)
02282           longest = name.length;
02283       }
02284       for (var i = 0, ii = times.length; i < ii; ++i) {
02285         var span = times[i];
02286         var duration = span.end - span.start;
02287         out += rpad(span['name'], ' ', longest) + ' ' + duration + 'ms\n';
02288       }
02289       return out;
02290     }
02291   };
02292   return StatTimer;
02293 })();

02295 PDFJS.createBlob = function createBlob(data, contentType) {
02296   if (typeof Blob === 'function')
02297     return new Blob([data], { type: contentType });
02298   // Blob builder is deprecated in FF14 and removed in FF18.
02299   var bb = new MozBlobBuilder();
02300   bb.append(data);
02301   return bb.getBlob(contentType);
02302 };

02337 PDFJS.getDocument = function getDocument(source,
02338                                          pdfDataRangeTransport,
02339                                          passwordCallback,
02340                                          progressCallback) {
02341   var workerInitializedPromise, workerReadyPromise, transport;
02342 
02343   if (typeof source === 'string') {
02344     source = { url: source };
02345   } else if (isArrayBuffer(source)) {
02346     source = { data: source };
02347   } else if (typeof source !== 'object') {
02348     error('Invalid parameter in getDocument, need either Uint8Array, ' +
02349           'string or a parameter object');
02350   }
02351 
02352   if (!source.url && !source.data)
02353     error('Invalid parameter array, need either .data or .url');
02354 
02355   // copy/use all keys as is except 'url' -- full path is required
02356   var params = {};
02357   for (var key in source) {
02358     if (key === 'url' && typeof window !== 'undefined') {
02359       params[key] = combineUrl(window.location.href, source[key]);
02360       continue;
02361     }
02362     params[key] = source[key];
02363   }
02364 
02365   workerInitializedPromise = new PDFJS.Promise();
02366   workerReadyPromise = new PDFJS.Promise();
02367   transport = new WorkerTransport(workerInitializedPromise,
02368       workerReadyPromise, pdfDataRangeTransport, progressCallback);
02369   workerInitializedPromise.then(function transportInitialized() {
02370     transport.passwordCallback = passwordCallback;
02371     transport.fetchDocument(params);
02372   });
02373   return workerReadyPromise;
02374 };
