02496 var PDFPageProxy = (function PDFPageProxyClosure() {
02497   function PDFPageProxy(pageInfo, transport) {
02498     this.pageInfo = pageInfo;
02499     this.transport = transport;
02500     this.stats = new StatTimer();
02501     this.stats.enabled = !!globalScope.PDFJS.enableStats;
02502     this.commonObjs = transport.commonObjs;
02503     this.objs = new PDFObjects();
02504     this.renderInProgress = false;
02505     this.cleanupAfterRender = false;
02506   }
02507   PDFPageProxy.prototype = {
02511     get pageNumber() {
02512       return this.pageInfo.pageIndex + 1;
02513     },
02517     get rotate() {
02518       return this.pageInfo.rotate;
02519     },
02524     get ref() {
02525       return this.pageInfo.ref;
02526     },
02531     get view() {
02532       return this.pageInfo.view;
02533     },
02541     getViewport: function PDFPageProxy_getViewport(scale, rotate) {
02542       if (arguments.length < 2)
02543         rotate = this.rotate;
02544       return new PDFJS.PageViewport(this.view, scale, rotate, 0, 0);
02545     },
02550     getAnnotations: function PDFPageProxy_getAnnotations() {
02551       if (this.annotationsPromise)
02552         return this.annotationsPromise;
02553 
02554       var promise = new PDFJS.Promise();
02555       this.annotationsPromise = promise;
02556       this.transport.getAnnotations(this.pageInfo.pageIndex);
02557       return promise;
02558     },
02576     render: function PDFPageProxy_render(params) {
02577       this.renderInProgress = true;
02578 
02579       var promise = new Promise();
02580       var stats = this.stats;
02581       stats.time('Overall');
02582       // If there is no displayReadyPromise yet, then the operatorList was never
02583       // requested before. Make the request and create the promise.
02584       if (!this.displayReadyPromise) {
02585         this.displayReadyPromise = new Promise();
02586         this.destroyed = false;
02587 
02588         this.stats.time('Page Request');
02589         this.transport.messageHandler.send('RenderPageRequest', {
02590           pageIndex: this.pageNumber - 1
02591         });
02592       }
02593 
02594       var self = this;
02595       function complete(error) {
02596         self.renderInProgress = false;
02597         if (self.destroyed || self.cleanupAfterRender) {
02598           delete self.displayReadyPromise;
02599           delete self.operatorList;
02600           self.objs.clear();
02601         }
02602 
02603         if (error)
02604           promise.reject(error);
02605         else
02606           promise.resolve();
02607       }
02608       var continueCallback = params.continueCallback;
02609 
02610       // Once the operatorList and fonts are loaded, do the actual rendering.
02611       this.displayReadyPromise.then(
02612         function pageDisplayReadyPromise() {
02613           if (self.destroyed) {
02614             complete();
02615             return;
02616           }
02617 
02618           var gfx = new CanvasGraphics(params.canvasContext, this.commonObjs,
02619             this.objs, params.textLayer, params.imageLayer);
02620           try {
02621             this.display(gfx, params.viewport, complete, continueCallback);
02622           } catch (e) {
02623             complete(e);
02624           }
02625         }.bind(this),
02626         function pageDisplayReadPromiseError(reason) {
02627           complete(reason);
02628         }
02629       );
02630 
02631       return promise;
02632     },
02636     startRenderingFromOperatorList:
02637       function PDFPageProxy_startRenderingFromOperatorList(operatorList,
02638                                                            fonts) {
02639       var self = this;
02640       this.operatorList = operatorList;
02641 
02642       this.ensureFonts(fonts,
02643         function pageStartRenderingFromOperatorListEnsureFonts() {
02644           self.displayReadyPromise.resolve();
02645         }
02646       );
02647     },
02651     ensureFonts: function PDFPageProxy_ensureFonts(fonts, callback) {
02652       this.stats.time('Font Loading');
02653       // Convert the font names to the corresponding font obj.
02654       var fontObjs = [];
02655       for (var i = 0, ii = fonts.length; i < ii; i++) {
02656         var obj = this.commonObjs.getData(fonts[i]);
02657         if (obj.error) {
02658           warn('Error during font loading: ' + obj.error);
02659           continue;
02660         }
02661         if (!obj.coded) {
02662           this.transport.embeddedFontsUsed = true;
02663         }
02664         fontObjs.push(obj);
02665       }
02666 
02667       // Load all the fonts
02668       FontLoader.bind(
02669         fontObjs,
02670         function pageEnsureFontsFontObjs(fontObjs) {
02671           this.stats.timeEnd('Font Loading');
02672 
02673           callback.call(this);
02674         }.bind(this)
02675       );
02676     },
02680     display: function PDFPageProxy_display(gfx, viewport, callback,
02681                                            continueCallback) {
02682       var stats = this.stats;
02683       stats.time('Rendering');
02684 
02685       var operatorList = this.operatorList;
02686       gfx.beginDrawing(viewport, operatorList.transparency);
02687 
02688       var startIdx = 0;
02689       var length = operatorList.fnArray.length;
02690       var stepper = null;
02691       if (PDFJS.pdfBug && 'StepperManager' in globalScope &&
02692           globalScope['StepperManager'].enabled) {
02693         stepper = globalScope['StepperManager'].create(this.pageNumber - 1);
02694         stepper.init(operatorList);
02695         stepper.nextBreakPoint = stepper.getNextBreakPoint();
02696       }
02697 
02698       var continueWrapper;
02699       if (continueCallback)
02700         continueWrapper = function() { continueCallback(next); };
02701       else
02702         continueWrapper = next;
02703 
02704       var self = this;
02705       function next() {
02706         startIdx = gfx.executeOperatorList(operatorList, startIdx,
02707                                            continueWrapper, stepper);
02708         if (startIdx == length) {
02709           gfx.endDrawing();
02710           stats.timeEnd('Rendering');
02711           stats.timeEnd('Overall');
02712           if (callback) callback();
02713         }
02714       }
02715       continueWrapper();
02716     },
02721     getTextContent: function PDFPageProxy_getTextContent() {
02722       var promise = new PDFJS.Promise();
02723       this.transport.messageHandler.send('GetTextContent', {
02724           pageIndex: this.pageNumber - 1
02725         },
02726         function textContentCallback(textContent) {
02727           promise.resolve(textContent);
02728         }
02729       );
02730       return promise;
02731     },
02735     getOperationList: function PDFPageProxy_getOperationList() {
02736       var promise = new PDFJS.Promise();
02737       var operationList = { // not implemented
02738         dependencyFontsID: null,
02739         operatorList: null
02740       };
02741       promise.resolve(operationList);
02742       return promise;
02743     },
02747     destroy: function PDFPageProxy_destroy() {
02748       this.destroyed = true;
02749 
02750       if (!this.renderInProgress) {
02751         delete this.operatorList;
02752         delete this.displayReadyPromise;
02753         this.objs.clear();
02754       }
02755     }
02756   };
02757   return PDFPageProxy;
02758 })();
02762 var WorkerTransport = (function WorkerTransportClosure() {
02763   function WorkerTransport(workerInitializedPromise, workerReadyPromise,
02764       pdfDataRangeTransport, progressCallback) {
02765     this.pdfDataRangeTransport = pdfDataRangeTransport;
02766 
02767     this.workerReadyPromise = workerReadyPromise;
02768     this.progressCallback = progressCallback;
02769     this.commonObjs = new PDFObjects();
02770 
02771     this.pageCache = [];
02772     this.pagePromises = [];
02773     this.embeddedFontsUsed = false;
02774 
02775     this.passwordCallback = null;
02776 
02777     // If worker support isn't disabled explicit and the browser has worker
02778     // support, create a new web worker and test if it/the browser fullfills
02779     // all requirements to run parts of pdf.js in a web worker.
02780     // Right now, the requirement is, that an Uint8Array is still an Uint8Array
02781     // as it arrives on the worker. Chrome added this with version 15.
02782     if (!globalScope.PDFJS.disableWorker && typeof Worker !== 'undefined') {
02783       var workerSrc = PDFJS.workerSrc;
02784       if (typeof workerSrc === 'undefined') {
02785         error('No PDFJS.workerSrc specified');
02786       }
02787 
02788       try {
02789         // Some versions of FF can't create a worker on localhost, see:
02790         // https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=683280
02791         var worker = new Worker(workerSrc);
02792         var messageHandler = new MessageHandler('main', worker);
02793         this.messageHandler = messageHandler;
02794 
02795         messageHandler.on('test', function transportTest(supportTypedArray) {
02796           if (supportTypedArray) {
02797             this.worker = worker;
02798             this.setupMessageHandler(messageHandler);
02799           } else {
02800             globalScope.PDFJS.disableWorker = true;
02801             this.setupFakeWorker();
02802           }
02803           workerInitializedPromise.resolve();
02804         }.bind(this));
02805 
02806         var testObj = new Uint8Array(1);
02807         // Some versions of Opera throw a DATA_CLONE_ERR on
02808         // serializing the typed array.
02809         messageHandler.send('test', testObj);
02810         return;
02811       } catch (e) {
02812         info('The worker has been disabled.');
02813       }
02814     }
02815     // Either workers are disabled, not supported or have thrown an exception.
02816     // Thus, we fallback to a faked worker.
02817     globalScope.PDFJS.disableWorker = true;
02818     this.setupFakeWorker();
02819     workerInitializedPromise.resolve();
02820   }
02821   WorkerTransport.prototype = {
02822     destroy: function WorkerTransport_destroy() {
02823       this.pageCache = [];
02824       this.pagePromises = [];
02825       var self = this;
02826       this.messageHandler.send('Terminate', null, function () {
02827         if (self.worker) {
02828           self.worker.terminate();
02829         }
02830       });
02831     },
02832     setupFakeWorker: function WorkerTransport_setupFakeWorker() {
02833       warn('Setting up fake worker.');
02834       // If we don't use a worker, just post/sendMessage to the main thread.
02835       var fakeWorker = {
02836         postMessage: function WorkerTransport_postMessage(obj) {
02837           fakeWorker.onmessage({data: obj});
02838         },
02839         terminate: function WorkerTransport_terminate() {}
02840       };
02841 
02842       var messageHandler = new MessageHandler('main', fakeWorker);
02843       this.setupMessageHandler(messageHandler);
02844 
02845       // If the main thread is our worker, setup the handling for the messages
02846       // the main thread sends to it self.
02847       WorkerMessageHandler.setup(messageHandler);
02848     },
02849

02899         this.workerReadyPromise.reject(data.exception.message, data.exception);
02900       }, this);

02929         var page = this.pageCache[data.pageIndex];
02930         var depFonts = data.depFonts;
02931

02935 
02936       messageHandler.on('commonobj', function transportObj(data) {
02937         var id = data[0];
02938         var type = data[1];
02939         if (this.commonObjs.hasData(id))
02940           return;
02941 
02942         switch (type) {
02943           case 'Font':
02944             var exportedData = data[2];
02945 
02946             // At this point, only the font object is created but the font is
02947             // not yet attached to the DOM. This is done in `FontLoader.bind`.
02948             var font;
02949             if ('error' in exportedData)
02950               font = new ErrorFont(exportedData.error);
02951             else
02952               font = new Font(exportedData);
02953             this.commonObjs.resolve(id, font);
02954             break;
02955           default:
02956             error('Got unknown common object type ' + type);
02957         }
02958       }, this);
02959 
02960       messageHandler.on('obj', function transportObj(data) {
02961         var id = data[0];
02962         var pageIndex = data[1];
02963         var type = data[2];
02964         var pageProxy = this.pageCache[pageIndex];
02965         if (pageProxy.objs.hasData(id))
02966           return;
02967 
02968         switch (type) {
02969           case 'JpegStream':
02970             var imageData = data[3];
02971             loadJpegStream(id, imageData, pageProxy.objs);
02972             break;
02973           case 'Image':
02974             var imageData = data[3];
02975             pageProxy.objs.resolve(id, imageData);
02976 
02977             // heuristics that will allow not to store large data
02978             var MAX_IMAGE_SIZE_TO_STORE = 8000000;
02979             if ('data' in imageData &&
02980                 imageData.data.length > MAX_IMAGE_SIZE_TO_STORE) {
02981               pageProxy.cleanupAfterRender = true;
02982             }
02983             break;
02984           default:
02985             error('Got unknown object type ' + type);
02986         }
02987       }, this);
02988 
02989       messageHandler.on('DocProgress', function transportDocProgress(data) {
02990         if (this.progressCallback) {
02991           this.progressCallback({
02992             loaded: data.loaded,
02993             total: data.total
02994           });
02995         }
02996       }, this);
02997 
02998       messageHandler.on('DocError', function transportDocError(data) {
02999         this.workerReadyPromise.reject(data);
03000       }, this);
03001 
03002       messageHandler.on('PageError', function transportError(data) {
03003         var page = this.pageCache[data.pageNum - 1];
03004         if (page.displayReadyPromise)
03005           page.displayReadyPromise.reject(data.error);
03006         else
03007           error(data.error);
03008       }, this);
03009 
03010       messageHandler.on('JpegDecode', function(data, promise) {
03011         var imageData = data[0];
03012         var components = data[1];
03013         if (components != 3 && components != 1)
03014           error('Only 3 component or 1 component can be returned');
03015 
03016         var img = new Image();
03017         img.onload = (function messageHandler_onloadClosure() {
03018           var width = img.width;
03019           var height = img.height;
03020           var size = width * height;
03021           var rgbaLength = size * 4;
03022           var buf = new Uint8Array(size * components);
03023           var tmpCanvas = createScratchCanvas(width, height);
03024           var tmpCtx = tmpCanvas.getContext('2d');
03025           tmpCtx.drawImage(img, 0, 0);
03026           var data = tmpCtx.getImageData(0, 0, width, height).data;
03027 
03028           if (components == 3) {
03029             for (var i = 0, j = 0; i < rgbaLength; i += 4, j += 3) {
03030               buf[j] = data[i];
03031               buf[j + 1] = data[i + 1];
03032               buf[j + 2] = data[i + 2];
03033             }
03034           } else if (components == 1) {
03035             for (var i = 0, j = 0; i < rgbaLength; i += 4, j++) {
03036               buf[j] = data[i];
03037             }
03038           }
03039           promise.resolve({ data: buf, width: width, height: height});
03040         }).bind(this);
03041         var src = 'data:image/jpeg;base64,' + window.btoa(imageData);
03042         img.src = src;
03043       });
03044     },
03045

03049       this.messageHandler.send('GetDocRequest', {

03051         disableRange: PDFJS.disableRange,
03052         maxImageSize: PDFJS.maxImageSize
03053       });
03054     },

03103 var TextRenderingMode = {
03104   FILL: 0,
03105   STROKE: 1,
03106   FILL_STROKE: 2,
03107   INVISIBLE: 3,
03108   FILL_ADD_TO_PATH: 4,
03109   STROKE_ADD_TO_PATH: 5,
03110   FILL_STROKE_ADD_TO_PATH: 6,
03111   ADD_TO_PATH: 7,
03112   FILL_STROKE_MASK: 3,

03121 function createScratchCanvas(width, height) {
03122   var canvas = document.createElement('canvas');
03123   canvas.width = width;
03124   canvas.height = height;
03125   return canvas;

03127 
03128 function addContextCurrentTransform(ctx) {
03129   // If the context doesn't expose a `mozCurrentTransform`, add a JS based on.
03130   if (!ctx.mozCurrentTransform) {
03131     // Store the original context
03132     ctx._scaleX = ctx._scaleX || 1.0;
03133     ctx._scaleY = ctx._scaleY || 1.0;
03134     ctx._originalSave = ctx.save;
03135     ctx._originalRestore = ctx.restore;
03136     ctx._originalRotate = ctx.rotate;
03137     ctx._originalScale = ctx.scale;
03138     ctx._originalTranslate = ctx.translate;
03139     ctx._originalTransform = ctx.transform;
03140     ctx._originalSetTransform = ctx.setTransform;
03141 
03142     ctx._transformMatrix = [ctx._scaleX, 0, 0, ctx._scaleY, 0, 0];
03143     ctx._transformStack = [];
03144 
03145     Object.defineProperty(ctx, 'mozCurrentTransform', {
03146       get: function getCurrentTransform() {
03147         return this._transformMatrix;
03148       }
03149     });
03150 
03151     Object.defineProperty(ctx, 'mozCurrentTransformInverse', {
03152       get: function getCurrentTransformInverse() {
03153         // Calculation done using WolframAlpha:
03154         // http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?
03155         //   i=Inverse+{{a%2C+c%2C+e}%2C+{b%2C+d%2C+f}%2C+{0%2C+0%2C+1}}
03156 
03157         var m = this._transformMatrix;
03158         var a = m[0], b = m[1], c = m[2], d = m[3], e = m[4], f = m[5];
03159 
03160         var ad_bc = a * d - b * c;
03161         var bc_ad = b * c - a * d;
03162 
03163         return [
03164           d / ad_bc,
03165           b / bc_ad,
03166           c / bc_ad,
03167           a / ad_bc,
03168           (d * e - c * f) / bc_ad,
03169           (b * e - a * f) / ad_bc
03170         ];
03171       }
03172     });
03173 
03174     ctx.save = function ctxSave() {
03175       var old = this._transformMatrix;
03176       this._transformStack.push(old);
03177       this._transformMatrix = old.slice(0, 6);
03178 
03179       this._originalSave();
03180     };
03181 
03182     ctx.restore = function ctxRestore() {
03183       var prev = this._transformStack.pop();
03184       if (prev) {
03185         this._transformMatrix = prev;
03186         this._originalRestore();
03187       }
03188     };
03189 
03190     ctx.translate = function ctxTranslate(x, y) {
03191       var m = this._transformMatrix;
03192       m[4] = m[0] * x + m[2] * y + m[4];
03193       m[5] = m[1] * x + m[3] * y + m[5];
03194 
03195       this._originalTranslate(x, y);
03196     };
03197 
03198     ctx.scale = function ctxScale(x, y) {
03199       var m = this._transformMatrix;
03200       m[0] = m[0] * x;
03201       m[1] = m[1] * x;
03202       m[2] = m[2] * y;
03203       m[3] = m[3] * y;
03204 
03205       this._originalScale(x, y);
03206     };
03207 
03208     ctx.transform = function ctxTransform(a, b, c, d, e, f) {
03209       var m = this._transformMatrix;
03210       this._transformMatrix = [
03211         m[0] * a + m[2] * b,
03212         m[1] * a + m[3] * b,
03213         m[0] * c + m[2] * d,
03214         m[1] * c + m[3] * d,
03215         m[0] * e + m[2] * f + m[4],
03216         m[1] * e + m[3] * f + m[5]
03217       ];
03218 
03219       ctx._originalTransform(a, b, c, d, e, f);
03220     };
03221 
03222     ctx.setTransform = function ctxSetTransform(a, b, c, d, e, f) {
03223       this._transformMatrix = [a, b, c, d, e, f];
03224 
03225       ctx._originalSetTransform(a, b, c, d, e, f);
03226     };
03227 
03228     ctx.rotate = function ctxRotate(angle) {
03229       var cosValue = Math.cos(angle);
03230       var sinValue = Math.sin(angle);
03231 
03232       var m = this._transformMatrix;
03233       this._transformMatrix = [
03234         m[0] * cosValue + m[2] * sinValue,
03235         m[1] * cosValue + m[3] * sinValue,
03236         m[0] * (-sinValue) + m[2] * cosValue,
03237         m[1] * (-sinValue) + m[3] * cosValue,
03238         m[4],
03239         m[5]
03240       ];
03241 
03242       this._originalRotate(angle);
03243     };
03244   }
03245 }

03247 var CachedCanvases = (function CachedCanvasesClosure() {
03248   var cache = {};
03249   return {
03250     getCanvas: function CachedCanvases_getCanvas(id, width, height) {
03251       var canvas;
03252       if (id in cache) {
03253         canvas = cache[id];
03254         canvas.width = width;
03255         canvas.height = height;
03256         // reset canvas transform for emulated mozCurrentTransform, if needed
03257         canvas.getContext('2d').setTransform(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0);
03258       } else {
03259         canvas = createScratchCanvas(width, height);
03260         cache[id] = canvas;
03261       }
03262       return canvas;
03263     },
03264     clear: function () {
03265       cache = {};
03266     }
03267   };
03268 })();

03270 function compileType3Glyph(imgData) {
03271   var POINT_TO_PROCESS_LIMIT = 1000;
03272 
03273   var width = imgData.width, height = imgData.height;
03274   var i, j, j0, width1 = width + 1;
03275   var points = new Uint8Array(width1 * (height + 1));
03276   var POINT_TYPES =
03277       new Uint8Array([0, 2, 4, 0, 1, 0, 5, 4, 8, 10, 0, 8, 0, 2, 1, 0]);
03278   // finding iteresting points: every point is located between mask pixels,
03279   // so there will be points of the (width + 1)x(height + 1) grid. Every point
03280   // will have flags assigned based on neighboring mask pixels:
03281   //   4 | 8
03282   //   --P--
03283   //   2 | 1
03284   // We are interested only in points with the flags:
03285   //   - outside corners: 1, 2, 4, 8;
03286   //   - inside corners: 7, 11, 13, 14;
03287   //   - and, intersections: 5, 10.
03288   var pos = 3, data = imgData.data, lineSize = width * 4, count = 0;
03289   if (data[3] !== 0) {
03290     points[0] = 1;
03291     ++count;
03292   }
03293   for (j = 1; j < width; j++) {
03294     if (data[pos] !== data[pos + 4]) {
03295       points[j] = data[pos] ? 2 : 1;
03296       ++count;
03297     }
03298     pos += 4;
03299   }
03300   if (data[pos] !== 0) {
03301     points[j] = 2;
03302     ++count;
03303   }
03304   pos += 4;
03305   for (i = 1; i < height; i++) {
03306     j0 = i * width1;
03307     if (data[pos - lineSize] !== data[pos]) {
03308       points[j0] = data[pos] ? 1 : 8;
03309       ++count;
03310     }
03311     // 'sum' is the position of the current pixel configuration in the 'TYPES'
03312     // array (in order 8-1-2-4, so we can use '>>2' to shift the column).
03313     var sum = (data[pos] ? 4 : 0) + (data[pos - lineSize] ? 8 : 0);
03314     for (j = 1; j < width; j++) {
03315       sum = (sum >> 2) + (data[pos + 4] ? 4 : 0) +
03316             (data[pos - lineSize + 4] ? 8 : 0);
03317       if (POINT_TYPES[sum]) {
03318         points[j0 + j] = POINT_TYPES[sum];
03319         ++count;
03320       }
03321       pos += 4;
03322     }
03323     if (data[pos - lineSize] !== data[pos]) {
03324       points[j0 + j] = data[pos] ? 2 : 4;
03325       ++count;
03326     }
03327     pos += 4;
03328 
03329     if (count > POINT_TO_PROCESS_LIMIT) {
03330       return null;
03331     }
03332   }
03333 
03334   pos -= lineSize;
03335   j0 = i * width1;
03336   if (data[pos] !== 0) {
03337     points[j0] = 8;
03338     ++count;
03339   }
03340   for (j = 1; j < width; j++) {
03341     if (data[pos] !== data[pos + 4]) {
03342       points[j0 + j] = data[pos] ? 4 : 8;
03343       ++count;
03344     }
03345     pos += 4;
03346   }
03347   if (data[pos] !== 0) {
03348     points[j0 + j] = 4;
03349     ++count;
03350   }
03351   if (count > POINT_TO_PROCESS_LIMIT) {
03352     return null;
03353   }
03354 
03355   // building outlines
03356   var steps = new Int32Array([0, width1, -1, 0, -width1, 0, 0, 0, 1]);
03357   var outlines = [];
03358   for (i = 0; count && i <= height; i++) {
03359     var p = i * width1;
03360     var end = p + width;
03361     while (p < end && !points[p]) {
03362       p++;
03363     }
03364     if (p === end) {
03365       continue;
03366     }
03367     var coords = [p % width1, i];
03368 
03369     var type = points[p], p0 = p, pp;
03370     do {
03371       var step = steps[type];
03372       do { p += step; } while (!points[p]);
03373 
03374       pp = points[p];
03375       if (pp !== 5 && pp !== 10) {
03376         // set new direction
03377         type = pp;
03378         // delete mark
03379         points[p] = 0;
03380       } else { // type is 5 or 10, ie, a crossing
03381         // set new direction
03382         type = pp & ((0x33 * type) >> 4);
03383         // set new type for "future hit"
03384         points[p] &= (type >> 2 | type << 2);
03385       }
03386 
03387       coords.push(p % width1);
03388       coords.push((p / width1) | 0);
03389       --count;
03390     } while (p0 !== p);
03391     outlines.push(coords);
03392     --i;
03393   }
03394 
03395   var drawOutline = function(c) {
03396     c.save();
03397     // the path shall be painted in [0..1]x[0..1] space
03398     c.scale(1 / width, -1 / height);
03399     c.translate(0, -height);
03400     c.beginPath();
03401     for (var i = 0, ii = outlines.length; i < ii; i++) {
03402       var o = outlines[i];
03403       c.moveTo(o[0], o[1]);
03404       for (var j = 2, jj = o.length; j < jj; j += 2) {
03405         c.lineTo(o[j], o[j+1]);
03406       }
03407     }
03408     c.fill();
03409     c.beginPath();
03410     c.restore();
03411   };
03412 
03413   return drawOutline;
03414 }

03416 var CanvasExtraState = (function CanvasExtraStateClosure() {
03417   function CanvasExtraState(old) {
03418     // Are soft masks and alpha values shapes or opacities?
03419     this.alphaIsShape = false;
03420     this.fontSize = 0;
03421     this.fontSizeScale = 1;
03422     this.textMatrix = IDENTITY_MATRIX;
03423     this.fontMatrix = FONT_IDENTITY_MATRIX;
03424     this.leading = 0;
03425     // Current point (in user coordinates)
03426     this.x = 0;
03427     this.y = 0;
03428     // Start of text line (in text coordinates)
03429     this.lineX = 0;
03430     this.lineY = 0;
03431     // Character and word spacing
03432     this.charSpacing = 0;
03433     this.wordSpacing = 0;
03434     this.textHScale = 1;
03435     this.textRenderingMode = TextRenderingMode.FILL;
03436     this.textRise = 0;
03437     // Color spaces
03438     this.fillColorSpace = new DeviceGrayCS();
03439     this.fillColorSpaceObj = null;
03440     this.strokeColorSpace = new DeviceGrayCS();
03441     this.strokeColorSpaceObj = null;
03442     this.fillColorObj = null;
03443     this.strokeColorObj = null;
03444     // Default fore and background colors
03445     this.fillColor = '#000000';
03446     this.strokeColor = '#000000';
03447     // Note: fill alpha applies to all non-stroking operations
03448     this.fillAlpha = 1;
03449     this.strokeAlpha = 1;
03450     this.lineWidth = 1;
03451     this.paintFormXObjectDepth = 0;
03452 
03453     this.old = old;
03454   }

03468 var CanvasGraphics = (function CanvasGraphicsClosure() {
03469   // Defines the time the executeOperatorList is going to be executing
03470   // before it stops and shedules a continue of execution.
03471   var EXECUTION_TIME = 15;
03472 
03473   function CanvasGraphics(canvasCtx, commonObjs, objs, textLayer, imageLayer) {
03474     this.ctx = canvasCtx;
03475     this.current = new CanvasExtraState();
03476     this.stateStack = [];
03477     this.pendingClip = null;
03478     this.pendingEOFill = false;
03479     this.res = null;

03481     this.commonObjs = commonObjs;
03482     this.objs = objs;

03485     this.groupStack = [];
03486     this.processingType3 = null;

03488       addContextCurrentTransform(canvasCtx);
03489     }

03492   function putBinaryImageData(ctx, imgData) {
03493     if (typeof ImageData !== 'undefined' && imgData instanceof ImageData) {
03494       ctx.putImageData(imgData, 0, 0);
03495       return;
03496     }
03497 
03498     var tmpImgData = ctx.createImageData(imgData.width, imgData.height);
03499 
03500     var data = imgData.data;
03501     var tmpImgDataPixels = tmpImgData.data;
03502     if ('set' in tmpImgDataPixels)
03503       tmpImgDataPixels.set(data);
03504     else {
03505       // Copy over the imageData pixel by pixel.
03506       for (var i = 0, ii = tmpImgDataPixels.length; i < ii; i++)
03507         tmpImgDataPixels[i] = data[i];
03508     }
03509 
03510     ctx.putImageData(tmpImgData, 0, 0);
03511   }

03513   function copyCtxState(sourceCtx, destCtx) {
03514     var properties = ['strokeStyle', 'fillStyle', 'fillRule', 'globalAlpha',
03515                       'lineWidth', 'lineCap', 'lineJoin', 'miterLimit',
03516                       'globalCompositeOperation', 'font'];
03517     for (var i = 0, ii = properties.length; i < ii; i++) {
03518       var property = properties[i];
03519       if (property in sourceCtx) {
03520         destCtx[property] = sourceCtx[property];
03521       }
03522     }
03523     if ('setLineDash' in sourceCtx) {
03524       destCtx.setLineDash(sourceCtx.getLineDash());
03525       destCtx.lineDashOffset =  sourceCtx.lineDashOffset;
03526     } else if ('mozDash' in sourceCtx) {
03527       destCtx.mozDash = sourceCtx.mozDash;
03528       destCtx.mozDashOffset = sourceCtx.mozDashOffset;
03529     }
03530   }

03570     beginDrawing: function CanvasGraphics_beginDrawing(viewport, transparency) {
03571       // For pdfs that use blend modes we have to clear the canvas else certain
03572       // blend modes can look wrong since we'd be blending with a white
03573       // backdrop. The problem with a transparent backdrop though is we then
03574       // don't get sub pixel anti aliasing on text, so we fill with white if
03575       // we can.
03576       var width = this.ctx.canvas.width;
03577       var height = this.ctx.canvas.height;
03578       if (transparency) {
03579         this.ctx.clearRect(0, 0, width, height);
03580       } else {
03581         this.ctx.mozOpaque = true;
03582         this.ctx.save();
03583         this.ctx.fillStyle = 'rgb(255, 255, 255)';
03584         this.ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);
03585         this.ctx.restore();
03586       }
03587 
03588       var transform = viewport.transform;
03589       this.ctx.save();
03590       this.ctx.transform.apply(this.ctx, transform);
03591 
03592       if (this.textLayer) {
03593         this.textLayer.beginLayout();
03594       }
03595       if (this.imageLayer) {
03596         this.imageLayer.beginLayout();
03597       }
03598     },
03599 
03600     executeOperatorList: function CanvasGraphics_executeOperatorList(
03601                                     operatorList,
03602                                     executionStartIdx, continueCallback,
03603                                     stepper) {
03604       var argsArray = operatorList.argsArray;
03605       var fnArray = operatorList.fnArray;
03606       var i = executionStartIdx || 0;
03607       var argsArrayLen = argsArray.length;
03608 
03609       // Sometimes the OperatorList to execute is empty.
03610       if (argsArrayLen == i) {
03611         return i;
03612       }
03613 
03614       var executionEndIdx;
03615       var endTime = Date.now() + EXECUTION_TIME;
03616 
03617       var commonObjs = this.commonObjs;
03618       var objs = this.objs;
03619       var fnName;
03620       var slowCommands = this.slowCommands;
03621 
03622       while (true) {
03623         if (stepper && i === stepper.nextBreakPoint) {
03624           stepper.breakIt(i, continueCallback);
03625           return i;
03626         }
03627 
03628         fnName = fnArray[i];
03629 
03630         if (fnName !== 'dependency') {
03631           this[fnName].apply(this, argsArray[i]);
03632         } else {
03633           var deps = argsArray[i];
03634           for (var n = 0, nn = deps.length; n < nn; n++) {
03635             var depObjId = deps[n];
03636             var common = depObjId.substring(0, 2) == 'g_';
03637 
03638             // If the promise isn't resolved yet, add the continueCallback
03639             // to the promise and bail out.
03640             if (!common && !objs.isResolved(depObjId)) {
03641               objs.get(depObjId, continueCallback);
03642               return i;
03643             }
03644             if (common && !commonObjs.isResolved(depObjId)) {
03645               commonObjs.get(depObjId, continueCallback);
03646               return i;
03647             }
03648           }
03649         }
03650 
03651         i++;
03652 
03653         // If the entire operatorList was executed, stop as were done.
03654         if (i == argsArrayLen) {
03655           return i;
03656         }
03657 
03658         // If the execution took longer then a certain amount of time, shedule
03659         // to continue exeution after a short delay.
03660         // However, this is only possible if a 'continueCallback' is passed in.
03661         if (continueCallback && slowCommands[fnName] && Date.now() > endTime) {
03662           setTimeout(continueCallback, 0);
03663           return i;
03664         }
03665 
03666         // If the operatorList isn't executed completely yet OR the execution
03667         // time was short enough, do another execution round.
03668       }
03669     },
03670 
03671     endDrawing: function CanvasGraphics_endDrawing() {
03672       this.ctx.restore();
03673       CachedCanvases.clear();
03674 
03675       if (this.textLayer) {
03676         this.textLayer.endLayout();
03677       }
03678       if (this.imageLayer) {
03679         this.imageLayer.endLayout();
03680       }
03681     },

03697     setDash: function CanvasGraphics_setDash(dashArray, dashPhase) {
03698       var ctx = this.ctx;
03699       if ('setLineDash' in ctx) {
03700         ctx.setLineDash(dashArray);
03701         ctx.lineDashOffset = dashPhase;
03702       } else {
03703         ctx.mozDash = dashArray;

03707     setRenderingIntent: function CanvasGraphics_setRenderingIntent(intent) {
03708       // Maybe if we one day fully support color spaces this will be important
03709       // for now we can ignore.
03710       // TODO set rendering intent?
03711     },
03712     setFlatness: function CanvasGraphics_setFlatness(flatness) {
03713       // There's no way to control this with canvas, but we can safely ignore.
03714       // TODO set flatness?
03715     },
03716     setGState: function CanvasGraphics_setGState(states) {
03717       for (var i = 0, ii = states.length; i < ii; i++) {
03718         var state = states[i];
03719         var key = state[0];
03720         var value = state[1];
03721 
03722         switch (key) {
03723           case 'LW':
03724             this.setLineWidth(value);
03725             break;
03726           case 'LC':
03727             this.setLineCap(value);
03728             break;
03729           case 'LJ':
03730             this.setLineJoin(value);
03731             break;
03732           case 'ML':
03733             this.setMiterLimit(value);
03734             break;
03735           case 'D':
03736             this.setDash(value[0], value[1]);
03737             break;
03738           case 'RI':
03739             this.setRenderingIntent(value);
03740             break;
03741           case 'FL':
03742             this.setFlatness(value);
03743             break;
03744           case 'Font':
03745             this.setFont(state[1], state[2]);
03746             break;
03747           case 'CA':
03748             this.current.strokeAlpha = state[1];
03749             break;
03750           case 'ca':
03751             this.current.fillAlpha = state[1];
03752             this.ctx.globalAlpha = state[1];
03753             break;
03754           case 'BM':
03755             if (value && value.name && (value.name !== 'Normal')) {
03756               var mode = value.name.replace(/([A-Z])/g,
03757                 function(c) {
03758                   return '-' + c.toLowerCase();
03759                 }
03760               ).substring(1);
03761               this.ctx.globalCompositeOperation = mode;
03762               if (this.ctx.globalCompositeOperation !== mode) {
03763                 warn('globalCompositeOperation "' + mode +
03764                      '" is not supported');
03765               }
03766             } else {
03767               this.ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'source-over';
03768             }
03769             break;
03770         }
03771       }
03772     },
03773     save: function CanvasGraphics_save() {
03774       this.ctx.save();
03775       var old = this.current;
03776       this.stateStack.push(old);
03777       this.current = old.clone();
03778     },
03779     restore: function CanvasGraphics_restore() {
03780       var prev = this.stateStack.pop();
03781       if (prev) {
03782         this.current = prev;
03783         this.ctx.restore();
03784       }
03785     },
03786     transform: function CanvasGraphics_transform(a, b, c, d, e, f) {
03787       this.ctx.transform(a, b, c, d, e, f);
03788     },

03812     closePath: function CanvasGraphics_closePath() {
03813       this.ctx.closePath();
03814     },
03815     rectangle: function CanvasGraphics_rectangle(x, y, width, height) {
03816       this.ctx.rect(x, y, width, height);
03817     },
03818     stroke: function CanvasGraphics_stroke(consumePath) {
03819       consumePath = typeof consumePath !== 'undefined' ? consumePath : true;
03820       var ctx = this.ctx;
03821       var strokeColor = this.current.strokeColor;
03822       if (this.current.lineWidth === 0)
03823         ctx.lineWidth = this.getSinglePixelWidth();
03824       // For stroke we want to temporarily change the global alpha to the
03825       // stroking alpha.
03826       ctx.globalAlpha = this.current.strokeAlpha;
03827       if (strokeColor && strokeColor.hasOwnProperty('type') &&
03828           strokeColor.type === 'Pattern') {
03829         // for patterns, we transform to pattern space, calculate
03830         // the pattern, call stroke, and restore to user space
03831         ctx.save();
03832         ctx.strokeStyle = strokeColor.getPattern(ctx);
03833         ctx.stroke();
03834         ctx.restore();
03835       } else {
03836         ctx.stroke();
03837       }
03838       if (consumePath)
03839         this.consumePath();
03840       // Restore the global alpha to the fill alpha
03841       ctx.globalAlpha = this.current.fillAlpha;
03842     },
03843     closeStroke: function CanvasGraphics_closeStroke() {
03844       this.closePath();
03845       this.stroke();
03846     },
03847     fill: function CanvasGraphics_fill(consumePath) {
03848       consumePath = typeof consumePath !== 'undefined' ? consumePath : true;
03849       var ctx = this.ctx;
03850       var fillColor = this.current.fillColor;
03851       var needRestore = false;
03852 
03853       if (fillColor && fillColor.hasOwnProperty('type') &&
03854           fillColor.type === 'Pattern') {
03855         ctx.save();
03856         ctx.fillStyle = fillColor.getPattern(ctx);
03857         needRestore = true;
03858       }
03859 
03860       if (this.pendingEOFill) {
03861         if ('mozFillRule' in this.ctx) {
03862           this.ctx.mozFillRule = 'evenodd';
03863           this.ctx.fill();
03864           this.ctx.mozFillRule = 'nonzero';
03865         } else {
03866           try {
03867             this.ctx.fill('evenodd');
03868           } catch (ex) {
03869             // shouldn't really happen, but browsers might think differently
03870             this.ctx.fill();
03871           }
03872         }
03873         this.pendingEOFill = false;
03874       } else {
03875         this.ctx.fill();
03876       }
03877 
03878       if (needRestore) {
03879         ctx.restore();
03880       }
03881       if (consumePath) {
03882         this.consumePath();
03883       }
03884     },
03885     eoFill: function CanvasGraphics_eoFill() {
03886       this.pendingEOFill = true;
03887       this.fill();
03888     },
03889     fillStroke: function CanvasGraphics_fillStroke() {
03890       this.fill(false);
03891       this.stroke(false);
03892 
03893       this.consumePath();
03894     },
03895     eoFillStroke: function CanvasGraphics_eoFillStroke() {
03896       this.pendingEOFill = true;
03897       this.fillStroke();
03898     },
03899     closeFillStroke: function CanvasGraphics_closeFillStroke() {
03900       this.closePath();
03901       this.fillStroke();
03902     },
03903     closeEOFillStroke: function CanvasGraphics_closeEOFillStroke() {
03904       this.pendingEOFill = true;
03905       this.closePath();
03906       this.fillStroke();
03907     },
03908     endPath: function CanvasGraphics_endPath() {
03909       this.consumePath();
03910     },

03920     // Text
03921     beginText: function CanvasGraphics_beginText() {
03922       this.current.textMatrix = IDENTITY_MATRIX;
03923       this.current.x = this.current.lineX = 0;
03924       this.current.y = this.current.lineY = 0;
03925     },
03926     endText: function CanvasGraphics_endText() {
03927       if (!('pendingTextPaths' in this)) {
03928         this.ctx.beginPath();
03929         return;
03930       }
03931       var paths = this.pendingTextPaths;
03932       var ctx = this.ctx;
03933 
03934       ctx.save();
03935       ctx.beginPath();
03936       for (var i = 0; i < paths.length; i++) {
03937         var path = paths[i];
03938         ctx.setTransform.apply(ctx, path.transform);
03939         ctx.translate(path.x, path.y);
03940         path.addToPath(ctx, path.fontSize);
03941       }
03942       ctx.restore();
03943       ctx.clip();
03944       ctx.beginPath();
03945       delete this.pendingTextPaths;
03946     },
03947     setCharSpacing: function CanvasGraphics_setCharSpacing(spacing) {
03948       this.current.charSpacing = spacing;
03949     },
03950     setWordSpacing: function CanvasGraphics_setWordSpacing(spacing) {
03951       this.current.wordSpacing = spacing;
03952     },
03953     setHScale: function CanvasGraphics_setHScale(scale) {
03954       this.current.textHScale = scale / 100;
03955     },
03956     setLeading: function CanvasGraphics_setLeading(leading) {
03957       this.current.leading = -leading;
03958     },
03959     setFont: function CanvasGraphics_setFont(fontRefName, size) {
03960       var fontObj = this.commonObjs.get(fontRefName);
03961       var current = this.current;
03962 
03963       if (!fontObj)
03964         error('Can\'t find font for ' + fontRefName);
03965 
03966       current.fontMatrix = fontObj.fontMatrix ? fontObj.fontMatrix :
03967                                                 FONT_IDENTITY_MATRIX;
03968 
03969       // A valid matrix needs all main diagonal elements to be non-zero
03970       // This also ensures we bypass FF bugzilla bug #719844.
03971       if (current.fontMatrix[0] === 0 ||
03972           current.fontMatrix[3] === 0) {
03973         warn('Invalid font matrix for font ' + fontRefName);
03974       }
03975 
03976       // The spec for Tf (setFont) says that 'size' specifies the font 'scale',
03977       // and in some docs this can be negative (inverted x-y axes).
03978       if (size < 0) {
03979         size = -size;
03980         current.fontDirection = -1;
03981       } else {
03982         current.fontDirection = 1;
03983       }
03984 
03985       this.current.font = fontObj;
03986       this.current.fontSize = size;
03987 
03988       if (fontObj.coded)
03989         return; // we don't need ctx.font for Type3 fonts
03990 
03991       var name = fontObj.loadedName || 'sans-serif';
03992       var bold = fontObj.black ? (fontObj.bold ? 'bolder' : 'bold') :
03993                                  (fontObj.bold ? 'bold' : 'normal');
03994 
03995       var italic = fontObj.italic ? 'italic' : 'normal';
03996       var typeface = '"' + name + '", ' + fontObj.fallbackName;
03997 
03998       // Some font backends cannot handle fonts below certain size.
03999       // Keeping the font at minimal size and using the fontSizeScale to change
04000       // the current transformation matrix before the fillText/strokeText.
04001       // See https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=726227
04002       var browserFontSize = size >= MIN_FONT_SIZE ? size : MIN_FONT_SIZE;
04003       this.current.fontSizeScale = browserFontSize != MIN_FONT_SIZE ? 1.0 :
04004                                    size / MIN_FONT_SIZE;
04005 
04006       var rule = italic + ' ' + bold + ' ' + browserFontSize + 'px ' + typeface;
04007       this.ctx.font = rule;
04008     },
04009     setTextRenderingMode: function CanvasGraphics_setTextRenderingMode(mode) {
04010       this.current.textRenderingMode = mode;
04011     },
04012     setTextRise: function CanvasGraphics_setTextRise(rise) {
04013       this.current.textRise = rise;
04014     },
04015     moveText: function CanvasGraphics_moveText(x, y) {
04016       this.current.x = this.current.lineX += x;
04017       this.current.y = this.current.lineY += y;
04018     },
04019     setLeadingMoveText: function CanvasGraphics_setLeadingMoveText(x, y) {
04020       this.setLeading(-y);
04021       this.moveText(x, y);
04022     },
04023     setTextMatrix: function CanvasGraphics_setTextMatrix(a, b, c, d, e, f) {
04024       this.current.textMatrix = [a, b, c, d, e, f];
04025 
04026       this.current.x = this.current.lineX = 0;
04027       this.current.y = this.current.lineY = 0;
04028     },
04029     nextLine: function CanvasGraphics_nextLine() {
04030       this.moveText(0, this.current.leading);
04031     },
04032     applyTextTransforms: function CanvasGraphics_applyTextTransforms() {
04033       var ctx = this.ctx;
04034       var current = this.current;
04035       ctx.transform.apply(ctx, current.textMatrix);
04036       ctx.translate(current.x, current.y + current.textRise);
04037       if (current.fontDirection > 0) {
04038         ctx.scale(current.textHScale, -1);
04039       } else {
04040         ctx.scale(-current.textHScale, 1);
04041       }
04042     },
04043     createTextGeometry: function CanvasGraphics_createTextGeometry() {
04044       var geometry = {};
04045       var ctx = this.ctx;
04046       var font = this.current.font;
04047       var ctxMatrix = ctx.mozCurrentTransform;
04048       var a = ctxMatrix[0], b = ctxMatrix[1], c = ctxMatrix[2];
04049       var d = ctxMatrix[3], e = ctxMatrix[4], f = ctxMatrix[5];
04050       var sx = (a >= 0) ?
04051           Math.sqrt((a * a) + (b * b)) : -Math.sqrt((a * a) + (b * b));
04052       var sy = (d >= 0) ?
04053           Math.sqrt((c * c) + (d * d)) : -Math.sqrt((c * c) + (d * d));
04054       var angle = Math.atan2(b, a);
04055       var x = e;
04056       var y = f;
04057       geometry.x = x;
04058       geometry.y = y;
04059       geometry.hScale = sx;
04060       geometry.vScale = sy;
04061       geometry.angle = angle;
04062       geometry.spaceWidth = font.spaceWidth;
04063       geometry.fontName = font.loadedName;
04064       geometry.fontFamily = font.fallbackName;
04065       geometry.fontSize = this.current.fontSize;
04066       return geometry;
04067     },
04068 
04069     paintChar: function (character, x, y) {
04070       var ctx = this.ctx;
04071       var current = this.current;
04072       var font = current.font;
04073       var fontSize = current.fontSize / current.fontSizeScale;
04074       var textRenderingMode = current.textRenderingMode;
04075       var fillStrokeMode = textRenderingMode &
04076         TextRenderingMode.FILL_STROKE_MASK;
04077       var isAddToPathSet = !!(textRenderingMode &
04078         TextRenderingMode.ADD_TO_PATH_FLAG);
04079 
04080       var addToPath;
04081       if (font.disableFontFace || isAddToPathSet) {
04082         addToPath = font.renderer.getPathGenerator(character);
04083       }
04084 
04085       if (font.disableFontFace) {
04086         ctx.save();
04087         ctx.translate(x, y);
04088         ctx.beginPath();
04089         addToPath(ctx, fontSize);
04090         if (fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.FILL ||
04091             fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.FILL_STROKE) {
04092           ctx.fill();
04093         }
04094         if (fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.STROKE ||
04095             fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.FILL_STROKE) {
04096           ctx.stroke();
04097         }
04098         ctx.restore();
04099       } else {
04100         if (fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.FILL ||
04101             fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.FILL_STROKE) {
04102           ctx.fillText(character, x, y);
04103         }
04104         if (fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.STROKE ||
04105             fillStrokeMode === TextRenderingMode.FILL_STROKE) {
04106           ctx.strokeText(character, x, y);
04107         }
04108       }
04109 
04110       if (isAddToPathSet) {
04111         var paths = this.pendingTextPaths || (this.pendingTextPaths = []);
04112         paths.push({
04113           transform: ctx.mozCurrentTransform,
04114           x: x,
04115           y: y,
04116           fontSize: fontSize,
04117           addToPath: addToPath
04118         });
04119       }
04120     },
04121 
04122     showText: function CanvasGraphics_showText(str, skipTextSelection) {
04123       var ctx = this.ctx;
04124       var current = this.current;
04125       var font = current.font;
04126       var glyphs = font.charsToGlyphs(str);
04127       var fontSize = current.fontSize;
04128       var fontSizeScale = current.fontSizeScale;
04129       var charSpacing = current.charSpacing;
04130       var wordSpacing = current.wordSpacing;
04131       var textHScale = current.textHScale * current.fontDirection;
04132       var fontMatrix = current.fontMatrix || FONT_IDENTITY_MATRIX;
04133       var glyphsLength = glyphs.length;
04134       var textLayer = this.textLayer;
04135       var geom;
04136       var textSelection = textLayer && !skipTextSelection ? true : false;
04137       var canvasWidth = 0.0;
04138       var vertical = font.vertical;
04139       var defaultVMetrics = font.defaultVMetrics;
04140 
04141       // Type3 fonts - each glyph is a "mini-PDF"
04142       if (font.coded) {
04143         ctx.save();
04144         ctx.transform.apply(ctx, current.textMatrix);
04145         ctx.translate(current.x, current.y);
04146 
04147         ctx.scale(textHScale, 1);
04148 
04149         if (textSelection) {
04150           this.save();
04151           ctx.scale(1, -1);
04152           geom = this.createTextGeometry();
04153           this.restore();
04154         }
04155         for (var i = 0; i < glyphsLength; ++i) {
04156 
04157           var glyph = glyphs[i];
04158           if (glyph === null) {
04159             // word break
04160             this.ctx.translate(wordSpacing, 0);
04161             current.x += wordSpacing * textHScale;
04162             continue;
04163           }
04164 
04165           this.processingType3 = glyph;
04166           this.save();
04167           ctx.scale(fontSize, fontSize);
04168           ctx.transform.apply(ctx, fontMatrix);
04169           this.executeOperatorList(glyph.operatorList);
04170           this.restore();
04171 
04172           var transformed = Util.applyTransform([glyph.width, 0], fontMatrix);
04173           var width = (transformed[0] * fontSize + charSpacing) *
04174                       current.fontDirection;
04175 
04176           ctx.translate(width, 0);
04177           current.x += width * textHScale;
04178 
04179           canvasWidth += width;
04180         }
04181         ctx.restore();
04182         this.processingType3 = null;
04183       } else {
04184         ctx.save();
04185         this.applyTextTransforms();
04186 
04187         var lineWidth = current.lineWidth;
04188         var a1 = current.textMatrix[0], b1 = current.textMatrix[1];
04189         var scale = Math.sqrt(a1 * a1 + b1 * b1);
04190         if (scale === 0 || lineWidth === 0)
04191           lineWidth = this.getSinglePixelWidth();
04192         else
04193           lineWidth /= scale;
04194 
04195         if (textSelection)
04196           geom = this.createTextGeometry();
04197 
04198         if (fontSizeScale != 1.0) {
04199           ctx.scale(fontSizeScale, fontSizeScale);
04200           lineWidth /= fontSizeScale;
04201         }
04202 
04203         ctx.lineWidth = lineWidth;
04204 
04205         var x = 0;
04206         for (var i = 0; i < glyphsLength; ++i) {
04207           var glyph = glyphs[i];
04208           if (glyph === null) {
04209             // word break
04210             x += current.fontDirection * wordSpacing;
04211             continue;
04212           }
04213 
04214           var restoreNeeded = false;
04215           var character = glyph.fontChar;
04216           var vmetric = glyph.vmetric || defaultVMetrics;
04217           if (vertical) {
04218             var vx = glyph.vmetric ? vmetric[1] : glyph.width * 0.5;
04219             vx = -vx * fontSize * current.fontMatrix[0];
04220             var vy = vmetric[2] * fontSize * current.fontMatrix[0];
04221           }
04222           var width = vmetric ? -vmetric[0] : glyph.width;
04223           var charWidth = width * fontSize * current.fontMatrix[0] +
04224                           charSpacing * current.fontDirection;
04225           var accent = glyph.accent;
04226 
04227           var scaledX, scaledY, scaledAccentX, scaledAccentY;
04228           if (!glyph.disabled) {
04229             if (vertical) {
04230               scaledX = vx / fontSizeScale;
04231               scaledY = (x + vy) / fontSizeScale;
04232             } else {
04233               scaledX = x / fontSizeScale;
04234               scaledY = 0;
04235             }
04236 
04237             if (font.remeasure && width > 0) {
04238               // some standard fonts may not have the exact width, trying to
04239               // rescale per character
04240               var measuredWidth = ctx.measureText(character).width * 1000 /
04241                 current.fontSize * current.fontSizeScale;
04242               var characterScaleX = width / measuredWidth;
04243               restoreNeeded = true;
04244               ctx.save();
04245               ctx.scale(characterScaleX, 1);
04246               scaledX /= characterScaleX;
04247               if (accent) {
04248                 scaledAccentX /= characterScaleX;
04249               }
04250             }
04251 
04252             this.paintChar(character, scaledX, scaledY);
04253             if (accent) {
04254               scaledAccentX = scaledX + accent.offset.x / fontSizeScale;
04255               scaledAccentY = scaledY - accent.offset.y / fontSizeScale;
04256               this.paintChar(accent.fontChar, scaledAccentX, scaledAccentY);
04257             }
04258           }
04259 
04260           x += charWidth;
04261 
04262           canvasWidth += charWidth;
04263 
04264           if (restoreNeeded) {
04265             ctx.restore();
04266           }
04267         }
04268         if (vertical) {
04269           current.y -= x * textHScale;
04270         } else {
04271           current.x += x * textHScale;
04272         }
04273         ctx.restore();
04274       }
04275 
04276       if (textSelection) {
04277         geom.canvasWidth = canvasWidth;
04278         if (vertical) {
04279           var vmetric = font.defaultVMetrics;
04280           geom.x += vmetric[1] * fontSize * current.fontMatrix[0] /
04281                     fontSizeScale * geom.hScale;
04282           geom.y += vmetric[2] * fontSize * current.fontMatrix[0] /
04283                     fontSizeScale * geom.vScale;
04284         }
04285         this.textLayer.appendText(geom);
04286       }
04287 
04288       return canvasWidth;
04289     },
04290     showSpacedText: function CanvasGraphics_showSpacedText(arr) {
04291       var ctx = this.ctx;
04292       var current = this.current;
04293       var font = current.font;
04294       var fontSize = current.fontSize;
04295       // TJ array's number is independent from fontMatrix
04296       var textHScale = current.textHScale * 0.001 * current.fontDirection;
04297       var arrLength = arr.length;
04298       var textLayer = this.textLayer;
04299       var geom;
04300       var canvasWidth = 0.0;
04301       var textSelection = textLayer ? true : false;
04302       var vertical = font.vertical;
04303       var spacingAccumulator = 0;
04304 
04305       if (textSelection) {
04306         ctx.save();
04307         this.applyTextTransforms();
04308         geom = this.createTextGeometry();
04309         ctx.restore();
04310       }
04311 
04312       for (var i = 0; i < arrLength; ++i) {
04313         var e = arr[i];
04314         if (isNum(e)) {
04315           var spacingLength = -e * fontSize * textHScale;
04316           if (vertical) {
04317             current.y += spacingLength;
04318           } else {
04319             current.x += spacingLength;
04320           }
04321 
04322           if (textSelection)
04323             spacingAccumulator += spacingLength;
04324         } else if (isString(e)) {
04325           var shownCanvasWidth = this.showText(e, true);
04326 
04327           if (textSelection) {
04328             canvasWidth += spacingAccumulator + shownCanvasWidth;
04329             spacingAccumulator = 0;
04330           }
04331         } else {
04332           error('TJ array element ' + e + ' is not string or num');
04333         }
04334       }
04335 
04336       if (textSelection) {
04337         geom.canvasWidth = canvasWidth;
04338         if (vertical) {
04339           var fontSizeScale = current.fontSizeScale;
04340           var vmetric = font.defaultVMetrics;
04341           geom.x += vmetric[1] * fontSize * current.fontMatrix[0] /
04342                     fontSizeScale * geom.hScale;
04343           geom.y += vmetric[2] * fontSize * current.fontMatrix[0] /
04344                     fontSizeScale * geom.vScale;
04345         }
04346         this.textLayer.appendText(geom);
04347       }
04348     },
04349     nextLineShowText: function CanvasGraphics_nextLineShowText(text) {
04350       this.nextLine();
04351       this.showText(text);
04352     },
04353     nextLineSetSpacingShowText:
04354       function CanvasGraphics_nextLineSetSpacingShowText(wordSpacing,
04355                                                          charSpacing,
04356                                                          text) {
04357       this.setWordSpacing(wordSpacing);
04358       this.setCharSpacing(charSpacing);
04359       this.nextLineShowText(text);
04360     },

04394     getColorN_Pattern: function CanvasGraphics_getColorN_Pattern(IR, cs) {
04395       if (IR[0] == 'TilingPattern') {
04396         var args = IR[1];
04397         var base = cs.base;
04398         var color;
04399         if (base) {
04400           var baseComps = base.numComps;
04401 
04402           color = base.getRgb(args, 0);
04403         }
04404         var pattern = new TilingPattern(IR, color, this.ctx, this.objs,
04405                                         this.commonObjs);
04406       } else if (IR[0] == 'RadialAxial' || IR[0] == 'Dummy') {
04407         var pattern = Pattern.shadingFromIR(IR);
04408       } else {
04409         error('Unkown IR type ' + IR[0]);
04410       }
04411       return pattern;
04412     },
04413     setStrokeColorN: function CanvasGraphics_setStrokeColorN(/*...*/) {
04414       var cs = this.current.strokeColorSpace;
04415 
04416       if (cs.name == 'Pattern') {
04417         this.current.strokeColor = this.getColorN_Pattern(arguments, cs);
04418       } else {
04419         this.setStrokeColor.apply(this, arguments);
04420       }
04421     },

04491     shadingFill: function CanvasGraphics_shadingFill(patternIR) {
04492       var ctx = this.ctx;
04493 
04494       this.save();
04495       var pattern = Pattern.shadingFromIR(patternIR);
04496       ctx.fillStyle = pattern.getPattern(ctx);
04497 
04498       var inv = ctx.mozCurrentTransformInverse;
04499       if (inv) {
04500         var canvas = ctx.canvas;
04501         var width = canvas.width;
04502         var height = canvas.height;
04503 
04504         var bl = Util.applyTransform([0, 0], inv);
04505         var br = Util.applyTransform([0, height], inv);
04506         var ul = Util.applyTransform([width, 0], inv);
04507         var ur = Util.applyTransform([width, height], inv);
04508 
04509         var x0 = Math.min(bl[0], br[0], ul[0], ur[0]);
04510         var y0 = Math.min(bl[1], br[1], ul[1], ur[1]);
04511         var x1 = Math.max(bl[0], br[0], ul[0], ur[0]);
04512         var y1 = Math.max(bl[1], br[1], ul[1], ur[1]);
04513 
04514         this.ctx.fillRect(x0, y0, x1 - x0, y1 - y0);
04515       } else {
04516         // HACK to draw the gradient onto an infinite rectangle.
04517         // PDF gradients are drawn across the entire image while
04518         // Canvas only allows gradients to be drawn in a rectangle
04519         // The following bug should allow us to remove this.
04520         // https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=664884
04521 
04522         this.ctx.fillRect(-1e10, -1e10, 2e10, 2e10);
04523       }
04524 
04525       this.restore();
04526     },

04536     paintFormXObjectBegin: function CanvasGraphics_paintFormXObjectBegin(matrix,
04537                                                                         bbox) {
04538       this.save();
04539       this.current.paintFormXObjectDepth++;
04540 
04541       if (matrix && isArray(matrix) && 6 == matrix.length)
04542         this.transform.apply(this, matrix);
04543 
04544       if (bbox && isArray(bbox) && 4 == bbox.length) {
04545         var width = bbox[2] - bbox[0];
04546         var height = bbox[3] - bbox[1];
04547         this.rectangle(bbox[0], bbox[1], width, height);
04548         this.clip();
04549         this.endPath();
04550       }
04551     },
04552 
04553     paintFormXObjectEnd: function CanvasGraphics_paintFormXObjectEnd() {
04554       var depth = this.current.paintFormXObjectDepth;
04555       do {
04556         this.restore();
04557         // some pdf don't close all restores inside object
04558         // closing those for them
04559       } while (this.current.paintFormXObjectDepth >= depth);
04560     },
04561 
04562     beginGroup: function CanvasGraphics_beginGroup(group) {
04563       this.save();
04564       var currentCtx = this.ctx;
04565       // TODO non-isolated groups - according to Rik at adobe non-isolated
04566       // group results aren't usually that different and they even have tools
04567       // that ignore this setting. Notes from Rik on implmenting:
04568       // - When you encounter an transparency group, create a new canvas with
04569       // the dimensions of the bbox
04570       // - copy the content from the previous canvas to the new canvas
04571       // - draw as usual
04572       // - remove the backdrop alpha:
04573       // alphaNew = 1 - (1 - alpha)/(1 - alphaBackdrop) with 'alpha' the alpha
04574       // value of your transparency group and 'alphaBackdrop' the alpha of the
04575       // backdrop
04576       // - remove background color:
04577       // colorNew = color - alphaNew *colorBackdrop /(1 - alphaNew)
04578       if (!group.isolated) {
04579         info('TODO: Support non-isolated groups.');
04580       }
04581 
04582       // TODO knockout - supposedly possible with the clever use of compositing
04583       // modes.
04584       if (group.knockout) {
04585         TODO('Support knockout groups.');
04586       }
04587 
04588       var currentTransform = currentCtx.mozCurrentTransform;
04589       if (group.matrix) {
04590         currentCtx.transform.apply(currentCtx, group.matrix);
04591       }
04592       assert(group.bbox, 'Bounding box is required.');
04593 
04594       // Based on the current transform figure out how big the bounding box
04595       // will actually be.
04596       var bounds = Util.getAxialAlignedBoundingBox(
04597                     group.bbox,
04598                     currentCtx.mozCurrentTransform);
04599       // Use ceil in case we're between sizes so we don't create canvas that is
04600       // too small and make the canvas at least 1x1 pixels.
04601       var drawnWidth = Math.max(Math.ceil(bounds[2] - bounds[0]), 1);
04602       var drawnHeight = Math.max(Math.ceil(bounds[3] - bounds[1]), 1);
04603 
04604       var scratchCanvas = createScratchCanvas(drawnWidth, drawnHeight);
04605       var groupCtx = scratchCanvas.getContext('2d');
04606       addContextCurrentTransform(groupCtx);
04607       // Since we created a new canvas that is just the size of the bounding box
04608       // we have to translate the group ctx.
04609       var offsetX = bounds[0];
04610       var offsetY = bounds[1];
04611       groupCtx.translate(-offsetX, -offsetY);
04612       groupCtx.transform.apply(groupCtx, currentTransform);
04613 
04614       // Setup the current ctx so when the group is popped we draw it the right
04615       // location.
04616       currentCtx.setTransform(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0);
04617       currentCtx.translate(offsetX, offsetY);
04618 
04619       // The transparency group inherits all off the current graphics state
04620       // except the blend mode, soft mask, and alpha constants.
04621       copyCtxState(currentCtx, groupCtx);
04622       this.ctx = groupCtx;
04623       this.setGState([
04624         ['SMask', 'None'],
04625         ['BM', 'Normal'],
04626         ['ca', 1],
04627         ['CA', 1]
04628       ]);
04629       this.groupStack.push(currentCtx);
04630     },
04631 
04632     endGroup: function CanvasGraphics_endGroup(group) {
04633       var groupCtx = this.ctx;
04634       this.ctx = this.groupStack.pop();
04635       // Turn off image smoothing to avoid sub pixel interpolation which can
04636       // look kind of blurry for some pdfs.
04637       if ('imageSmoothingEnabled' in this.ctx) {
04638         this.ctx.imageSmoothingEnabled = false;
04639       } else {
04640         this.ctx.mozImageSmoothingEnabled = false;
04641       }
04642       this.ctx.drawImage(groupCtx.canvas, 0, 0);
04643       this.restore();
04644     },
04645

04648       this.current = new CanvasExtraState();
04649     },
04650 
04651     endAnnotations: function CanvasGraphics_endAnnotations() {

04655     beginAnnotation: function CanvasGraphics_beginAnnotation(rect, transform,
04656                                                              matrix) {
04657       this.save();
04658 
04659       if (rect && isArray(rect) && 4 == rect.length) {
04660         var width = rect[2] - rect[0];
04661         var height = rect[3] - rect[1];
04662         this.rectangle(rect[0], rect[1], width, height);
04663         this.clip();
04664         this.endPath();
04665       }
04666 
04667       this.transform.apply(this, transform);
04668       this.transform.apply(this, matrix);
04669     },
04670

04672       this.restore();
04673     },

04675     paintJpegXObject: function CanvasGraphics_paintJpegXObject(objId, w, h) {
04676       var domImage = this.objs.get(objId);
04677       if (!domImage) {
04678         error('Dependent image isn\'t ready yet');
04679       }
04680 
04681       this.save();
04682 
04683       var ctx = this.ctx;
04684       // scale the image to the unit square
04685       ctx.scale(1 / w, -1 / h);
04686 
04687       ctx.drawImage(domImage, 0, 0, domImage.width, domImage.height,
04688                     0, -h, w, h);
04689       if (this.imageLayer) {
04690         var currentTransform = ctx.mozCurrentTransformInverse;
04691         var position = this.getCanvasPosition(0, 0);
04692         this.imageLayer.appendImage({
04693           objId: objId,
04694           left: position[0],
04695           top: position[1],
04696           width: w / currentTransform[0],
04697           height: h / currentTransform[3]
04698         });
04699       }
04700       this.restore();
04701     },
04702 
04703     paintImageMaskXObject: function CanvasGraphics_paintImageMaskXObject(img) {
04704       var ctx = this.ctx;
04705       var width = img.width, height = img.height;
04706 
04707       var glyph = this.processingType3;
04708 
04709       if (COMPILE_TYPE3_GLYPHS && glyph && !('compiled' in glyph)) {
04710         var MAX_SIZE_TO_COMPILE = 1000;
04711         if (width <= MAX_SIZE_TO_COMPILE && height <= MAX_SIZE_TO_COMPILE) {
04712           glyph.compiled =
04713             compileType3Glyph({data: img.data, width: width, height: height});
04714         } else {
04715           glyph.compiled = null;
04716         }
04717       }
04718 
04719       if (glyph && glyph.compiled) {
04720         glyph.compiled(ctx);
04721         return;
04722       }
04723 
04724       var maskCanvas = CachedCanvases.getCanvas('maskCanvas', width, height);
04725       var maskCtx = maskCanvas.getContext('2d');
04726       maskCtx.save();
04727 
04728       putBinaryImageData(maskCtx, img);
04729 
04730       maskCtx.globalCompositeOperation = 'source-in';
04731 
04732       var fillColor = this.current.fillColor;
04733       maskCtx.fillStyle = (fillColor && fillColor.hasOwnProperty('type') &&
04734                           fillColor.type === 'Pattern') ?
04735                           fillColor.getPattern(maskCtx) : fillColor;
04736       maskCtx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);
04737 
04738       maskCtx.restore();
04739 
04740       this.paintInlineImageXObject(maskCanvas);
04741     },
04742 
04743     paintImageMaskXObjectGroup:
04744       function CanvasGraphics_paintImageMaskXObjectGroup(images) {
04745       var ctx = this.ctx;
04746 
04747       for (var i = 0, ii = images.length; i < ii; i++) {
04748         var image = images[i];
04749         var width = image.width, height = image.height;
04750 
04751         var maskCanvas = CachedCanvases.getCanvas('maskCanvas', width, height);
04752         var maskCtx = maskCanvas.getContext('2d');
04753         maskCtx.save();
04754 
04755         putBinaryImageData(maskCtx, image);
04756 
04757         maskCtx.globalCompositeOperation = 'source-in';
04758 
04759         var fillColor = this.current.fillColor;
04760         maskCtx.fillStyle = (fillColor && fillColor.hasOwnProperty('type') &&
04761                             fillColor.type === 'Pattern') ?
04762                             fillColor.getPattern(maskCtx) : fillColor;
04763         maskCtx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);
04764 
04765         maskCtx.restore();
04766 
04767         ctx.save();
04768         ctx.transform.apply(ctx, image.transform);
04769         ctx.scale(1, -1);
04770         ctx.drawImage(maskCanvas, 0, 0, width, height,
04771                       0, -1, 1, 1);
04772         ctx.restore();
04773       }
04774     },
04775 
04776     paintImageXObject: function CanvasGraphics_paintImageXObject(objId) {
04777       var imgData = this.objs.get(objId);
04778       if (!imgData)
04779         error('Dependent image isn\'t ready yet');
04780 
04781       this.paintInlineImageXObject(imgData);
04782     },
04783 
04784     paintInlineImageXObject:
04785       function CanvasGraphics_paintInlineImageXObject(imgData) {
04786       var width = imgData.width;
04787       var height = imgData.height;
04788       var ctx = this.ctx;
04789 
04790       this.save();
04791       // scale the image to the unit square
04792       ctx.scale(1 / width, -1 / height);
04793 
04794       var currentTransform = ctx.mozCurrentTransformInverse;
04795       var a = currentTransform[0], b = currentTransform[1];
04796       var widthScale = Math.max(Math.sqrt(a * a + b * b), 1);
04797       var c = currentTransform[2], d = currentTransform[3];
04798       var heightScale = Math.max(Math.sqrt(c * c + d * d), 1);
04799 
04800       var imgToPaint;
04801       if (imgData instanceof HTMLElement) {
04802         imgToPaint = imgData;
04803       } else {
04804         var tmpCanvas = CachedCanvases.getCanvas('inlineImage', width, height);
04805         var tmpCtx = tmpCanvas.getContext('2d');
04806         putBinaryImageData(tmpCtx, imgData);
04807         imgToPaint = tmpCanvas;
04808       }
04809 
04810       var paintWidth = width, paintHeight = height;
04811       var tmpCanvasId = 'prescale1';
04812       // Vertial or horizontal scaling shall not be more than 2 to not loose the
04813       // pixels during drawImage operation, painting on the temporary canvas(es)
04814       // that are twice smaller in size
04815       while ((widthScale > 2 && paintWidth > 1) ||
04816              (heightScale > 2 && paintHeight > 1)) {
04817         var newWidth = paintWidth, newHeight = paintHeight;
04818         if (widthScale > 2 && paintWidth > 1) {
04819           newWidth = Math.ceil(paintWidth / 2);
04820           widthScale /= paintWidth / newWidth;
04821         }
04822         if (heightScale > 2 && paintHeight > 1) {
04823           newHeight = Math.ceil(paintHeight / 2);
04824           heightScale /= paintHeight / newHeight;
04825         }
04826         var tmpCanvas = CachedCanvases.getCanvas(tmpCanvasId,
04827                                                  newWidth, newHeight);
04828         tmpCtx = tmpCanvas.getContext('2d');
04829         tmpCtx.clearRect(0, 0, newWidth, newHeight);
04830         tmpCtx.drawImage(imgToPaint, 0, 0, paintWidth, paintHeight,
04831                                      0, 0, newWidth, newHeight);
04832         imgToPaint = tmpCanvas;
04833         paintWidth = newWidth;
04834         paintHeight = newHeight;
04835         tmpCanvasId = tmpCanvasId === 'prescale1' ? 'prescale2' : 'prescale1';
04836       }
04837       ctx.drawImage(imgToPaint, 0, 0, paintWidth, paintHeight,
04838                                 0, -height, width, height);
04839 
04840       if (this.imageLayer) {
04841         var position = this.getCanvasPosition(0, -height);
04842         this.imageLayer.appendImage({
04843           imgData: imgData,
04844           left: position[0],
04845           top: position[1],
04846           width: width / currentTransform[0],
04847           height: height / currentTransform[3]
04848         });
04849       }
04850       this.restore();
04851     },
04852 
04853     paintInlineImageXObjectGroup:
04854       function CanvasGraphics_paintInlineImageXObjectGroup(imgData, map) {
04855       var ctx = this.ctx;
04856       var w = imgData.width;
04857       var h = imgData.height;
04858 
04859       var tmpCanvas = CachedCanvases.getCanvas('inlineImage', w, h);
04860       var tmpCtx = tmpCanvas.getContext('2d');
04861       putBinaryImageData(tmpCtx, imgData);
04862 
04863       for (var i = 0, ii = map.length; i < ii; i++) {
04864         var entry = map[i];
04865         ctx.save();
04866         ctx.transform.apply(ctx, entry.transform);
04867         ctx.scale(1, -1);
04868         ctx.drawImage(tmpCanvas, entry.x, entry.y, entry.w, entry.h,
04869                       0, -1, 1, 1);
04870         if (this.imageLayer) {
04871           var position = this.getCanvasPosition(entry.x, entry.y);
04872           this.imageLayer.appendImage({
04873             imgData: imgData,
04874             left: position[0],
04875             top: position[1],
04876             width: w,
04877             height: h
04878           });
04879         }
04880         ctx.restore();
04881       }
04882     },
04883

04913 
04914     consumePath: function CanvasGraphics_consumePath() {
04915       if (this.pendingClip) {
04916         if (this.pendingClip == EO_CLIP) {
04917           if ('mozFillRule' in this.ctx) {
04918             this.ctx.mozFillRule = 'evenodd';
04919             this.ctx.clip();
04920             this.ctx.mozFillRule = 'nonzero';
04921           } else {
04922             try {
04923               this.ctx.clip('evenodd');
04924             } catch (ex) {
04925               // shouldn't really happen, but browsers might think differently
04926               this.ctx.clip();
04927             }
04928           }
04929         } else {
04930           this.ctx.clip();
04931         }
04932         this.pendingClip = null;
04933       }
04934       this.ctx.beginPath();
04935     },
04936     getSinglePixelWidth: function CanvasGraphics_getSinglePixelWidth(scale) {
04937       var inverse = this.ctx.mozCurrentTransformInverse;
04938       // max of the current horizontal and vertical scale
04939       return Math.sqrt(Math.max(
04940         (inverse[0] * inverse[0] + inverse[1] * inverse[1]),
04941         (inverse[2] * inverse[2] + inverse[3] * inverse[3])));
04942     },
04943     getCanvasPosition: function CanvasGraphics_getCanvasPosition(x, y) {
04944         var transform = this.ctx.mozCurrentTransform;
04945         return [
04946           transform[0] * x + transform[2] * y + transform[4],
04947           transform[1] * x + transform[3] * y + transform[5]
04948         ];
04949     }
04950   };
04951 
04952   return CanvasGraphics;
04953 })();

04967 var Cmd = (function CmdClosure() {
04968   function Cmd(cmd) {
04969     this.cmd = cmd;
04970   }
04971 
04972   Cmd.prototype = {};
04973 
04974   var cmdCache = {};
04975 
04976   Cmd.get = function Cmd_get(cmd) {
04977     var cmdValue = cmdCache[cmd];
04978     if (cmdValue)
04979       return cmdValue;
