04987 var Dict = (function DictClosure() {
04988   var nonSerializable = function nonSerializableClosure() {
04989     return nonSerializable; // creating closure on some variable
04990   };
04991 
04992   // xref is optional
04993   function Dict(xref) {
04994     // Map should only be used internally, use functions below to access.
04995     this.map = Object.create(null);
04996     this.xref = xref;
04997     this.__nonSerializable__ = nonSerializable; // disable cloning of the Dict
04998   }
04999 
05000   Dict.prototype = {
05001     assignXref: function Dict_assignXref(newXref) {
05002       this.xref = newXref;
05003     },
05004 
05005     // automatically dereferences Ref objects
05006     get: function Dict_get(key1, key2, key3) {
05007       var value;
05008       var xref = this.xref;
05009       if (typeof (value = this.map[key1]) != 'undefined' || key1 in this.map ||
05010           typeof key2 == 'undefined') {
05011         return xref ? xref.fetchIfRef(value) : value;
05012       }
05013       if (typeof (value = this.map[key2]) != 'undefined' || key2 in this.map ||
05014           typeof key3 == 'undefined') {
05015         return xref ? xref.fetchIfRef(value) : value;
05016       }
05017       value = this.map[key3] || null;
05018       return xref ? xref.fetchIfRef(value) : value;
05019     },
05020 
05021     // Same as get(), but returns a promise and uses fetchIfRefAsync().
05022     getAsync: function Dict_getAsync(key1, key2, key3) {
05023       var value;
05024       var promise;
05025       var xref = this.xref;
05026       if (typeof (value = this.map[key1]) !== undefined || key1 in this.map ||
05027           typeof key2 === undefined) {
05028         if (xref) {
05029           return xref.fetchIfRefAsync(value);
05030         }
05031         promise = new Promise();
05032         promise.resolve(value);
05033         return promise;
05034       }
05035       if (typeof (value = this.map[key2]) !== undefined || key2 in this.map ||
05036           typeof key3 === undefined) {
05037         if (xref) {
05038           return xref.fetchIfRefAsync(value);
05039         }
05040         promise = new Promise();
05041         promise.resolve(value);
05042         return promise;
05043       }
05044       value = this.map[key3] || null;
05045       if (xref) {
05046         return xref.fetchIfRefAsync(value);
05047       }
05048       promise = new Promise();
05049       promise.resolve(value);
05050       return promise;
05051     },
05052 
05053     // no dereferencing
05054     getRaw: function Dict_getRaw(key) {
05055       return this.map[key];
05056     },
05057 
05058     // creates new map and dereferences all Refs
05059     getAll: function Dict_getAll() {
05060       var all = {};
05061       for (var key in this.map) {
05062         var obj = this.get(key);
05063         all[key] = obj instanceof Dict ? obj.getAll() : obj;
05064       }
05065       return all;
05066     },
05067 
05068     set: function Dict_set(key, value) {
05069       this.map[key] = value;
05070     },
05071 
05072     has: function Dict_has(key) {
05073       return key in this.map;
05074     },
05075 
05076     forEach: function Dict_forEach(callback) {
05077       for (var key in this.map) {
05078         callback(key, this.get(key));
05079       }
05080     }
05081   };
05082 
05083   return Dict;
05084 })();

05097 // The reference is identified by number and generation,
05098 // this structure stores only one instance of the reference.
05099 var RefSet = (function RefSetClosure() {
05100   function RefSet() {
05101     this.dict = {};
05102   }
05103 
05104   RefSet.prototype = {
05105     has: function RefSet_has(ref) {
05106       return ('R' + ref.num + '.' + ref.gen) in this.dict;
05107     },
05108 
05109     put: function RefSet_put(ref) {
05110       this.dict['R' + ref.num + '.' + ref.gen] = true;
05111     },
05112 
05113     remove: function RefSet_remove(ref) {
05114       delete this.dict['R' + ref.num + '.' + ref.gen];
05115     }
05116   };
05117 
05118   return RefSet;
05119 })();

05121 var RefSetCache = (function RefSetCacheClosure() {

05124   }
05125 
05126   RefSetCache.prototype = {
05127     get: function RefSetCache_get(ref) {
05128       return this.dict['R' + ref.num + '.' + ref.gen];
05129     },
05130 
05131     has: function RefSetCache_has(ref) {
05132       return ('R' + ref.num + '.' + ref.gen) in this.dict;
05133     },

05142 
05143 var Catalog = (function CatalogClosure() {
05144   function Catalog(pdfManager, xref) {
05145     this.pdfManager = pdfManager;
05146     this.xref = xref;
05147     this.catDict = xref.getCatalogObj();
05148     assertWellFormed(isDict(this.catDict),
05149       'catalog object is not a dictionary');
05150 
05151     // Stores state as we traverse the pages catalog so that we can resume
05152     // parsing if an exception is thrown
05153     this.traversePagesQueue = [{
05154       pagesDict: this.toplevelPagesDict,
05155       posInKids: 0
05156     }];
05157     this.pagePromises = [];
05158     this.currPageIndex = 0;
05159   }
05160 
05161   Catalog.prototype = {
05162     get metadata() {
05163       var streamRef = this.catDict.getRaw('Metadata');
05164       if (!isRef(streamRef))
05165         return shadow(this, 'metadata', null);
05166 
05167       var encryptMetadata = !this.xref.encrypt ? false :
05168         this.xref.encrypt.encryptMetadata;
05169 
05170       var stream = this.xref.fetch(streamRef, !encryptMetadata);
05171       var metadata;
05172       if (stream && isDict(stream.dict)) {
05173         var type = stream.dict.get('Type');
05174         var subtype = stream.dict.get('Subtype');
05175 
05176         if (isName(type) && isName(subtype) &&
05177             type.name === 'Metadata' && subtype.name === 'XML') {
05178           // XXX: This should examine the charset the XML document defines,
05179           // however since there are currently no real means to decode
05180           // arbitrary charsets, let's just hope that the author of the PDF
05181           // was reasonable enough to stick with the XML default charset,
05182           // which is UTF-8.
05183           try {
05184             metadata = stringToUTF8String(bytesToString(stream.getBytes()));
05185           } catch (e) {
05186             info('Skipping invalid metadata.');
05187           }
05188         }
05189       }
05190 
05191       return shadow(this, 'metadata', metadata);
05192     },
05193     get toplevelPagesDict() {
05194       var pagesObj = this.catDict.get('Pages');
05195       assertWellFormed(isDict(pagesObj), 'invalid top-level pages dictionary');
05196       // shadow the prototype getter
05197       return shadow(this, 'toplevelPagesDict', pagesObj);
05198     },
05199     get documentOutline() {
05200       var obj = null;
05201       try {
05202         obj = this.readDocumentOutline();
05203       } catch (ex) {
05204         if (ex instanceof MissingDataException) {
05205           throw ex;
05206         }
05207         warn('Unable to read document outline');
05208       }
05209       return shadow(this, 'documentOutline', obj);
05210     },
05211     readDocumentOutline: function Catalog_readDocumentOutline() {
05212       var xref = this.xref;
05213       var obj = this.catDict.get('Outlines');
05214       var root = { items: [] };
05215       if (isDict(obj)) {
05216         obj = obj.getRaw('First');
05217         var processed = new RefSet();
05218         if (isRef(obj)) {
05219           var queue = [{obj: obj, parent: root}];
05220           // to avoid recursion keeping track of the items
05221           // in the processed dictionary
05222           processed.put(obj);
05223           while (queue.length > 0) {
05224             var i = queue.shift();
05225             var outlineDict = xref.fetchIfRef(i.obj);
05226             if (outlineDict === null)
05227               continue;
05228             if (!outlineDict.has('Title'))
05229               error('Invalid outline item');
05230             var dest = outlineDict.get('A');
05231             if (dest)
05232               dest = dest.get('D');
05233             else if (outlineDict.has('Dest')) {
05234               dest = outlineDict.getRaw('Dest');
05235               if (isName(dest))
05236                 dest = dest.name;
05237             }
05238             var title = outlineDict.get('Title');
05239             var outlineItem = {
05240               dest: dest,
05241               title: stringToPDFString(title),
05242               color: outlineDict.get('C') || [0, 0, 0],
05243               count: outlineDict.get('Count'),
05244               bold: !!(outlineDict.get('F') & 2),
05245               italic: !!(outlineDict.get('F') & 1),
05246               items: []
05247             };
05248             i.parent.items.push(outlineItem);
05249             obj = outlineDict.getRaw('First');
05250             if (isRef(obj) && !processed.has(obj)) {
05251               queue.push({obj: obj, parent: outlineItem});
05252               processed.put(obj);
05253             }
05254             obj = outlineDict.getRaw('Next');
05255             if (isRef(obj) && !processed.has(obj)) {
05256               queue.push({obj: obj, parent: i.parent});
05257               processed.put(obj);
05258             }
05259           }
05260         }
05261       }
05262       return root.items.length > 0 ? root.items : null;
05263     },
05264     get numPages() {
05265       var obj = this.toplevelPagesDict.get('Count');
05266       assertWellFormed(
05267         isInt(obj),
05268         'page count in top level pages object is not an integer'
05269       );
05270       // shadow the prototype getter
05271       return shadow(this, 'num', obj);
05272     },
05273     get destinations() {
05274       function fetchDestination(dest) {
05275         return isDict(dest) ? dest.get('D') : dest;
05276       }
05277 
05278       var xref = this.xref;
05279       var dests = {}, nameTreeRef, nameDictionaryRef;
05280       var obj = this.catDict.get('Names');
05281       if (obj)
05282         nameTreeRef = obj.getRaw('Dests');
05283       else if (this.catDict.has('Dests'))
05284         nameDictionaryRef = this.catDict.get('Dests');
05285 
05286       if (nameDictionaryRef) {
05287         // reading simple destination dictionary
05288         obj = nameDictionaryRef;
05289         obj.forEach(function catalogForEach(key, value) {
05290           if (!value) return;
05291           dests[key] = fetchDestination(value);
05292         });
05293       }
05294       if (nameTreeRef) {
05295         var nameTree = new NameTree(nameTreeRef, xref);
05296         var names = nameTree.getAll();
05297         for (var name in names) {
05298           if (!names.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
05299             continue;
05300           }
05301           dests[name] = fetchDestination(names[name]);
05302         }
05303       }
05304       return shadow(this, 'destinations', dests);
05305     },
05306     get javaScript() {
05307       var xref = this.xref;
05308       var obj = this.catDict.get('Names');
05309 
05310       var javaScript = [];
05311       if (obj && obj.has('JavaScript')) {
05312         var nameTree = new NameTree(obj.getRaw('JavaScript'), xref);
05313         var names = nameTree.getAll();
05314         for (var name in names) {
05315           if (!names.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
05316             continue;
05317           }
05318           // We don't really use the JavaScript right now so this code is
05319           // defensive so we don't cause errors on document load.
05320           var jsDict = names[name];
05321           if (!isDict(jsDict)) {
05322             continue;
05323           }
05324           var type = jsDict.get('S');
05325           if (!isName(type) || type.name !== 'JavaScript') {
05326             continue;
05327           }
05328           var js = jsDict.get('JS');
05329           if (!isString(js) && !isStream(js)) {
05330             continue;
05331           }
05332           if (isStream(js)) {
05333             js = bytesToString(js.getBytes());
05334           }
05335           javaScript.push(stringToPDFString(js));
05336         }
05337       }
05338       return shadow(this, 'javaScript', javaScript);
05339     },
05340 
05341     getPage: function Catalog_getPage(pageIndex) {
05342       if (!(pageIndex in this.pagePromises)) {
05343         this.pagePromises[pageIndex] = new Promise();
05344       }
05345       return this.pagePromises[pageIndex];
05346     },
05347 
05348     // Traverses pages in DFS order so that pages are processed in increasing
05349     // order
05350     traversePages: function Catalog_traversePages() {
05351       var queue = this.traversePagesQueue;
05352       while (queue.length) {
05353         var queueItem = queue[queue.length - 1];
05354         var pagesDict = queueItem.pagesDict;
05355 
05356         var kids = pagesDict.get('Kids');
05357         assert(isArray(kids), 'page dictionary kids object is not an array');
05358         if (queueItem.posInKids >= kids.length) {
05359           queue.pop();
05360           continue;
05361         }
05362         var kidRef = kids[queueItem.posInKids];
05363         assert(isRef(kidRef), 'page dictionary kid is not a reference');
05364 
05365         var kid = this.xref.fetch(kidRef);
05366         if (isDict(kid, 'Page') || (isDict(kid) && !kid.has('Kids'))) {
05367           var pageIndex = this.currPageIndex++;
05368           var page = new Page(this.pdfManager, this.xref, pageIndex, kid,
05369                               kidRef);
05370           if (!(pageIndex in this.pagePromises)) {
05371             this.pagePromises[pageIndex] = new Promise();
05372           }
05373           this.pagePromises[pageIndex].resolve(page);
05374 
05375         } else { // must be a child page dictionary
05376           assert(
05377             isDict(kid),
05378             'page dictionary kid reference points to wrong type of object'
05379           );
05380 
05381           queue.push({
05382             pagesDict: kid,
05383             posInKids: 0
05384           });
05385         }
05386         ++queueItem.posInKids;
05387       }
05388     }
05389   };
05390 
05391   return Catalog;
05392 })();
05393 
05394 var XRef = (function XRefClosure() {
05395   function XRef(stream, password) {
05396 
05397     this.stream = stream;
05398     this.entries = [];
05399     this.xrefstms = {};
05400     // prepare the XRef cache
05401     this.cache = [];
05402     this.password = password;
05403   }
05404 
05405   XRef.prototype = {
05406     setStartXRef: function XRef_setStartXRef(startXRef) {
05407       // Store the starting positions of xref tables as we process them
05408       // so we can recover from missing data errors
05409       this.startXRefQueue = [startXRef];
05410     },
05411 
05412     parse: function XRef_parse(recoveryMode) {
05413       var trailerDict;
05414       if (!recoveryMode) {
05415         trailerDict = this.readXRef();
05416       } else {
05417         warn('Indexing all PDF objects');
05418         trailerDict = this.indexObjects();
05419       }
05420       trailerDict.assignXref(this);
05421       this.trailer = trailerDict;
05422       var encrypt = trailerDict.get('Encrypt');
05423       if (encrypt) {
05424         var ids = trailerDict.get('ID');
05425         var fileId = (ids && ids.length) ? ids[0] : '';
05426         this.encrypt = new CipherTransformFactory(
05427             encrypt, fileId, this.password);
05428       }
05429 
05430       // get the root dictionary (catalog) object
05431       if (!(this.root = trailerDict.get('Root'))) {
05432         error('Invalid root reference');
05433       }
05434     },
05435 
05436     processXRefTable: function XRef_processXRefTable(parser) {
05437       if (!('tableState' in this)) {
05438         // Stores state of the table as we process it so we can resume
05439         // from middle of table in case of missing data error
05440         this.tableState = {
05441           entryNum: 0,
05442           streamPos: parser.lexer.stream.pos,
05443           parserBuf1: parser.buf1,
05444           parserBuf2: parser.buf2
05445         };
05446       }
05447 
05448       var obj = this.readXRefTable(parser);
05449 
05450       // Sanity check
05451       if (!isCmd(obj, 'trailer'))
05452         error('Invalid XRef table: could not find trailer dictionary');
05453 
05454       // Read trailer dictionary, e.g.
05455       // trailer
05456       //    << /Size 22
05457       //      /Root 20R
05458       //      /Info 10R
05459       //      /ID [ <81b14aafa313db63dbd6f981e49f94f4> ]
05460       //    >>
05461       // The parser goes through the entire stream << ... >> and provides
05462       // a getter interface for the key-value table
05463       var dict = parser.getObj();
05464       if (!isDict(dict))
05465         error('Invalid XRef table: could not parse trailer dictionary');
05466 
05467       delete this.tableState;
05468 
05469       return dict;
05470     },
05471 
05472     readXRefTable: function XRef_readXRefTable(parser) {
05473       // Example of cross-reference table:
05474       // xref
05475       // 0 1                    <-- subsection header (first obj #, obj count)
05476       // 0000000000 65535 f     <-- actual object (offset, generation #, f/n)
05477       // 23 2                   <-- subsection header ... and so on ...
05478       // 0000025518 00002 n
05479       // 0000025635 00000 n
05480       // trailer
05481       // ...
05482 
05483       var stream = parser.lexer.stream;
05484       var tableState = this.tableState;
05485       stream.pos = tableState.streamPos;
05486       parser.buf1 = tableState.parserBuf1;
05487       parser.buf2 = tableState.parserBuf2;
05488 
05489       // Outer loop is over subsection headers
05490       var obj;
05491 
05492       while (true) {
05493         if (!('firstEntryNum' in tableState) || !('entryCount' in tableState)) {
05494           if (isCmd(obj = parser.getObj(), 'trailer')) {
05495             break;
05496           }
05497           tableState.firstEntryNum = obj;
05498           tableState.entryCount = parser.getObj();
05499         }
05500 
05501         var first = tableState.firstEntryNum;
05502         var count = tableState.entryCount;
05503         if (!isInt(first) || !isInt(count))
05504           error('Invalid XRef table: wrong types in subsection header');
05505 
05506         // Inner loop is over objects themselves
05507         for (var i = tableState.entryNum; i < count; i++) {
05508           tableState.streamPos = stream.pos;
05509           tableState.entryNum = i;
05510           tableState.parserBuf1 = parser.buf1;
05511           tableState.parserBuf2 = parser.buf2;
05512 
05513           var entry = {};
05514           entry.offset = parser.getObj();
05515           entry.gen = parser.getObj();
05516           var type = parser.getObj();
05517 
05518           if (isCmd(type, 'f'))
05519             entry.free = true;
05520           else if (isCmd(type, 'n'))
05521             entry.uncompressed = true;
05522 
05523           // Validate entry obj
05524           if (!isInt(entry.offset) || !isInt(entry.gen) ||
05525               !(entry.free || entry.uncompressed)) {
05526             console.log(entry.offset, entry.gen, entry.free,
05527                 entry.uncompressed);
05528             error('Invalid entry in XRef subsection: ' + first + ', ' + count);
05529           }
05530 
05531           if (!this.entries[i + first])
05532             this.entries[i + first] = entry;
05533         }
05534 
05535         tableState.entryNum = 0;
05536         tableState.streamPos = stream.pos;
05537         tableState.parserBuf1 = parser.buf1;
05538         tableState.parserBuf2 = parser.buf2;
05539         delete tableState.firstEntryNum;
05540         delete tableState.entryCount;
05541       }
05542 
05543       // Per issue 3248: hp scanners generate bad XRef
05544       if (first === 1 && this.entries[1] && this.entries[1].free) {
05545         // shifting the entries
05546         this.entries.shift();
05547       }
05548 
05549       // Sanity check: as per spec, first object must be free
05550       if (this.entries[0] && !this.entries[0].free)
05551         error('Invalid XRef table: unexpected first object');
05552 
05553       return obj;
05554     },
05555 
05556     processXRefStream: function XRef_processXRefStream(stream) {
05557       if (!('streamState' in this)) {
05558         // Stores state of the stream as we process it so we can resume
05559         // from middle of stream in case of missing data error
05560         var streamParameters = stream.dict;
05561         var byteWidths = streamParameters.get('W');
05562         var range = streamParameters.get('Index');
05563         if (!range) {
05564           range = [0, streamParameters.get('Size')];
05565         }
05566 
05567         this.streamState = {
05568           entryRanges: range,
05569           byteWidths: byteWidths,
05570           entryNum: 0,
05571           streamPos: stream.pos
05572         };
05573       }
05574       this.readXRefStream(stream);
05575       delete this.streamState;
05576 
05577       return stream.dict;
05578     },
05579 
05580     readXRefStream: function XRef_readXRefStream(stream) {
05581       var i, j;
05582       var streamState = this.streamState;
05583       stream.pos = streamState.streamPos;
05584 
05585       var byteWidths = streamState.byteWidths;
05586       var typeFieldWidth = byteWidths[0];
05587       var offsetFieldWidth = byteWidths[1];
05588       var generationFieldWidth = byteWidths[2];
05589 
05590       var entryRanges = streamState.entryRanges;
05591       while (entryRanges.length > 0) {
05592 
05593         var first = entryRanges[0];
05594         var n = entryRanges[1];
05595 
05596         if (!isInt(first) || !isInt(n))
05597           error('Invalid XRef range fields: ' + first + ', ' + n);
05598 
05599         if (!isInt(typeFieldWidth) || !isInt(offsetFieldWidth) ||
05600             !isInt(generationFieldWidth)) {
05601           error('Invalid XRef entry fields length: ' + first + ', ' + n);
05602         }
05603         for (i = streamState.entryNum; i < n; ++i) {
05604           streamState.entryNum = i;
05605           streamState.streamPos = stream.pos;
05606 
05607           var type = 0, offset = 0, generation = 0;
05608           for (j = 0; j < typeFieldWidth; ++j)
05609             type = (type << 8) | stream.getByte();
05610           // if type field is absent, its default value = 1
05611           if (typeFieldWidth === 0)
05612             type = 1;
05613           for (j = 0; j < offsetFieldWidth; ++j)
05614             offset = (offset << 8) | stream.getByte();
05615           for (j = 0; j < generationFieldWidth; ++j)
05616             generation = (generation << 8) | stream.getByte();
05617           var entry = {};
05618           entry.offset = offset;
05619           entry.gen = generation;
05620           switch (type) {
05621             case 0:
05622               entry.free = true;
05623               break;
05624             case 1:
05625               entry.uncompressed = true;
05626               break;
05627             case 2:
05628               break;
05629             default:
05630               error('Invalid XRef entry type: ' + type);
05631           }
05632           if (!this.entries[first + i])
05633             this.entries[first + i] = entry;
05634         }
05635 
05636         streamState.entryNum = 0;
05637         streamState.streamPos = stream.pos;
05638         entryRanges.splice(0, 2);
05639       }
05640     },
05641     indexObjects: function XRef_indexObjects() {
05642       // Simple scan through the PDF content to find objects,
05643       // trailers and XRef streams.
05644       function readToken(data, offset) {
05645         var token = '', ch = data[offset];
05646         while (ch !== 13 && ch !== 10) {
05647           if (++offset >= data.length)
05648             break;
05649           token += String.fromCharCode(ch);
05650           ch = data[offset];
05651         }
05652         return token;
05653       }
05654       function skipUntil(data, offset, what) {
05655         var length = what.length, dataLength = data.length;
05656         var skipped = 0;
05657         // finding byte sequence
05658         while (offset < dataLength) {
05659           var i = 0;
05660           while (i < length && data[offset + i] == what[i])
05661             ++i;
05662           if (i >= length)
05663             break; // sequence found
05664 
05665           offset++;
05666           skipped++;
05667         }
05668         return skipped;
05669       }
05670       var trailerBytes = new Uint8Array([116, 114, 97, 105, 108, 101, 114]);
05671       var startxrefBytes = new Uint8Array([115, 116, 97, 114, 116, 120, 114,
05672                                           101, 102]);
05673       var endobjBytes = new Uint8Array([101, 110, 100, 111, 98, 106]);
05674       var xrefBytes = new Uint8Array([47, 88, 82, 101, 102]);
05675 
05676       var stream = this.stream;
05677       stream.pos = 0;
05678       var buffer = stream.getBytes();
05679       var position = stream.start, length = buffer.length;
05680       var trailers = [], xrefStms = [];
05681       var state = 0;
05682       var currentToken;
05683       while (position < length) {
05684         var ch = buffer[position];
05685         if (ch === 32 || ch === 9 || ch === 13 || ch === 10) {
05686           ++position;
05687           continue;
05688         }
05689         if (ch === 37) { // %-comment
05690           do {
05691             ++position;
05692             ch = buffer[position];
05693           } while (ch !== 13 && ch !== 10);
05694           continue;
05695         }
05696         var token = readToken(buffer, position);
05697         var m;
05698         if (token === 'xref') {
05699           position += skipUntil(buffer, position, trailerBytes);
05700           trailers.push(position);
05701           position += skipUntil(buffer, position, startxrefBytes);
05702         } else if ((m = /^(\d+)\s+(\d+)\s+obj\b/.exec(token))) {
05703           this.entries[m[1]] = {
05704             offset: position,
05705             gen: m[2] | 0,
05706             uncompressed: true
05707           };
05708 
05709           var contentLength = skipUntil(buffer, position, endobjBytes) + 7;
05710           var content = buffer.subarray(position, position + contentLength);
05711 
05712           // checking XRef stream suspect
05713           // (it shall have '/XRef' and next char is not a letter)
05714           var xrefTagOffset = skipUntil(content, 0, xrefBytes);
05715           if (xrefTagOffset < contentLength &&
05716               content[xrefTagOffset + 5] < 64) {
05717             xrefStms.push(position);
05718             this.xrefstms[position] = 1; // don't read it recursively
05719           }
05720 
05721           position += contentLength;
05722         } else
05723           position += token.length + 1;
05724       }
05725       // reading XRef streams
05726       for (var i = 0, ii = xrefStms.length; i < ii; ++i) {
05727         this.startXRefQueue.push(xrefStms[i]);
05728         this.readXRef(/* recoveryMode */ true);
05729       }
05730       // finding main trailer
05731       var dict;
05732       for (var i = 0, ii = trailers.length; i < ii; ++i) {
05733         stream.pos = trailers[i];
05734         var parser = new Parser(new Lexer(stream), true, null);
05735         var obj = parser.getObj();
05736         if (!isCmd(obj, 'trailer'))
05737           continue;
05738         // read the trailer dictionary
05739         if (!isDict(dict = parser.getObj()))
05740           continue;
05741         // taking the first one with 'ID'
05742         if (dict.has('ID'))
05743           return dict;
05744       }
05745       // no tailer with 'ID', taking last one (if exists)
05746       if (dict)
05747         return dict;
05748       // nothing helps
05749       // calling error() would reject worker with an UnknownErrorException.
05750       throw new InvalidPDFException('Invalid PDF structure');
05751     },
05752 
05753     readXRef: function XRef_readXRef(recoveryMode) {
05754       var stream = this.stream;
05755 
05756       try {
05757         while (this.startXRefQueue.length) {
05758           var startXRef = this.startXRefQueue[0];
05759 
05760           stream.pos = startXRef;
05761 
05762           var parser = new Parser(new Lexer(stream), true, null);
05763           var obj = parser.getObj();
05764           var dict;
05765 
05766           // Get dictionary
05767           if (isCmd(obj, 'xref')) {
05768 
05769             // Parse end-of-file XRef
05770             dict = this.processXRefTable(parser);
05771             if (!this.topDict) {
05772               this.topDict = dict;
05773             }
05774 
05775             // Recursively get other XRefs 'XRefStm', if any
05776             obj = dict.get('XRefStm');
05777             if (isInt(obj)) {
05778               var pos = obj;
05779               // ignore previously loaded xref streams
05780               // (possible infinite recursion)
05781               if (!(pos in this.xrefstms)) {
05782                 this.xrefstms[pos] = 1;
05783                 this.startXRefQueue.push(pos);
05784               }
05785             }
05786           } else if (isInt(obj)) {
05787 
05788             // Parse in-stream XRef
05789             if (!isInt(parser.getObj()) ||
05790                 !isCmd(parser.getObj(), 'obj') ||
05791                 !isStream(obj = parser.getObj())) {
05792               error('Invalid XRef stream');
05793             }
05794             dict = this.processXRefStream(obj);
05795             if (!this.topDict) {
05796               this.topDict = dict;
05797             }
05798 
05799             if (!dict)
05800               error('Failed to read XRef stream');
05801           }
05802 
05803           // Recursively get previous dictionary, if any
05804           obj = dict.get('Prev');
05805           if (isInt(obj)) {
05806             this.startXRefQueue.push(obj);
05807           } else if (isRef(obj)) {
05808             // The spec says Prev must not be a reference, i.e. "/Prev NNN"
05809             // This is a fallback for non-compliant PDFs, i.e. "/Prev NNN 0 R"
05810             this.startXRefQueue.push(obj.num);
05811           }
05812 
05813           this.startXRefQueue.shift();
05814         }
05815 
05816         return this.topDict;
05817       } catch (e) {
05818         if (e instanceof MissingDataException) {
05819           throw e;
05820         }
05821         log('(while reading XRef): ' + e);
05822       }
05823 
05824       if (recoveryMode)
05825         return;
05826       throw new XRefParseException();
05827     },
05828 
05829     getEntry: function XRef_getEntry(i) {
05830       var e = this.entries[i];
05831       if (e === null)
05832         return null;
05833       return e.free || !e.offset ? null : e; // returns null if entry is free
05834     },
05835     fetchIfRef: function XRef_fetchIfRef(obj) {
05836       if (!isRef(obj))
05837         return obj;
05838       return this.fetch(obj);
05839     },
05840     fetch: function XRef_fetch(ref, suppressEncryption) {
05841       assertWellFormed(isRef(ref), 'ref object is not a reference');
05842       var num = ref.num;
05843       var e;
05844       if (num in this.cache) {
05845         e = this.cache[num];
05846         if (e instanceof Stream) {
05847           return e.makeSubStream(e.start, e.length, e.dict);
05848         }
05849         return e;
05850       }
05851 
05852       e = this.getEntry(num);
05853 
05854       // the referenced entry can be free
05855       if (e === null)
05856         return (this.cache[num] = e);
05857 
05858       var gen = ref.gen;
05859       var stream, parser;
05860       if (e.uncompressed) {
05861         if (e.gen != gen)
05862           error('inconsistent generation in XRef');
05863         stream = this.stream.makeSubStream(e.offset);
05864         parser = new Parser(new Lexer(stream), true, this);
05865         var obj1 = parser.getObj();
05866         var obj2 = parser.getObj();
05867         var obj3 = parser.getObj();
05868         if (!isInt(obj1) || obj1 != num ||
05869             !isInt(obj2) || obj2 != gen ||
05870             !isCmd(obj3)) {
05871           error('bad XRef entry');
05872         }
05873         if (!isCmd(obj3, 'obj')) {
05874           // some bad pdfs use "obj1234" and really mean 1234
05875           if (obj3.cmd.indexOf('obj') === 0) {
05876             num = parseInt(obj3.cmd.substring(3), 10);
05877             if (!isNaN(num))
05878               return num;
05879           }
05880           error('bad XRef entry');
05881         }
05882         if (this.encrypt && !suppressEncryption) {
05883           try {
05884             e = parser.getObj(this.encrypt.createCipherTransform(num, gen));
05885           } catch (ex) {
05886             // almost all streams must be encrypted, but sometimes
05887             // they are not probably due to some broken generators
05888             // re-trying without encryption
05889             return this.fetch(ref, true);
05890           }
05891         } else {
05892           e = parser.getObj();
05893         }
05894         if (!isStream(e)) {
05895           this.cache[num] = e;
05896         }
05897         return e;
05898       }
05899 
05900       // compressed entry
05901       var tableOffset = e.offset;
05902       stream = this.fetch(new Ref(tableOffset, 0));
05903       if (!isStream(stream))
05904         error('bad ObjStm stream');
05905       var first = stream.dict.get('First');
05906       var n = stream.dict.get('N');
05907       if (!isInt(first) || !isInt(n)) {
05908         error('invalid first and n parameters for ObjStm stream');
05909       }
05910       parser = new Parser(new Lexer(stream), false, this);
05911       parser.allowStreams = true;
05912       var i, entries = [], nums = [];
05913       // read the object numbers to populate cache
05914       for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
05915         num = parser.getObj();
05916         if (!isInt(num)) {
05917           error('invalid object number in the ObjStm stream: ' + num);
05918         }
05919         nums.push(num);
05920         var offset = parser.getObj();
05921         if (!isInt(offset)) {
05922           error('invalid object offset in the ObjStm stream: ' + offset);
05923         }
05924       }
05925       // read stream objects for cache
05926       for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
05927         entries.push(parser.getObj());
05928         num = nums[i];
05929         var entry = this.entries[num];
05930         if (entry && entry.offset === tableOffset && entry.gen === i) {
05931           this.cache[num] = entries[i];
05932         }
05933       }
05934       e = entries[e.gen];
05935       if (e === undefined) {
05936         error('bad XRef entry for compressed object');
05937       }
05938       return e;
05939     },
05940     fetchIfRefAsync: function XRef_fetchIfRefAsync(obj) {
05941       if (!isRef(obj)) {
05942         var promise = new Promise();
05943         promise.resolve(obj);
05944         return promise;
05945       }
05946       return this.fetchAsync(obj);
05947     },
05948     fetchAsync: function XRef_fetchAsync(ref, suppressEncryption) {
05949       var promise = new Promise();
05950       var tryFetch = function (promise) {
05951         try {
05952           promise.resolve(this.fetch(ref, suppressEncryption));
05953         } catch (e) {
05954           if (e instanceof MissingDataException) {
05955             this.stream.manager.requestRange(e.begin, e.end, tryFetch);
05956             return;
05957           }
05958           promise.reject(e);
05959         }
05960       }.bind(this, promise);
05961       tryFetch();
05962       return promise;
05963     },
05964     getCatalogObj: function XRef_getCatalogObj() {
05965       return this.root;
05966     }
05967   };
05968 
05969   return XRef;
05970 })();
05971 
05977 var NameTree = (function NameTreeClosure() {
05978   function NameTree(root, xref) {
05979     this.root = root;
05980     this.xref = xref;
05981   }
05982 
05983   NameTree.prototype = {
05984     getAll: function NameTree_getAll() {
05985       var dict = {};
05986       if (!this.root) {
05987         return dict;
05988       }
05989       var xref = this.xref;
05990       // reading name tree
05991       var processed = new RefSet();
05992       processed.put(this.root);
05993       var queue = [this.root];
05994       while (queue.length > 0) {
05995         var i, n;
05996         var obj = xref.fetchIfRef(queue.shift());
05997         if (!isDict(obj)) {
05998           continue;
05999         }
06000         if (obj.has('Kids')) {
06001           var kids = obj.get('Kids');
06002           for (i = 0, n = kids.length; i < n; i++) {
06003             var kid = kids[i];
06004             if (processed.has(kid))
06005               error('invalid destinations');
06006             queue.push(kid);
06007             processed.put(kid);
06008           }
06009           continue;
06010         }
06011         var names = obj.get('Names');
06012         if (names) {
06013           for (i = 0, n = names.length; i < n; i += 2) {
06014             dict[names[i]] = xref.fetchIfRef(names[i + 1]);
06015           }
06016         }
06017       }
06018       return dict;
06019     }
06020   };
06021   return NameTree;
06022 })();
06023 
06030 var PDFObjects = (function PDFObjectsClosure() {
06031   function PDFObjects() {
06032     this.objs = {};
06033   }
06034 
06035   PDFObjects.prototype = {
06040     ensureObj: function PDFObjects_ensureObj(objId) {
06041       if (this.objs[objId])
06042         return this.objs[objId];
06043 
06044       var obj = {
06045         promise: new Promise(objId),
06046         data: null,
06047         resolved: false
06048       };
06049       this.objs[objId] = obj;
06050 
06051       return obj;
06052     },
06053 
06063     get: function PDFObjects_get(objId, callback) {
06064       // If there is a callback, then the get can be async and the object is
06065       // not required to be resolved right now
06066       if (callback) {
06067         this.ensureObj(objId).promise.then(callback);
06068         return null;
06069       }
06070 
06071       // If there isn't a callback, the user expects to get the resolved data
06072       // directly.
06073       var obj = this.objs[objId];
06074 
06075       // If there isn't an object yet or the object isn't resolved, then the
06076       // data isn't ready yet!
06077       if (!obj || !obj.resolved)
06078         error('Requesting object that isn\'t resolved yet ' + objId);
06079 
06080       return obj.data;
06081     },
06082 
06086     resolve: function PDFObjects_resolve(objId, data) {
06087       var obj = this.ensureObj(objId);
06088 
06089       obj.resolved = true;
06090       obj.data = data;
06091       obj.promise.resolve(data);
06092     },
06093 
06094     isResolved: function PDFObjects_isResolved(objId) {
06095       var objs = this.objs;
06096 
06097       if (!objs[objId]) {
06098         return false;
06099       } else {
06100         return objs[objId].resolved;
06101       }
06102     },
06103 
06104     hasData: function PDFObjects_hasData(objId) {
06105       return this.isResolved(objId);
06106     },
06107 
06111     getData: function PDFObjects_getData(objId) {
06112       var objs = this.objs;
06113       if (!objs[objId] || !objs[objId].resolved) {
06114         return null;
06115       } else {
06116         return objs[objId].data;
06117       }
06118     },
06119 
06120     clear: function PDFObjects_clear() {
06121       this.objs = {};
06122     }
06123   };
06124   return PDFObjects;
06125 })();

06138 var ObjectLoader = (function() {
06139 
06140   function mayHaveChildren(value) {
06141     return isRef(value) || isDict(value) || isArray(value) || isStream(value);
06142   }
06143 
06144   function addChildren(node, nodesToVisit) {
06145     if (isDict(node) || isStream(node)) {
06146       var map;
06147       if (isDict(node)) {
06148         map = node.map;
06149       } else {
06150         map = node.dict.map;
06151       }
06152       for (var key in map) {
06153         var value = map[key];
06154         if (mayHaveChildren(value)) {
06155           nodesToVisit.push(value);
06156         }
06157       }
06158     } else if (isArray(node)) {
06159       for (var i = 0, ii = node.length; i < ii; i++) {
06160         var value = node[i];
06161         if (mayHaveChildren(value)) {
06162           nodesToVisit.push(value);
06163         }
06164       }
06165     }
06166   }
06167 
06168   function ObjectLoader(obj, keys, xref) {
06169     this.obj = obj;
06170     this.keys = keys;
06171     this.xref = xref;
06172     this.refSet = null;
06173   }
06174 
06175   ObjectLoader.prototype = {
06176 
06177     load: function ObjectLoader_load() {
06178       var keys = this.keys;
06179       this.promise = new Promise();
06180       // Don't walk the graph if all the data is already loaded.
06181       if (!(this.xref.stream instanceof ChunkedStream) ||
06182           this.xref.stream.getMissingChunks().length === 0) {
06183         this.promise.resolve();
06184         return this.promise;
06185       }
06186 
06187       this.refSet = new RefSet();
06188       // Setup the initial nodes to visit.
06189       var nodesToVisit = [];
06190       for (var i = 0; i < keys.length; i++) {
06191         nodesToVisit.push(this.obj[keys[i]]);
06192       }
06193 
06194       this.walk(nodesToVisit);
06195       return this.promise;
06196     },
06197 
06198     walk: function ObjectLoader_walk(nodesToVisit) {
06199       var nodesToRevisit = [];
06200       var pendingRequests = [];
06201       // DFS walk of the object graph.
06202       while (nodesToVisit.length) {
06203         var currentNode = nodesToVisit.pop();
06204 
06205         // Only references or chunked streams can cause missing data exceptions.
06206         if (isRef(currentNode)) {
06207           // Skip nodes that have already been visited.
06208           if (this.refSet.has(currentNode)) {
06209             continue;
06210           }
06211           try {
06212             var ref = currentNode;
06213             this.refSet.put(ref);
06214             currentNode = this.xref.fetch(currentNode);
06215           } catch (e) {
06216             if (!(e instanceof MissingDataException)) {
06217               throw e;
06218             }
06219             nodesToRevisit.push(currentNode);
06220             pendingRequests.push({ begin: e.begin, end: e.end });
06221           }
06222         }
06223         if (currentNode && currentNode.getBaseStreams) {
06224           var baseStreams = currentNode.getBaseStreams();
06225           var foundMissingData = false;
06226           for (var i = 0; i < baseStreams.length; i++) {
06227             var stream = baseStreams[i];
06228             if (stream.getMissingChunks && stream.getMissingChunks().length) {
06229               foundMissingData = true;
06230               pendingRequests.push({
06231                 begin: stream.start,
06232                 end: stream.end
06233               });
06234             }
06235           }
06236           if (foundMissingData) {
06237             nodesToRevisit.push(currentNode);
06238           }
06239         }
06240 
06241         addChildren(currentNode, nodesToVisit);
06242       }
06243 
06244       if (pendingRequests.length) {
06245         this.xref.stream.manager.requestRanges(pendingRequests,
06246             function pendingRequestCallback() {
06247           nodesToVisit = nodesToRevisit;
06248           for (var i = 0; i < nodesToRevisit.length; i++) {
06249             var node = nodesToRevisit[i];
06250             // Remove any reference nodes from the currrent refset so they
06251             // aren't skipped when we revist them.
06252             if (isRef(node)) {
06253               this.refSet.remove(node);
06254             }
06255           }
06256           this.walk(nodesToVisit);
06257         }.bind(this));
06258         return;
06259       }
06260       // Everything is loaded.
06261       this.refSet = null;
06262       this.promise.resolve();
06263     }
06264 
06265   };
06266 
06267   return ObjectLoader;
06268 })();
06269

06273 var Annotation = (function AnnotationClosure() {
06274   // 12.5.5: Algorithm: Appearance streams
06275   function getTransformMatrix(rect, bbox, matrix) {
06276     var bounds = Util.getAxialAlignedBoundingBox(bbox, matrix);
06277     var minX = bounds[0];
06278     var minY = bounds[1];
06279     var maxX = bounds[2];
06280     var maxY = bounds[3];
06281 
06282     if (minX === maxX || minY === maxY) {
06283       // From real-life file, bbox was [0, 0, 0, 0]. In this case,
06284       // just apply the transform for rect
06285       return [1, 0, 0, 1, rect[0], rect[1]];
06286     }
06287 
06288     var xRatio = (rect[2] - rect[0]) / (maxX - minX);
06289     var yRatio = (rect[3] - rect[1]) / (maxY - minY);
06290     return [
06291       xRatio,
06292       0,
06293       0,
06294       yRatio,
06295       rect[0] - minX * xRatio,
06296       rect[1] - minY * yRatio
06297     ];
06298   }
06299 
06300   function getDefaultAppearance(dict) {
06301     var appearanceState = dict.get('AP');
06302     if (!isDict(appearanceState)) {
06303       return;
06304     }
06305 
06306     var appearance;
06307     var appearances = appearanceState.get('N');
06308     if (isDict(appearances)) {
06309       var as = dict.get('AS');
06310       if (as && appearances.has(as.name)) {
06311         appearance = appearances.get(as.name);
06312       }
06313     } else {
06314       appearance = appearances;
06315     }
06316     return appearance;
06317   }
06318 
06319   function Annotation(params) {
06320     if (params.data) {
06321       this.data = params.data;
06322       return;
06323     }
06324 
06325     var dict = params.dict;
06326     var data = this.data = {};
06327 
06328     data.subtype = dict.get('Subtype').name;
06329     var rect = dict.get('Rect');
06330     data.rect = Util.normalizeRect(rect);
06331     data.annotationFlags = dict.get('F');
06332 
06333     var color = dict.get('C');
06334     if (isArray(color) && color.length === 3) {
06335       // TODO(mack): currently only supporting rgb; need support different
06336       // colorspaces
06337       data.color = color;
06338     } else {
06339       data.color = [0, 0, 0];
06340     }
06341 
06342     // Some types of annotations have border style dict which has more
06343     // info than the border array
06344     if (dict.has('BS')) {
06345       var borderStyle = dict.get('BS');
06346       data.borderWidth = borderStyle.has('W') ? borderStyle.get('W') : 1;
06347     } else {
06348       var borderArray = dict.get('Border') || [0, 0, 1];
06349       data.borderWidth = borderArray[2];
06350     }
06351 
06352     this.appearance = getDefaultAppearance(dict);
06353   }

06392     loadResources: function(keys) {
06393       var promise = new Promise();
06394       this.appearance.dict.getAsync('Resources').then(function(resources) {
06395         if (!resources) {
06396           promise.resolve();
06397           return;
06398         }
06399         var objectLoader = new ObjectLoader(resources.map,
06400                                             keys,
06401                                             resources.xref);
06402         objectLoader.load().then(function() {
06403           promise.resolve(resources);
06404         });
06405       }.bind(this));
06406 
06407       return promise;
06408     },

06410     getOperatorList: function Annotation_getToOperatorList(evaluator) {
06411 
06412       var promise = new Promise();
06413 
06414       if (!this.appearance) {
06415         promise.resolve({
06416           queue: {
06417             fnArray: [],
06418             argsArray: []
06419           },
06420           dependency: {}
06421         });
06422         return promise;
06423       }
06424 
06425       var data = this.data;
06426 
06427       var appearanceDict = this.appearance.dict;
06428       var resourcesPromise = this.loadResources([
06429         'ExtGState',
06430         'ColorSpace',
06431         'Pattern',
06432         'Shading',
06433         'XObject',
06434         'Font'
06435         // ProcSet
06436         // Properties
06437       ]);
06438       var bbox = appearanceDict.get('BBox') || [0, 0, 1, 1];
06439       var matrix = appearanceDict.get('Matrix') || [1, 0, 0, 1, 0 ,0];
06440       var transform = getTransformMatrix(data.rect, bbox, matrix);
06441 
06442       var border = data.border;
06443 
06444       resourcesPromise.then(function(resources) {
06445         var listPromise = evaluator.getOperatorList(this.appearance, resources);
06446         listPromise.then(function(appearanceStreamData) {
06447           var fnArray = appearanceStreamData.queue.fnArray;
06448           var argsArray = appearanceStreamData.queue.argsArray;
06449 
06450           fnArray.unshift('beginAnnotation');
06451           argsArray.unshift([data.rect, transform, matrix]);
06452 
06453           fnArray.push('endAnnotation');
06454           argsArray.push([]);
06455 
06456           promise.resolve(appearanceStreamData);
06457         });
06458       }.bind(this));
06459 
06460       return promise;
06461     }
06462   };

06464   Annotation.getConstructor =
06465       function Annotation_getConstructor(subtype, fieldType) {
06466 
06467     if (!subtype) {
06468       return;
06469     }
06470 
06471     // TODO(mack): Implement FreeText annotations
06472     if (subtype === 'Link') {
06473       return LinkAnnotation;
06474     } else if (subtype === 'Text') {
06475       return TextAnnotation;
06476     } else if (subtype === 'Widget') {
06477       if (!fieldType) {
06478         return;
06479       }
06480 
06481       if (fieldType === 'Tx') {
06482         return TextWidgetAnnotation;
06483       } else {
06484         return WidgetAnnotation;
06485       }
06486     } else {
06487       return Annotation;
06488     }
06489   };

06495     var Constructor = Annotation.getConstructor(subtype, fieldType);
06496     if (Constructor) {
06497       return new Constructor({ data: data });
06498     }
06499   };

06501   Annotation.fromRef = function Annotation_fromRef(xref, ref) {
06502 
06503     var dict = xref.fetchIfRef(ref);
06504     if (!isDict(dict)) {
06505       return;
06506     }
06507 
06508     var subtype = dict.get('Subtype');
06509     subtype = isName(subtype) ? subtype.name : '';
06510     if (!subtype) {
06511       return;
06512     }
06513 
06514     var fieldType = Util.getInheritableProperty(dict, 'FT');
06515     fieldType = isName(fieldType) ? fieldType.name : '';
06516 
06517     var Constructor = Annotation.getConstructor(subtype, fieldType);
06518     if (!Constructor) {
06519       return;
06520     }
06521 
06522     var params = {
06523       dict: dict,
06524       ref: ref,
06525     };
06526 
06527     var annotation = new Constructor(params);
06528 
06529     if (annotation.isViewable()) {
06530       return annotation;
06531     } else {
06532       TODO('unimplemented annotation type: ' + subtype);
06533     }
06534   };
06535 
06536   Annotation.appendToOperatorList = function Annotation_appendToOperatorList(
06537       annotations, pageQueue, pdfManager, dependencies, partialEvaluator) {
06538 
06539     function reject(e) {
06540       annotationsReadyPromise.reject(e);
06541     }
06542 
06543     var annotationsReadyPromise = new Promise();
06544 
06545     var annotationPromises = [];
06546     for (var i = 0, n = annotations.length; i < n; ++i) {
06547       annotationPromises.push(annotations[i].getOperatorList(partialEvaluator));
06548     }
06549 
06550     Promise.all(annotationPromises).then(function(datas) {
06551       var fnArray = pageQueue.fnArray;
06552       var argsArray = pageQueue.argsArray;
06553       fnArray.push('beginAnnotations');
06554       argsArray.push([]);
06555       for (var i = 0, n = datas.length; i < n; ++i) {
06556         var annotationData = datas[i];
06557         var annotationQueue = annotationData.queue;
06558         Util.concatenateToArray(fnArray, annotationQueue.fnArray);
06559         Util.concatenateToArray(argsArray, annotationQueue.argsArray);
06560         Util.extendObj(dependencies, annotationData.dependencies);
06561       }
06562       fnArray.push('endAnnotations');
06563       argsArray.push([]);
06564 
06565       annotationsReadyPromise.resolve();
06566     }, reject);
06567 
06568     return annotationsReadyPromise;
06569   };
06570 
06571   return Annotation;
06572 })();

06576 var WidgetAnnotation = (function WidgetAnnotationClosure() {
06577 
06578   function WidgetAnnotation(params) {
06579     Annotation.call(this, params);
06580 
06581     if (params.data) {
06582       return;
06583     }
06584 
06585     var dict = params.dict;
06586     var data = this.data;
06587 
06588     data.fieldValue = stringToPDFString(
06589       Util.getInheritableProperty(dict, 'V') || '');
06590     data.alternativeText = stringToPDFString(dict.get('TU') || '');
06591     data.defaultAppearance = Util.getInheritableProperty(dict, 'DA') || '';
06592     var fieldType = Util.getInheritableProperty(dict, 'FT');
06593     data.fieldType = isName(fieldType) ? fieldType.name : '';
06594     data.fieldFlags = Util.getInheritableProperty(dict, 'Ff') || 0;
06595     this.fieldResources = Util.getInheritableProperty(dict, 'DR') || new Dict();
06596 
06597     // Building the full field name by collecting the field and
06598     // its ancestors 'T' data and joining them using '.'.
06599     var fieldName = [];
06600     var namedItem = dict;
06601     var ref = params.ref;
06602     while (namedItem) {
06603       var parent = namedItem.get('Parent');
06604       var parentRef = namedItem.getRaw('Parent');
06605       var name = namedItem.get('T');
06606       if (name) {
06607         fieldName.unshift(stringToPDFString(name));
06608       } else {
06609         // The field name is absent, that means more than one field
06610         // with the same name may exist. Replacing the empty name
06611         // with the '`' plus index in the parent's 'Kids' array.
06612         // This is not in the PDF spec but necessary to id the
06613         // the input controls.
06614         var kids = parent.get('Kids');
06615         var j, jj;
06616         for (j = 0, jj = kids.length; j < jj; j++) {
06617           var kidRef = kids[j];
06618           if (kidRef.num == ref.num && kidRef.gen == ref.gen)
06619             break;
06620         }
06621         fieldName.unshift('`' + j);
06622       }
06623       namedItem = parent;
06624       ref = parentRef;
06625     }
06626     data.fullName = fieldName.join('.');
06627   }

06638     }

06655   // TODO(mack): This dupes some of the logic in CanvasGraphics.setFont()
06656   function setTextStyles(element, item, fontObj) {
06657 
06658     var style = element.style;
06659     style.fontSize = item.fontSize + 'px';
06660     style.direction = item.fontDirection < 0 ? 'rtl': 'ltr';
06661 
06662     if (!fontObj) {
06663       return;
06664     }
06665 
06666     style.fontWeight = fontObj.black ?
06667                             (fontObj.bold ? 'bolder' : 'bold') :
06668                             (fontObj.bold ? 'bold' : 'normal');
06669     style.fontStyle = fontObj.italic ? 'italic' : 'normal';
06670 
06671     var fontName = fontObj.loadedName;
06672     var fontFamily = fontName ? '"' + fontName + '", ' : '';
06673     // Use a reasonable default font if the font doesn't specify a fallback
06674     var fallbackName = fontObj.fallbackName || 'Helvetica, sans-serif';
06675     style.fontFamily = fontFamily + fallbackName;
06676   }

06680   Util.inherit(TextWidgetAnnotation, WidgetAnnotation, {
06681     hasHtml: function TextWidgetAnnotation_hasHtml() {

06683     },
06684 
06685     getHtmlElement: function TextWidgetAnnotation_getHtmlElement(commonObjs) {
06686       assert(!isWorker, 'getHtmlElement() shall be called from main thread');
06687 
06688       var item = this.data;
06689 
06690       var element = this.getEmptyContainer('div');
06691       element.style.display = 'table';
06692

06694       content.textContent = item.fieldValue;
06695       var textAlignment = item.textAlignment;
06696       content.style.textAlign = ['left', 'center', 'right'][textAlignment];
06697       content.style.verticalAlign = 'middle';
06698       content.style.display = 'table-cell';
06699 
06700       var fontObj = item.fontRefName ?
06701                     commonObjs.getData(item.fontRefName) : null;
06702       var cssRules = setTextStyles(content, item, fontObj);
06703

06705

06708 
06709     getOperatorList: function TextWidgetAnnotation_getOperatorList(evaluator) {
06710 
06711 
06712       var promise = new Promise();
06713       var data = this.data;
06714 
06715       // Even if there is an appearance stream, ignore it. This is the
06716       // behaviour used by Adobe Reader.
06717 
06718       var defaultAppearance = data.defaultAppearance;
06719       if (!defaultAppearance) {
06720         promise.resolve({
06721           queue: {
06722             fnArray: [],
06723             argsArray: []
06724           },
06725           dependency: {}
06726         });
06727         return promise;
06728       }
06729 
06730       // Include any font resources found in the default appearance
06731 
06732       var stream = new Stream(stringToBytes(defaultAppearance));
06733       var listPromise = evaluator.getOperatorList(stream, this.fieldResources);
06734       listPromise.then(function(appearanceStreamData) {
06735         var appearanceFnArray = appearanceStreamData.queue.fnArray;
06736         var appearanceArgsArray = appearanceStreamData.queue.argsArray;
06737         var fnArray = [];
06738         var argsArray = [];
06739 
06740         // TODO(mack): Add support for stroke color
06741         data.rgb = [0, 0, 0];
06742         for (var i = 0, n = fnArray.length; i < n; ++i) {
06743           var fnName = appearanceFnArray[i];
06744           var args = appearanceArgsArray[i];
06745           if (fnName === 'dependency') {
06746             var dependency = args[i];
06747             if (dependency.indexOf('g_font_') === 0) {
06748               data.fontRefName = dependency;
06749             }
06750             fnArray.push(fnName);
06751             argsArray.push(args);
06752           } else if (fnName === 'setFont') {
06753             data.fontRefName = args[0];
06754             var size = args[1];
06755             if (size < 0) {
06756               data.fontDirection = -1;
06757               data.fontSize = -size;
06758             } else {
06759               data.fontDirection = 1;
06760               data.fontSize = size;
06761             }
06762           } else if (fnName === 'setFillRGBColor') {
06763             data.rgb = args;
06764           } else if (fnName === 'setFillGray') {
06765             var rgbValue = args[0] * 255;
06766             data.rgb = [rgbValue, rgbValue, rgbValue];
06767           }
06768         }
06769         promise.resolve({
06770           queue: {
06771             fnArray: fnArray,
06772             argsArray: argsArray
06773           },
06774           dependency: {}
06775         });
06776 
06777       });
06778 
06779       return promise;
06780     }
06781   });
06782 
06783   return TextWidgetAnnotation;
06784 })();

06808     getOperatorList: function TextAnnotation_getOperatorList(evaluator) {
06809       var promise = new Promise();
06810       promise.resolve({
06811         queue: {
06812           fnArray: [],
06813           argsArray: []

06815         dependency: {}
06816       });
06817       return promise;
06818     },
06819 
06820     hasHtml: function TextAnnotation_hasHtml() {
06821       return true;
06822     },
06823 
06824     getHtmlElement: function TextAnnotation_getHtmlElement(commonObjs) {
06825       assert(!isWorker, 'getHtmlElement() shall be called from main thread');
06826 
06827       var item = this.data;
06828       var rect = item.rect;
06829 
06830       // sanity check because of OOo-generated PDFs
06831       if ((rect[3] - rect[1]) < ANNOT_MIN_SIZE) {
06832         rect[3] = rect[1] + ANNOT_MIN_SIZE;
06833       }
06834       if ((rect[2] - rect[0]) < ANNOT_MIN_SIZE) {
06835         rect[2] = rect[0] + (rect[3] - rect[1]); // make it square
06836       }
06837 
06838       var container = this.getEmptyContainer('section', rect);
06839       container.className = 'annotText';
06840 
06841       var image = document.createElement('img');
06842       image.style.width = container.style.width;
06843       image.style.height = container.style.height;
06844       var iconName = item.name;
06845       image.src = PDFJS.imageResourcesPath + 'annotation-' +
06846         iconName.toLowerCase() + '.svg';
06847       image.alt = '[{{type}} Annotation]';
06848       image.dataset.l10nId = 'text_annotation_type';
06849       image.dataset.l10nArgs = JSON.stringify({type: iconName});
06850       var content = document.createElement('div');
06851       content.setAttribute('hidden', true);
06852       var title = document.createElement('h1');
06853       var text = document.createElement('p');
06854       content.style.left = Math.floor(rect[2] - rect[0]) + 'px';
06855       content.style.top = '0px';
06856       title.textContent = item.title;
06857 
06858       if (!item.content && !item.title) {
06859         content.setAttribute('hidden', true);
06860       } else {
06861         var e = document.createElement('span');
06862         var lines = item.content.split(/(?:\r\n?|\n)/);
06863         for (var i = 0, ii = lines.length; i < ii; ++i) {
06864           var line = lines[i];
06865           e.appendChild(document.createTextNode(line));
06866           if (i < (ii - 1))
06867             e.appendChild(document.createElement('br'));
06868         }
06869         text.appendChild(e);
06870         image.addEventListener('mouseover', function annotationImageOver() {
06871           container.style.zIndex += 1;
06872           content.removeAttribute('hidden');
06873         }, false);
06874 
06875         image.addEventListener('mouseout', function annotationImageOut() {
06876           container.style.zIndex -= 1;
06877           content.setAttribute('hidden', true);
06878         }, false);
06879       }
06880 
06881       content.appendChild(title);
06882       content.appendChild(text);
06883       container.appendChild(image);
06884       container.appendChild(content);
06885 
06886       return container;
06887     }
06888   });
06889 
06890   return TextAnnotation;
06891 })();

06893 var LinkAnnotation = (function LinkAnnotationClosure() {
06894   function LinkAnnotation(params) {
06895     Annotation.call(this, params);
06896 
06897     if (params.data) {
06898       return;
06899     }
06900 
06901     var dict = params.dict;
06902     var data = this.data;
06903 
06904     var action = dict.get('A');
06905     if (action) {
06906       var linkType = action.get('S').name;
06907       if (linkType === 'URI') {
06908         var url = action.get('URI');
06909         // TODO: pdf spec mentions urls can be relative to a Base
06910         // entry in the dictionary.
06911         if (!isValidUrl(url, false)) {
06912           url = '';
06913         }
06914         data.url = url;
06915       } else if (linkType === 'GoTo') {
06916         data.dest = action.get('D');
06917       } else if (linkType === 'GoToR') {
06918         var urlDict = action.get('F');
06919         if (isDict(urlDict)) {
06920           // We assume that the 'url' is a Filspec dictionary
06921           // and fetch the url without checking any further
06922           url = urlDict.get('F') || '';
06923         }
06924 
06925         // TODO: pdf reference says that GoToR
06926         // can also have 'NewWindow' attribute
06927         if (!isValidUrl(url, false)) {
06928           url = '';
06929         }
06930         data.url = url;
06931         data.dest = action.get('D');
06932       } else {
06933         TODO('unrecognized link type: ' + linkType);
06934       }
06935     } else if (dict.has('Dest')) {
06936       // simple destination link
06937       var dest = dict.get('Dest');
06938       data.dest = isName(dest) ? dest.name : dest;
06939     }
06940   }
06941 
06942   Util.inherit(LinkAnnotation, Annotation, {
06943     hasOperatorList: function LinkAnnotation_hasOperatorList() {
06944       return false;
06945     },

06949     },

06954       var borderWidth = this.data.borderWidth;
06955 
06956       element.style.borderWidth = borderWidth + 'px';
06957       var color = this.data.color;
06958       var rgb = [];
06959       for (var i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
06960         rgb[i] = Math.round(color[i] * 255);
06961       }
06962       element.style.borderColor = Util.makeCssRgb(rgb);
06963       element.style.borderStyle = 'solid';
06964 
06965       var width = rect[2] - rect[0] - 2 * borderWidth;
06966       var height = rect[3] - rect[1] - 2 * borderWidth;
06967       element.style.width = width + 'px';
06968       element.style.height = height + 'px';
06969 
06970       element.href = this.data.url || '';
06971       return element;
06972     }
06973   });
