06979 var PDFFunction = (function PDFFunctionClosure() {
06980   var CONSTRUCT_SAMPLED = 0;
06981   var CONSTRUCT_INTERPOLATED = 2;
06982   var CONSTRUCT_STICHED = 3;
06983   var CONSTRUCT_POSTSCRIPT = 4;
06984 
06985   return {
06986     getSampleArray: function PDFFunction_getSampleArray(size, outputSize, bps,
06987                                                        str) {
06988       var length = 1;
06989       for (var i = 0, ii = size.length; i < ii; i++)
06990         length *= size[i];
06991       length *= outputSize;
06992 
06993       var array = [];
06994       var codeSize = 0;
06995       var codeBuf = 0;
06996       // 32 is a valid bps so shifting won't work
06997       var sampleMul = 1.0 / (Math.pow(2.0, bps) - 1);
06998 
06999       var strBytes = str.getBytes((length * bps + 7) / 8);
07000       var strIdx = 0;
07001       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
07002         while (codeSize < bps) {
07003           codeBuf <<= 8;
07004           codeBuf |= strBytes[strIdx++];
07005           codeSize += 8;
07006         }
07007         codeSize -= bps;
07008         array.push((codeBuf >> codeSize) * sampleMul);
07009         codeBuf &= (1 << codeSize) - 1;
07010       }
07011       return array;
07012     },
07013 
07014     getIR: function PDFFunction_getIR(xref, fn) {
07015       var dict = fn.dict;
07016       if (!dict)
07017         dict = fn;
07018 
07019       var types = [this.constructSampled,
07020                    null,
07021                    this.constructInterpolated,
07022                    this.constructStiched,
07023                    this.constructPostScript];
07024 
07025       var typeNum = dict.get('FunctionType');
07026       var typeFn = types[typeNum];
07027       if (!typeFn)
07028         error('Unknown type of function');
07029 
07030       return typeFn.call(this, fn, dict, xref);
07031     },
07032 
07033     fromIR: function PDFFunction_fromIR(IR) {
07034       var type = IR[0];
07035       switch (type) {
07036         case CONSTRUCT_SAMPLED:
07037           return this.constructSampledFromIR(IR);
07038         case CONSTRUCT_INTERPOLATED:
07039           return this.constructInterpolatedFromIR(IR);
07040         case CONSTRUCT_STICHED:
07041           return this.constructStichedFromIR(IR);
07042         //case CONSTRUCT_POSTSCRIPT:
07043         default:
07044           return this.constructPostScriptFromIR(IR);
07045       }
07046     },
07047 
07048     parse: function PDFFunction_parse(xref, fn) {
07049       var IR = this.getIR(xref, fn);
07050       return this.fromIR(IR);
07051     },
07052 
07053     constructSampled: function PDFFunction_constructSampled(str, dict) {
07054       function toMultiArray(arr) {
07055         var inputLength = arr.length;
07056         var outputLength = arr.length / 2;
07057         var out = [];
07058         var index = 0;
07059         for (var i = 0; i < inputLength; i += 2) {
07060           out[index] = [arr[i], arr[i + 1]];
07061           ++index;
07062         }
07063         return out;
07064       }
07065       var domain = dict.get('Domain');
07066       var range = dict.get('Range');
07067 
07068       if (!domain || !range)
07069         error('No domain or range');
07070 
07071       var inputSize = domain.length / 2;
07072       var outputSize = range.length / 2;
07073 
07074       domain = toMultiArray(domain);
07075       range = toMultiArray(range);
07076 
07077       var size = dict.get('Size');
07078       var bps = dict.get('BitsPerSample');
07079       var order = dict.get('Order') || 1;
07080       if (order !== 1) {
07081         // No description how cubic spline interpolation works in PDF32000:2008
07082         // As in poppler, ignoring order, linear interpolation may work as good
07083         TODO('No support for cubic spline interpolation: ' + order);
07084       }
07085 
07086       var encode = dict.get('Encode');
07087       if (!encode) {
07088         encode = [];
07089         for (var i = 0; i < inputSize; ++i) {
07090           encode.push(0);
07091           encode.push(size[i] - 1);
07092         }
07093       }
07094       encode = toMultiArray(encode);
07095 
07096       var decode = dict.get('Decode');
07097       if (!decode)
07098         decode = range;
07099       else
07100         decode = toMultiArray(decode);
07101 
07102       var samples = this.getSampleArray(size, outputSize, bps, str);
07103 
07104       return [
07105         CONSTRUCT_SAMPLED, inputSize, domain, encode, decode, samples, size,
07106         outputSize, Math.pow(2, bps) - 1, range
07107       ];
07108     },
07109 
07110     constructSampledFromIR: function PDFFunction_constructSampledFromIR(IR) {
07111       // See chapter 3, page 109 of the PDF reference
07112       function interpolate(x, xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax) {
07113         return ymin + ((x - xmin) * ((ymax - ymin) / (xmax - xmin)));
07114       }
07115 
07116       return function constructSampledFromIRResult(args) {
07117         // See chapter 3, page 110 of the PDF reference.
07118         var m = IR[1];
07119         var domain = IR[2];
07120         var encode = IR[3];
07121         var decode = IR[4];
07122         var samples = IR[5];
07123         var size = IR[6];
07124         var n = IR[7];
07125         var mask = IR[8];
07126         var range = IR[9];
07127 
07128         if (m != args.length)
07129           error('Incorrect number of arguments: ' + m + ' != ' +
07130                 args.length);
07131 
07132         var x = args;
07133 
07134         // Building the cube vertices: its part and sample index
07135         // http://rjwagner49.com/Mathematics/Interpolation.pdf
07136         var cubeVertices = 1 << m;
07137         var cubeN = new Float64Array(cubeVertices);
07138         var cubeVertex = new Uint32Array(cubeVertices);
07139         for (var j = 0; j < cubeVertices; j++)
07140           cubeN[j] = 1;
07141 
07142         var k = n, pos = 1;
07143         // Map x_i to y_j for 0 <= i < m using the sampled function.
07144         for (var i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
07145           // x_i' = min(max(x_i, Domain_2i), Domain_2i+1)
07146           var domain_2i = domain[i][0];
07147           var domain_2i_1 = domain[i][1];
07148           var xi = Math.min(Math.max(x[i], domain_2i), domain_2i_1);
07149 
07150           // e_i = Interpolate(x_i', Domain_2i, Domain_2i+1,
07151           //                   Encode_2i, Encode_2i+1)
07152           var e = interpolate(xi, domain_2i, domain_2i_1,
07153                               encode[i][0], encode[i][1]);
07154 
07155           // e_i' = min(max(e_i, 0), Size_i - 1)
07156           var size_i = size[i];
07157           e = Math.min(Math.max(e, 0), size_i - 1);
07158 
07159           // Adjusting the cube: N and vertex sample index
07160           var e0 = e < size_i - 1 ? Math.floor(e) : e - 1; // e1 = e0 + 1;
07161           var n0 = e0 + 1 - e; // (e1 - e) / (e1 - e0);
07162           var n1 = e - e0; // (e - e0) / (e1 - e0);
07163           var offset0 = e0 * k;
07164           var offset1 = offset0 + k; // e1 * k
07165           for (var j = 0; j < cubeVertices; j++) {
07166             if (j & pos) {
07167               cubeN[j] *= n1;
07168               cubeVertex[j] += offset1;
07169             } else {
07170               cubeN[j] *= n0;
07171               cubeVertex[j] += offset0;
07172             }
07173           }
07174 
07175           k *= size_i;
07176           pos <<= 1;
07177         }
07178 
07179         var y = new Float64Array(n);
07180         for (var j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
07181           // Sum all cube vertices' samples portions
07182           var rj = 0;
07183           for (var i = 0; i < cubeVertices; i++)
07184             rj += samples[cubeVertex[i] + j] * cubeN[i];
07185 
07186           // r_j' = Interpolate(r_j, 0, 2^BitsPerSample - 1,
07187           //                    Decode_2j, Decode_2j+1)
07188           rj = interpolate(rj, 0, 1, decode[j][0], decode[j][1]);
07189 
07190           // y_j = min(max(r_j, range_2j), range_2j+1)
07191           y[j] = Math.min(Math.max(rj, range[j][0]), range[j][1]);
07192         }
07193 
07194         return y;
07195       };
07196     },
07197 
07198     constructInterpolated: function PDFFunction_constructInterpolated(str,
07199                                                                       dict) {
07200       var c0 = dict.get('C0') || [0];
07201       var c1 = dict.get('C1') || [1];
07202       var n = dict.get('N');
07203 
07204       if (!isArray(c0) || !isArray(c1))
07205         error('Illegal dictionary for interpolated function');
07206 
07207       var length = c0.length;
07208       var diff = [];
07209       for (var i = 0; i < length; ++i)
07210         diff.push(c1[i] - c0[i]);
07211 
07212       return [CONSTRUCT_INTERPOLATED, c0, diff, n];
07213     },
07214 
07215     constructInterpolatedFromIR:
07216       function PDFFunction_constructInterpolatedFromIR(IR) {
07217       var c0 = IR[1];
07218       var diff = IR[2];
07219       var n = IR[3];
07220 
07221       var length = diff.length;
07222 
07223       return function constructInterpolatedFromIRResult(args) {
07224         var x = n == 1 ? args[0] : Math.pow(args[0], n);
07225 
07226         var out = [];
07227         for (var j = 0; j < length; ++j)
07228           out.push(c0[j] + (x * diff[j]));
07229 
07230         return out;
07231 
07232       };
07233     },
07234 
07235     constructStiched: function PDFFunction_constructStiched(fn, dict, xref) {
07236       var domain = dict.get('Domain');
07237 
07238       if (!domain)
07239         error('No domain');
07240 
07241       var inputSize = domain.length / 2;
07242       if (inputSize != 1)
07243         error('Bad domain for stiched function');
07244 
07245       var fnRefs = dict.get('Functions');
07246       var fns = [];
07247       for (var i = 0, ii = fnRefs.length; i < ii; ++i)
07248         fns.push(PDFFunction.getIR(xref, xref.fetchIfRef(fnRefs[i])));
07249 
07250       var bounds = dict.get('Bounds');
07251       var encode = dict.get('Encode');
07252 
07253       return [CONSTRUCT_STICHED, domain, bounds, encode, fns];
07254     },
07255 
07256     constructStichedFromIR: function PDFFunction_constructStichedFromIR(IR) {
07257       var domain = IR[1];
07258       var bounds = IR[2];
07259       var encode = IR[3];
07260       var fnsIR = IR[4];
07261       var fns = [];
07262 
07263       for (var i = 0, ii = fnsIR.length; i < ii; i++) {
07264         fns.push(PDFFunction.fromIR(fnsIR[i]));
07265       }
07266 
07267       return function constructStichedFromIRResult(args) {
07268         var clip = function constructStichedFromIRClip(v, min, max) {
07269           if (v > max)
07270             v = max;
07271           else if (v < min)
07272             v = min;
07273           return v;
07274         };
07275 
07276         // clip to domain
07277         var v = clip(args[0], domain[0], domain[1]);
07278         // calulate which bound the value is in
07279         for (var i = 0, ii = bounds.length; i < ii; ++i) {
07280           if (v < bounds[i])
07281             break;
07282         }
07283 
07284         // encode value into domain of function
07285         var dmin = domain[0];
07286         if (i > 0)
07287           dmin = bounds[i - 1];
07288         var dmax = domain[1];
07289         if (i < bounds.length)
07290           dmax = bounds[i];
07291 
07292         var rmin = encode[2 * i];
07293         var rmax = encode[2 * i + 1];
07294 
07295         var v2 = rmin + (v - dmin) * (rmax - rmin) / (dmax - dmin);
07296 
07297         // call the appropropriate function
07298         return fns[i]([v2]);
07299       };
07300     },
07301 
07302     constructPostScript: function PDFFunction_constructPostScript(fn, dict,
07303                                                                   xref) {
07304       var domain = dict.get('Domain');
07305       var range = dict.get('Range');
07306 
07307       if (!domain)
07308         error('No domain.');
07309 
07310       if (!range)
07311         error('No range.');
07312 
07313       var lexer = new PostScriptLexer(fn);
07314       var parser = new PostScriptParser(lexer);
07315       var code = parser.parse();
07316 
07317       return [CONSTRUCT_POSTSCRIPT, domain, range, code];
07318     },
07319 
07320     constructPostScriptFromIR: function PDFFunction_constructPostScriptFromIR(
07321                                           IR) {
07322       var domain = IR[1];
07323       var range = IR[2];
07324       var code = IR[3];
07325       var numOutputs = range.length / 2;
07326       var evaluator = new PostScriptEvaluator(code);
07327       // Cache the values for a big speed up, the cache size is limited though
07328       // since the number of possible values can be huge from a PS function.
07329       var cache = new FunctionCache();
07330       return function constructPostScriptFromIRResult(args) {
07331         var initialStack = [];
07332         for (var i = 0, ii = (domain.length / 2); i < ii; ++i) {
07333           initialStack.push(args[i]);
07334         }
07335 
07336         var key = initialStack.join('_');
07337         if (cache.has(key))
07338           return cache.get(key);
07339 
07340         var stack = evaluator.execute(initialStack);
07341         var transformed = [];
07342         for (i = numOutputs - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
07343           var out = stack.pop();
07344           var rangeIndex = 2 * i;
07345           if (out < range[rangeIndex])
07346             out = range[rangeIndex];
07347           else if (out > range[rangeIndex + 1])
07348             out = range[rangeIndex + 1];
07349           transformed[i] = out;
07350         }
07351         cache.set(key, transformed);
07352         return transformed;
07353       };
07354     }
07355   };
07356 })();
07357 
07358 var FunctionCache = (function FunctionCacheClosure() {
07359   // Of 10 PDF's with type4 functions the maxium number of distinct values seen
07360   // was 256. This still may need some tweaking in the future though.
07361   var MAX_CACHE_SIZE = 1024;
07362   function FunctionCache() {
07363     this.cache = {};
07364     this.total = 0;
07365   }
07366   FunctionCache.prototype = {
07367     has: function FunctionCache_has(key) {
07368       return key in this.cache;
07369     },
07370     get: function FunctionCache_get(key) {
07371       return this.cache[key];
07372     },
07373     set: function FunctionCache_set(key, value) {
07374       if (this.total < MAX_CACHE_SIZE) {
07375         this.cache[key] = value;
07376         this.total++;
07377       }
07378     }
07379   };
07380   return FunctionCache;
07381 })();
07382 
07383 var PostScriptStack = (function PostScriptStackClosure() {
07384   var MAX_STACK_SIZE = 100;
07385   function PostScriptStack(initialStack) {
07386     this.stack = initialStack || [];
07387   }
07388 
07389   PostScriptStack.prototype = {
07390     push: function PostScriptStack_push(value) {
07391       if (this.stack.length >= MAX_STACK_SIZE)
07392         error('PostScript function stack overflow.');
07393       this.stack.push(value);
07394     },
07395     pop: function PostScriptStack_pop() {
07396       if (this.stack.length <= 0)
07397         error('PostScript function stack underflow.');
07398       return this.stack.pop();
07399     },
07400     copy: function PostScriptStack_copy(n) {
07401       if (this.stack.length + n >= MAX_STACK_SIZE)
07402         error('PostScript function stack overflow.');
07403       var stack = this.stack;
07404       for (var i = stack.length - n, j = n - 1; j >= 0; j--, i++)
07405         stack.push(stack[i]);
07406     },
07407     index: function PostScriptStack_index(n) {
07408       this.push(this.stack[this.stack.length - n - 1]);
07409     },
07410     // rotate the last n stack elements p times
07411     roll: function PostScriptStack_roll(n, p) {
07412       var stack = this.stack;
07413       var l = stack.length - n;
07414       var r = stack.length - 1, c = l + (p - Math.floor(p / n) * n), i, j, t;
07415       for (i = l, j = r; i < j; i++, j--) {
07416         t = stack[i]; stack[i] = stack[j]; stack[j] = t;
07417       }
07418       for (i = l, j = c - 1; i < j; i++, j--) {
07419         t = stack[i]; stack[i] = stack[j]; stack[j] = t;
07420       }
07421       for (i = c, j = r; i < j; i++, j--) {
07422         t = stack[i]; stack[i] = stack[j]; stack[j] = t;
07423       }
07424     }
07425   };
07426   return PostScriptStack;
07427 })();
07428 var PostScriptEvaluator = (function PostScriptEvaluatorClosure() {
07429   function PostScriptEvaluator(operators, operands) {
07430     this.operators = operators;
07431     this.operands = operands;
07432   }
07433   PostScriptEvaluator.prototype = {
07434     execute: function PostScriptEvaluator_execute(initialStack) {
07435       var stack = new PostScriptStack(initialStack);
07436       var counter = 0;
07437       var operators = this.operators;
07438       var length = operators.length;
07439       var operator, a, b;
07440       while (counter < length) {
07441         operator = operators[counter++];
07442         if (typeof operator == 'number') {
07443           // Operator is really an operand and should be pushed to the stack.
07444           stack.push(operator);
07445           continue;
07446         }
07447         switch (operator) {
07448           // non standard ps operators
07449           case 'jz': // jump if false
07450             b = stack.pop();
07451             a = stack.pop();
07452             if (!a)
07453               counter = b;
07454             break;
07455           case 'j': // jump
07456             a = stack.pop();
07457             counter = a;
07458             break;
07459 
07460           // all ps operators in alphabetical order (excluding if/ifelse)
07461           case 'abs':
07462             a = stack.pop();
07463             stack.push(Math.abs(a));
07464             break;
07465           case 'add':
07466             b = stack.pop();
07467             a = stack.pop();
07468             stack.push(a + b);
07469             break;
07470           case 'and':
07471             b = stack.pop();
07472             a = stack.pop();
07473             if (isBool(a) && isBool(b))
07474               stack.push(a && b);
07475             else
07476               stack.push(a & b);
07477             break;
07478           case 'atan':
07479             a = stack.pop();
07480             stack.push(Math.atan(a));
07481             break;
07482           case 'bitshift':
07483             b = stack.pop();
07484             a = stack.pop();
07485             if (a > 0)
07486               stack.push(a << b);
07487             else
07488               stack.push(a >> b);
07489             break;
07490           case 'ceiling':
07491             a = stack.pop();
07492             stack.push(Math.ceil(a));
07493             break;
07494           case 'copy':
07495             a = stack.pop();
07496             stack.copy(a);
07497             break;
07498           case 'cos':
07499             a = stack.pop();
07500             stack.push(Math.cos(a));
07501             break;
07502           case 'cvi':
07503             a = stack.pop() | 0;
07504             stack.push(a);
07505             break;
07506           case 'cvr':
07507             // noop
07508             break;
07509           case 'div':
07510             b = stack.pop();
07511             a = stack.pop();
07512             stack.push(a / b);
07513             break;
07514           case 'dup':
07515             stack.copy(1);
07516             break;
07517           case 'eq':
07518             b = stack.pop();
07519             a = stack.pop();
07520             stack.push(a == b);
07521             break;
07522           case 'exch':
07523             stack.roll(2, 1);
07524             break;
07525           case 'exp':
07526             b = stack.pop();
07527             a = stack.pop();
07528             stack.push(Math.pow(a, b));
07529             break;
07530           case 'false':
07531             stack.push(false);
07532             break;
07533           case 'floor':
07534             a = stack.pop();
07535             stack.push(Math.floor(a));
07536             break;
07537           case 'ge':
07538             b = stack.pop();
07539             a = stack.pop();
07540             stack.push(a >= b);
07541             break;
07542           case 'gt':
07543             b = stack.pop();
07544             a = stack.pop();
07545             stack.push(a > b);
07546             break;
07547           case 'idiv':
07548             b = stack.pop();
07549             a = stack.pop();
07550             stack.push((a / b) | 0);
07551             break;
07552           case 'index':
07553             a = stack.pop();
07554             stack.index(a);
07555             break;
07556           case 'le':
07557             b = stack.pop();
07558             a = stack.pop();
07559             stack.push(a <= b);
07560             break;
07561           case 'ln':
07562             a = stack.pop();
07563             stack.push(Math.log(a));
07564             break;
07565           case 'log':
07566             a = stack.pop();
07567             stack.push(Math.log(a) / Math.LN10);
07568             break;
07569           case 'lt':
07570             b = stack.pop();
07571             a = stack.pop();
07572             stack.push(a < b);
07573             break;
07574           case 'mod':
07575             b = stack.pop();
07576             a = stack.pop();
07577             stack.push(a % b);
07578             break;
07579           case 'mul':
07580             b = stack.pop();
07581             a = stack.pop();
07582             stack.push(a * b);
07583             break;
07584           case 'ne':
07585             b = stack.pop();
07586             a = stack.pop();
07587             stack.push(a != b);
07588             break;
07589           case 'neg':
07590             a = stack.pop();
07591             stack.push(-b);
07592             break;
07593           case 'not':
07594             a = stack.pop();
07595             if (isBool(a) && isBool(b))
07596               stack.push(a && b);
07597             else
07598               stack.push(a & b);
07599             break;
07600           case 'or':
07601             b = stack.pop();
07602             a = stack.pop();
07603             if (isBool(a) && isBool(b))
07604               stack.push(a || b);
07605             else
07606               stack.push(a | b);
07607             break;
07608           case 'pop':
07609             stack.pop();
07610             break;
07611           case 'roll':
07612             b = stack.pop();
07613             a = stack.pop();
07614             stack.roll(a, b);
07615             break;
07616           case 'round':
07617             a = stack.pop();
07618             stack.push(Math.round(a));
07619             break;
07620           case 'sin':
07621             a = stack.pop();
07622             stack.push(Math.sin(a));
07623             break;
07624           case 'sqrt':
07625             a = stack.pop();
07626             stack.push(Math.sqrt(a));
07627             break;
07628           case 'sub':
07629             b = stack.pop();
07630             a = stack.pop();
07631             stack.push(a - b);
07632             break;
07633           case 'true':
07634             stack.push(true);
07635             break;
07636           case 'truncate':
07637             a = stack.pop();
07638             a = a < 0 ? Math.ceil(a) : Math.floor(a);
07639             stack.push(a);
07640             break;
07641           case 'xor':
07642             b = stack.pop();
07643             a = stack.pop();
07644             if (isBool(a) && isBool(b))
07645               stack.push(a != b);
07646             else
07647               stack.push(a ^ b);
07648             break;
07649           default:
07650             error('Unknown operator ' + operator);
07651             break;
07652         }
07653       }
07654       return stack.stack;
07655     }
07656   };
07657   return PostScriptEvaluator;
07658 })();
07659 
07660 var PostScriptParser = (function PostScriptParserClosure() {
07661   function PostScriptParser(lexer) {
07662     this.lexer = lexer;
07663     this.operators = [];
07664     this.token = null;
07665     this.prev = null;
07666   }
07667   PostScriptParser.prototype = {
07668     nextToken: function PostScriptParser_nextToken() {
07669       this.prev = this.token;
07670       this.token = this.lexer.getToken();
07671     },
07672     accept: function PostScriptParser_accept(type) {
07673       if (this.token.type == type) {
07674         this.nextToken();
07675         return true;
07676       }
07677       return false;
07678     },
07679     expect: function PostScriptParser_expect(type) {
07680       if (this.accept(type))
07681         return true;
07682       error('Unexpected symbol: found ' + this.token.type + ' expected ' +
07683             type + '.');
07684     },
07685     parse: function PostScriptParser_parse() {
07686       this.nextToken();
07687       this.expect(PostScriptTokenTypes.LBRACE);
07688       this.parseBlock();
07689       this.expect(PostScriptTokenTypes.RBRACE);
07690       return this.operators;
07691     },
07692     parseBlock: function PostScriptParser_parseBlock() {
07693       while (true) {
07694         if (this.accept(PostScriptTokenTypes.NUMBER)) {
07695           this.operators.push(this.prev.value);
07696         } else if (this.accept(PostScriptTokenTypes.OPERATOR)) {
07697           this.operators.push(this.prev.value);
07698         } else if (this.accept(PostScriptTokenTypes.LBRACE)) {
07699           this.parseCondition();
07700         } else {
07701           return;
07702         }
07703       }
07704     },
07705     parseCondition: function PostScriptParser_parseCondition() {
07706       // Add two place holders that will be updated later
07707       var conditionLocation = this.operators.length;
07708       this.operators.push(null, null);
07709 
07710       this.parseBlock();
07711       this.expect(PostScriptTokenTypes.RBRACE);
07712       if (this.accept(PostScriptTokenTypes.IF)) {
07713         // The true block is right after the 'if' so it just falls through on
07714         // true else it jumps and skips the true block.
07715         this.operators[conditionLocation] = this.operators.length;
07716         this.operators[conditionLocation + 1] = 'jz';
07717       } else if (this.accept(PostScriptTokenTypes.LBRACE)) {
07718         var jumpLocation = this.operators.length;
07719         this.operators.push(null, null);
07720         var endOfTrue = this.operators.length;
07721         this.parseBlock();
07722         this.expect(PostScriptTokenTypes.RBRACE);
07723         this.expect(PostScriptTokenTypes.IFELSE);
07724         // The jump is added at the end of the true block to skip the false
07725         // block.
07726         this.operators[jumpLocation] = this.operators.length;
07727         this.operators[jumpLocation + 1] = 'j';
07728 
07729         this.operators[conditionLocation] = endOfTrue;
07730         this.operators[conditionLocation + 1] = 'jz';
07731       } else {
07732         error('PS Function: error parsing conditional.');
07733       }
07734     }
07735   };
07736   return PostScriptParser;
07737 })();
07738 
07739 var PostScriptTokenTypes = {
07740   LBRACE: 0,
07741   RBRACE: 1,
07742   NUMBER: 2,
07743   OPERATOR: 3,
07744   IF: 4,
07745   IFELSE: 5
07746 };
07747 
07748 var PostScriptToken = (function PostScriptTokenClosure() {
07749   function PostScriptToken(type, value) {
07750     this.type = type;
07751     this.value = value;
07752   }
07753 
07754   var opCache = {};
07755 
07756   PostScriptToken.getOperator = function PostScriptToken_getOperator(op) {
07757     var opValue = opCache[op];
07758     if (opValue)
07759       return opValue;
07760 
07761     return opCache[op] = new PostScriptToken(PostScriptTokenTypes.OPERATOR, op);
07762   };
07763 
07764   PostScriptToken.LBRACE = new PostScriptToken(PostScriptTokenTypes.LBRACE,
07765                                                 '{');
07766   PostScriptToken.RBRACE = new PostScriptToken(PostScriptTokenTypes.RBRACE,
07767                                                 '}');
07768   PostScriptToken.IF = new PostScriptToken(PostScriptTokenTypes.IF, 'IF');
07769   PostScriptToken.IFELSE = new PostScriptToken(PostScriptTokenTypes.IFELSE,
07770                                                 'IFELSE');
07771   return PostScriptToken;
07772 })();
07773 
07774 var PostScriptLexer = (function PostScriptLexerClosure() {
07775   function PostScriptLexer(stream) {
07776     this.stream = stream;
07777     this.nextChar();
07778   }
07779   PostScriptLexer.prototype = {
07780     nextChar: function PostScriptLexer_nextChar() {
07781       return (this.currentChar = this.stream.getByte());
07782     },
07783     getToken: function PostScriptLexer_getToken() {
07784       var s = '';
07785       var comment = false;
07786       var ch = this.currentChar;
07787 
07788       // skip comments
07789       while (true) {
07790         if (ch < 0) {
07791           return EOF;
07792         }
07793 
07794         if (comment) {
07795           if (ch === 0x0A || ch === 0x0D) {
07796             comment = false;
07797           }
07798         } else if (ch == 0x25) { // '%'
07799           comment = true;
07800         } else if (!Lexer.isSpace(ch)) {
07801           break;
07802         }
07803         ch = this.nextChar();
07804       }
07805       switch (ch | 0) {
07806         case 0x30: case 0x31: case 0x32: case 0x33: case 0x34: // '0'-'4'
07807         case 0x35: case 0x36: case 0x37: case 0x38: case 0x39: // '5'-'9'
07808         case 0x2B: case 0x2D: case 0x2E: // '+', '-', '.'
07809           return new PostScriptToken(PostScriptTokenTypes.NUMBER,
07810                                       this.getNumber());
07811         case 0x7B: // '{'
07812           this.nextChar();
07813           return PostScriptToken.LBRACE;
07814         case 0x7D: // '}'
07815           this.nextChar();
07816           return PostScriptToken.RBRACE;
07817       }
07818       // operator
07819       var str = String.fromCharCode(ch);
07820       while ((ch = this.nextChar()) >= 0 && // and 'A'-'Z', 'a'-'z'
07821              ((ch >= 0x41 && ch <= 0x5A) || (ch >= 0x61 && ch <= 0x7A))) {
07822         str += String.fromCharCode(ch);
07823       }
07824       switch (str.toLowerCase()) {
07825         case 'if':
07826           return PostScriptToken.IF;
07827         case 'ifelse':
07828           return PostScriptToken.IFELSE;
07829         default:
07830           return PostScriptToken.getOperator(str);
07831       }
07832     },
07833     getNumber: function PostScriptLexer_getNumber() {
07834       var ch = this.currentChar;
07835       var str = String.fromCharCode(ch);
07836       while ((ch = this.nextChar()) >= 0) {
07837         if ((ch >= 0x30 && ch <= 0x39) || // '0'-'9'
07838              ch === 0x2D || ch === 0x2E) { // '-', '.'
07839           str += String.fromCharCode(ch);
07840         } else {
07841           break;
07842         }
07843       }
07844       var value = parseFloat(str);
07845       if (isNaN(value))
07846         error('Invalid floating point number: ' + value);
07847       return value;
07848     }
07849   };
07850   return PostScriptLexer;
07851 })();
07852

14887 
14888 var ColorSpace = (function ColorSpaceClosure() {
14889   // Constructor should define this.numComps, this.defaultColor, this.name
14890   function ColorSpace() {
14891     error('should not call ColorSpace constructor');
14892   }
14893 
14894   ColorSpace.prototype = {
14900     getRgb: function ColorSpace_getRgb(src, srcOffset) {
14901       error('Should not call ColorSpace.getRgb');
14902     },
14907     getRgbItem: function ColorSpace_getRgb(src, srcOffset, dest, destOffset) {
14908       error('Should not call ColorSpace.getRgbItem');
14909     },
14917     getRgbBuffer: function ColorSpace_getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count,
14918                                                    dest, destOffset, bits) {
14919       error('Should not call ColorSpace.getRgbBuffer');
14920     },
14925     getOutputLength: function ColorSpace_getOutputLength(inputLength) {
14926       error('Should not call ColorSpace.getOutputLength');
14927     },
14931     isPassthrough: function ColorSpace_isPassthrough(bits) {
14932       return false;
14933     },
14938     createRgbBuffer: function ColorSpace_createRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset,
14939                                                          count, bits) {
14940       if (this.isPassthrough(bits)) {
14941         return src.subarray(srcOffset);
14942       }
14943       var dest = new Uint8Array(count * 3);
14944       var numComponentColors = 1 << bits;
14945       // Optimization: create a color map when there is just one component and
14946       // we are converting more colors than the size of the color map. We
14947       // don't build the map if the colorspace is gray or rgb since those
14948       // methods are faster than building a map. This mainly offers big speed
14949       // ups for indexed and alternate colorspaces.
14950       if (this.numComps === 1 && count > numComponentColors &&
14951           this.name !== 'DeviceGray' && this.name !== 'DeviceRGB') {
14952         // TODO it may be worth while to cache the color map. While running
14953         // testing I never hit a cache so I will leave that out for now (perhaps
14954         // we are reparsing colorspaces too much?).
14955         var allColors = bits <= 8 ? new Uint8Array(numComponentColors) :
14956                                     new Uint16Array(numComponentColors);
14957         for (var i = 0; i < numComponentColors; i++) {
14958           allColors[i] = i;
14959         }
14960         var colorMap = new Uint8Array(numComponentColors * 3);
14961         this.getRgbBuffer(allColors, 0, numComponentColors, colorMap, 0, bits);
14962 
14963         var destOffset = 0;
14964         for (var i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
14965           var key = src[srcOffset++] * 3;
14966           dest[destOffset++] = colorMap[key];
14967           dest[destOffset++] = colorMap[key + 1];
14968           dest[destOffset++] = colorMap[key + 2];
14969         }
14970         return dest;
14971       }
14972       this.getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count, dest, 0, bits);
14973       return dest;
14974     },
14980     usesZeroToOneRange: true
14981   };
14982 
14983   ColorSpace.parse = function ColorSpace_parse(cs, xref, res) {
14984     var IR = ColorSpace.parseToIR(cs, xref, res);
14985     if (IR instanceof AlternateCS)
14986       return IR;
14987 
14988     return ColorSpace.fromIR(IR);
14989   };
14990 
14991   ColorSpace.fromIR = function ColorSpace_fromIR(IR) {
14992     var name = isArray(IR) ? IR[0] : IR;
14993 
14994     switch (name) {
14995       case 'DeviceGrayCS':
14996         return new DeviceGrayCS();
14997       case 'DeviceRgbCS':
14998         return new DeviceRgbCS();
14999       case 'DeviceCmykCS':
15000         return new DeviceCmykCS();
15001       case 'PatternCS':
15002         var basePatternCS = IR[1];
15003         if (basePatternCS)
15004           basePatternCS = ColorSpace.fromIR(basePatternCS);
15005         return new PatternCS(basePatternCS);
15006       case 'IndexedCS':
15007         var baseIndexedCS = IR[1];
15008         var hiVal = IR[2];
15009         var lookup = IR[3];
15010         return new IndexedCS(ColorSpace.fromIR(baseIndexedCS), hiVal, lookup);
15011       case 'AlternateCS':
15012         var numComps = IR[1];
15013         var alt = IR[2];
15014         var tintFnIR = IR[3];
15015 
15016         return new AlternateCS(numComps, ColorSpace.fromIR(alt),
15017                                 PDFFunction.fromIR(tintFnIR));
15018       case 'LabCS':
15019         var whitePoint = IR[1].WhitePoint;
15020         var blackPoint = IR[1].BlackPoint;
15021         var range = IR[1].Range;
15022         return new LabCS(whitePoint, blackPoint, range);
15023       default:
15024         error('Unkown name ' + name);
15025     }
15026     return null;
15027   };
15028 
15029   ColorSpace.parseToIR = function ColorSpace_parseToIR(cs, xref, res) {
15030     if (isName(cs)) {
15031       var colorSpaces = res.get('ColorSpace');
15032       if (isDict(colorSpaces)) {
15033         var refcs = colorSpaces.get(cs.name);
15034         if (refcs)
15035           cs = refcs;
15036       }
15037     }
15038 
15039     cs = xref.fetchIfRef(cs);
15040     var mode;
15041 
15042     if (isName(cs)) {
15043       mode = cs.name;
15044       this.mode = mode;
15045 
15046       switch (mode) {
15047         case 'DeviceGray':
15048         case 'G':
15049           return 'DeviceGrayCS';
15050         case 'DeviceRGB':
15051         case 'RGB':
15052           return 'DeviceRgbCS';
15053         case 'DeviceCMYK':
15054         case 'CMYK':
15055           return 'DeviceCmykCS';
15056         case 'Pattern':
15057           return ['PatternCS', null];
15058         default:
15059           error('unrecognized colorspace ' + mode);
15060       }
15061     } else if (isArray(cs)) {
15062       mode = cs[0].name;
15063       this.mode = mode;
15064 
15065       switch (mode) {
15066         case 'DeviceGray':
15067         case 'G':
15068           return 'DeviceGrayCS';
15069         case 'DeviceRGB':
15070         case 'RGB':
15071           return 'DeviceRgbCS';
15072         case 'DeviceCMYK':
15073         case 'CMYK':
15074           return 'DeviceCmykCS';
15075         case 'CalGray':
15076           return 'DeviceGrayCS';
15077         case 'CalRGB':
15078           return 'DeviceRgbCS';
15079         case 'ICCBased':
15080           var stream = xref.fetchIfRef(cs[1]);
15081           var dict = stream.dict;
15082           var numComps = dict.get('N');
15083           if (numComps == 1)
15084             return 'DeviceGrayCS';
15085           if (numComps == 3)
15086             return 'DeviceRgbCS';
15087           if (numComps == 4)
15088             return 'DeviceCmykCS';
15089           break;
15090         case 'Pattern':
15091           var basePatternCS = cs[1];
15092           if (basePatternCS)
15093             basePatternCS = ColorSpace.parseToIR(basePatternCS, xref, res);
15094           return ['PatternCS', basePatternCS];
15095         case 'Indexed':
15096         case 'I':
15097           var baseIndexedCS = ColorSpace.parseToIR(cs[1], xref, res);
15098           var hiVal = cs[2] + 1;
15099           var lookup = xref.fetchIfRef(cs[3]);
15100           if (isStream(lookup)) {
15101             lookup = lookup.getBytes();
15102           }
15103           return ['IndexedCS', baseIndexedCS, hiVal, lookup];
15104         case 'Separation':
15105         case 'DeviceN':
15106           var name = cs[1];
15107           var numComps = 1;
15108           if (isName(name))
15109             numComps = 1;
15110           else if (isArray(name))
15111             numComps = name.length;
15112           var alt = ColorSpace.parseToIR(cs[2], xref, res);
15113           var tintFnIR = PDFFunction.getIR(xref, xref.fetchIfRef(cs[3]));
15114           return ['AlternateCS', numComps, alt, tintFnIR];
15115         case 'Lab':
15116           var params = cs[1].getAll();
15117           return ['LabCS', params];
15118         default:
15119           error('unimplemented color space object "' + mode + '"');
15120       }
15121     } else {
15122       error('unrecognized color space object: "' + cs + '"');
15123     }
15124     return null;
15125   };
15135   ColorSpace.isDefaultDecode = function ColorSpace_isDefaultDecode(decode, n) {
15136     if (!decode)
15137       return true;
15138 
15139     if (n * 2 !== decode.length) {
15140       warn('The decode map is not the correct length');
15141       return true;
15142     }
15143     for (var i = 0, ii = decode.length; i < ii; i += 2) {
15144       if (decode[i] !== 0 || decode[i + 1] != 1)
15145         return false;
15146     }
15147     return true;
15148   };
15149 
15150   return ColorSpace;
15151 })();
15152 
15159 var AlternateCS = (function AlternateCSClosure() {
15160   function AlternateCS(numComps, base, tintFn) {
15161     this.name = 'Alternate';
15162     this.numComps = numComps;
15163     this.defaultColor = new Float32Array(numComps);
15164     for (var i = 0; i < numComps; ++i) {
15165       this.defaultColor[i] = 1;
15166     }
15167     this.base = base;
15168     this.tintFn = tintFn;
15169   }
15170 
15171   AlternateCS.prototype = {
15172     getRgb: function AlternateCS_getRgb(src, srcOffset) {
15173       var rgb = new Uint8Array(3);
15174       this.getRgbItem(src, srcOffset, rgb, 0);
15175       return rgb;
15176     },
15177     getRgbItem: function AlternateCS_getRgbItem(src, srcOffset,
15178                                                 dest, destOffset) {
15179       var baseNumComps = this.base.numComps;
15180       var input = 'subarray' in src ?
15181         src.subarray(srcOffset, srcOffset + this.numComps) :
15182         Array.prototype.slice.call(src, srcOffset, srcOffset + this.numComps);
15183       var tinted = this.tintFn(input);
15184       this.base.getRgbItem(tinted, 0, dest, destOffset);
15185     },
15186     getRgbBuffer: function AlternateCS_getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count,
15187                                                     dest, destOffset, bits) {
15188       var tintFn = this.tintFn;
15189       var base = this.base;
15190       var scale = 1 / ((1 << bits) - 1);
15191       var baseNumComps = base.numComps;
15192       var usesZeroToOneRange = base.usesZeroToOneRange;
15193       var isPassthrough = base.isPassthrough(8) || !usesZeroToOneRange;
15194       var pos = isPassthrough ? destOffset : 0;
15195       var baseBuf = isPassthrough ? dest : new Uint8Array(baseNumComps * count);
15196       var numComps = this.numComps;
15197 
15198       var scaled = new Float32Array(numComps);
15199       for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
15200         for (var j = 0; j < numComps; j++) {
15201           scaled[j] = src[srcOffset++] * scale;
15202         }
15203         var tinted = tintFn(scaled);
15204         if (usesZeroToOneRange) {
15205           for (var j = 0; j < baseNumComps; j++) {
15206             baseBuf[pos++] = tinted[j] * 255;
15207           }
15208         } else {
15209           base.getRgbItem(tinted, 0, baseBuf, pos);
15210           pos += baseNumComps;
15211         }
15212       }
15213       if (!isPassthrough) {
15214         base.getRgbBuffer(baseBuf, 0, count, dest, destOffset, 8);
15215       }
15216     },
15217     getOutputLength: function AlternateCS_getOutputLength(inputLength) {
15218       return this.base.getOutputLength(inputLength *
15219                                        this.base.numComps / this.numComps);
15220     },
15221     isPassthrough: ColorSpace.prototype.isPassthrough,
15222     createRgbBuffer: ColorSpace.prototype.createRgbBuffer,
15223     isDefaultDecode: function AlternateCS_isDefaultDecode(decodeMap) {
15224       return ColorSpace.isDefaultDecode(decodeMap, this.numComps);
15225     },
15226     usesZeroToOneRange: true
15227   };
15228 
15229   return AlternateCS;
15230 })();
15231

15234     this.name = 'Pattern';
15235     this.base = baseCS;

15237   PatternCS.prototype = {};

15242 var IndexedCS = (function IndexedCSClosure() {
15243   function IndexedCS(base, highVal, lookup) {
15244     this.name = 'Indexed';
15245     this.numComps = 1;
15246     this.defaultColor = new Uint8Array([0]);
15247     this.base = base;
15248     this.highVal = highVal;
15249 
15250     var baseNumComps = base.numComps;
15251     var length = baseNumComps * highVal;
15252     var lookupArray;
15253 
15254     if (isStream(lookup)) {
15255       lookupArray = new Uint8Array(length);
15256       var bytes = lookup.getBytes(length);
15257       lookupArray.set(bytes);
15258     } else if (isString(lookup)) {
15259       lookupArray = new Uint8Array(length);
15260       for (var i = 0; i < length; ++i)
15261         lookupArray[i] = lookup.charCodeAt(i);
15262     } else if (lookup instanceof Uint8Array || lookup instanceof Array) {
15263       lookupArray = lookup;
15264     } else {
15265       error('Unrecognized lookup table: ' + lookup);
15266     }
15267     this.lookup = lookupArray;
15268   }
15269 
15270   IndexedCS.prototype = {
15271     getRgb: function IndexedCS_getRgb(src, srcOffset) {
15272       var numComps = this.base.numComps;
15273       var start = src[srcOffset] * numComps;
15274       return this.base.getRgb(this.lookup, start);
15275     },
15276     getRgbItem: function IndexedCS_getRgbItem(src, srcOffset,
15277                                               dest, destOffset) {
15278       var numComps = this.base.numComps;
15279       var start = src[srcOffset] * numComps;
15280       this.base.getRgbItem(this.lookup, start, dest, destOffset);
15281     },
15282     getRgbBuffer: function IndexedCS_getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count,
15283                                                   dest, destOffset) {
15284       var base = this.base;
15285       var numComps = base.numComps;
15286       var outputDelta = base.getOutputLength(numComps);
15287       var lookup = this.lookup;
15288 
15289       for (var i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
15290         var lookupPos = src[srcOffset++] * numComps;
15291         base.getRgbBuffer(lookup, lookupPos, 1, dest, destOffset, 8);
15292         destOffset += outputDelta;
15293       }
15294     },
15295     getOutputLength: function IndexedCS_getOutputLength(inputLength) {
15296       return this.base.getOutputLength(inputLength * this.base.numComps);
15297     },
15298     isPassthrough: ColorSpace.prototype.isPassthrough,
15299     createRgbBuffer: ColorSpace.prototype.createRgbBuffer,
15300     isDefaultDecode: function IndexedCS_isDefaultDecode(decodeMap) {
15301       // indexed color maps shouldn't be changed
15302       return true;
15303     },
15304     usesZeroToOneRange: true
15305   };
15306   return IndexedCS;
15307 })();

15309 var DeviceGrayCS = (function DeviceGrayCSClosure() {
15310   function DeviceGrayCS() {
15311     this.name = 'DeviceGray';
15312     this.numComps = 1;
15313     this.defaultColor = new Float32Array([0]);
15314   }
15315 
15316   DeviceGrayCS.prototype = {
15317     getRgb: function DeviceGrayCS_getRgb(src, srcOffset) {
15318       var rgb = new Uint8Array(3);
15319       this.getRgbItem(src, srcOffset, rgb, 0);
15320       return rgb;
15321     },
15322     getRgbItem: function DeviceGrayCS_getRgbItem(src, srcOffset,
15323                                                  dest, destOffset) {
15324       var c = (src[srcOffset] * 255) | 0;
15325       c = c < 0 ? 0 : c > 255 ? 255 : c;
15326       dest[destOffset] = dest[destOffset + 1] = dest[destOffset + 2] = c;
15327     },
15328     getRgbBuffer: function DeviceGrayCS_getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count,
15329                                                      dest, destOffset, bits) {
15330       var scale = 255 / ((1 << bits) - 1);
15331       var j = srcOffset, q = destOffset;
15332       for (var i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
15333         var c = (scale * src[j++]) | 0;
15334         dest[q++] = c;
15335         dest[q++] = c;
15336         dest[q++] = c;
15337       }
15338     },
15339     getOutputLength: function DeviceGrayCS_getOutputLength(inputLength) {
15340       return inputLength * 3;
15341     },
15342     isPassthrough: ColorSpace.prototype.isPassthrough,
15343     createRgbBuffer: ColorSpace.prototype.createRgbBuffer,
15344     isDefaultDecode: function DeviceGrayCS_isDefaultDecode(decodeMap) {
15345       return ColorSpace.isDefaultDecode(decodeMap, this.numComps);
15346     },
15347     usesZeroToOneRange: true
15348   };
15349   return DeviceGrayCS;
15350 })();

15352 var DeviceRgbCS = (function DeviceRgbCSClosure() {
15353   function DeviceRgbCS() {
15354     this.name = 'DeviceRGB';
15355     this.numComps = 3;
15356     this.defaultColor = new Float32Array([0, 0, 0]);
15357   }
15358   DeviceRgbCS.prototype = {
15359     getRgb: function DeviceRgbCS_getRgb(src, srcOffset) {
15360       var rgb = new Uint8Array(3);
15361       this.getRgbItem(src, srcOffset, rgb, 0);
15362       return rgb;
15363     },
15364     getRgbItem: function DeviceRgbCS_getRgbItem(src, srcOffset,
15365                                                 dest, destOffset) {
15366       var r = (src[srcOffset] * 255) | 0;
15367       var g = (src[srcOffset + 1] * 255) | 0;
15368       var b = (src[srcOffset + 2] * 255) | 0;
15369       dest[destOffset] = r < 0 ? 0 : r > 255 ? 255 : r;
15370       dest[destOffset + 1] = g < 0 ? 0 : g > 255 ? 255 : g;
15371       dest[destOffset + 2] = b < 0 ? 0 : b > 255 ? 255 : b;
15372     },
15373     getRgbBuffer: function DeviceRgbCS_getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count,
15374                                                     dest, destOffset, bits) {
15375       var length = count * 3;
15376       if (bits == 8) {
15377         dest.set(src.subarray(srcOffset, srcOffset + length), destOffset);
15378         return;
15379       }
15380       var scale = 255 / ((1 << bits) - 1);
15381       var j = srcOffset, q = destOffset;
15382       for (var i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
15383         dest[q++] = (scale * src[j++]) | 0;
15384       }
15385     },
15386     getOutputLength: function DeviceRgbCS_getOutputLength(inputLength) {
15387       return inputLength;
15388     },
15389     isPassthrough: function DeviceRgbCS_isPassthrough(bits) {
15390       return bits == 8;
15391     },
15392     createRgbBuffer: ColorSpace.prototype.createRgbBuffer,
15393     isDefaultDecode: function DeviceRgbCS_isDefaultDecode(decodeMap) {
15394       return ColorSpace.isDefaultDecode(decodeMap, this.numComps);
15395     },
15396     usesZeroToOneRange: true
15397   };
15398   return DeviceRgbCS;
15399 })();

15401 var DeviceCmykCS = (function DeviceCmykCSClosure() {
15402   // The coefficients below was found using numerical analysis: the method of
15403   // steepest descent for the sum((f_i - color_value_i)^2) for r/g/b colors,
15404   // where color_value is the tabular value from the table of sampled RGB colors
15405   // from CMYK US Web Coated (SWOP) colorspace, and f_i is the corresponding
15406   // CMYK color conversion using the estimation below:
15407   //   f(A, B,.. N) = Acc+Bcm+Ccy+Dck+c+Fmm+Gmy+Hmk+Im+Jyy+Kyk+Ly+Mkk+Nk+255
15408   function convertToRgb(src, srcOffset, srcScale, dest, destOffset) {
15409     var c = src[srcOffset + 0] * srcScale;
15410     var m = src[srcOffset + 1] * srcScale;
15411     var y = src[srcOffset + 2] * srcScale;
15412     var k = src[srcOffset + 3] * srcScale;
15413 
15414     var r =
15415       c * (-4.387332384609988 * c + 54.48615194189176 * m +
15416            18.82290502165302 * y + 212.25662451639585 * k +
15417            -285.2331026137004) +
15418       m * (1.7149763477362134 * m - 5.6096736904047315 * y +
15419            -17.873870861415444 * k - 5.497006427196366) +
15420       y * (-2.5217340131683033 * y - 21.248923337353073 * k +
15421            17.5119270841813) +
15422       k * (-21.86122147463605 * k - 189.48180835922747) + 255;
15423     var g =
15424       c * (8.841041422036149 * c + 60.118027045597366 * m +
15425            6.871425592049007 * y + 31.159100130055922 * k +
15426            -79.2970844816548) +
15427       m * (-15.310361306967817 * m + 17.575251261109482 * y +
15428            131.35250912493976 * k - 190.9453302588951) +
15429       y * (4.444339102852739 * y + 9.8632861493405 * k - 24.86741582555878) +
15430       k * (-20.737325471181034 * k - 187.80453709719578) + 255;
15431     var b =
15432       c * (0.8842522430003296 * c + 8.078677503112928 * m +
15433            30.89978309703729 * y - 0.23883238689178934 * k +
15434            -14.183576799673286) +
15435       m * (10.49593273432072 * m + 63.02378494754052 * y +
15436            50.606957656360734 * k - 112.23884253719248) +
15437       y * (0.03296041114873217 * y + 115.60384449646641 * k +
15438            -193.58209356861505) +
15439       k * (-22.33816807309886 * k - 180.12613974708367) + 255;
15440 
15441     dest[destOffset] = r > 255 ? 255 : r < 0 ? 0 : r;
15442     dest[destOffset + 1] = g > 255 ? 255 : g < 0 ? 0 : g;
15443     dest[destOffset + 2] = b > 255 ? 255 : b < 0 ? 0 : b;
15444   }
15445 
15446   function DeviceCmykCS() {
15447     this.name = 'DeviceCMYK';
15448     this.numComps = 4;
15449     this.defaultColor = new Float32Array([0, 0, 0, 1]);
15450   }
15451   DeviceCmykCS.prototype = {
15452     getRgb: function DeviceCmykCS_getRgb(src, srcOffset) {
15453       var rgb = new Uint8Array(3);
15454       convertToRgb(src, srcOffset, 1, rgb, 0);
15455       return rgb;
15456     },
15457     getRgbItem: function DeviceCmykCS_getRgbItem(src, srcOffset,
15458                                                  dest, destOffset) {
15459       convertToRgb(src, srcOffset, 1, dest, destOffset);
15460     },
15461     getRgbBuffer: function DeviceCmykCS_getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count,
15462                                                      dest, destOffset, bits) {
15463       var scale = 1 / ((1 << bits) - 1);
15464       for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
15465         convertToRgb(src, srcOffset, scale, dest, destOffset);
15466         srcOffset += 4;
15467         destOffset += 3;
15468       }
15469     },
15470     getOutputLength: function DeviceCmykCS_getOutputLength(inputLength) {
15471       return (inputLength >> 2) * 3;
15472     },
15473     isPassthrough: ColorSpace.prototype.isPassthrough,
15474     createRgbBuffer: ColorSpace.prototype.createRgbBuffer,
15475     isDefaultDecode: function DeviceCmykCS_isDefaultDecode(decodeMap) {
15476       return ColorSpace.isDefaultDecode(decodeMap, this.numComps);
15477     },
15478     usesZeroToOneRange: true
15479   };
15480 
15481   return DeviceCmykCS;
15482 })();
15483 
15484 //
15485 // LabCS: Based on "PDF Reference, Sixth Ed", p.250
15486 //
15487 var LabCS = (function LabCSClosure() {
15488   function LabCS(whitePoint, blackPoint, range) {
15489     this.name = 'Lab';
15490     this.numComps = 3;
15491     this.defaultColor = new Float32Array([0, 0, 0]);
15492 
15493     if (!whitePoint)
15494       error('WhitePoint missing - required for color space Lab');
15495     blackPoint = blackPoint || [0, 0, 0];
15496     range = range || [-100, 100, -100, 100];
15497 
15498     // Translate args to spec variables
15499     this.XW = whitePoint[0];
15500     this.YW = whitePoint[1];
15501     this.ZW = whitePoint[2];
15502     this.amin = range[0];
15503     this.amax = range[1];
15504     this.bmin = range[2];
15505     this.bmax = range[3];
15506 
15507     // These are here just for completeness - the spec doesn't offer any
15508     // formulas that use BlackPoint in Lab
15509     this.XB = blackPoint[0];
15510     this.YB = blackPoint[1];
15511     this.ZB = blackPoint[2];
15512 
15513     // Validate vars as per spec
15514     if (this.XW < 0 || this.ZW < 0 || this.YW !== 1)
15515       error('Invalid WhitePoint components, no fallback available');
15516 
15517     if (this.XB < 0 || this.YB < 0 || this.ZB < 0) {
15518       info('Invalid BlackPoint, falling back to default');
15519       this.XB = this.YB = this.ZB = 0;
15520     }
15521 
15522     if (this.amin > this.amax || this.bmin > this.bmax) {
15523       info('Invalid Range, falling back to defaults');
15524       this.amin = -100;
15525       this.amax = 100;
15526       this.bmin = -100;
15527       this.bmax = 100;
15528     }
15529   }
15530 
15531   // Function g(x) from spec
15532   function fn_g(x) {
15533     if (x >= 6 / 29)
15534       return x * x * x;
15535     else
15536       return (108 / 841) * (x - 4 / 29);
15537   }
15538 
15539   function decode(value, high1, low2, high2) {
15540     return low2 + (value) * (high2 - low2) / (high1);
15541   }
15542 
15543   // If decoding is needed maxVal should be 2^bits per component - 1.
15544   function convertToRgb(cs, src, srcOffset, maxVal, dest, destOffset) {
15545     // XXX: Lab input is in the range of [0, 100], [amin, amax], [bmin, bmax]
15546     // not the usual [0, 1]. If a command like setFillColor is used the src
15547     // values will already be within the correct range. However, if we are
15548     // converting an image we have to map the values to the correct range given
15549     // above.
15550     // Ls,as,bs <---> L*,a*,b* in the spec
15551     var Ls = src[srcOffset];
15552     var as = src[srcOffset + 1];
15553     var bs = src[srcOffset + 2];
15554     if (maxVal !== false) {
15555       Ls = decode(Ls, maxVal, 0, 100);
15556       as = decode(as, maxVal, cs.amin, cs.amax);
15557       bs = decode(bs, maxVal, cs.bmin, cs.bmax);
15558     }
15559 
15560     // Adjust limits of 'as' and 'bs'
15561     as = as > cs.amax ? cs.amax : as < cs.amin ? cs.amin : as;
15562     bs = bs > cs.bmax ? cs.bmax : bs < cs.bmin ? cs.bmin : bs;
15563 
15564     // Computes intermediate variables X,Y,Z as per spec
15565     var M = (Ls + 16) / 116;
15566     var L = M + (as / 500);
15567     var N = M - (bs / 200);
15568 
15569     var X = cs.XW * fn_g(L);
15570     var Y = cs.YW * fn_g(M);
15571     var Z = cs.ZW * fn_g(N);
15572 
15573     var r, g, b;
15574     // Using different conversions for D50 and D65 white points,
15575     // per http://www.color.org/srgb.pdf
15576     if (cs.ZW < 1) {
15577       // Assuming D50 (X=0.9642, Y=1.00, Z=0.8249)
15578       r = X * 3.1339 + Y * -1.6170 + Z * -0.4906;
15579       g = X * -0.9785 + Y * 1.9160 + Z * 0.0333;
15580       b = X * 0.0720 + Y * -0.2290 + Z * 1.4057;
15581     } else {
15582       // Assuming D65 (X=0.9505, Y=1.00, Z=1.0888)
15583       r = X * 3.2406 + Y * -1.5372 + Z * -0.4986;
15584       g = X * -0.9689 + Y * 1.8758 + Z * 0.0415;
15585       b = X * 0.0557 + Y * -0.2040 + Z * 1.0570;
15586     }
15587     // clamp color values to [0,1] range then convert to [0,255] range.
15588     dest[destOffset] = Math.sqrt(r < 0 ? 0 : r > 1 ? 1 : r) * 255;
15589     dest[destOffset + 1] = Math.sqrt(g < 0 ? 0 : g > 1 ? 1 : g) * 255;
15590     dest[destOffset + 2] = Math.sqrt(b < 0 ? 0 : b > 1 ? 1 : b) * 255;
15591   }
15592 
15593   LabCS.prototype = {
15594     getRgb: function LabCS_getRgb(src, srcOffset) {
15595       var rgb = new Uint8Array(3);
15596       convertToRgb(this, src, srcOffset, false, rgb, 0);
15597       return rgb;
15598     },
15599     getRgbItem: function LabCS_getRgbItem(src, srcOffset, dest, destOffset) {
15600       convertToRgb(this, src, srcOffset, false, dest, destOffset);
15601     },
15602     getRgbBuffer: function LabCS_getRgbBuffer(src, srcOffset, count,
15603                                               dest, destOffset, bits) {
15604       var maxVal = (1 << bits) - 1;
15605       for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
15606         convertToRgb(this, src, srcOffset, maxVal, dest, destOffset);
15607         srcOffset += 3;
15608         destOffset += 3;
15609       }
15610     },
15611     getOutputLength: function LabCS_getOutputLength(inputLength) {
15612       return inputLength;
15613     },
15614     isPassthrough: ColorSpace.prototype.isPassthrough,
15615     isDefaultDecode: function LabCS_isDefaultDecode(decodeMap) {
15616       // XXX: Decoding is handled with the lab conversion because of the strange
15617       // ranges that are used.
15618       return true;
15619     },
15620     usesZeroToOneRange: false
15621   };
15622   return LabCS;
15623 })();

15626 var ARCFourCipher = (function ARCFourCipherClosure() {
15627   function ARCFourCipher(key) {
15628     this.a = 0;
15629     this.b = 0;
15630     var s = new Uint8Array(256);
15631     var i, j = 0, tmp, keyLength = key.length;
15632     for (i = 0; i < 256; ++i)
15633       s[i] = i;
15634     for (i = 0; i < 256; ++i) {
15635       tmp = s[i];
15636       j = (j + tmp + key[i % keyLength]) & 0xFF;
15637       s[i] = s[j];
15638       s[j] = tmp;
15639     }
15640     this.s = s;
15641   }
15642 
15643   ARCFourCipher.prototype = {
15644     encryptBlock: function ARCFourCipher_encryptBlock(data) {
15645       var i, n = data.length, tmp, tmp2;
15646       var a = this.a, b = this.b, s = this.s;
15647       var output = new Uint8Array(n);
15648       for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
15649         a = (a + 1) & 0xFF;
15650         tmp = s[a];
15651         b = (b + tmp) & 0xFF;
15652         tmp2 = s[b];
15653         s[a] = tmp2;
15654         s[b] = tmp;
15655         output[i] = data[i] ^ s[(tmp + tmp2) & 0xFF];
15656       }
15657       this.a = a;
15658       this.b = b;
15659       return output;
15660     }
15661   };
15662   ARCFourCipher.prototype.decryptBlock = ARCFourCipher.prototype.encryptBlock;
15663 
15664   return ARCFourCipher;
15665 })();

15667 var calculateMD5 = (function calculateMD5Closure() {
15668   var r = new Uint8Array([
15669     7, 12, 17, 22, 7, 12, 17, 22, 7, 12, 17, 22, 7, 12, 17, 22,
15670     5, 9, 14, 20, 5, 9, 14, 20, 5, 9, 14, 20, 5, 9, 14, 20,
15671     4, 11, 16, 23, 4, 11, 16, 23, 4, 11, 16, 23, 4, 11, 16, 23,
15672     6, 10, 15, 21, 6, 10, 15, 21, 6, 10, 15, 21, 6, 10, 15, 21]);
15673 
15674   var k = new Int32Array([
15675     -680876936, -389564586, 606105819, -1044525330, -176418897, 1200080426,
15676     -1473231341, -45705983, 1770035416, -1958414417, -42063, -1990404162,
15677     1804603682, -40341101, -1502002290, 1236535329, -165796510, -1069501632,
15678     643717713, -373897302, -701558691, 38016083, -660478335, -405537848,
15679     568446438, -1019803690, -187363961, 1163531501, -1444681467, -51403784,
15680     1735328473, -1926607734, -378558, -2022574463, 1839030562, -35309556,
15681     -1530992060, 1272893353, -155497632, -1094730640, 681279174, -358537222,
15682     -722521979, 76029189, -640364487, -421815835, 530742520, -995338651,
15683     -198630844, 1126891415, -1416354905, -57434055, 1700485571, -1894986606,
15684     -1051523, -2054922799, 1873313359, -30611744, -1560198380, 1309151649,
15685     -145523070, -1120210379, 718787259, -343485551]);
15686 
15687   function hash(data, offset, length) {
15688     var h0 = 1732584193, h1 = -271733879, h2 = -1732584194, h3 = 271733878;
15689     // pre-processing
15690     var paddedLength = (length + 72) & ~63; // data + 9 extra bytes
15691     var padded = new Uint8Array(paddedLength);
15692     var i, j, n;
15693     for (i = 0; i < length; ++i)
15694       padded[i] = data[offset++];
15695     padded[i++] = 0x80;
15696     n = paddedLength - 8;
15697     while (i < n)
15698       padded[i++] = 0;
15699     padded[i++] = (length << 3) & 0xFF;
15700     padded[i++] = (length >> 5) & 0xFF;
15701     padded[i++] = (length >> 13) & 0xFF;
15702     padded[i++] = (length >> 21) & 0xFF;
15703     padded[i++] = (length >>> 29) & 0xFF;
15704     padded[i++] = 0;
15705     padded[i++] = 0;
15706     padded[i++] = 0;
15707     // chunking
15708     // TODO ArrayBuffer ?
15709     var w = new Int32Array(16);
15710     for (i = 0; i < paddedLength;) {
15711       for (j = 0; j < 16; ++j, i += 4) {
15712         w[j] = (padded[i] | (padded[i + 1] << 8) |
15713                 (padded[i + 2] << 16) | (padded[i + 3] << 24));
15714       }
15715       var a = h0, b = h1, c = h2, d = h3, f, g;
15716       for (j = 0; j < 64; ++j) {
15717         if (j < 16) {
15718           f = (b & c) | ((~b) & d);
15719           g = j;
15720         } else if (j < 32) {
15721           f = (d & b) | ((~d) & c);
15722           g = (5 * j + 1) & 15;
15723         } else if (j < 48) {
15724           f = b ^ c ^ d;
15725           g = (3 * j + 5) & 15;
15726         } else {
15727           f = c ^ (b | (~d));
15728           g = (7 * j) & 15;
15729         }
15730         var tmp = d, rotateArg = (a + f + k[j] + w[g]) | 0, rotate = r[j];
15731         d = c;
15732         c = b;
15733         b = (b + ((rotateArg << rotate) | (rotateArg >>> (32 - rotate)))) | 0;
15734         a = tmp;
15735       }
15736       h0 = (h0 + a) | 0;
15737       h1 = (h1 + b) | 0;
15738       h2 = (h2 + c) | 0;
15739       h3 = (h3 + d) | 0;
15740     }
15741     return new Uint8Array([
15742         h0 & 0xFF, (h0 >> 8) & 0xFF, (h0 >> 16) & 0xFF, (h0 >>> 24) & 0xFF,
15743         h1 & 0xFF, (h1 >> 8) & 0xFF, (h1 >> 16) & 0xFF, (h1 >>> 24) & 0xFF,
15744         h2 & 0xFF, (h2 >> 8) & 0xFF, (h2 >> 16) & 0xFF, (h2 >>> 24) & 0xFF,
15745         h3 & 0xFF, (h3 >> 8) & 0xFF, (h3 >> 16) & 0xFF, (h3 >>> 24) & 0xFF
15746     ]);
15747   }
15748   return hash;
15749 })();

15873     0x10187da7, 0x1e1170ac, 0x342e539d, 0x3a275e96, 0x283c498b, 0x26354480,
15874     0x7c420fe9, 0x724b02e2, 0x605015ff, 0x6e5918f4, 0x44663bc5, 0x4a6f36ce,
15875     0x587421d3, 0x567d2cd8, 0x37a10c7a, 0x39a80171, 0x2bb3166c, 0x25ba1b67,
15876     0x0f853856, 0x018c355d, 0x13972240, 0x1d9e2f4b, 0x47e96422, 0x49e06929,
15877     0x5bfb7e34, 0x55f2733f, 0x7fcd500e, 0x71c45d05, 0x63df4a18, 0x6dd64713,
15878     0xd731dcca, 0xd938d1c1, 0xcb23c6dc, 0xc52acbd7, 0xef15e8e6, 0xe11ce5ed,
15879     0xf307f2f0, 0xfd0efffb, 0xa779b492, 0xa970b999, 0xbb6bae84, 0xb562a38f,
15880     0x9f5d80be, 0x91548db5, 0x834f9aa8, 0x8d4697a3]);
15881 
15882   function expandKey128(cipherKey) {
15883     var b = 176, result = new Uint8Array(b);
15884     result.set(cipherKey);
15885     for (var j = 16, i = 1; j < b; ++i) {
15886       // RotWord
15887       var t1 = result[j - 3], t2 = result[j - 2],
15888           t3 = result[j - 1], t4 = result[j - 4];
15889       // SubWord
15890       t1 = s[t1]; t2 = s[t2]; t3 = s[t3]; t4 = s[t4];
15891       // Rcon
15892       t1 = t1 ^ rcon[i];
15893       for (var n = 0; n < 4; ++n) {
15894         result[j] = (t1 ^= result[j - 16]); j++;
15895         result[j] = (t2 ^= result[j - 16]); j++;
15896         result[j] = (t3 ^= result[j - 16]); j++;
15897         result[j] = (t4 ^= result[j - 16]); j++;
15898       }
15899     }
15900     return result;
15901   }
15902 
15903   function decrypt128(input, key) {
15904     var state = new Uint8Array(16);
15905     state.set(input);
15906     var i, j, k;
15907     var t, u, v;
15908     // AddRoundKey
15909     for (j = 0, k = 160; j < 16; ++j, ++k)
15910       state[j] ^= key[k];
15911     for (i = 9; i >= 1; --i) {
15912       // InvShiftRows
15913       t = state[13]; state[13] = state[9]; state[9] = state[5];
15914       state[5] = state[1]; state[1] = t;
15915       t = state[14]; u = state[10]; state[14] = state[6];
15916       state[10] = state[2]; state[6] = t; state[2] = u;
15917       t = state[15]; u = state[11]; v = state[7]; state[15] = state[3];
15918       state[11] = t; state[7] = u; state[3] = v;
15919       // InvSubBytes
15920       for (j = 0; j < 16; ++j)
15921         state[j] = inv_s[state[j]];
15922       // AddRoundKey
15923       for (j = 0, k = i * 16; j < 16; ++j, ++k)
15924         state[j] ^= key[k];
15925       // InvMixColumns
15926       for (j = 0; j < 16; j += 4) {
15927         var s0 = mix[state[j]], s1 = mix[state[j + 1]],
15928             s2 = mix[state[j + 2]], s3 = mix[state[j + 3]];
15929         t = (s0 ^ (s1 >>> 8) ^ (s1 << 24) ^ (s2 >>> 16) ^ (s2 << 16) ^
15930             (s3 >>> 24) ^ (s3 << 8));
15931         state[j] = (t >>> 24) & 0xFF;
15932         state[j + 1] = (t >> 16) & 0xFF;
15933         state[j + 2] = (t >> 8) & 0xFF;
15934         state[j + 3] = t & 0xFF;
15935       }
15936     }
15937     // InvShiftRows
15938     t = state[13]; state[13] = state[9]; state[9] = state[5];
15939     state[5] = state[1]; state[1] = t;
15940     t = state[14]; u = state[10]; state[14] = state[6];
15941     state[10] = state[2]; state[6] = t; state[2] = u;
15942     t = state[15]; u = state[11]; v = state[7]; state[15] = state[3];
15943     state[11] = t; state[7] = u; state[3] = v;
15944     for (j = 0; j < 16; ++j) {
15945       // InvSubBytes
15946       state[j] = inv_s[state[j]];
15947       // AddRoundKey
15948       state[j] ^= key[j];
15949     }
15950     return state;
15951   }
15952 
15953   function AES128Cipher(key) {
15954     this.key = expandKey128(key);
15955     this.buffer = new Uint8Array(16);
15956     this.bufferPosition = 0;
15957   }
15958 
15959   function decryptBlock2(data, finalize) {
15960     var i, j, ii, sourceLength = data.length,
15961         buffer = this.buffer, bufferLength = this.bufferPosition,
15962         result = [], iv = this.iv;
15963     for (i = 0; i < sourceLength; ++i) {
15964       buffer[bufferLength] = data[i];
15965       ++bufferLength;
15966       if (bufferLength < 16)
15967         continue;
15968       // buffer is full, decrypting
15969       var plain = decrypt128(buffer, this.key);
15970       // xor-ing the IV vector to get plain text
15971       for (j = 0; j < 16; ++j)
15972         plain[j] ^= iv[j];
15973       iv = buffer;
15974       result.push(plain);
15975       buffer = new Uint8Array(16);
15976       bufferLength = 0;
15977     }
15978     // saving incomplete buffer
15979     this.buffer = buffer;
15980     this.bufferLength = bufferLength;
15981     this.iv = iv;
15982     if (result.length === 0) {
15983       return new Uint8Array([]);
15984     }
15985     // combining plain text blocks into one
15986     var outputLength = 16 * result.length;
15987     if (finalize) {
15988       // undo a padding that is described in RFC 2898
15989       var lastBlock = result[result.length - 1];
15990       outputLength -= lastBlock[15];
15991       result[result.length - 1] = lastBlock.subarray(0, 16 - lastBlock[15]);
15992     }
15993     var output = new Uint8Array(outputLength);
15994     for (i = 0, j = 0, ii = result.length; i < ii; ++i, j += 16)
15995       output.set(result[i], j);
15996     return output;
15997   }
15998 
15999   AES128Cipher.prototype = {
16000     decryptBlock: function AES128Cipher_decryptBlock(data, finalize) {
16001       var i, sourceLength = data.length;
16002       var buffer = this.buffer, bufferLength = this.bufferPosition;
16003       // waiting for IV values -- they are at the start of the stream
16004       for (i = 0; bufferLength < 16 && i < sourceLength; ++i, ++bufferLength)
16005         buffer[bufferLength] = data[i];
16006       if (bufferLength < 16) {
16007         // need more data
16008         this.bufferLength = bufferLength;
16009         return new Uint8Array([]);
16010       }
16011       this.iv = buffer;
16012       this.buffer = new Uint8Array(16);
16013       this.bufferLength = 0;
16014       // starting decryption
16015       this.decryptBlock = decryptBlock2;
16016       return this.decryptBlock(data.subarray(16), finalize);
16017     }
16018   };
16019 
16020   return AES128Cipher;
16021 })();

16025     this.stringCipherConstructor = stringCipherConstructor;
16026     this.streamCipherConstructor = streamCipherConstructor;
16027   }
16028   CipherTransform.prototype = {
16029     createStream: function CipherTransform_createStream(stream) {
16030       var cipher = new this.streamCipherConstructor();
16031       return new DecryptStream(stream,
16032         function cipherTransformDecryptStream(data, finalize) {
16033           return cipher.decryptBlock(data, finalize);
16034         }
16035       );
16036     },
16037     decryptString: function CipherTransform_decryptString(s) {
16038       var cipher = new this.stringCipherConstructor();
16039       var data = stringToBytes(s);
16040       data = cipher.decryptBlock(data, true);
16041       return bytesToString(data);
16042     }
16043   };
16044   return CipherTransform;
