16047 var CipherTransformFactory = (function CipherTransformFactoryClosure() {
16048   var defaultPasswordBytes = new Uint8Array([
16049     0x28, 0xBF, 0x4E, 0x5E, 0x4E, 0x75, 0x8A, 0x41,
16050     0x64, 0x00, 0x4E, 0x56, 0xFF, 0xFA, 0x01, 0x08,
16051     0x2E, 0x2E, 0x00, 0xB6, 0xD0, 0x68, 0x3E, 0x80,
16052     0x2F, 0x0C, 0xA9, 0xFE, 0x64, 0x53, 0x69, 0x7A]);
16053 
16054   function prepareKeyData(fileId, password, ownerPassword, userPassword,
16055                           flags, revision, keyLength, encryptMetadata) {
16056     var hashData = new Uint8Array(100), i = 0, j, n;
16057     if (password) {
16058       n = Math.min(32, password.length);
16059       for (; i < n; ++i)
16060         hashData[i] = password[i];
16061     }
16062     j = 0;
16063     while (i < 32) {
16064       hashData[i++] = defaultPasswordBytes[j++];
16065     }
16066     // as now the padded password in the hashData[0..i]
16067     for (j = 0, n = ownerPassword.length; j < n; ++j)
16068       hashData[i++] = ownerPassword[j];
16069     hashData[i++] = flags & 0xFF;
16070     hashData[i++] = (flags >> 8) & 0xFF;
16071     hashData[i++] = (flags >> 16) & 0xFF;
16072     hashData[i++] = (flags >>> 24) & 0xFF;
16073     for (j = 0, n = fileId.length; j < n; ++j)
16074       hashData[i++] = fileId[j];
16075     if (revision >= 4 && !encryptMetadata) {
16076       hashData[i++] = 0xFF;
16077       hashData[i++] = 0xFF;
16078       hashData[i++] = 0xFF;
16079       hashData[i++] = 0xFF;
16080     }
16081     var hash = calculateMD5(hashData, 0, i);
16082     var keyLengthInBytes = keyLength >> 3;
16083     if (revision >= 3) {
16084       for (j = 0; j < 50; ++j) {
16085          hash = calculateMD5(hash, 0, keyLengthInBytes);
16086       }
16087     }
16088     var encryptionKey = hash.subarray(0, keyLengthInBytes);
16089     var cipher, checkData;
16090 
16091     if (revision >= 3) {
16092       for (i = 0; i < 32; ++i)
16093         hashData[i] = defaultPasswordBytes[i];
16094       for (j = 0, n = fileId.length; j < n; ++j)
16095         hashData[i++] = fileId[j];
16096       cipher = new ARCFourCipher(encryptionKey);
16097       var checkData = cipher.encryptBlock(calculateMD5(hashData, 0, i));
16098       n = encryptionKey.length;
16099       var derivedKey = new Uint8Array(n), k;
16100       for (j = 1; j <= 19; ++j) {
16101         for (k = 0; k < n; ++k)
16102           derivedKey[k] = encryptionKey[k] ^ j;
16103         cipher = new ARCFourCipher(derivedKey);
16104         checkData = cipher.encryptBlock(checkData);
16105       }
16106       for (j = 0, n = checkData.length; j < n; ++j) {
16107         if (userPassword[j] != checkData[j])
16108           return null;
16109       }
16110     } else {
16111       cipher = new ARCFourCipher(encryptionKey);
16112       checkData = cipher.encryptBlock(defaultPasswordBytes);
16113       for (j = 0, n = checkData.length; j < n; ++j) {
16114         if (userPassword[j] != checkData[j])
16115           return null;
16116       }
16117     }
16118     return encryptionKey;
16119   }
16120   function decodeUserPassword(password, ownerPassword, revision, keyLength) {
16121     var hashData = new Uint8Array(32), i = 0, j, n;
16122     n = Math.min(32, password.length);
16123     for (; i < n; ++i)
16124       hashData[i] = password[i];
16125     j = 0;
16126     while (i < 32) {
16127       hashData[i++] = defaultPasswordBytes[j++];
16128     }
16129     var hash = calculateMD5(hashData, 0, i);
16130     var keyLengthInBytes = keyLength >> 3;
16131     if (revision >= 3) {
16132       for (j = 0; j < 50; ++j) {
16133          hash = calculateMD5(hash, 0, hash.length);
16134       }
16135     }
16136 
16137     var cipher, userPassword;
16138     if (revision >= 3) {
16139       userPassword = ownerPassword;
16140       var derivedKey = new Uint8Array(keyLengthInBytes), k;
16141       for (j = 19; j >= 0; j--) {
16142         for (k = 0; k < keyLengthInBytes; ++k)
16143           derivedKey[k] = hash[k] ^ j;
16144         cipher = new ARCFourCipher(derivedKey);
16145         userPassword = cipher.encryptBlock(userPassword);
16146       }
16147     } else {
16148       cipher = new ARCFourCipher(hash.subarray(0, keyLengthInBytes));
16149       userPassword = cipher.encryptBlock(ownerPassword);
16150     }
16151     return userPassword;
16152   }
16153 
16154   var identityName = new Name('Identity');
16155 
16156   function CipherTransformFactory(dict, fileId, password) {
16157     var filter = dict.get('Filter');
16158     if (!isName(filter) || filter.name != 'Standard')
16159       error('unknown encryption method');
16160     this.dict = dict;
16161     var algorithm = dict.get('V');
16162     if (!isInt(algorithm) ||
16163       (algorithm != 1 && algorithm != 2 && algorithm != 4))
16164       error('unsupported encryption algorithm');
16165     this.algorithm = algorithm;
16166     var keyLength = dict.get('Length') || 40;
16167     if (!isInt(keyLength) ||
16168       keyLength < 40 || (keyLength % 8) !== 0)
16169       error('invalid key length');
16170     // prepare keys
16171     var ownerPassword = stringToBytes(dict.get('O'));
16172     var userPassword = stringToBytes(dict.get('U'));
16173     var flags = dict.get('P');
16174     var revision = dict.get('R');
16175     var encryptMetadata = algorithm == 4 &&  // meaningful when V is 4
16176       dict.get('EncryptMetadata') !== false; // makes true as default value
16177     this.encryptMetadata = encryptMetadata;
16178 
16179     var fileIdBytes = stringToBytes(fileId);
16180     var passwordBytes;
16181     if (password)
16182       passwordBytes = stringToBytes(password);
16183 
16184     var encryptionKey = prepareKeyData(fileIdBytes, passwordBytes,
16185                                        ownerPassword, userPassword, flags,
16186                                        revision, keyLength, encryptMetadata);
16187     if (!encryptionKey && !password) {
16188       throw new PasswordException('No password given',
16189                                   PasswordResponses.NEED_PASSWORD);
16190     } else if (!encryptionKey && password) {
16191       // Attempting use the password as an owner password
16192       var decodedPassword = decodeUserPassword(passwordBytes, ownerPassword,
16193                                                revision, keyLength);
16194       encryptionKey = prepareKeyData(fileIdBytes, decodedPassword,
16195                                      ownerPassword, userPassword, flags,
16196                                      revision, keyLength, encryptMetadata);
16197     }
16198 
16199     if (!encryptionKey)
16200       throw new PasswordException('Incorrect Password',
16201                                   PasswordResponses.INCORRECT_PASSWORD);
16202 
16203     this.encryptionKey = encryptionKey;
16204 
16205     if (algorithm == 4) {
16206       this.cf = dict.get('CF');
16207       this.stmf = dict.get('StmF') || identityName;
16208       this.strf = dict.get('StrF') || identityName;
16209       this.eff = dict.get('EFF') || this.strf;
16210     }
16211   }
16212 
16213   function buildObjectKey(num, gen, encryptionKey, isAes) {
16214     var key = new Uint8Array(encryptionKey.length + 9), i, n;
16215     for (i = 0, n = encryptionKey.length; i < n; ++i)
16216       key[i] = encryptionKey[i];
16217     key[i++] = num & 0xFF;
16218     key[i++] = (num >> 8) & 0xFF;
16219     key[i++] = (num >> 16) & 0xFF;
16220     key[i++] = gen & 0xFF;
16221     key[i++] = (gen >> 8) & 0xFF;
16222     if (isAes) {
16223       key[i++] = 0x73;
16224       key[i++] = 0x41;
16225       key[i++] = 0x6C;
16226       key[i++] = 0x54;
16227     }
16228     var hash = calculateMD5(key, 0, i);
16229     return hash.subarray(0, Math.min(encryptionKey.length + 5, 16));
16230   }
16231 
16232   function buildCipherConstructor(cf, name, num, gen, key) {
16233     var cryptFilter = cf.get(name.name);
16234     var cfm;
16235     if (cryptFilter !== null && cryptFilter !== undefined)
16236       cfm = cryptFilter.get('CFM');
16237     if (!cfm || cfm.name == 'None') {
16238       return function cipherTransformFactoryBuildCipherConstructorNone() {
16239         return new NullCipher();
16240       };
16241     }
16242     if ('V2' == cfm.name) {
16243       return function cipherTransformFactoryBuildCipherConstructorV2() {
16244         return new ARCFourCipher(
16245           buildObjectKey(num, gen, key, false));
16246       };
16247     }
16248     if ('AESV2' == cfm.name) {
16249       return function cipherTransformFactoryBuildCipherConstructorAESV2() {
16250         return new AES128Cipher(
16251           buildObjectKey(num, gen, key, true));
16252       };
16253     }
16254     error('Unknown crypto method');
16255   }
16256 
16257   CipherTransformFactory.prototype = {
16258     createCipherTransform:
16259       function CipherTransformFactory_createCipherTransform(num, gen) {
16260       if (this.algorithm == 4) {
16261         return new CipherTransform(
16262           buildCipherConstructor(this.cf, this.stmf,
16263             num, gen, this.encryptionKey),
16264           buildCipherConstructor(this.cf, this.strf,
16265             num, gen, this.encryptionKey));
16266       }
16267       // algorithms 1 and 2
16268       var key = buildObjectKey(num, gen, this.encryptionKey, false);
16269       var cipherConstructor = function buildCipherCipherConstructor() {
16270         return new ARCFourCipher(key);
16271       };
16272       return new CipherTransform(cipherConstructor, cipherConstructor);
16273     }
16274   };
16275 
16276   return CipherTransformFactory;
16277 })();

16370     RG: { fnName: 'setStrokeRGBColor', numArgs: 3, variableArgs: false },
16371     rg: { fnName: 'setFillRGBColor', numArgs: 3, variableArgs: false },
16372     K: { fnName: 'setStrokeCMYKColor', numArgs: 4, variableArgs: false },
16373     k: { fnName: 'setFillCMYKColor', numArgs: 4, variableArgs: false },
16374 
16375     // Shading
16376     sh: { fnName: 'shadingFill', numArgs: 1, variableArgs: false },
16377 
16378     // Images
16379     BI: { fnName: 'beginInlineImage', numArgs: 0, variableArgs: false },
16380     ID: { fnName: 'beginImageData', numArgs: 0, variableArgs: false },
16381     EI: { fnName: 'endInlineImage', numArgs: 1, variableArgs: false },
16382 
16383     // XObjects
16384     Do: { fnName: 'paintXObject', numArgs: 1, variableArgs: false },
16385     MP: { fnName: 'markPoint', numArgs: 1, variableArgs: false },
16386     DP: { fnName: 'markPointProps', numArgs: 2, variableArgs: false },
16387     BMC: { fnName: 'beginMarkedContent', numArgs: 1, variableArgs: false },
16388     BDC: { fnName: 'beginMarkedContentProps', numArgs: 2, variableArgs: false },
16389     EMC: { fnName: 'endMarkedContent', numArgs: 0, variableArgs: false },
16390 
16391     // Compatibility
16392     BX: { fnName: 'beginCompat', numArgs: 0, variableArgs: false },
16393     EX: { fnName: 'endCompat', numArgs: 0, variableArgs: false },
16394 
16395     // (reserved partial commands for the lexer)
16396     BM: null,
16397     BD: null,
16398     'true': null,
16399     fa: null,
16400     fal: null,
16401     fals: null,
16402     'false': null,
16403     nu: null,
16404     nul: null,
16405     'null': null
16406   };
16407 
16408   var TILING_PATTERN = 1, SHADING_PATTERN = 2;
16409 
16410   function createOperatorList(fnArray, argsArray, dependencies) {
16411     return {
16412       queue: {
16413         fnArray: fnArray || [],
16414         argsArray: argsArray || []
16415       },
16416       dependencies: dependencies || {}
16417     };
16418   }
16419 
16420   PartialEvaluator.prototype = {
16421 
16422     buildFormXObject: function PartialEvaluator_buildFormXObject(resources,
16423                                                                  xobj, smask) {
16424       var self = this;
16425       var promise = new Promise();
16426       var fnArray = [];
16427       var argsArray = [];
16428 
16429       var matrix = xobj.dict.get('Matrix');
16430       var bbox = xobj.dict.get('BBox');
16431       var group = xobj.dict.get('Group');
16432       if (group) {
16433         var groupOptions = {
16434           matrix: matrix,
16435           bbox: bbox,
16436           smask: !!smask,
16437           isolated: false,
16438           knockout: false
16439         };
16440 
16441         var groupSubtype = group.get('S');
16442         if (isName(groupSubtype) && groupSubtype.name === 'Transparency') {
16443           groupOptions.isolated = group.get('I') || false;
16444           groupOptions.knockout = group.get('K') || false;
16445           // There is also a group colorspace, but since we put everything in
16446           // RGB I'm not sure we need it.
16447         }
16448         fnArray.push('beginGroup');
16449         argsArray.push([groupOptions]);
16450       }
16451 
16452       fnArray.push('paintFormXObjectBegin');
16453       argsArray.push([matrix, bbox]);
16454 
16455       // Pass in the current `queue` object. That means the `fnArray`
16456       // and the `argsArray` in this scope is reused and new commands
16457       // are added to them.
16458       var opListPromise = this.getOperatorList(xobj,
16459           xobj.dict.get('Resources') || resources);
16460       opListPromise.then(function(data) {
16461         var queue = data.queue;
16462         var dependencies = data.dependencies;
16463         Util.prependToArray(queue.fnArray, fnArray);
16464         Util.prependToArray(queue.argsArray, argsArray);
16465         self.insertDependencies(queue, dependencies);
16466 
16467         queue.fnArray.push('paintFormXObjectEnd');
16468         queue.argsArray.push([]);
16469 
16470         if (group) {
16471           queue.fnArray.push('endGroup');
16472           queue.argsArray.push([groupOptions]);
16473         }
16474 
16475         promise.resolve({
16476           queue: queue,
16477           dependencies: dependencies
16478         });
16479       });
16480 
16481       return promise;
16482     },
16483 
16484     buildPaintImageXObject: function PartialEvaluator_buildPaintImageXObject(
16485                                 resources, image, inline) {
16486       var self = this;
16487       var dict = image.dict;
16488       var w = dict.get('Width', 'W');
16489       var h = dict.get('Height', 'H');
16490 
16491       if (PDFJS.maxImageSize !== -1 && w * h > PDFJS.maxImageSize) {
16492         warn('Image exceeded maximum allowed size and was removed.');
16493         return null;
16494       }
16495 
16496       var dependencies = {};
16497       var retData = {
16498         dependencies: dependencies
16499       };
16500 
16501       var imageMask = dict.get('ImageMask', 'IM') || false;
16502       if (imageMask) {
16503         // This depends on a tmpCanvas beeing filled with the
16504         // current fillStyle, such that processing the pixel
16505         // data can't be done here. Instead of creating a
16506         // complete PDFImage, only read the information needed
16507         // for later.
16508 
16509         var width = dict.get('Width', 'W');
16510         var height = dict.get('Height', 'H');
16511         var bitStrideLength = (width + 7) >> 3;
16512         var imgArray = image.getBytes(bitStrideLength * height);
16513         var decode = dict.get('Decode', 'D');
16514         var inverseDecode = !!decode && decode[0] > 0;
16515 
16516         retData.fn = 'paintImageMaskXObject';
16517         retData.args = [PDFImage.createMask(imgArray, width, height,
16518                                             inverseDecode)];
16519         return retData;
16520       }
16521 
16522       var softMask = dict.get('SMask', 'SM') || false;
16523       var mask = dict.get('Mask') || false;
16524 
16525       var SMALL_IMAGE_DIMENSIONS = 200;
16526       // Inlining small images into the queue as RGB data
16527       if (inline && !softMask && !mask &&
16528           !(image instanceof JpegStream) &&
16529           (w + h) < SMALL_IMAGE_DIMENSIONS) {
16530         var imageObj = new PDFImage(this.xref, resources, image,
16531                                     inline, null, null);
16532         var imgData = imageObj.getImageData();
16533         retData.fn = 'paintInlineImageXObject';
16534         retData.args = [imgData];
16535         return retData;
16536       }
16537 
16538       // If there is no imageMask, create the PDFImage and a lot
16539       // of image processing can be done here.
16540       var uniquePrefix = this.uniquePrefix || '';
16541       var objId = 'img_' + uniquePrefix + (++this.idCounters.obj);
16542       dependencies[objId] = true;
16543       retData.args = [objId, w, h];
16544 
16545       if (!softMask && !mask && image instanceof JpegStream &&
16546           image.isNativelySupported(this.xref, resources)) {
16547         // These JPEGs don't need any more processing so we can just send it.
16548         retData.fn = 'paintJpegXObject';
16549         this.handler.send(
16550             'obj', [objId, this.pageIndex, 'JpegStream', image.getIR()]);
16551         return retData;
16552       }
16553 
16554       retData.fn = 'paintImageXObject';
16555 
16556       PDFImage.buildImage(function(imageObj) {
16557           var imgData = imageObj.getImageData();
16558           self.handler.send('obj', [objId, self.pageIndex, 'Image', imgData]);
16559         }, self.handler, self.xref, resources, image, inline);
16560 
16561       return retData;
16562     },
16563 
16564     handleTilingType: function PartialEvaluator_handleTilingType(
16565                           fn, args, resources, pattern, patternDict) {
16566       var self = this;
16567       // Create an IR of the pattern code.
16568       var promise = new Promise();
16569       var opListPromise = this.getOperatorList(pattern,
16570           patternDict.get('Resources') || resources);
16571       opListPromise.then(function(data) {
16572         var opListData = createOperatorList([], [], data.dependencies);
16573         var queue = opListData.queue;
16574 
16575         // Add the dependencies that are required to execute the
16576         // operatorList.
16577         self.insertDependencies(queue, data.dependencies);
16578         queue.fnArray.push(fn);
16579         queue.argsArray.push(
16580           TilingPattern.getIR(data.queue, patternDict, args));
16581         promise.resolve(opListData);
16582       });
16583 
16584       return promise;
16585     },
16586 
16587     handleSetFont: function PartialEvaluator_handleSetFont(
16588                       resources, fontArgs, font) {
16589 
16590       var promise = new Promise();
16591       // TODO(mack): Not needed?
16592       var fontName;
16593       if (fontArgs) {
16594         fontArgs = fontArgs.slice();
16595         fontName = fontArgs[0].name;
16596       }
16597       var self = this;
16598       var fontPromise = this.loadFont(fontName, font, this.xref, resources);
16599       fontPromise.then(function(data) {
16600         var font = data.font;
16601         var loadedName = font.loadedName;
16602         if (!font.sent) {
16603           var fontData = font.translated.exportData();
16604 
16605           self.handler.send('commonobj', [
16606             loadedName,
16607             'Font',
16608             fontData
16609           ]);
16610           font.sent = true;
16611         }
16612 
16613         // Ensure the font is ready before the font is set
16614         // and later on used for drawing.
16615         // OPTIMIZE: This should get insert to the operatorList only once per
16616         // page.
16617         var fnArray = [];
16618         var argsArray = [];
16619         var queue = {
16620           fnArray: fnArray,
16621           argsArray: argsArray
16622         };
16623         var dependencies = data.dependencies;
16624         dependencies[loadedName] = true;
16625         self.insertDependencies(queue, dependencies);
16626         if (fontArgs) {
16627           fontArgs[0] = loadedName;
16628           fnArray.push('setFont');
16629           argsArray.push(fontArgs);
16630         }
16631         promise.resolve({
16632           loadedName: loadedName,
16633           queue: queue,
16634           dependencies: dependencies
16635         });
16636       });
16637       return promise;
16638     },
16639 
16640     insertDependencies: function PartialEvaluator_insertDependencies(
16641                             queue, dependencies) {
16642 
16643       var fnArray = queue.fnArray;
16644       var argsArray = queue.argsArray;
16645       var depList = Object.keys(dependencies);
16646       if (depList.length) {
16647         fnArray.push('dependency');
16648         argsArray.push(depList);
16649       }
16650     },
16651 
16652     setGState: function PartialEvaluator_setGState(resources, gState) {
16653 
16654       var self = this;
16655       var opListData = createOperatorList();
16656       var queue = opListData.queue;
16657       var fnArray = queue.fnArray;
16658       var argsArray = queue.argsArray;
16659       var dependencies = opListData.dependencies;
16660 
16661       // TODO(mack): This should be rewritten so that this function returns
16662       // what should be added to the queue during each iteration
16663       function setGStateForKey(gStateObj, key, value) {
16664         switch (key) {
16665           case 'Type':
16666             break;
16667           case 'LW':
16668           case 'LC':
16669           case 'LJ':
16670           case 'ML':
16671           case 'D':
16672           case 'RI':
16673           case 'FL':
16674           case 'CA':
16675           case 'ca':
16676             gStateObj.push([key, value]);
16677             break;
16678           case 'Font':
16679             var promise = new Promise();
16680             self.handleSetFont(resources, null, value[0]).then(function(data) {
16681               var gState = ['Font', data.loadedName, value[1]];
16682               promise.resolve({
16683                 gState: gState,
16684                 queue: data.queue,
16685                 dependencies: data.dependencies
16686               });
16687             });
16688             gStateObj.push(['promise', promise]);
16689             break;
16690           case 'BM':
16691             if (!isName(value) || value.name !== 'Normal') {
16692               queue.transparency = true;
16693             }
16694             gStateObj.push([key, value]);
16695             break;
16696           case 'SMask':
16697             // We support the default so don't trigger the TODO.
16698             if (!isName(value) || value.name != 'None')
16699               TODO('graphic state operator ' + key);
16700             break;
16701           // Only generate info log messages for the following since
16702           // they are unlikey to have a big impact on the rendering.
16703           case 'OP':
16704           case 'op':
16705           case 'OPM':
16706           case 'BG':
16707           case 'BG2':
16708           case 'UCR':
16709           case 'UCR2':
16710           case 'TR':
16711           case 'TR2':
16712           case 'HT':
16713           case 'SM':
16714           case 'SA':
16715           case 'AIS':
16716           case 'TK':
16717             // TODO implement these operators.
16718             info('graphic state operator ' + key);
16719             break;
16720           default:
16721             info('Unknown graphic state operator ' + key);
16722             break;
16723         }
16724       }
16725 
16726       // This array holds the converted/processed state data.
16727       var gStateObj = [];
16728       var gStateMap = gState.map;
16729       for (var key in gStateMap) {
16730         var value = gStateMap[key];
16731         setGStateForKey(gStateObj, key, value);
16732       }
16733 
16734       var promises = [];
16735       var indices = [];
16736       for (var i = 0, n = gStateObj.length; i < n; ++i) {
16737         var value = gStateObj[i];
16738         if (value[0] === 'promise') {
16739           promises.push(value[1]);
16740           indices.push(i);
16741         }
16742       }
16743 
16744       var promise = new Promise();
16745       Promise.all(promises).then(function(datas) {
16746         for (var i = 0, n = datas.length; i < n; ++i) {
16747           var data = datas[i];
16748           var index = indices[i];
16749           gStateObj[index] = data.gState;
16750           var subQueue = data.queue;
16751           Util.concatenateToArray(fnArray, subQueue.fnArray);
16752           Util.concatenateToArray(argsArray, subQueue.argsArray);
16753           queue.transparency = subQueue.transparency || queue.transparency;
16754           Util.extendObj(dependencies, data.dependencies);
16755         }
16756         fnArray.push('setGState');
16757         argsArray.push([gStateObj]);
16758         promise.resolve(opListData);
16759       });
16760 
16761       return promise;
16762     },
16763 
16764     loadFont: function PartialEvaluator_loadFont(fontName, font, xref,
16765                                                  resources) {
16766       function errorFont(promise) {
16767         promise.resolve({
16768           font: {
16769             translated: new ErrorFont('Font ' + fontName + ' is not available'),
16770             loadedName: 'g_font_error'
16771           },
16772           dependencies: {}
16773         });
16774         return promise;
16775       }
16776 
16777       var fontRef;
16778       if (font) { // Loading by ref.
16779         assert(isRef(font));
16780         fontRef = font;
16781       } else { // Loading by name.
16782         var fontRes = resources.get('Font');
16783         if (fontRes) {
16784           fontRef = fontRes.getRaw(fontName);
16785         } else {
16786           warn('fontRes not available');
16787           return errorFont(new Promise());
16788         }
16789       }
16790       if (this.fontCache.has(fontRef)) {
16791         return this.fontCache.get(fontRef);
16792       }
16793 
16794       var promise = new Promise();
16795       this.fontCache.put(fontRef, promise);
16796 
16797       font = xref.fetchIfRef(fontRef);
16798       if (!isDict(font)) {
16799         return errorFont(promise);
16800       }
16801 
16802       // keep track of each font we translated so the caller can
16803       // load them asynchronously before calling display on a page
16804       font.loadedName = 'g_font_' + fontRef.num + '_' + fontRef.gen;
16805 
16806       if (!font.translated) {
16807         var translated;
16808         try {
16809           translated = this.translateFont(font, xref);
16810         } catch (e) {
16811           translated = new ErrorFont(e instanceof Error ? e.message : e);
16812         }
16813         font.translated = translated;
16814       }
16815 
16816       if (font.translated.loadCharProcs) {
16817         var charProcs = font.get('CharProcs').getAll();
16818         var fontResources = font.get('Resources') || resources;
16819         var opListPromises = [];
16820         var charProcKeys = Object.keys(charProcs);
16821         for (var i = 0, n = charProcKeys.length; i < n; ++i) {
16822           var key = charProcKeys[i];
16823           var glyphStream = charProcs[key];
16824           opListPromises.push(
16825             this.getOperatorList(glyphStream, fontResources));
16826         }
16827         Promise.all(opListPromises).then(function(datas) {
16828           var charProcOperatorList = {};
16829           var dependencies = {};
16830           for (var i = 0, n = charProcKeys.length; i < n; ++i) {
16831             var key = charProcKeys[i];
16832             var data = datas[i];
16833             charProcOperatorList[key] = data.queue;
16834             Util.extendObj(dependencies, data.dependencies);
16835           }
16836           font.translated.charProcOperatorList = charProcOperatorList;
16837           font.loaded = true;
16838           promise.resolve({
16839             font: font,
16840             dependencies: dependencies
16841           });
16842         }.bind(this));
16843       } else {
16844         font.loaded = true;
16845         promise.resolve({
16846           font: font,
16847           dependencies: {}
16848         });
16849       }
16850       return promise;
16851     },
16852 
16853     getOperatorList: function PartialEvaluator_getOperatorList(stream,
16854                                                                resources) {
16855 
16856       var self = this;
16857       var xref = this.xref;
16858       var handler = this.handler;
16859 
16860       var fnArray = [];
16861       var argsArray = [];
16862       var queue = {
16863         transparency: false,
16864         fnArray: fnArray,
16865         argsArray: argsArray
16866       };
16867       var dependencies = {};
16868 
16869       resources = resources || new Dict();
16870       var xobjs = resources.get('XObject') || new Dict();
16871       var patterns = resources.get('Pattern') || new Dict();
16872       // TODO(mduan): pass array of knownCommands rather than OP_MAP
16873       // dictionary
16874       var parser = new Parser(new Lexer(stream, OP_MAP), false, xref);
16875 
16876       var promise = new Promise();
16877       var args = [];
16878       while (true) {
16879 
16880         var obj = parser.getObj();
16881 
16882         if (isEOF(obj)) {
16883           break;
16884         }
16885 
16886         if (isCmd(obj)) {
16887           var cmd = obj.cmd;
16888 
16889           // Check that the command is valid
16890           var opSpec = OP_MAP[cmd];
16891           if (!opSpec) {
16892             warn('Unknown command "' + cmd + '"');
16893             continue;
16894           }
16895 
16896           var fn = opSpec.fnName;
16897 
16898           // Validate the number of arguments for the command
16899           if (opSpec.variableArgs) {
16900             if (args.length > opSpec.numArgs) {
16901               info('Command ' + fn + ': expected [0,' + opSpec.numArgs +
16902                   '] args, but received ' + args.length + ' args');
16903             }
16904           } else {
16905             if (args.length < opSpec.numArgs) {
16906               // If we receive too few args, it's not possible to possible
16907               // to execute the command, so skip the command
16908               info('Command ' + fn + ': because expected ' +
16909                    opSpec.numArgs + ' args, but received ' + args.length +
16910                    ' args; skipping');
16911               args = [];
16912               continue;
16913             } else if (args.length > opSpec.numArgs) {
16914               info('Command ' + fn + ': expected ' + opSpec.numArgs +
16915                   ' args, but received ' + args.length + ' args');
16916             }
16917           }
16918 
16919           // TODO figure out how to type-check vararg functions
16920 
16921           if ((cmd == 'SCN' || cmd == 'scn') &&
16922                !args[args.length - 1].code) {
16923             // compile tiling patterns
16924             var patternName = args[args.length - 1];
16925             // SCN/scn applies patterns along with normal colors
16926             var pattern;
16927             if (isName(patternName) &&
16928                 (pattern = patterns.get(patternName.name))) {
16929 
16930               var dict = isStream(pattern) ? pattern.dict : pattern;
16931               var typeNum = dict.get('PatternType');
16932 
16933               if (typeNum == TILING_PATTERN) {
16934                 var patternPromise = self.handleTilingType(
16935                     fn, args, resources, pattern, dict);
16936                 fn = 'promise';
16937                 args = [patternPromise];
16938               } else if (typeNum == SHADING_PATTERN) {
16939                 var shading = dict.get('Shading');
16940                 var matrix = dict.get('Matrix');
16941                 var pattern = Pattern.parseShading(shading, matrix, xref,
16942                                                     resources);
16943                 args = pattern.getIR();
16944               } else {
16945                 error('Unkown PatternType ' + typeNum);
16946               }
16947             }
16948           } else if (cmd == 'Do' && !args[0].code) {
16949             // eagerly compile XForm objects
16950             var name = args[0].name;
16951             var xobj = xobjs.get(name);
16952             if (xobj) {
16953               assertWellFormed(
16954                   isStream(xobj), 'XObject should be a stream');
16955 
16956               var type = xobj.dict.get('Subtype');
16957               assertWellFormed(
16958                 isName(type),
16959                 'XObject should have a Name subtype'
16960               );
16961 
16962               if ('Form' == type.name) {
16963                 fn = 'promise';
16964                 args = [self.buildFormXObject(resources, xobj)];
16965               } else if ('Image' == type.name) {
16966                 var data = self.buildPaintImageXObject(
16967                     resources, xobj, false);
16968                 if (!data) {
16969                   args = [];
16970                   continue;
16971                 }
16972                 Util.extendObj(dependencies, data.dependencies);
16973                 self.insertDependencies(queue, data.dependencies);
16974                 fn = data.fn;
16975                 args = data.args;
16976               } else {
16977                 error('Unhandled XObject subtype ' + type.name);
16978               }
16979             }
16980           } else if (cmd == 'Tf') { // eagerly collect all fonts
16981             fn = 'promise';
16982             args = [self.handleSetFont(resources, args)];
16983           } else if (cmd == 'EI') {
16984             var data = self.buildPaintImageXObject(
16985                 resources, args[0], true);
16986             if (!data) {
16987               args = [];
16988               continue;
16989             }
16990             Util.extendObj(dependencies, data.dependencies);
16991             self.insertDependencies(queue, data.dependencies);
16992             fn = data.fn;
16993             args = data.args;
16994           }
16995 
16996           switch (fn) {
16997             // Parse the ColorSpace data to a raw format.
16998             case 'setFillColorSpace':
16999             case 'setStrokeColorSpace':
17000               args = [ColorSpace.parseToIR(args[0], xref, resources)];
17001               break;
17002             case 'shadingFill':
17003               var shadingRes = resources.get('Shading');
17004               if (!shadingRes)
17005                 error('No shading resource found');
17006 
17007               var shading = shadingRes.get(args[0].name);
17008               if (!shading)
17009                 error('No shading object found');
17010 
17011               var shadingFill = Pattern.parseShading(
17012                   shading, null, xref, resources);
17013               var patternIR = shadingFill.getIR();
17014               args = [patternIR];
17015               fn = 'shadingFill';
17016               break;
17017             case 'setGState':
17018               var dictName = args[0];
17019               var extGState = resources.get('ExtGState');
17020 
17021               if (!isDict(extGState) || !extGState.has(dictName.name))
17022                 break;
17023 
17024               var gState = extGState.get(dictName.name);
17025               fn = 'promise';
17026               args = [self.setGState(resources, gState)];
17027           } // switch
17028 
17029           fnArray.push(fn);
17030           argsArray.push(args);
17031           args = [];
17032           parser.saveState();
17033         } else if (obj !== null && obj !== undefined) {
17034           args.push(obj instanceof Dict ? obj.getAll() : obj);
17035           assertWellFormed(args.length <= 33, 'Too many arguments');
17036         }
17037       }
17038 
17039       var subQueuePromises = [];
17040       for (var i = 0; i < fnArray.length; ++i) {
17041         if (fnArray[i] === 'promise') {
17042           subQueuePromises.push(argsArray[i][0]);
17043         }
17044       }
17045       Promise.all(subQueuePromises).then(function(datas) {
17046         // TODO(mack): Optimize by using repositioning elements
17047         // in original queue rather than creating new queue
17048 
17049         for (var i = 0, n = datas.length; i < n; ++i) {
17050           var data = datas[i];
17051           var subQueue = data.queue;
17052           queue.transparency = subQueue.transparency || queue.transparency;
17053           Util.extendObj(dependencies, data.dependencies);
17054         }
17055 
17056         var newFnArray = [];
17057         var newArgsArray = [];
17058         var currOffset = 0;
17059         var subQueueIdx = 0;
17060         for (var i = 0, n = fnArray.length; i < n; ++i) {
17061           var offset = i + currOffset;
17062           if (fnArray[i] === 'promise') {
17063             var data = datas[subQueueIdx++];
17064             var subQueue = data.queue;
17065             var subQueueFnArray = subQueue.fnArray;
17066             var subQueueArgsArray = subQueue.argsArray;
17067             for (var j = 0, nn = subQueueFnArray.length; j < nn; ++j) {
17068               newFnArray[offset + j] = subQueueFnArray[j];
17069               newArgsArray[offset + j] = subQueueArgsArray[j];
17070             }
17071             currOffset += subQueueFnArray.length - 1;
17072           } else {
17073             newFnArray[offset] = fnArray[i];
17074             newArgsArray[offset] = argsArray[i];
17075           }
17076         }
17077 
17078         promise.resolve({
17079           queue: {
17080             fnArray: newFnArray,
17081             argsArray: newArgsArray,
17082             transparency: queue.transparency
17083           },
17084           dependencies: dependencies
17085         });
17086       });
17087 
17088       return promise;
17089     },
17090 
17091     getTextContent: function PartialEvaluator_getTextContent(
17092                                                     stream, resources) {
17093 
17094       var SPACE_FACTOR = 0.35;
17095       var MULTI_SPACE_FACTOR = 1.5;
17096       var self = this;
17097 
17098       var statePromise = new Promise();
17099 
17100       function handleSetFont(fontName, fontRef, resources) {
17101         var promise = new Promise();
17102         self.loadFont(fontName, fontRef, self.xref, resources).then(
17103           function(data) {
17104             promise.resolve(data.font.translated);
17105           }
17106         );
17107         return promise;
17108       }
17109 
17110       function getBidiText(str, startLevel, vertical) {
17111         if (str) {
17112           return PDFJS.bidi(str, -1, vertical);
17113         }
17114       }
17115 
17116       resources = this.xref.fetchIfRef(resources) || new Dict();
17117       // The xobj is parsed iff it's needed, e.g. if there is a `DO` cmd.
17118       var xobjs = null;
17119 
17120       var parser = new Parser(new Lexer(stream), false);
17121 
17122       var chunkPromises = [];
17123       var fontPromise;
17124       var args = [];
17125 
17126       while (true) {
17127         var obj = parser.getObj();
17128         if (isEOF(obj)) {
17129           break;
17130         }
17131 
17132         if (isCmd(obj)) {
17133           var cmd = obj.cmd;
17134           switch (cmd) {
17135             // TODO: Add support for SAVE/RESTORE and XFORM here.
17136             case 'Tf':
17137               fontPromise = handleSetFont(args[0].name, null, resources);
17138               //.translated;
17139               break;
17140             case 'TJ':
17141               var chunkPromise = new Promise();
17142               chunkPromises.push(chunkPromise);
17143               fontPromise.then(function(items, chunkPromise, font) {
17144                 var chunk = '';
17145                 for (var j = 0, jj = items.length; j < jj; j++) {
17146                   if (typeof items[j] === 'string') {
17147                     chunk += fontCharsToUnicode(items[j], font);
17148                   } else if (items[j] < 0 && font.spaceWidth > 0) {
17149                     var fakeSpaces = -items[j] / font.spaceWidth;
17150                     if (fakeSpaces > MULTI_SPACE_FACTOR) {
17151                       fakeSpaces = Math.round(fakeSpaces);
17152                       while (fakeSpaces--) {
17153                         chunk += ' ';
17154                       }
17155                     } else if (fakeSpaces > SPACE_FACTOR) {
17156                       chunk += ' ';
17157                     }
17158                   }
17159                 }
17160                 chunkPromise.resolve(
17161                     getBidiText(chunk, -1, font.vertical));
17162               }.bind(null, args[0], chunkPromise));
17163               break;
17164             case 'Tj':
17165               var chunkPromise = new Promise();
17166               chunkPromises.push(chunkPromise);
17167               fontPromise.then(function(charCodes, chunkPromise, font) {
17168                 var chunk = fontCharsToUnicode(charCodes, font);
17169                 chunkPromise.resolve(
17170                     getBidiText(chunk, -1, font.vertical));
17171               }.bind(null, args[0], chunkPromise));
17172               break;
17173             case '\'':
17174               // For search, adding a extra white space for line breaks
17175               // would be better here, but that causes too much spaces in
17176               // the text-selection divs.
17177               var chunkPromise = new Promise();
17178               chunkPromises.push(chunkPromise);
17179               fontPromise.then(function(charCodes, chunkPromise, font) {
17180                 var chunk = fontCharsToUnicode(charCodes, font);
17181                 chunkPromise.resolve(
17182                     getBidiText(chunk, -1, font.vertical));
17183               }.bind(null, args[0], chunkPromise));
17184               break;
17185             case '"':
17186               // Note comment in "'"
17187               var chunkPromise = new Promise();
17188               chunkPromises.push(chunkPromise);
17189               fontPromise.then(function(charCodes, chunkPromise, font) {
17190                 var chunk = fontCharsToUnicode(charCodes, font);
17191                 chunkPromise.resolve(
17192                     getBidiText(chunk, -1, font.vertical));
17193               }.bind(null, args[2], chunkPromise));
17194               break;
17195             case 'Do':
17196               if (args[0].code) {
17197                 break;
17198               }
17199 
17200               if (!xobjs) {
17201                 xobjs = resources.get('XObject') || new Dict();
17202               }
17203 
17204               var name = args[0].name;
17205               var xobj = xobjs.get(name);
17206               if (!xobj)
17207                 break;
17208               assertWellFormed(isStream(xobj),
17209                                'XObject should be a stream');
17210 
17211               var type = xobj.dict.get('Subtype');
17212               assertWellFormed(
17213                 isName(type),
17214                 'XObject should have a Name subtype'
17215               );
17216 
17217               if ('Form' !== type.name)
17218                 break;
17219 
17220               var chunkPromise = self.getTextContent(
17221                 xobj,
17222                 xobj.dict.get('Resources') || resources
17223               );
17224               chunkPromises.push(chunkPromise);
17225               break;
17226             case 'gs':
17227               var dictName = args[0];
17228               var extGState = resources.get('ExtGState');
17229 
17230               if (!isDict(extGState) || !extGState.has(dictName.name))
17231                 break;
17232 
17233               var gsState = extGState.get(dictName.name);
17234 
17235               for (var i = 0; i < gsState.length; i++) {
17236                 if (gsState[i] === 'Font') {
17237                   fontPromise = handleSetFont(
17238                       args[0].name, null, resources);
17239                 }
17240               }
17241               break;
17242           } // switch
17243 
17244           args = [];
17245           parser.saveState();
17246         } else if (obj !== null && obj !== undefined) {
17247           assertWellFormed(args.length <= 33, 'Too many arguments');
17248           args.push(obj);
17249         }
17250       } // while
17251 
17252       Promise.all(chunkPromises).then(function(datas) {
17253         var bidiTexts = [];
17254         for (var i = 0, n = datas.length; i < n; ++i) {
17255           var bidiText = datas[i];
17256           if (!bidiText) {
17257             continue;
17258           } else if (isArray(bidiText)) {
17259             Util.concatenateToArray(bidiTexts, bidiText);
17260           } else {
17261             bidiTexts.push(bidiText);
17262           }
17263         }
17264         statePromise.resolve(bidiTexts);
17265       });
17266 
17267       return statePromise;
17268     },
17269 
17270     extractDataStructures: function
17271       partialEvaluatorExtractDataStructures(dict, baseDict,
17272                                             xref, properties) {
17273       // 9.10.2
17274       var toUnicode = dict.get('ToUnicode') ||
17275         baseDict.get('ToUnicode');
17276       if (toUnicode)
17277         properties.toUnicode = this.readToUnicode(toUnicode, xref, properties);
17278 
17279       if (properties.composite) {
17280         // CIDSystemInfo helps to match CID to glyphs
17281         var cidSystemInfo = dict.get('CIDSystemInfo');
17282         if (isDict(cidSystemInfo)) {
17283           properties.cidSystemInfo = {
17284             registry: cidSystemInfo.get('Registry'),
17285             ordering: cidSystemInfo.get('Ordering'),
17286             supplement: cidSystemInfo.get('Supplement')
17287           };
17288         }
17289 
17290         var cidToGidMap = dict.get('CIDToGIDMap');
17291         if (isStream(cidToGidMap))
17292           properties.cidToGidMap = this.readCidToGidMap(cidToGidMap);
17293       }
17294 
17295       // Based on 9.6.6 of the spec the encoding can come from multiple places
17296       // but should be prioritized in the following order:
17297       // 1. Encoding dictionary
17298       // 2. Encoding within font file (Type1 or Type1C)
17299       // 3. Default (depends on font type)
17300       // Differences applied to the above.
17301       // Note: we don't fill in the encoding from the font file(2) here but use
17302       // the flag overridableEncoding to signal that the font can override the
17303       // encoding if it has one built in.
17304       var overridableEncoding = true;
17305       var hasEncoding = false;
17306       var flags = properties.flags;
17307       var differences = [];
17308       var baseEncoding = properties.type === 'TrueType' ?
17309                           Encodings.WinAnsiEncoding :
17310                           Encodings.StandardEncoding;
17311       // The Symbolic attribute can be misused for regular fonts
17312       // Heuristic: we have to check if the font is a standard one also
17313       if (!!(flags & FontFlags.Symbolic)) {
17314         baseEncoding = !properties.file ? Encodings.symbolsEncoding :
17315                                           Encodings.MacRomanEncoding;
17316       }
17317       if (dict.has('Encoding')) {
17318         var encoding = dict.get('Encoding');
17319         if (isDict(encoding)) {
17320           var baseName = encoding.get('BaseEncoding');
17321           if (baseName) {
17322             overridableEncoding = false;
17323             hasEncoding = true;
17324             baseEncoding = Encodings[baseName.name];
17325           }
17326 
17327           // Load the differences between the base and original
17328           if (encoding.has('Differences')) {
17329             hasEncoding = true;
17330             var diffEncoding = encoding.get('Differences');
17331             var index = 0;
17332             for (var j = 0, jj = diffEncoding.length; j < jj; j++) {
17333               var data = diffEncoding[j];
17334               if (isNum(data))
17335                 index = data;
17336               else
17337                 differences[index++] = data.name;
17338             }
17339           }
17340         } else if (isName(encoding)) {
17341           overridableEncoding = false;
17342           hasEncoding = true;
17343           baseEncoding = Encodings[encoding.name];
17344         } else {
17345           error('Encoding is not a Name nor a Dict');
17346         }
17347       }
17348 
17349       properties.differences = differences;
17350       properties.baseEncoding = baseEncoding;
17351       properties.hasEncoding = hasEncoding;
17352       properties.overridableEncoding = overridableEncoding;
17353     },
17354 
17355     readToUnicode: function PartialEvaluator_readToUnicode(toUnicode, xref,
17356                                                            properties) {
17357       var cmapObj = toUnicode;
17358       var charToUnicode = [];
17359       if (isName(cmapObj)) {
17360         var isIdentityMap = cmapObj.name.substr(0, 9) == 'Identity-';
17361         if (!isIdentityMap)
17362           error('ToUnicode file cmap translation not implemented');
17363       } else if (isStream(cmapObj)) {
17364         var tokens = [];
17365         var token = '';
17366         var beginArrayToken = {};
17367 
17368         var cmap = cmapObj.getBytes(cmapObj.length);
17369         for (var i = 0, ii = cmap.length; i < ii; i++) {
17370           var octet = cmap[i];
17371           if (octet == 0x20 || octet == 0x0D || octet == 0x0A ||
17372               octet == 0x3C || octet == 0x5B || octet == 0x5D) {
17373             switch (token) {
17374               case 'usecmap':
17375                 error('usecmap is not implemented');
17376                 break;
17377 
17378               case 'beginbfchar':
17379               case 'beginbfrange':
17380               case 'begincidchar':
17381               case 'begincidrange':
17382                 token = '';
17383                 tokens = [];
17384                 break;
17385 
17386               case 'endcidrange':
17387               case 'endbfrange':
17388                 for (var j = 0, jj = tokens.length; j < jj; j += 3) {
17389                   var startRange = tokens[j];
17390                   var endRange = tokens[j + 1];
17391                   var code = tokens[j + 2];
17392                   if (code == 0xFFFF) {
17393                     // CMap is broken, assuming code == startRange
17394                     code = startRange;
17395                   }
17396                   if (isArray(code)) {
17397                     var codeindex = 0;
17398                     while (startRange <= endRange) {
17399                       charToUnicode[startRange] = code[codeindex++];
17400                       ++startRange;
17401                     }
17402                   } else {
17403                     while (startRange <= endRange) {
17404                       charToUnicode[startRange] = code++;
17405                       ++startRange;
17406                     }
17407                   }
17408                 }
17409                 break;
17410 
17411               case 'endcidchar':
17412               case 'endbfchar':
17413                 for (var j = 0, jj = tokens.length; j < jj; j += 2) {
17414                   var index = tokens[j];
17415                   var code = tokens[j + 1];
17416                   charToUnicode[index] = code;
17417                 }
17418                 break;
17419 
17420               case '':
17421                 break;
17422 
17423               default:
17424                 if (token[0] >= '0' && token[0] <= '9')
17425                   token = parseInt(token, 10); // a number
17426                 tokens.push(token);
17427                 token = '';
17428             }
17429             switch (octet) {
17430               case 0x5B:
17431                 // begin list parsing
17432                 tokens.push(beginArrayToken);
17433                 break;
17434               case 0x5D:
17435                 // collect array items
17436                 var items = [], item;
17437                 while (tokens.length &&
17438                        (item = tokens.pop()) != beginArrayToken)
17439                   items.unshift(item);
17440                 tokens.push(items);
17441                 break;
17442             }
17443           } else if (octet == 0x3E) {
17444             if (token.length) {
17445               // Heuristic: guessing chars size by checking numbers sizes
17446               // in the CMap entries.
17447               if (token.length == 2 && properties.composite)
17448                 properties.wideChars = false;
17449 
17450               if (token.length <= 4) {
17451                 // parsing hex number
17452                 tokens.push(parseInt(token, 16));
17453                 token = '';
17454               } else {
17455                 // parsing hex UTF-16BE numbers
17456                 var str = [];
17457                 for (var k = 0, kk = token.length; k < kk; k += 4) {
17458                   var b = parseInt(token.substr(k, 4), 16);
17459                   if (b <= 0x10) {
17460                     k += 4;
17461                     b = (b << 16) | parseInt(token.substr(k, 4), 16);
17462                     b -= 0x10000;
17463                     str.push(0xD800 | (b >> 10));
17464                     str.push(0xDC00 | (b & 0x3FF));
17465                     break;
17466                   }
17467                   str.push(b);
17468                 }
17469                 tokens.push(String.fromCharCode.apply(String, str));
17470                 token = '';
17471               }
17472             }
17473           } else {
17474             token += String.fromCharCode(octet);
17475           }
17476         }
17477       }
17478       return charToUnicode;
17479     },
17480     readCidToGidMap: function PartialEvaluator_readCidToGidMap(cidToGidStream) {
17481       // Extract the encoding from the CIDToGIDMap
17482       var glyphsData = cidToGidStream.getBytes();
17483 
17484       // Set encoding 0 to later verify the font has an encoding
17485       var result = [];
17486       for (var j = 0, jj = glyphsData.length; j < jj; j++) {
17487         var glyphID = (glyphsData[j++] << 8) | glyphsData[j];
17488         if (glyphID === 0)
17489           continue;
17490 
17491         var code = j >> 1;
17492         result[code] = glyphID;
17493       }
17494       return result;
17495     },
17496 
17497     extractWidths: function PartialEvaluator_extractWidths(dict,
17498                                                    xref,
17499                                                    descriptor,
17500                                                    properties) {
17501       var glyphsWidths = [];
17502       var defaultWidth = 0;
17503       var glyphsVMetrics = [];
17504       var defaultVMetrics;
17505       if (properties.composite) {
17506         defaultWidth = dict.get('DW') || 1000;
17507 
17508         var widths = dict.get('W');
17509         if (widths) {
17510           for (var i = 0, ii = widths.length; i < ii; i++) {
17511             var start = widths[i++];
17512             var code = xref.fetchIfRef(widths[i]);
17513             if (isArray(code)) {
17514               for (var j = 0, jj = code.length; j < jj; j++)
17515                 glyphsWidths[start++] = code[j];
17516             } else {
17517               var width = widths[++i];
17518               for (var j = start; j <= code; j++)
17519                 glyphsWidths[j] = width;
17520             }
17521           }
17522         }
17523 
17524         if (properties.vertical) {
17525           var vmetrics = dict.get('DW2') || [880, -1000];
17526           defaultVMetrics = [vmetrics[1], defaultWidth * 0.5, vmetrics[0]];
17527           vmetrics = dict.get('W2');
17528           if (vmetrics) {
17529             for (var i = 0, ii = vmetrics.length; i < ii; i++) {
17530               var start = vmetrics[i++];
17531               var code = xref.fetchIfRef(vmetrics[i]);
17532               if (isArray(code)) {
17533                 for (var j = 0, jj = code.length; j < jj; j++)
17534                   glyphsVMetrics[start++] = [code[j++], code[j++], code[j]];
17535               } else {
17536                 var vmetric = [vmetrics[++i], vmetrics[++i], vmetrics[++i]];
17537                 for (var j = start; j <= code; j++)
17538                   glyphsVMetrics[j] = vmetric;
17539               }
17540             }
17541           }
17542         }
17543       } else {
17544         var firstChar = properties.firstChar;
17545         var widths = dict.get('Widths');
17546         if (widths) {
17547           var j = firstChar;
17548           for (var i = 0, ii = widths.length; i < ii; i++)
17549             glyphsWidths[j++] = widths[i];
17550           defaultWidth = parseFloat(descriptor.get('MissingWidth')) || 0;
17551         } else {
17552           // Trying get the BaseFont metrics (see comment above).
17553           var baseFontName = dict.get('BaseFont');
17554           if (isName(baseFontName)) {
17555             var metrics = this.getBaseFontMetrics(baseFontName.name);
17556 
17557             glyphsWidths = metrics.widths;
17558             defaultWidth = metrics.defaultWidth;
17559           }
17560         }
17561       }
17562 
17563       // Heuristic: detection of monospace font by checking all non-zero widths
17564       var isMonospace = true, firstWidth = defaultWidth;
17565       for (var glyph in glyphsWidths) {
17566         var glyphWidth = glyphsWidths[glyph];
17567         if (!glyphWidth)
17568           continue;
17569         if (!firstWidth) {
17570           firstWidth = glyphWidth;
17571           continue;
17572         }
17573         if (firstWidth != glyphWidth) {
17574           isMonospace = false;
17575           break;
17576         }
17577       }
17578       if (isMonospace)
17579         properties.flags |= FontFlags.FixedPitch;
17580 
17581       properties.defaultWidth = defaultWidth;
17582       properties.widths = glyphsWidths;
17583       properties.defaultVMetrics = defaultVMetrics;
17584       properties.vmetrics = glyphsVMetrics;
17585     },
17586 
17587     isSerifFont: function PartialEvaluator_isSerifFont(baseFontName) {
17588 
17589       // Simulating descriptor flags attribute
17590       var fontNameWoStyle = baseFontName.split('-')[0];
17591       return (fontNameWoStyle in serifFonts) ||
17592           (fontNameWoStyle.search(/serif/gi) !== -1);
17593     },
17594 
17595     getBaseFontMetrics: function PartialEvaluator_getBaseFontMetrics(name) {
17596       var defaultWidth = 0, widths = [], monospace = false;
17597 
17598       var lookupName = stdFontMap[name] || name;
17599 
17600       if (!(lookupName in Metrics)) {
17601         // Use default fonts for looking up font metrics if the passed
17602         // font is not a base font
17603         if (this.isSerifFont(name)) {
17604           lookupName = 'Times-Roman';
17605         } else {
17606           lookupName = 'Helvetica';
17607         }
17608       }
17609       var glyphWidths = Metrics[lookupName];
17610 
17611       if (isNum(glyphWidths)) {
17612         defaultWidth = glyphWidths;
17613         monospace = true;
17614       } else {
17615         widths = glyphWidths;
17616       }
17617 
17618       return {
17619         defaultWidth: defaultWidth,
17620         monospace: monospace,
17621         widths: widths
17622       };
17623     },
17624 
17625     translateFont: function PartialEvaluator_translateFont(dict,
17626                                                            xref) {
17627       var baseDict = dict;
17628       var type = dict.get('Subtype');
17629       assertWellFormed(isName(type), 'invalid font Subtype');
17630 
17631       var composite = false;
17632       if (type.name == 'Type0') {
17633         // If font is a composite
17634         //  - get the descendant font
17635         //  - set the type according to the descendant font
17636         //  - get the FontDescriptor from the descendant font
17637         var df = dict.get('DescendantFonts');
17638         if (!df)
17639           error('Descendant fonts are not specified');
17640 
17641         dict = isArray(df) ? xref.fetchIfRef(df[0]) : df;
17642 
17643         type = dict.get('Subtype');
17644         assertWellFormed(isName(type), 'invalid font Subtype');
17645         composite = true;
17646       }
17647       var maxCharIndex = composite ? 0xFFFF : 0xFF;
17648 
17649       var descriptor = dict.get('FontDescriptor');
17650       if (!descriptor) {
17651         if (type.name == 'Type3') {
17652           // FontDescriptor is only required for Type3 fonts when the document
17653           // is a tagged pdf. Create a barbebones one to get by.
17654           descriptor = new Dict();
17655           descriptor.set('FontName', new Name(type.name));
17656         } else {
17657           // Before PDF 1.5 if the font was one of the base 14 fonts, having a
17658           // FontDescriptor was not required.
17659           // This case is here for compatibility.
17660           var baseFontName = dict.get('BaseFont');
17661           if (!isName(baseFontName))
17662             error('Base font is not specified');
17663 
17664           // Using base font name as a font name.
17665           baseFontName = baseFontName.name.replace(/[,_]/g, '-');
17666           var metrics = this.getBaseFontMetrics(baseFontName);
17667 
17668           // Simulating descriptor flags attribute
17669           var fontNameWoStyle = baseFontName.split('-')[0];
17670           var flags = (
17671             this.isSerifFont(fontNameWoStyle) ? FontFlags.Serif : 0) |
17672             (metrics.monospace ? FontFlags.FixedPitch : 0) |
17673             (symbolsFonts[fontNameWoStyle] ? FontFlags.Symbolic :
17674             FontFlags.Nonsymbolic);
17675 
17676           var properties = {
17677             type: type.name,
17678             widths: metrics.widths,
17679             defaultWidth: metrics.defaultWidth,
17680             flags: flags,
17681             firstChar: 0,
17682             lastChar: maxCharIndex
17683           };
17684           this.extractDataStructures(dict, dict, xref, properties);
17685 
17686           return new Font(baseFontName, null, properties);
17687         }
17688       }
17689 
17690       // According to the spec if 'FontDescriptor' is declared, 'FirstChar',
17691       // 'LastChar' and 'Widths' should exist too, but some PDF encoders seem
17692       // to ignore this rule when a variant of a standart font is used.
17693       // TODO Fill the width array depending on which of the base font this is
17694       // a variant.
17695       var firstChar = dict.get('FirstChar') || 0;
17696       var lastChar = dict.get('LastChar') || maxCharIndex;
17697 
17698       var fontName = descriptor.get('FontName');
17699       var baseFont = dict.get('BaseFont');
17700       // Some bad pdf's have a string as the font name.
17701       if (isString(fontName)) {
17702         fontName = new Name(fontName);
17703       }
17704       if (isString(baseFont)) {
17705         baseFont = new Name(baseFont);
17706       }
17707 
17708       if (type.name !== 'Type3') {
17709         var fontNameStr = fontName && fontName.name;
17710         var baseFontStr = baseFont && baseFont.name;
17711         if (fontNameStr !== baseFontStr) {
17712           info('The FontDescriptor\'s FontName is "' + fontNameStr +
17713                '" but should be the same as the Font\'s BaseFont "' +
17714                baseFontStr + '"');
17715         }
17716       }
17717       fontName = fontName || baseFont;
17718 
17719       assertWellFormed(isName(fontName), 'invalid font name');
17720 
17721       var fontFile = descriptor.get('FontFile', 'FontFile2', 'FontFile3');
17722       if (fontFile) {
17723         if (fontFile.dict) {
17724           var subtype = fontFile.dict.get('Subtype');
17725           if (subtype)
17726             subtype = subtype.name;
17727 
17728           var length1 = fontFile.dict.get('Length1');
17729 
17730           var length2 = fontFile.dict.get('Length2');
17731         }
17732       }
17733 
17734       var properties = {
17735         type: type.name,
17736         subtype: subtype,
17737         file: fontFile,
17738         length1: length1,
17739         length2: length2,
17740         loadedName: baseDict.loadedName,
17741         composite: composite,
17742         wideChars: composite,
17743         fixedPitch: false,
17744         fontMatrix: dict.get('FontMatrix') || FONT_IDENTITY_MATRIX,
17745         firstChar: firstChar || 0,
17746         lastChar: lastChar || maxCharIndex,
17747         bbox: descriptor.get('FontBBox'),
17748         ascent: descriptor.get('Ascent'),
17749         descent: descriptor.get('Descent'),
17750         xHeight: descriptor.get('XHeight'),
17751         capHeight: descriptor.get('CapHeight'),
17752         flags: descriptor.get('Flags'),
17753         italicAngle: descriptor.get('ItalicAngle'),
17754         coded: false
17755       };
17756 
17757       if (composite) {
17758         var cidEncoding = baseDict.get('Encoding');
17759         if (isName(cidEncoding)) {
17760           properties.cidEncoding = cidEncoding.name;
17761           properties.vertical = /-V$/.test(cidEncoding.name);
17762         }
17763       }
17764       this.extractWidths(dict, xref, descriptor, properties);
17765       this.extractDataStructures(dict, baseDict, xref, properties);
17766 
17767       if (type.name === 'Type3') {
17768         properties.coded = true;
17769       }
17770 
17771       return new Font(fontName.name, fontFile, properties);
17772     }
17773   };
17774 
17775   PartialEvaluator.optimizeQueue =
17776       function PartialEvaluator_optimizeQueue(queue) {
17777 
17778     var fnArray = queue.fnArray, argsArray = queue.argsArray;
17779     // grouping paintInlineImageXObject's into paintInlineImageXObjectGroup
17780     // searching for (save, transform, paintInlineImageXObject, restore)+
17781     var MIN_IMAGES_IN_INLINE_IMAGES_BLOCK = 10;
17782     var MAX_IMAGES_IN_INLINE_IMAGES_BLOCK = 200;
17783     var MAX_WIDTH = 1000;
17784     var IMAGE_PADDING = 1;
17785     for (var i = 0, ii = fnArray.length; i < ii; i++) {
17786       if (fnArray[i] === 'paintInlineImageXObject' &&
17787           fnArray[i - 2] === 'save' && fnArray[i - 1] === 'transform' &&
17788           fnArray[i + 1] === 'restore') {
17789         var j = i - 2;
17790         for (i += 2; i < ii && fnArray[i - 4] === fnArray[i]; i++) {
17791         }
17792         var count = Math.min((i - j) >> 2,
17793                              MAX_IMAGES_IN_INLINE_IMAGES_BLOCK);
17794         if (count < MIN_IMAGES_IN_INLINE_IMAGES_BLOCK) {
17795           continue;
17796         }
17797         // assuming that heights of those image is too small (~1 pixel)
17798         // packing as much as possible by lines
17799         var maxX = 0;
17800         var map = [], maxLineHeight = 0;
17801         var currentX = IMAGE_PADDING, currentY = IMAGE_PADDING;
17802         for (var q = 0; q < count; q++) {
17803           var transform = argsArray[j + (q << 2) + 1];
17804           var img = argsArray[j + (q << 2) + 2][0];
17805           if (currentX + img.width > MAX_WIDTH) {
17806             // starting new line
17807             maxX = Math.max(maxX, currentX);
17808             currentY += maxLineHeight + 2 * IMAGE_PADDING;
17809             currentX = 0;
17810             maxLineHeight = 0;
17811           }
17812           map.push({
17813             transform: transform,
17814             x: currentX, y: currentY,
17815             w: img.width, h: img.height
17816           });
17817           currentX += img.width + 2 * IMAGE_PADDING;
17818           maxLineHeight = Math.max(maxLineHeight, img.height);
17819         }
17820         var imgWidth = Math.max(maxX, currentX) + IMAGE_PADDING;
17821         var imgHeight = currentY + maxLineHeight + IMAGE_PADDING;
17822         var imgData = new Uint8Array(imgWidth * imgHeight * 4);
17823         var imgRowSize = imgWidth << 2;
17824         for (var q = 0; q < count; q++) {
17825           var data = argsArray[j + (q << 2) + 2][0].data;
17826           // copy image by lines and extends pixels into padding
17827           var rowSize = map[q].w << 2;
17828           var dataOffset = 0;
17829           var offset = (map[q].x + map[q].y * imgWidth) << 2;
17830           imgData.set(
17831             data.subarray(0, rowSize), offset - imgRowSize);
17832           for (var k = 0, kk = map[q].h; k < kk; k++) {
17833             imgData.set(
17834               data.subarray(dataOffset, dataOffset + rowSize), offset);
17835             dataOffset += rowSize;
17836             offset += imgRowSize;
17837           }
17838           imgData.set(
17839             data.subarray(dataOffset - rowSize, dataOffset), offset);
17840           while (offset >= 0) {
17841             data[offset - 4] = data[offset];
17842             data[offset - 3] = data[offset + 1];
17843             data[offset - 2] = data[offset + 2];
17844             data[offset - 1] = data[offset + 3];
17845             data[offset + rowSize] = data[offset + rowSize - 4];
17846             data[offset + rowSize + 1] = data[offset + rowSize - 3];
17847             data[offset + rowSize + 2] = data[offset + rowSize - 2];
17848             data[offset + rowSize + 3] = data[offset + rowSize - 1];
17849             offset -= imgRowSize;
17850           }
17851         }
17852         // replacing queue items
17853         fnArray.splice(j, count * 4, ['paintInlineImageXObjectGroup']);
17854         argsArray.splice(j, count * 4,
17855           [{width: imgWidth, height: imgHeight, data: imgData}, map]);
17856         i = j;
17857         ii = fnArray.length;
17858       }
17859     }
17860     // grouping paintImageMaskXObject's into paintImageMaskXObjectGroup
17861     // searching for (save, transform, paintImageMaskXObject, restore)+
17862     var MIN_IMAGES_IN_MASKS_BLOCK = 10;
17863     var MAX_IMAGES_IN_MASKS_BLOCK = 100;
17864     for (var i = 0, ii = fnArray.length; i < ii; i++) {
17865       if (fnArray[i] === 'paintImageMaskXObject' &&
17866           fnArray[i - 2] === 'save' && fnArray[i - 1] === 'transform' &&
17867           fnArray[i + 1] === 'restore') {
17868         var j = i - 2;
17869         for (i += 2; i < ii && fnArray[i - 4] === fnArray[i]; i++) {
17870         }
17871         var count = Math.min((i - j) >> 2,
17872                              MAX_IMAGES_IN_MASKS_BLOCK);
17873         if (count < MIN_IMAGES_IN_MASKS_BLOCK) {
17874           continue;
17875         }
17876         var images = [];
17877         for (var q = 0; q < count; q++) {
17878           var transform = argsArray[j + (q << 2) + 1];
17879           var maskParams = argsArray[j + (q << 2) + 2][0];
17880           images.push({data: maskParams.data, width: maskParams.width,
17881             height: maskParams.height, transform: transform});
17882         }
17883         // replacing queue items
17884         fnArray.splice(j, count * 4, ['paintImageMaskXObjectGroup']);
17885         argsArray.splice(j, count * 4, [images]);
17886         i = j;
17887         ii = fnArray.length;
17888       }
17889     }
17890   };
17891 
17892 
17893   return PartialEvaluator;
17894 })();
17895 
17896 var EvalState = (function EvalStateClosure() {
17897   function EvalState() {
17898     // Are soft masks and alpha values shapes or opacities?
17899     this.alphaIsShape = false;
17900     this.fontSize = 0;
17901     this.textMatrix = IDENTITY_MATRIX;
17902     this.leading = 0;
17903     // Start of text line (in text coordinates)
17904     this.lineX = 0;
17905     this.lineY = 0;
17906     // Character and word spacing
17907     this.charSpacing = 0;
17908     this.wordSpacing = 0;
17909     this.textHScale = 1;
17910     // Color spaces
17911     this.fillColorSpace = null;
17912     this.strokeColorSpace = null;
17913   }
17914   EvalState.prototype = {
17915   };
17916   return EvalState;
17917 })();

18358 var decodeBytes;
18359 if (typeof TextDecoder !== 'undefined') {
18360   // The encodings supported by TextDecoder can be found at:
18361   // http://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/#concept-encoding-get
18362   decodeBytes = function(bytes, encoding, fatal) {
18363     return new TextDecoder(encoding, {fatal: !!fatal}).decode(bytes);
18364   };
18365 } else if (typeof FileReaderSync !== 'undefined') {
18366   decodeBytes = function(bytes, encoding) {
18367     return new FileReaderSync().readAsText(new Blob([bytes]), encoding);
18368   };
18369 } else {
18370   // Clear the list so that decodeBytes will never be called.
18371   CMapConverterList = {};
18372 }
18373 
18374 function jis7ToUnicode(str) {
18375   var bytes = stringToBytes(str);
18376   var length = bytes.length;
18377   for (var i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
18378     bytes[i] |= 0x80;
18379   }
18380   return decodeBytes(bytes, 'euc-jp');
18381 }
18382 
18383 function eucjpToUnicode(str) {
18384   return decodeBytes(stringToBytes(str), 'euc-jp');
18385 }
18386 
18387 function sjisToUnicode(str) {
18388   return decodeBytes(stringToBytes(str), 'shift_jis');
18389 }
18390 
18391 function sjis83pvToUnicode(str) {
18392   var bytes = stringToBytes(str);
18393   try {
18394     // TODO: 83pv has incompatible mappings in ed40..ee9c range.
18395     return decodeBytes(bytes, 'shift_jis', true);
18396   } catch (e) {
18397     TODO('Unsupported 83pv character found');
18398     // Just retry without checking errors for now.
18399     return decodeBytes(bytes, 'shift_jis');
18400   }
18401 }
18402 
18403 function sjis90pvToUnicode(str) {
18404   var bytes = stringToBytes(str);
18405   try {
18406     // TODO: 90pv has incompatible mappings in 8740..879c and eb41..ee9c.
18407     return decodeBytes(bytes, 'shift_jis', true);
18408   } catch (e) {
18409     TODO('Unsupported 90pv character found');
18410     // Just retry without checking errors for now.
18411     return decodeBytes(bytes, 'shift_jis');
18412   }
18413 }
18414 
18415 function gbkToUnicode(str) {
18416   return decodeBytes(stringToBytes(str), 'gbk');
18417 }
18418 
18419 function big5ToUnicode(str) {
18420   return decodeBytes(stringToBytes(str), 'big5');
18421 }
