21926       } else {
21927         this.useToFontChar = true;
21928         // Most of the following logic in this code branch is based on the
21929         // 9.6.6.4 of the PDF spec.
21930 
21931         // TODO(mack):
21932         // We are using this.hasEncoding to mean that the encoding is either
21933         // MacRomanEncoding or WinAnsiEncoding (following spec in 9.6.6.4),
21934         // but this.hasEncoding is currently true for any encodings on the
21935         // Encodings object (e.g. MacExpertEncoding). So should consider using
21936         // better check for this.
21937         var cmapTable = readCmapTable(tables.cmap, font, this.hasEncoding,
21938             this.isSymbolicFont);
21939 
21940         // TODO(mack): If the (3, 0) cmap table used, then the font is
21941         // symbolic. The range of charcodes in the cmap table should be
21942         // one of the following:
21943         //   -> 0x0000 - 0x00FF
21944         //   -> 0xF000 - 0xF0FF
21945         //   -> 0xF100 - 0xF1FF
21946         //   -> 0xF200 - 0xF2FF
21947         // If it is not, we should change not consider this a symbolic font
21948         this.isSymbolicFont = cmapTable.isSymbolicFont;
21949 
21950         var cmapPlatformId = cmapTable.platformId;
21951         var cmapEncodingId = cmapTable.encodingId;
21952         var cmapMappings = cmapTable.mappings;
21953         var cmapMappingsLength = cmapMappings.length;
21954         var glyphs = [];
21955         var ids = [];
21956         for (var i = 0; i < cmapMappingsLength; ++i) {
21957           var cmapMapping = cmapMappings[i];
21958           var charcode = cmapMapping.charcode;
21959           var unicode = cmapCharcodeToUnicode(charcode, this.isSymbolicFont,
21960               cmapPlatformId, cmapEncodingId);
21961 
21962           if (!unicode) {
21963             // TODO(mack): gotta check if skipping mappings where we cannot find
21964             // a unicode is the correct behaviour
21965             continue;
21966           }
21967           glyphs.push({
21968             code: charcode,
21969             unicode: unicode
21970           });
21971           ids.push(cmapMapping.glyphId);
21972         }
21973 
21974         var hasShortCmap = cmapTable.hasShortCmap;
21975         var toFontChar = this.toFontChar;
21976 
21977         if (hasShortCmap && ids.length == numGlyphs) {
21978           // Fixes the short cmap tables -- some generators use incorrect
21979           // glyph id.
21980           for (var i = 0, ii = ids.length; i < ii; i++) {
21981             ids[i] = i;
21982           }
21983         }
21984 
21985         // Rewrite the whole toFontChar dictionary with a new one using the
21986         // information from the mappings in the cmap table.
21987         var newToFontChar = [];
21988         if (this.isSymbolicFont) {
21989           for (var i = 0, ii = glyphs.length; i < ii; i++) {
21990             var glyph = glyphs[i];
21991             // For (3, 0) cmap tables:
21992             // The charcode key being stored in toFontChar is the lower byte
21993             // of the two-byte charcodes of the cmap table since according to
21994             // the spec: 'each byte from the string shall be prepended with the
21995             // high byte of the range [of charcodes in the cmap table], to form
21996             // a two-byte character, which shall be used to select the
21997             // associated glyph description from the subtable'.
21998             //
21999             // For (1, 0) cmap tables:
22000             // 'single bytes from the string shall be used to look up the
22001             // associated glyph descriptions from the subtable'. This means
22002             // charcodes in the cmap will be single bytes, so no-op since
22003             // glyph.code & 0xFF === glyph.code
22004             newToFontChar[glyph.code & 0xFF] = glyph.unicode;
22005           }
22006         } else {
22007 
22008           var encoding = properties.baseEncoding;
22009           var differences = properties.differences;
22010 
22011           // TODO(mack): check if it is necessary to shift control characters
22012           // for non-symbolic fonts so that browsers dont't render them using
22013           // space characters
22014 
22015           var glyphCodeMapping = cmapTable.glyphCodeMapping;
22016           for (var charcode = 0; charcode < encoding.length; ++charcode) {
22017             if (!encoding.hasOwnProperty(charcode)) {
22018               continue;
22019             }
22020 
22021             // Since the cmap table that we will be writing out is a (3, 1)
22022             // unicode table, in this section we will rewrites the charcodes
22023             // in the pdf into unicodes
22024 
22025             var glyphName = encoding[charcode];
22026             // A nonsymbolic font should not have a Differences array, but
22027             // if it does have one, we should still use it
22028             if (charcode in differences) {
22029               glyphName = differences[charcode];
22030             }
22031 
22032             // Finally, any undefined entries in the table shall be filled
22033             // using StandardEncoding
22034             if (!glyphName) {
22035               glyphName = Encodings.StandardEncoding[charcode];
22036             }
22037 
22038             // TODO(mack): Handle the case that the glyph name cannot be
22039             // mapped as specified, in which case the glyph name shall be
22040             // looked up in the font program's 'post' table (if one is
22041             // present) and the associated glyph id shall be used.
22042             //
22043             // For now, we're just using the '.notdef' glyph name in this
22044             // case.
22045             glyphName = glyphName || '.notdef';
22046 
22047             var unicode = GlyphsUnicode[glyphName];
22048             newToFontChar[charcode] = unicode;
22049           }
22050         }
22051         this.toFontChar = toFontChar = newToFontChar;
22052 
22053         createGlyphNameMap(glyphs, ids, properties);
22054         this.glyphNameMap = properties.glyphNameMap;
22055       }
22056 
22057       if (glyphs.length === 0) {
22058         // defines at least one glyph
22059         glyphs.push({ unicode: 0xF000, code: 0xF000, glyph: '.notdef' });
22060         ids.push(0);
22061       }
22062 
22063       // Converting glyphs and ids into font's cmap table
22064       tables.cmap.data = createCmapTable(glyphs, ids);
22065       var unicodeIsEnabled = [];
22066       for (var i = 0, ii = glyphs.length; i < ii; i++) {
22067         unicodeIsEnabled[glyphs[i].unicode] = true;
22068       }
22069       this.unicodeIsEnabled = unicodeIsEnabled;
22070 
22071       if (!tables['OS/2'] || !validateOS2Table(tables['OS/2'])) {
22072         // extract some more font properties from the OpenType head and
22073         // hhea tables; yMin and descent value are always negative
22074         var override = {
22075           unitsPerEm: int16([tables.head.data[18], tables.head.data[19]]),
22076           yMax: int16([tables.head.data[42], tables.head.data[43]]),
22077           yMin: int16([tables.head.data[38], tables.head.data[39]]) - 0x10000,
22078           ascent: int16([tables.hhea.data[4], tables.hhea.data[5]]),
22079           descent: int16([tables.hhea.data[6], tables.hhea.data[7]]) - 0x10000
22080         };
22081 
22082         tables['OS/2'] = {
22083           tag: 'OS/2',
22084           data: stringToArray(createOS2Table(properties, glyphs, override))
22085         };
22086       }
22087 
22088       // Rewrite the 'post' table if needed
22089       if (!tables.post) {
22090         tables.post = {
22091           tag: 'post',
22092           data: stringToArray(createPostTable(properties))
22093         };
22094       }
22095 
22096       if (!isTrueType) {
22097         try {
22098           // Trying to repair CFF file
22099           var cffFile = new Stream(tables['CFF '].data);
22100           var parser = new CFFParser(cffFile, properties);
22101           var cff = parser.parse();
22102           var compiler = new CFFCompiler(cff);
22103           tables['CFF '].data = compiler.compile();
22104         } catch (e) {
22105           warn('Failed to compile font ' + properties.loadedName);
22106         }
22107       }
22108 
22109       // Re-creating 'name' table
22110       if (!tables.name) {
22111         tables.name = {
22112           tag: 'name',
22113           data: stringToArray(createNameTable(this.name))
22114         };
22115       } else {
22116         // ... using existing 'name' table as prototype
22117         var namePrototype = readNameTable(tables.name);
22118         tables.name.data = stringToArray(createNameTable(name, namePrototype));
22119       }
22120 
22121       // rewrite the tables but tweak offsets
22122       for (var i = 0; i < numTables; i++) {
22123         var table = tables[tablesNames[i]];
22124         var data = [];
22125 
22126         var tableData = table.data;
22127         for (var j = 0, jj = tableData.length; j < jj; j++)
22128           data.push(tableData[j]);
22129         createTableEntry(ttf, table.tag, data);
22130       }
22131 
22132       // Add the table datas
22133       for (var i = 0; i < numTables; i++) {
22134         var table = tables[tablesNames[i]];
22135         var tableData = table.data;
22136         ttf.file += arrayToString(tableData);
22137 
22138         // 4-byte aligned data
22139         while (ttf.file.length & 3)
22140           ttf.file += String.fromCharCode(0);
22141       }
22142 
22143       return stringToArray(ttf.file);
22144     },
22145 
22146     convert: function Font_convert(fontName, font, properties) {
22147       function isFixedPitch(glyphs) {
22148         for (var i = 0, ii = glyphs.length - 1; i < ii; i++) {
22149           if (glyphs[i] != glyphs[i + 1])
22150             return false;
22151         }
22152         return true;
22153       }
22154 
22155       // The offsets object holds at the same time a representation of where
22156       // to write the table entry information about a table and another offset
22157       // representing the offset where to draw the actual data of a particular
22158       // table
22159       var REQ_TABLES_CNT = 9;
22160 
22161       var otf = {
22162         file: '',
22163         virtualOffset: 9 * (4 * 4)
22164       };
22165 
22166       createOpenTypeHeader('\x4F\x54\x54\x4F', otf, 9);
22167 
22168       var charstrings = font.charstrings;
22169       properties.fixedPitch = isFixedPitch(charstrings);
22170 
22171       var glyphNameMap = {};
22172       for (var i = 0; i < charstrings.length; ++i) {
22173         var charstring = charstrings[i];
22174         glyphNameMap[charstring.glyph] = charstring.unicode;
22175       }
22176       this.glyphNameMap = glyphNameMap;
22177 
22178       var seacs = font.seacs;
22179       if (SEAC_ANALYSIS_ENABLED && seacs) {
22180         var seacMap = [];
22181         var matrix = properties.fontMatrix || FONT_IDENTITY_MATRIX;
22182         for (var i = 0; i < charstrings.length; ++i) {
22183           var charstring = charstrings[i];
22184           var seac = seacs[charstring.gid];
22185           if (!seac) {
22186             continue;
22187           }
22188           var baseGlyphName = Encodings.StandardEncoding[seac[2]];
22189           var baseUnicode = glyphNameMap[baseGlyphName];
22190           var accentGlyphName = Encodings.StandardEncoding[seac[3]];
22191           var accentUnicode = glyphNameMap[accentGlyphName];
22192           if (!baseUnicode || !accentUnicode) {
22193             continue;
22194           }
22195           var accentOffset = {
22196             x: seac[0] * matrix[0] + seac[1] * matrix[2] + matrix[4],
22197             y: seac[0] * matrix[1] + seac[1] * matrix[3] + matrix[5]
22198           };
22199           seacMap[charstring.unicode] = {
22200             baseUnicode: baseUnicode,
22201             accentUnicode: accentUnicode,
22202             accentOffset: accentOffset
22203           };
22204         }
22205         properties.seacMap = seacMap;
22206       }
22207 
22208       if (!properties.hasEncoding && (properties.subtype == 'Type1C' ||
22209           properties.subtype == 'CIDFontType0C')) {
22210         var encoding = [];
22211         for (var i = 0; i < charstrings.length; ++i) {
22212           var charstring = charstrings[i];
22213           encoding[charstring.code] = charstring.glyph;
22214         }
22215         properties.baseEncoding = encoding;
22216       }
22217       if (properties.subtype == 'CIDFontType0C') {
22218         var toFontChar = [];
22219         for (var i = 0; i < charstrings.length; ++i) {
22220           var charstring = charstrings[i];
22221           toFontChar[charstring.code] = charstring.unicode;
22222         }
22223         this.toFontChar = toFontChar;
22224       }
22225       var unitsPerEm = 1 / (properties.fontMatrix || FONT_IDENTITY_MATRIX)[0];
22226 
22227       var fields = {
22228         // PostScript Font Program
22229         'CFF ': font.data,
22230 
22231         // OS/2 and Windows Specific metrics
22232         'OS/2': stringToArray(createOS2Table(properties, charstrings)),
22233 
22234         // Character to glyphs mapping
22235         'cmap': createCmapTable(charstrings.slice(),
22236                                 ('glyphIds' in font) ? font.glyphIds : null),
22237 
22238         // Font header
22239         'head': (function fontFieldsHead() {
22240           return stringToArray(
22241               '\x00\x01\x00\x00' + // Version number
22242               '\x00\x00\x10\x00' + // fontRevision
22243               '\x00\x00\x00\x00' + // checksumAdjustement
22244               '\x5F\x0F\x3C\xF5' + // magicNumber
22245               '\x00\x00' + // Flags
22246               safeString16(unitsPerEm) + // unitsPerEM
22247               '\x00\x00\x00\x00\x9e\x0b\x7e\x27' + // creation date
22248               '\x00\x00\x00\x00\x9e\x0b\x7e\x27' + // modifification date
22249               '\x00\x00' + // xMin
22250               safeString16(properties.descent) + // yMin
22251               '\x0F\xFF' + // xMax
22252               safeString16(properties.ascent) + // yMax
22253               string16(properties.italicAngle ? 2 : 0) + // macStyle
22254               '\x00\x11' + // lowestRecPPEM
22255               '\x00\x00' + // fontDirectionHint
22256               '\x00\x00' + // indexToLocFormat
22257               '\x00\x00');  // glyphDataFormat
22258         })(),
22259 
22260         // Horizontal header
22261         'hhea': (function fontFieldsHhea() {
22262           return stringToArray(
22263               '\x00\x01\x00\x00' + // Version number
22264               safeString16(properties.ascent) + // Typographic Ascent
22265               safeString16(properties.descent) + // Typographic Descent
22266               '\x00\x00' + // Line Gap
22267               '\xFF\xFF' + // advanceWidthMax
22268               '\x00\x00' + // minLeftSidebearing
22269               '\x00\x00' + // minRightSidebearing
22270               '\x00\x00' + // xMaxExtent
22271               safeString16(properties.capHeight) + // caretSlopeRise
22272               safeString16(Math.tan(properties.italicAngle) *
22273                        properties.xHeight) + // caretSlopeRun
22274               '\x00\x00' + // caretOffset
22275               '\x00\x00' + // -reserved-
22276               '\x00\x00' + // -reserved-
22277               '\x00\x00' + // -reserved-
22278               '\x00\x00' + // -reserved-
22279               '\x00\x00' + // metricDataFormat
22280               string16(charstrings.length + 1)); // Number of HMetrics
22281         })(),
22282 
22283         // Horizontal metrics
22284         'hmtx': (function fontFieldsHmtx() {
22285           var hmtx = '\x00\x00\x00\x00'; // Fake .notdef
22286           for (var i = 0, ii = charstrings.length; i < ii; i++) {
22287             var charstring = charstrings[i];
22288             var width = 'width' in charstring ? charstring.width : 0;
22289             hmtx += string16(width) + string16(0);
22290           }
22291           return stringToArray(hmtx);
22292         })(),
22293 
22294         // Maximum profile
22295         'maxp': (function fontFieldsMaxp() {
22296           return stringToArray(
22297               '\x00\x00\x50\x00' + // Version number
22298              string16(charstrings.length + 1)); // Num of glyphs
22299         })(),
22300 
22301         // Naming tables
22302         'name': stringToArray(createNameTable(fontName)),
22303 
22304         // PostScript informations
22305         'post': stringToArray(createPostTable(properties))
22306       };
22307 
22308       for (var field in fields)
22309         createTableEntry(otf, field, fields[field]);
22310 
22311       for (var field in fields) {
22312         var table = fields[field];
22313         otf.file += arrayToString(table);
22314       }
22315 
22316       return stringToArray(otf.file);
22317     },
22318 
22319     buildToFontChar: function Font_buildToFontChar(toUnicode) {
22320       var result = [];
22321       var unusedUnicode = CMAP_GLYPH_OFFSET;
22322       for (var i = 0, ii = toUnicode.length; i < ii; i++) {
22323         var unicode = toUnicode[i];
22324         var fontCharCode = typeof unicode === 'object' ? unusedUnicode++ :
22325           unicode;
22326         if (typeof unicode !== 'undefined')
22327           result[i] = fontCharCode;
22328       }
22329       return result;
22330     },
22331 
22332     rebuildToUnicode: function Font_rebuildToUnicode(properties) {
22333       var firstChar = properties.firstChar, lastChar = properties.lastChar;
22334       var map = [];
22335       var toUnicode = this.toUnicode || this.cidToUnicode;
22336       if (toUnicode) {
22337         var isIdentityMap = toUnicode.length === 0;
22338         for (var i = firstChar, ii = lastChar; i <= ii; i++) {
22339           // TODO missing map the character according font's CMap
22340           map[i] = isIdentityMap ? i : toUnicode[i];
22341         }
22342       } else {
22343         for (var i = firstChar, ii = lastChar; i <= ii; i++) {
22344           var glyph = properties.differences[i];
22345           if (!glyph)
22346             glyph = properties.baseEncoding[i];
22347           if (!!glyph && (glyph in GlyphsUnicode))
22348             map[i] = GlyphsUnicode[glyph];
22349         }
22350       }
22351       this.toUnicode = map;
22352     },
22353 
22354     loadCidToUnicode: function Font_loadCidToUnicode(properties) {
22355       if (!properties.cidSystemInfo)
22356         return;
22357 
22358       var cidToUnicodeMap = [], unicodeToCIDMap = [];
22359       this.cidToUnicode = cidToUnicodeMap;
22360       this.unicodeToCID = unicodeToCIDMap;
22361 
22362       var cidEncoding = properties.cidEncoding;
22363       if (properties.toUnicode) {
22364         if (cidEncoding && cidEncoding.indexOf('Identity-') !== 0) {
22365           TODO('Need to create a reverse mapping from \'ToUnicode\' CMap');
22366         }
22367         return; // 'ToUnicode' CMap will be used
22368       }
22369 
22370       var cidSystemInfo = properties.cidSystemInfo;
22371       var cidToUnicode;
22372       if (cidSystemInfo) {
22373         cidToUnicode = CIDToUnicodeMaps[
22374           cidSystemInfo.registry + '-' + cidSystemInfo.ordering];
22375       }
22376 
22377       if (!cidToUnicode)
22378         return; // identity encoding
22379 
22380       var overwrite = HalfwidthCMaps[cidEncoding];
22381       var cid = 1, i, j, k, ii;
22382       for (i = 0, ii = cidToUnicode.length; i < ii; ++i) {
22383         var unicode = cidToUnicode[i];
22384         if (isArray(unicode)) {
22385           var length = unicode.length;
22386           for (j = 0; j < length; j++) {
22387             cidToUnicodeMap[cid] = k = unicode[j];
22388             if (!unicodeToCIDMap[k] || overwrite) {
22389               unicodeToCIDMap[k] = cid;
22390             }
22391           }
22392           cid++;
22393         } else if (typeof unicode === 'object') {
22394           var fillLength = unicode.f;
22395           if (fillLength) {
22396             k = unicode.c;
22397             for (j = 0; j < fillLength; ++j) {
22398               cidToUnicodeMap[cid] = k;
22399               if (!unicodeToCIDMap[k] || overwrite) {
22400                 unicodeToCIDMap[k] = cid;
22401               }
22402               cid++;
22403               k++;
22404             }
22405           } else
22406             cid += unicode.s;
22407         } else if (unicode) {
22408           cidToUnicodeMap[cid] = unicode;
22409           if (!unicodeToCIDMap[unicode] || overwrite) {
22410             unicodeToCIDMap[unicode] = cid;
22411           }
22412           cid++;
22413         } else
22414           cid++;
22415       }
22416 
22417       if (!cidEncoding) {
22418         return;
22419       }
22420       if (cidEncoding.indexOf('Identity-') !== 0) {
22421         // input is already Unicode for non-Identity CMap encodings.
22422         this.cidToUnicode = [];
22423         // For CIDFontType2, however, we need cid-to-Unicode conversion
22424         // to rebuild cmap.
22425         if (properties.type == 'CIDFontType2') {
22426           this.cidToFontChar = cidToUnicodeMap;
22427         }
22428       } else {
22429         // We don't have to do reverse conversions if the string is
22430         // already CID.
22431         this.unicodeToCID = [];
22432       }
22433     },
22434 
22435     bindDOM: function Font_bindDOM() {
22436       if (!this.data)
22437         return null;
22438 
22439       if (PDFJS.disableFontFace) {
22440         this.disableFontFace = true;
22441         return null;
22442       }
22443 
22444       var data = bytesToString(this.data);
22445       var fontName = this.loadedName;
22446 
22447       // Add the font-face rule to the document
22448       var url = ('url(data:' + this.mimetype + ';base64,' +
22449                  window.btoa(data) + ');');
22450       var rule = '@font-face { font-family:"' + fontName + '";src:' + url + '}';
22451 
22452       var styleElement = document.getElementById('PDFJS_FONT_STYLE_TAG');
22453       if (!styleElement) {
22454           styleElement = document.createElement('style');
22455           styleElement.id = 'PDFJS_FONT_STYLE_TAG';
22456           document.documentElement.getElementsByTagName('head')[0].appendChild(
22457             styleElement);
22458       }
22459 
22460       var styleSheet = styleElement.sheet;
22461       styleSheet.insertRule(rule, styleSheet.cssRules.length);
22462 
22463       if (PDFJS.pdfBug && 'FontInspector' in globalScope &&
22464           globalScope['FontInspector'].enabled)
22465         globalScope['FontInspector'].fontAdded(this, url);
22466 
22467       return rule;
22468     },
22469 
22470     get spaceWidth() {
22471       if ('_shadowWidth' in this) {
22472         return this._shadowWidth;
22473       }
22474 
22475       // trying to estimate space character width
22476       var possibleSpaceReplacements = ['space', 'minus', 'one', 'i'];
22477       var width;
22478       for (var i = 0, ii = possibleSpaceReplacements.length; i < ii; i++) {
22479         var glyphName = possibleSpaceReplacements[i];
22480         // if possible, getting width by glyph name
22481         if (glyphName in this.widths) {
22482           width = this.widths[glyphName];
22483           break;
22484         }
22485         var glyphUnicode = GlyphsUnicode[glyphName];
22486         // finding the charcode via unicodeToCID map
22487         var charcode = 0;
22488         if (this.composite)
22489           charcode = this.unicodeToCID[glyphUnicode];
22490         // ... via toUnicode map
22491         if (!charcode && 'toUnicode' in this)
22492           charcode = this.toUnicode.indexOf(glyphUnicode);
22493         // setting it to unicode if negative or undefined
22494         if (charcode <= 0)
22495           charcode = glyphUnicode;
22496         // trying to get width via charcode
22497         width = this.widths[charcode];
22498         if (width)
22499           break; // the non-zero width found
22500       }
22501       width = width || this.defaultWidth;
22502       // Do not shadow the property here. See discussion:
22503       // https://github.com/mozilla/pdf.js/pull/2127#discussion_r1662280
22504       this._shadowWidth = width;
22505       return width;
22506     },
22507 
22508     charToGlyph: function Font_charToGlyph(charcode) {
22509       var fontCharCode, width, operatorList, disabled;
22510 
22511       var width = this.widths[charcode];
22512       var vmetric = this.vmetrics && this.vmetrics[charcode];
22513 
22514       switch (this.type) {
22515         case 'CIDFontType0':
22516           var cid = this.unicodeToCID[charcode] || charcode;
22517           if (this.unicodeToCID.length > 0) {
22518             width = this.widths[cid];
22519             vmetric = this.vmetrics && this.vmetrics[cid];
22520           }
22521           if (this.noUnicodeAdaptation) {
22522             fontCharCode = this.toFontChar[charcode] || charcode;
22523             break;
22524           }
22525           // CIDFontType0 is not encoded in Unicode.
22526           fontCharCode = this.toFontChar[cid] || cid;
22527           break;
22528         case 'CIDFontType2':
22529           if (this.unicodeToCID.length > 0) {
22530             var cid = this.unicodeToCID[charcode] || charcode;
22531             width = this.widths[cid];
22532             vmetric = this.vmetrics && this.vmetrics[cid];
22533             fontCharCode = charcode;
22534             break;
22535           }
22536           fontCharCode = this.toFontChar[charcode] || charcode;
22537           break;
22538         case 'MMType1': // XXX at the moment only "standard" fonts are supported
22539         case 'Type1':
22540           var glyphName = this.differences[charcode] || this.encoding[charcode];
22541           if (!isNum(width))
22542             width = this.widths[glyphName];
22543           if (this.noUnicodeAdaptation) {
22544             fontCharCode = mapPrivateUseChars(GlyphsUnicode[glyphName] ||
22545               charcode);
22546             break;
22547           }
22548           fontCharCode = this.glyphNameMap[glyphName] ||
22549             GlyphsUnicode[glyphName] || charcode;
22550           break;
22551         case 'Type3':
22552           var glyphName = this.differences[charcode] || this.encoding[charcode];
22553           operatorList = this.charProcOperatorList[glyphName];
22554           fontCharCode = charcode;
22555           break;
22556         case 'TrueType':
22557           if (this.useToFontChar) {
22558             fontCharCode = this.toFontChar[charcode] || charcode;
22559             break;
22560           }
22561           var glyphName = this.differences[charcode] || this.encoding[charcode];
22562           if (!glyphName)
22563             glyphName = Encodings.StandardEncoding[charcode];
22564           if (!isNum(width))
22565             width = this.widths[glyphName];
22566           if (this.noUnicodeAdaptation) {
22567             fontCharCode = GlyphsUnicode[glyphName] || charcode;
22568             break;
22569           }
22570           if (!this.hasEncoding || this.isSymbolicFont) {
22571             fontCharCode = this.useToFontChar ? this.toFontChar[charcode] :
22572               charcode;
22573             break;
22574           }
22575 
22576           // MacRoman encoding address by re-encoding the cmap table
22577 
22578           fontCharCode = glyphName in this.glyphNameMap ?
22579             this.glyphNameMap[glyphName] : GlyphsUnicode[glyphName];
22580           break;
22581         default:
22582           warn('Unsupported font type: ' + this.type);
22583           break;
22584       }
22585 
22586       var unicodeChars = !('toUnicode' in this) ? charcode :
22587         this.toUnicode[charcode] || charcode;
22588       if (typeof unicodeChars === 'number') {
22589         unicodeChars = String.fromCharCode(unicodeChars);
22590       }
22591 
22592       width = isNum(width) ? width : this.defaultWidth;
22593       disabled = this.unicodeIsEnabled ?
22594         !this.unicodeIsEnabled[fontCharCode] : false;
22595 
22596       var accent = null;
22597       if (this.seacMap && this.seacMap[fontCharCode]) {
22598         var seac = this.seacMap[fontCharCode];
22599         fontCharCode = seac.baseUnicode;
22600         accent = {
22601           fontChar: String.fromCharCode(seac.accentUnicode),
22602           offset: seac.accentOffset
22603         };
22604       }
22605 
22606       return {
22607         fontChar: String.fromCharCode(fontCharCode),
22608         unicode: unicodeChars,
22609         accent: accent,
22610         width: width,
22611         vmetric: vmetric,
22612         disabled: disabled,
22613         operatorList: operatorList
22614       };
22615     },
22616 
22617     charsToGlyphs: function Font_charsToGlyphs(chars) {
22618       var charsCache = this.charsCache;
22619       var glyphs;
22620 
22621       // if we translated this string before, just grab it from the cache
22622       if (charsCache) {
22623         glyphs = charsCache[chars];
22624         if (glyphs)
22625           return glyphs;
22626       }
22627 
22628       // lazily create the translation cache
22629       if (!charsCache)
22630         charsCache = this.charsCache = Object.create(null);
22631 
22632       glyphs = [];
22633       var charsCacheKey = chars;
22634 
22635       var converter;
22636       var cidEncoding = this.cidEncoding;
22637       if (cidEncoding) {
22638         converter = CMapConverterList[cidEncoding];
22639         if (converter) {
22640           chars = converter(chars);
22641         } else if (cidEncoding.indexOf('Uni') !== 0 &&
22642                    cidEncoding.indexOf('Identity-') !== 0) {
22643           warn('Unsupported CMap: ' + cidEncoding);
22644         }
22645       }
22646       if (!converter && this.wideChars) {
22647         // composite fonts have multi-byte strings convert the string from
22648         // single-byte to multi-byte
22649         // XXX assuming CIDFonts are two-byte - later need to extract the
22650         // correct byte encoding according to the PDF spec
22651         var length = chars.length - 1; // looping over two bytes at a time so
22652                                        // loop should never end on the last byte
22653         for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
22654           var charcode = int16([chars.charCodeAt(i++), chars.charCodeAt(i)]);
22655           var glyph = this.charToGlyph(charcode);
22656           glyphs.push(glyph);
22657           // placing null after each word break charcode (ASCII SPACE)
22658           if (charcode == 0x20)
22659             glyphs.push(null);
22660         }
22661       }
22662       else {
22663         for (var i = 0, ii = chars.length; i < ii; ++i) {
22664           var charcode = chars.charCodeAt(i);
22665           var glyph = this.charToGlyph(charcode);
22666           glyphs.push(glyph);
22667           if (charcode == 0x20)
22668             glyphs.push(null);
22669         }
22670       }
22671 
22672       // Enter the translated string into the cache
22673       return (charsCache[charsCacheKey] = glyphs);
22674     }
22675   };
22676 
22677   return Font;
22678 })();
22679 
22680 var ErrorFont = (function ErrorFontClosure() {
22681   function ErrorFont(error) {
22682     this.error = error;
22683   }
22684 
22685   ErrorFont.prototype = {
22686     charsToGlyphs: function ErrorFont_charsToGlyphs() {
22687       return [];
22688     },
22689     exportData: function ErrorFont_exportData() {
22690       return {error: this.error};
22691     }
22692   };
22693 
22694   return ErrorFont;
22695 })();
22696 
22697 /*
22698  * CharStrings are encoded following the the CharString Encoding sequence
22699  * describe in Chapter 6 of the "Adobe Type1 Font Format" specification.
22700  * The value in a byte indicates a command, a number, or subsequent bytes
22701  * that are to be interpreted in a special way.
22702  *
22703  * CharString Number Encoding:
22704  *  A CharString byte containing the values from 32 through 255 inclusive
22705  *  indicate an integer. These values are decoded in four ranges.
22706  *
22707  * 1. A CharString byte containing a value, v, between 32 and 246 inclusive,
22708  * indicate the integer v - 139. Thus, the integer values from -107 through
22709  * 107 inclusive may be encoded in single byte.
22710  *
22711  * 2. A CharString byte containing a value, v, between 247 and 250 inclusive,
22712  * indicates an integer involving the next byte, w, according to the formula:
22713  * [(v - 247) x 256] + w + 108
22714  *
22715  * 3. A CharString byte containing a value, v, between 251 and 254 inclusive,
22716  * indicates an integer involving the next byte, w, according to the formula:
22717  * -[(v - 251) * 256] - w - 108
22718  *
22719  * 4. A CharString containing the value 255 indicates that the next 4 bytes
22720  * are a two complement signed integer. The first of these bytes contains the
22721  * highest order bits, the second byte contains the next higher order bits
22722  * and the fourth byte contain the lowest order bits.
22723  *
22724  *
22725  * CharString Command Encoding:
22726  *  CharStrings commands are encoded in 1 or 2 bytes.
22727  *
22728  *  Single byte commands are encoded in 1 byte that contains a value between
22729  *  0 and 31 inclusive.
22730  *  If a command byte contains the value 12, then the value in the next byte
22731  *  indicates a command. This "escape" mechanism allows many extra commands
22732  * to be encoded and this encoding technique helps to minimize the length of
22733  * the charStrings.
22734  */
22735 var Type1CharString = (function Type1CharStringClosure() {
22736   var COMMAND_MAP = {
22737     'hstem': [1],
22738     'vstem': [3],
22739     'vmoveto': [4],
22740     'rlineto': [5],
22741     'hlineto': [6],
22742     'vlineto': [7],
22743     'rrcurveto': [8],
22744     'callsubr': [10],
22745     'flex': [12, 35],
22746     'drop' : [12, 18],
22747     'endchar': [14],
22748     'rmoveto': [21],
22749     'hmoveto': [22],
22750     'vhcurveto': [30],
22751     'hvcurveto': [31]
22752   };
22753 
22754   function Type1CharString() {
22755     this.width = 0;
22756     this.lsb = 0;
22757     this.flexing = false;
22758     this.output = [];
22759     this.stack = [];
22760   }
22761 
22762   Type1CharString.prototype = {
22763     convert: function Type1CharString_convert(encoded, subrs) {
22764       var count = encoded.length;
22765       var error = false;
22766       for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
22767         var value = encoded[i];
22768         if (value < 32) {
22769           if (value === 12) {
22770             value = (value << 8) + encoded[++i];
22771           }
22772           switch (value) {
22773             case 1: // hstem
22774               if (!HINTING_ENABLED) {
22775                 this.stack = [];
22776                 break;
22777               }
22778               error = this.executeCommand(2, COMMAND_MAP.hstem);
22779               break;
22780             case 3: // vstem
22781               if (!HINTING_ENABLED) {
22782                 this.stack = [];
22783                 break;
22784               }
22785               error = this.executeCommand(2, COMMAND_MAP.vstem);
22786               break;
22787             case 4: // vmoveto
22788               if (this.flexing) {
22789                 if (this.stack.length < 1) {
22790                   error = true;
22791                   break;
22792                 }
22793                 // Add the dx for flex and but also swap the values so they are
22794                 // the right order.
22795                 var dy = this.stack.pop();
22796                 this.stack.push(0, dy);
22797                 break;
22798               }
22799               error = this.executeCommand(1, COMMAND_MAP.vmoveto);
22800               break;
22801             case 5: // rlineto
22802               error = this.executeCommand(2, COMMAND_MAP.rlineto);
22803               break;
22804             case 6: // hlineto
22805               error = this.executeCommand(1, COMMAND_MAP.hlineto);
22806               break;
22807             case 7: // vlineto
22808               error = this.executeCommand(1, COMMAND_MAP.vlineto);
22809               break;
22810             case 8: // rrcurveto
22811               error = this.executeCommand(6, COMMAND_MAP.rrcurveto);
22812               break;
22813             case 9: // closepath
22814               // closepath is a Type1 command that does not take argument and is
22815               // useless in Type2 and it can simply be ignored.
22816               this.stack = [];
22817               break;
22818             case 10: // callsubr
22819               if (this.stack.length < 1) {
22820                 error = true;
22821                 break;
22822               }
22823               var subrNumber = this.stack.pop();
22824               error = this.convert(subrs[subrNumber], subrs);
22825               break;
22826             case 11: // return
22827               return error;
22828             case 13: // hsbw
22829               if (this.stack.length < 2) {
22830                 error = true;
22831                 break;
22832               }
22833               // To convert to type2 we have to move the width value to the
22834               // first part of the charstring and then use hmoveto with lsb.
22835               var wx = this.stack.pop();
22836               var sbx = this.stack.pop();
22837               this.lsb = sbx;
22838               this.width = wx;
22839               this.stack.push(sbx);
22840               error = this.executeCommand(1, COMMAND_MAP.hmoveto);
22841               break;
22842             case 14: // endchar
22843               this.output.push(COMMAND_MAP.endchar[0]);
22844               break;
22845             case 21: // rmoveto
22846               if (this.flexing) {
22847                 break;
22848               }
22849               error = this.executeCommand(2, COMMAND_MAP.rmoveto);
22850               break;
22851             case 22: // hmoveto
22852               if (this.flexing) {
22853                 // Add the dy for flex.
22854                 this.stack.push(0);
22855                 break;
22856               }
22857               error = this.executeCommand(1, COMMAND_MAP.hmoveto);
22858               break;
22859             case 30: // vhcurveto
22860               error = this.executeCommand(4, COMMAND_MAP.vhcurveto);
22861               break;
22862             case 31: // hvcurveto
22863               error = this.executeCommand(4, COMMAND_MAP.hvcurveto);
22864               break;
22865             case (12 << 8) + 0: // dotsection
22866               // dotsection is a Type1 command to specify some hinting feature
22867               // for dots that do not take a parameter and it can safely be
22868               // ignored for Type2.
22869               this.stack = [];
22870               break;
22871             case (12 << 8) + 1: // vstem3
22872               if (!HINTING_ENABLED) {
22873                 this.stack = [];
22874                 break;
22875               }
22876               // [vh]stem3 are Type1 only and Type2 supports [vh]stem with
22877               // multiple parameters, so instead of returning [vh]stem3 take a
22878               // shortcut and return [vhstem] instead.
22879               error = this.executeCommand(2, COMMAND_MAP.vstem);
22880               break;
22881             case (12 << 8) + 2: // hstem3
22882               if (!HINTING_ENABLED) {
22883                  this.stack = [];
22884                 break;
22885               }
22886               // See vstem3.
22887               error = this.executeCommand(2, COMMAND_MAP.hstem);
22888               break;
22889             case (12 << 8) + 6: // seac
22890               // seac is like type 2's special endchar but it doesn't use the
22891               // first argument asb, so remove it.
22892               if (SEAC_ANALYSIS_ENABLED) {
22893                 this.seac = this.stack.splice(-4, 4);
22894                 error = this.executeCommand(0, COMMAND_MAP.endchar);
22895               } else {
22896                 error = this.executeCommand(4, COMMAND_MAP.endchar);
22897               }
22898               break;
22899             case (12 << 8) + 7: // sbw
22900               if (this.stack.length < 4) {
22901                 error = true;
22902                 break;
22903               }
22904               // To convert to type2 we have to move the width value to the
22905               // first part of the charstring and then use rmoveto with
22906               // (dx, dy). The height argument will not be used for vmtx and
22907               // vhea tables reconstruction -- ignoring it.
22908               var wy = this.stack.pop();
22909               var wx = this.stack.pop();
22910               var sby = this.stack.pop();
22911               var sbx = this.stack.pop();
22912               this.lsb = sbx;
22913               this.width = wx;
22914               this.stack.push(sbx, sby);
22915               error = this.executeCommand(2, COMMAND_MAP.rmoveto);
22916               break;
22917             case (12 << 8) + 12: // div
22918               if (this.stack.length < 2) {
22919                 error = true;
22920                 break;
22921               }
22922               var num2 = this.stack.pop();
22923               var num1 = this.stack.pop();
22924               this.stack.push(num1 / num2);
22925               break;
22926             case (12 << 8) + 16: // callothersubr
22927               if (this.stack.length < 2) {
22928                 error = true;
22929                 break;
22930               }
22931               var subrNumber = this.stack.pop();
22932               var numArgs = this.stack.pop();
22933               if (subrNumber === 0 && numArgs === 3) {
22934                 var flexArgs = this.stack.splice(this.stack.length - 17, 17);
22935                 this.stack.push(
22936                   flexArgs[2] + flexArgs[0], // bcp1x + rpx
22937                   flexArgs[3] + flexArgs[1], // bcp1y + rpy
22938                   flexArgs[4], // bcp2x
22939                   flexArgs[5], // bcp2y
22940                   flexArgs[6], // p2x
22941                   flexArgs[7], // p2y
22942                   flexArgs[8], // bcp3x
22943                   flexArgs[9], // bcp3y
22944                   flexArgs[10], // bcp4x
22945                   flexArgs[11], // bcp4y
22946                   flexArgs[12], // p3x
22947                   flexArgs[13], // p3y
22948                   flexArgs[14] // flexDepth
22949                   // 15 = finalx unused by flex
22950                   // 16 = finaly unused by flex
22951                 );
22952                 error = this.executeCommand(13, COMMAND_MAP.flex, true);
22953                 this.flexing = false;
22954                 this.stack.push(flexArgs[15], flexArgs[16]);
22955               } else if (subrNumber === 1 && numArgs === 0) {
22956                 this.flexing = true;
22957               }
22958               break;
22959             case (12 << 8) + 17: // pop
22960               // Ignore this since it is only used with othersubr.
22961               break;
22962             case (12 << 8) + 33: // setcurrentpoint
22963               // Ignore for now.
22964               this.stack = [];
22965               break;
22966             default:
22967               warn('Unknown type 1 charstring command of "' + value + '"');
22968               break;
22969           }
22970           if (error) {
22971             break;
22972           }
22973           continue;
22974         } else if (value <= 246) {
22975           value = value - 139;
22976         } else if (value <= 250) {
22977           value = ((value - 247) * 256) + encoded[++i] + 108;
22978         } else if (value <= 254) {
22979           value = -((value - 251) * 256) - encoded[++i] - 108;
22980         } else {
22981           value = (encoded[++i] & 0xff) << 24 | (encoded[++i] & 0xff) << 16 |
22982                   (encoded[++i] & 0xff) << 8 | (encoded[++i] & 0xff) << 0;
22983         }
22984         this.stack.push(value);
22985       }
22986       return error;
22987     },
22988 
22989     executeCommand: function(howManyArgs, command, keepStack) {
22990       var stackLength = this.stack.length;
22991       if (howManyArgs > stackLength) {
22992         return true;
22993       }
22994       var start = stackLength - howManyArgs;
22995       for (var i = start; i < stackLength; i++) {
22996         var value = this.stack[i];
22997         if (value === (value | 0)) { // int
22998           this.output.push(28, (value >> 8) & 0xff, value & 0xff);
22999         } else { // fixed point
23000           value = (65536 * value) | 0;
23001           this.output.push(255,
23002                            (value >> 24) & 0xFF,
23003                            (value >> 16) & 0xFF,
23004                            (value >> 8) & 0xFF,
23005                            value & 0xFF);
23006         }
23007       }
23008       this.output.push.apply(this.output, command);
23009       if (keepStack) {
23010         this.stack.splice(start, howManyArgs);
23011       } else {
23012         this.stack = [];
23013       }
23014       return false;
23015     }
23016   };
23017 
23018   return Type1CharString;
23019 })();
23020 
23021 /*
23022  * Type1Parser encapsulate the needed code for parsing a Type1 font
23023  * program. Some of its logic depends on the Type2 charstrings
23024  * structure.
23025  * Note: this doesn't really parse the font since that would require evaluation
23026  * of PostScript, but it is possible in most cases to extract what we need
23027  * without a full parse.
23028  */
23029 var Type1Parser = (function Type1ParserClosure() {
23030   /*
23031    * Decrypt a Sequence of Ciphertext Bytes to Produce the Original Sequence
23032    * of Plaintext Bytes. The function took a key as a parameter which can be
23033    * for decrypting the eexec block of for decoding charStrings.
23034    */
23035   var EEXEC_ENCRYPT_KEY = 55665;
23036   var CHAR_STRS_ENCRYPT_KEY = 4330;
23037 
23038   function decrypt(stream, key, discardNumber) {
23039     var r = key, c1 = 52845, c2 = 22719;
23040     var decryptedString = [];
23041 
23042     var value = '';
23043     var count = stream.length;
23044     for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
23045       value = stream[i];
23046       decryptedString[i] = value ^ (r >> 8);
23047       r = ((value + r) * c1 + c2) & ((1 << 16) - 1);
23048     }
23049     return decryptedString.slice(discardNumber);
23050   }
23051 
23052   function isSpecial(c) {
23053     return c === 0x2F || // '/'
23054            c === 0x5B || c === 0x5D || // '[', ']'
23055            c === 0x7B || c === 0x7D || // '{', '}'
23056            c === 0x28 || c === 0x29; // '(', ')'
23057   }
23058 
23059   function Type1Parser(stream, encrypted) {
23060     if (encrypted) {
23061       stream = new Stream(decrypt(stream.getBytes(), EEXEC_ENCRYPT_KEY, 4));
23062     }
23063     this.stream = stream;
23064     this.nextChar();
23065   }
23066 
23067   Type1Parser.prototype = {
23068     readNumberArray: function Type1Parser_readNumberArray() {
23069       this.getToken(); // read '[' or '{' (arrays can start with either)
23070       var array = [];
23071       while (true) {
23072         var token = this.getToken();
23073         if (token === null || token === ']' || token === '}') {
23074           break;
23075         }
23076         array.push(parseFloat(token || 0));
23077       }
23078       return array;
23079     },
23080 
23081     readNumber: function Type1Parser_readNumber() {
23082       var token = this.getToken();
23083       return parseFloat(token || 0);
23084     },
23085 
23086     readInt: function Type1Parser_readInt() {
23087       // Use '| 0' to prevent setting a double into length such as the double
23088       // does not flow into the loop variable.
23089       var token = this.getToken();
23090       return parseInt(token || 0, 10) | 0;
23091     },
23092 
23093     readBoolean: function Type1Parser_readBoolean() {
23094       var token = this.getToken();
23095 
23096       // Use 1 and 0 since that's what type2 charstrings use.
23097       return token === 'true' ? 1 : 0;
23098     },
23099 
23100     nextChar : function Type1_nextChar() {
23101       return (this.currentChar = this.stream.getByte());
23102     },
23103 
23104     getToken: function Type1Parser_getToken() {
23105       // Eat whitespace and comments.
23106       var comment = false;
23107       var ch = this.currentChar;
23108       while (true) {
23109         if (ch === -1) {
23110           return null;
23111         }
23112 
23113         if (comment) {
23114           if (ch === 0x0A || ch === 0x0D) {
23115             comment = false;
23116           }
23117         } else if (ch === 0x25) { // '%'
23118           comment = true;
23119         } else if (!Lexer.isSpace(ch)) {
23120           break;
23121         }
23122         ch = this.nextChar();
23123       }
23124       if (isSpecial(ch)) {
23125         this.nextChar();
23126         return String.fromCharCode(ch);
23127       }
23128       var token = '';
23129       do {
23130         token += String.fromCharCode(ch);
23131         ch = this.nextChar();
23132       } while (ch >= 0 && !Lexer.isSpace(ch) && !isSpecial(ch));
23133       return token;
23134     },
23135 
23136     /*
23137      * Returns an object containing a Subrs array and a CharStrings
23138      * array extracted from and eexec encrypted block of data
23139      */
23140     extractFontProgram: function Type1Parser_extractFontProgram() {
23141       var stream = this.stream;
23142 
23143       var subrs = [], charstrings = [];
23144       var program = {
23145         subrs: [],
23146         charstrings: [],
23147         properties: {
23148           'privateData': {
23149             'lenIV': 4
23150           }
23151         }
23152       };
23153       var token;
23154       while ((token = this.getToken()) !== null) {
23155         if (token !== '/') {
23156           continue;
23157         }
23158         token = this.getToken();
23159         switch (token) {
23160           case 'CharStrings':
23161             // The number immediately following CharStrings must be greater or
23162             // equal to the number of CharStrings.
23163             this.getToken();
23164             this.getToken(); // read in 'dict'
23165             this.getToken(); // read in 'dup'
23166             this.getToken(); // read in 'begin'
23167             while(true) {
23168               token = this.getToken();
23169               if (token === null || token === 'end') {
23170                 break;
23171               }
23172 
23173               if (token !== '/') {
23174                 continue;
23175               }
23176               var glyph = this.getToken();
23177               var length = this.readInt();
23178               this.getToken(); // read in 'RD' or '-|'
23179               var data = stream.makeSubStream(stream.pos, length);
23180               var lenIV = program.properties.privateData['lenIV'];
23181               var encoded = decrypt(data.getBytes(), CHAR_STRS_ENCRYPT_KEY,
23182                                     lenIV);
23183               // Skip past the required space and binary data.
23184               stream.skip(length);
23185               this.nextChar();
23186               token = this.getToken(); // read in 'ND' or '|-'
23187               if (token === 'noaccess') {
23188                 this.getToken(); // read in 'def'
23189               }
23190               charstrings.push({
23191                 glyph: glyph,
23192                 encoded: encoded
23193               });
23194             }
23195             break;
23196           case 'Subrs':
23197             var num = this.readInt();
23198             this.getToken(); // read in 'array'
23199             while ((token = this.getToken()) === 'dup') {
23200               var index = this.readInt();
23201               var length = this.readInt();
23202               this.getToken(); // read in 'RD' or '-|'
23203               var data = stream.makeSubStream(stream.pos, length);
23204               var lenIV = program.properties.privateData['lenIV'];
23205               var encoded = decrypt(data.getBytes(), CHAR_STRS_ENCRYPT_KEY,
23206                                     lenIV);
23207               // Skip past the required space and binary data.
23208               stream.skip(length);
23209               this.nextChar();
23210               token = this.getToken(); // read in 'NP' or '|'
23211               if (token === 'noaccess') {
23212                 this.getToken(); // read in 'put'
23213               }
23214               subrs[index] = encoded;
23215             }
23216             break;
23217           case 'BlueValues':
23218           case 'OtherBlues':
23219           case 'FamilyBlues':
23220           case 'FamilyOtherBlues':
23221             var blueArray = this.readNumberArray();
23222             // *Blue* values may contain invalid data: disables reading of
23223             // those values when hinting is disabled.
23224             if (blueArray.length > 0 && (blueArray.length % 2) === 0 &&
23225                 HINTING_ENABLED) {
23226               program.properties.privateData[token] = blueArray;
23227             }
23228             break;
23229           case 'StemSnapH':
23230           case 'StemSnapV':
23231             program.properties.privateData[token] = this.readNumberArray();
23232             break;
23233           case 'StdHW':
23234           case 'StdVW':
23235             program.properties.privateData[token] =
23236               this.readNumberArray()[0];
23237             break;
23238           case 'BlueShift':
23239           case 'lenIV':
23240           case 'BlueFuzz':
23241           case 'BlueScale':
23242           case 'LanguageGroup':
23243           case 'ExpansionFactor':
23244             program.properties.privateData[token] = this.readNumber();
23245             break;
23246           case 'ForceBold':
23247             program.properties.privateData[token] = this.readBoolean();
23248             break;
23249         }
23250       }
23251 
23252       for (var i = 0; i < charstrings.length; i++) {
23253         var glyph = charstrings[i].glyph;
23254         var encoded = charstrings[i].encoded;
23255         var charString = new Type1CharString();
23256         var error = charString.convert(encoded, subrs);
23257         var output = charString.output;
23258         if (error) {
23259           // It seems when FreeType encounters an error while evaluating a glyph
23260           // that it completely ignores the glyph so we'll mimic that behaviour
23261           // here and put an endchar to make the validator happy.
23262           output = [14];
23263         }
23264         program.charstrings.push({
23265           glyph: glyph,
23266           data: output,
23267           seac: charString.seac,
23268           lsb: charString.lsb,
23269           width: charString.width
23270         });
23271       }
23272 
23273       return program;
23274     },
23275 
23276     extractFontHeader: function Type1Parser_extractFontHeader(properties) {
23277       var token;
23278       while ((token = this.getToken()) !== null) {
23279         if (token !== '/') {
23280           continue;
23281         }
23282         token = this.getToken();
23283         switch (token) {
23284           case 'FontMatrix':
23285             var matrix = this.readNumberArray();
23286             properties.fontMatrix = matrix;
23287             break;
23288           case 'Encoding':
23289             var encodingArg = this.getToken();
23290             var encoding;
23291             if (!/^\d+$/.test(encodingArg)) {
23292               // encoding name is specified
23293               encoding = Encodings[encodingArg];
23294             } else {
23295               encoding = [];
23296               var size = parseInt(encodingArg, 10) | 0;
23297               this.getToken(); // read in 'array'
23298 
23299               for (var j = 0; j < size; j++) {
23300                 var token = this.getToken();
23301                 if (token === 'dup') {
23302                   var index = this.readInt();
23303                   this.getToken(); // read in '/'
23304                   var glyph = this.getToken();
23305                   encoding[index] = glyph;
23306                   this.getToken(); // read the in 'put'
23307                 }
23308               }
23309             }
23310             if (properties.overridableEncoding && encoding) {
23311               properties.baseEncoding = encoding;
23312               break;
23313             }
23314             break;
23315         }
23316       }
23317     }
23318   };
23319 
23320   return Type1Parser;
23321 })();

23395 // Type1Font is also a CIDFontType0.
23396 var Type1Font = function Type1Font(name, file, properties) {
23397   // Get the data block containing glyphs and subrs informations
23398   var headerBlock = new Stream(file.getBytes(properties.length1));
23399   var headerBlockParser = new Type1Parser(headerBlock);
23400   headerBlockParser.extractFontHeader(properties);
23401 
23402   // Decrypt the data blocks and retrieve it's content
23403   var eexecBlock = new Stream(file.getBytes(properties.length2));
23404   var eexecBlockParser = new Type1Parser(eexecBlock, true);
23405   var data = eexecBlockParser.extractFontProgram();
23406   for (var info in data.properties)
23407     properties[info] = data.properties[info];
23408 
23409   var charstrings = this.getOrderedCharStrings(data.charstrings, properties);
23410   var type2Charstrings = this.getType2Charstrings(charstrings);
23411   var subrs = this.getType2Subrs(data.subrs);
23412 
23413   this.charstrings = charstrings;
23414   this.data = this.wrap(name, type2Charstrings, this.charstrings,
23415                         subrs, properties);
23416   this.seacs = this.getSeacs(data.charstrings);
23417 };
23418 
23419 Type1Font.prototype = {
23420   getOrderedCharStrings: function Type1Font_getOrderedCharStrings(glyphs,
23421                                                             properties) {
23422     var charstrings = [];
23423     var usedUnicodes = [];
23424     var i, length, glyphName;
23425     var unusedUnicode = CMAP_GLYPH_OFFSET;
23426     for (i = 0, length = glyphs.length; i < length; i++) {
23427       var item = glyphs[i];
23428       var glyphName = item.glyph;
23429       var unicode = glyphName in GlyphsUnicode ?
23430         GlyphsUnicode[glyphName] : unusedUnicode++;
23431       while (usedUnicodes[unicode]) {
23432         unicode = unusedUnicode++;
23433       }
23434       usedUnicodes[unicode] = true;
23435       charstrings.push({
23436         glyph: glyphName,
23437         unicode: unicode,
23438         gid: i,
23439         charstring: item.data,
23440         width: item.width,
23441         lsb: item.lsb
23442       });
23443     }
23444 
23445     charstrings.sort(function charstrings_sort(a, b) {
23446       return a.unicode - b.unicode;
23447     });
23448     return charstrings;
23449   },
23450 
23451   getSeacs: function Type1Font_getSeacs(charstrings) {
23452     var i, ii;
23453     var seacMap = [];
23454     for (i = 0, ii = charstrings.length; i < ii; i++) {
23455       var charstring = charstrings[i];
23456       if (charstring.seac) {
23457         seacMap[i] = charstring.seac;
23458       }
23459     }
23460     return seacMap;
23461   },
23462 
23463   getType2Charstrings: function Type1Font_getType2Charstrings(
23464                                   type1Charstrings) {
23465     var type2Charstrings = [];
23466     for (var i = 0, ii = type1Charstrings.length; i < ii; i++) {
23467       type2Charstrings.push(type1Charstrings[i].charstring);
23468     }
23469     return type2Charstrings;
23470   },
23471 
23472   getType2Subrs: function Type1Font_getType2Subrs(type1Subrs) {
23473     var bias = 0;
23474     var count = type1Subrs.length;
23475     if (count < 1133)
23476       bias = 107;
23477     else if (count < 33769)
23478       bias = 1131;
23479     else
23480       bias = 32768;
23481 
23482     // Add a bunch of empty subrs to deal with the Type2 bias
23483     var type2Subrs = [];
23484     for (var i = 0; i < bias; i++)
23485       type2Subrs.push([0x0B]);
23486 
23487     for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
23488       type2Subrs.push(type1Subrs[i]);
23489     }
23490 
23491     return type2Subrs;
23492   },
23493 
23494   wrap: function Type1Font_wrap(name, glyphs, charstrings, subrs, properties) {
23495     var cff = new CFF();
23496     cff.header = new CFFHeader(1, 0, 4, 4);
23497 
23498     cff.names = [name];
23499 
23500     var topDict = new CFFTopDict();
23501     // CFF strings IDs 0...390 are predefined names, so refering
23502     // to entries in our own String INDEX starts at SID 391.
23503     topDict.setByName('version', 391);
23504     topDict.setByName('Notice', 392);
23505     topDict.setByName('FullName', 393);
23506     topDict.setByName('FamilyName', 394);
23507     topDict.setByName('Weight', 395);
23508     topDict.setByName('Encoding', null); // placeholder
23509     topDict.setByName('FontMatrix', properties.fontMatrix);
23510     topDict.setByName('FontBBox', properties.bbox);
23511     topDict.setByName('charset', null); // placeholder
23512     topDict.setByName('CharStrings', null); // placeholder
23513     topDict.setByName('Private', null); // placeholder
23514     cff.topDict = topDict;
23515 
23516     var strings = new CFFStrings();
23517     strings.add('Version 0.11'); // Version
23518     strings.add('See original notice'); // Notice
23519     strings.add(name); // FullName
23520     strings.add(name); // FamilyName
23521     strings.add('Medium'); // Weight
23522     cff.strings = strings;
23523 
23524     cff.globalSubrIndex = new CFFIndex();
23525 
23526     var count = glyphs.length;
23527     var charsetArray = [0];
23528     for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
23529       var index = CFFStandardStrings.indexOf(charstrings[i].glyph);
23530       // Some characters like asterikmath && circlecopyrt are
23531       // missing from the original strings, for the moment let's
23532       // map them to .notdef and see later if it cause any
23533       // problems
23534       if (index == -1)
23535         index = 0;
23536 
23537       charsetArray.push((index >> 8) & 0xff, index & 0xff);
23538     }
23539     cff.charset = new CFFCharset(false, 0, [], charsetArray);
23540 
23541     var charStringsIndex = new CFFIndex();
23542     charStringsIndex.add([0x8B, 0x0E]); // .notdef
23543     for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
23544       charStringsIndex.add(glyphs[i]);
23545     }
23546     cff.charStrings = charStringsIndex;
23547 
23548     var privateDict = new CFFPrivateDict();
23549     privateDict.setByName('Subrs', null); // placeholder
23550     var fields = [
23551       'BlueValues',
23552       'OtherBlues',
23553       'FamilyBlues',
23554       'FamilyOtherBlues',
23555       'StemSnapH',
23556       'StemSnapV',
23557       'BlueShift',
23558       'BlueFuzz',
23559       'BlueScale',
23560       'LanguageGroup',
23561       'ExpansionFactor',
23562       'ForceBold',
23563       'StdHW',
23564       'StdVW'
23565     ];
23566     for (var i = 0, ii = fields.length; i < ii; i++) {
23567       var field = fields[i];
23568       if (!properties.privateData.hasOwnProperty(field))
23569         continue;
23570       var value = properties.privateData[field];
23571       if (isArray(value)) {
23572         // All of the private dictionary array data in CFF must be stored as
23573         // "delta-encoded" numbers.
23574         for (var j = value.length - 1; j > 0; j--) {
23575           value[j] -= value[j - 1]; // ... difference from previous value
23576         }
23577       }
23578       privateDict.setByName(field, value);
23579     }
23580     cff.topDict.privateDict = privateDict;
23581 
23582     var subrIndex = new CFFIndex();
23583     for (var i = 0, ii = subrs.length; i < ii; i++) {
23584       subrIndex.add(subrs[i]);
23585     }
23586     privateDict.subrsIndex = subrIndex;
23587 
23588     var compiler = new CFFCompiler(cff);
23589     return compiler.compile();
23590   }
23591 };
23592 
23593 var CFFFont = (function CFFFontClosure() {
23594   function CFFFont(file, properties) {
23595     this.properties = properties;
23596 
23597     var parser = new CFFParser(file, properties);
23598     this.cff = parser.parse();
23599     var compiler = new CFFCompiler(this.cff);
23600     this.readExtra();
23601     try {
23602       this.data = compiler.compile();
23603     } catch (e) {
23604       warn('Failed to compile font ' + properties.loadedName);
23605       // There may have just been an issue with the compiler, set the data
23606       // anyway and hope the font loaded.
23607       this.data = file;
23608     }
23609   }
23610 
23611   CFFFont.prototype = {
23612     readExtra: function CFFFont_readExtra() {
23613       // charstrings contains info about glyphs (one element per glyph
23614       // containing mappings for {unicode, width})
23615       var charstrings = this.getCharStrings();
23616 
23617       // create the mapping between charstring and glyph id
23618       var glyphIds = [];
23619       for (var i = 0, ii = charstrings.length; i < ii; i++)
23620         glyphIds.push(charstrings[i].gid);
23621 
23622       this.charstrings = charstrings;
23623       this.glyphIds = glyphIds;
23624       this.seacs = this.cff.seacs;
23625     },
23626     getCharStrings: function CFFFont_getCharStrings() {
23627       var cff = this.cff;
23628       var charsets = cff.charset.charset;
23629       var encoding = cff.encoding ? cff.encoding.encoding : null;
23630       var charstrings = [];
23631       var unicodeUsed = [];
23632       var unassignedUnicodeItems = [];
23633       var inverseEncoding = [];
23634       var gidStart = 0;
23635       // Even though the CFF font may not actually be a CID font is could have
23636       // CID information in the font descriptor.
23637       if (this.properties.cidSystemInfo) {
23638         // According to section 9.7.4.2 if the font is actually a CID font then
23639         // we should use the charset to map CIDs to GIDs. If it is not actually
23640         // a CID font then CIDs can be mapped directly to GIDs.
23641         if (this.cff.isCIDFont) {
23642           inverseEncoding = charsets;
23643         } else {
23644           for (var i = 0, ii = charsets.length; i < charsets.length; i++) {
23645             inverseEncoding.push(i);
23646           }
23647         }
23648       } else {
23649         for (var charcode in encoding)
23650           inverseEncoding[encoding[charcode]] = charcode | 0;
23651         if (charsets[0] === '.notdef') {
23652           gidStart = 1;
23653         }
23654       }
23655 
23656       for (var i = gidStart, ii = charsets.length; i < ii; i++) {
23657         var glyph = charsets[i];
23658 
23659         var code = inverseEncoding[i];
23660         if (!code || isSpecialUnicode(code)) {
23661           unassignedUnicodeItems.push(i);
23662           continue;
23663         }
23664         charstrings.push({
23665           unicode: code,
23666           code: code,
23667           gid: i,
23668           glyph: glyph
23669         });
23670         unicodeUsed[code] = true;
23671       }
23672 
23673       var nextUnusedUnicode = CMAP_GLYPH_OFFSET;
23674       for (var j = 0, jj = unassignedUnicodeItems.length; j < jj; ++j) {
23675         var i = unassignedUnicodeItems[j];
23676         // giving unicode value anyway
23677         while (nextUnusedUnicode in unicodeUsed)
23678           nextUnusedUnicode++;
23679         var unicode = nextUnusedUnicode++;
23680         charstrings.push({
23681           unicode: unicode,
23682           code: inverseEncoding[i] || 0,
23683           gid: i,
23684           glyph: charsets[i]
23685         });
23686       }
23687 
23688       // sort the array by the unicode value (again)
23689       charstrings.sort(function getCharStringsSort(a, b) {
23690         return a.unicode - b.unicode;
23691       });
23692       return charstrings;
23693     }
23694   };
23695 
23696   return CFFFont;
23697 })();
23698
