23782     { id: 'dup', min: 1, stackDelta: 1 },
23783     { id: 'exch', min: 2, stackDelta: 0 },
23784     { id: 'index', min: 2, stackDelta: 0 },
23785     { id: 'roll', min: 3, stackDelta: -2 },
23786     null,
23787     null,
23788     null,
23789     { id: 'hflex', min: 7, resetStack: true },
23790     { id: 'flex', min: 13, resetStack: true },
23791     { id: 'hflex1', min: 9, resetStack: true },
23792     { id: 'flex1', min: 11, resetStack: true }
23793   ];
23794 
23795   function CFFParser(file, properties) {
23796     this.bytes = file.getBytes();
23797     this.properties = properties;
23798   }
23799   CFFParser.prototype = {
23800     parse: function CFFParser_parse() {
23801       var properties = this.properties;
23802       var cff = new CFF();
23803       this.cff = cff;
23804 
23805       // The first five sections must be in order, all the others are reached
23806       // via offsets contained in one of the below.
23807       var header = this.parseHeader();
23808       var nameIndex = this.parseIndex(header.endPos);
23809       var topDictIndex = this.parseIndex(nameIndex.endPos);
23810       var stringIndex = this.parseIndex(topDictIndex.endPos);
23811       var globalSubrIndex = this.parseIndex(stringIndex.endPos);
23812 
23813       var topDictParsed = this.parseDict(topDictIndex.obj.get(0));
23814       var topDict = this.createDict(CFFTopDict, topDictParsed, cff.strings);
23815 
23816       cff.header = header.obj;
23817       cff.names = this.parseNameIndex(nameIndex.obj);
23818       cff.strings = this.parseStringIndex(stringIndex.obj);
23819       cff.topDict = topDict;
23820       cff.globalSubrIndex = globalSubrIndex.obj;
23821 
23822       this.parsePrivateDict(cff.topDict);
23823 
23824       cff.isCIDFont = topDict.hasName('ROS');
23825 
23826       var charStringOffset = topDict.getByName('CharStrings');
23827       var charStringsAndSeacs = this.parseCharStrings(charStringOffset);
23828       cff.charStrings = charStringsAndSeacs.charStrings;
23829       cff.seacs = charStringsAndSeacs.seacs;
23830 
23831       var fontMatrix = topDict.getByName('FontMatrix');
23832       if (fontMatrix) {
23833         properties.fontMatrix = fontMatrix;
23834       }
23835 
23836       var fontBBox = topDict.getByName('FontBBox');
23837       if (fontBBox) {
23838         // adjusting ascent/descent
23839         properties.ascent = fontBBox[3];
23840         properties.descent = fontBBox[1];
23841         properties.ascentScaled = true;
23842       }
23843 
23844       var charset, encoding;
23845       if (cff.isCIDFont) {
23846         var fdArrayIndex = this.parseIndex(topDict.getByName('FDArray')).obj;
23847         for (var i = 0, ii = fdArrayIndex.count; i < ii; ++i) {
23848           var dictRaw = fdArrayIndex.get(i);
23849           var fontDict = this.createDict(CFFTopDict, this.parseDict(dictRaw),
23850                                          cff.strings);
23851           this.parsePrivateDict(fontDict);
23852           cff.fdArray.push(fontDict);
23853         }
23854         // cid fonts don't have an encoding
23855         encoding = null;
23856         charset = this.parseCharsets(topDict.getByName('charset'),
23857                                      cff.charStrings.count, cff.strings, true);
23858         cff.fdSelect = this.parseFDSelect(topDict.getByName('FDSelect'),
23859                                              cff.charStrings.count);
23860       } else {
23861         charset = this.parseCharsets(topDict.getByName('charset'),
23862                                      cff.charStrings.count, cff.strings, false);
23863         encoding = this.parseEncoding(topDict.getByName('Encoding'),
23864                                       properties,
23865                                       cff.strings, charset.charset);
23866       }
23867       cff.charset = charset;
23868       cff.encoding = encoding;
23869 
23870       return cff;
23871     },
23872     parseHeader: function CFFParser_parseHeader() {
23873       var bytes = this.bytes;
23874       var offset = 0;
23875 
23876       while (bytes[offset] != 1)
23877         ++offset;
23878 
23879       if (offset !== 0) {
23880         info('cff data is shifted');
23881         bytes = bytes.subarray(offset);
23882         this.bytes = bytes;
23883       }
23884       var major = bytes[0];
23885       var minor = bytes[1];
23886       var hdrSize = bytes[2];
23887       var offSize = bytes[3];
23888       var header = new CFFHeader(major, minor, hdrSize, offSize);
23889       return {obj: header, endPos: hdrSize};
23890     },
23891     parseDict: function CFFParser_parseDict(dict) {
23892       var pos = 0;
23893 
23894       function parseOperand() {
23895         var value = dict[pos++];
23896         if (value === 30) {
23897           return parseFloatOperand(pos);
23898         } else if (value === 28) {
23899           value = dict[pos++];
23900           value = ((value << 24) | (dict[pos++] << 16)) >> 16;
23901           return value;
23902         } else if (value === 29) {
23903           value = dict[pos++];
23904           value = (value << 8) | dict[pos++];
23905           value = (value << 8) | dict[pos++];
23906           value = (value << 8) | dict[pos++];
23907           return value;
23908         } else if (value >= 32 && value <= 246) {
23909           return value - 139;
23910         } else if (value >= 247 && value <= 250) {
23911           return ((value - 247) * 256) + dict[pos++] + 108;
23912         } else if (value >= 251 && value <= 254) {
23913           return -((value - 251) * 256) - dict[pos++] - 108;
23914         } else {
23915           error('255 is not a valid DICT command');
23916         }
23917         return -1;
23918       }
23919 
23920       function parseFloatOperand() {
23921         var str = '';
23922         var eof = 15;
23923         var lookup = ['0', '1', '2', '3', '4', '5', '6', '7', '8',
23924             '9', '.', 'E', 'E-', null, '-'];
23925         var length = dict.length;
23926         while (pos < length) {
23927           var b = dict[pos++];
23928           var b1 = b >> 4;
23929           var b2 = b & 15;
23930 
23931           if (b1 == eof)
23932             break;
23933           str += lookup[b1];
23934 
23935           if (b2 == eof)
23936             break;
23937           str += lookup[b2];
23938         }
23939         return parseFloat(str);
23940       }
23941 
23942       var operands = [];
23943       var entries = [];
23944 
23945       var pos = 0;
23946       var end = dict.length;
23947       while (pos < end) {
23948         var b = dict[pos];
23949         if (b <= 21) {
23950           if (b === 12)
23951             b = (b << 8) | dict[++pos];
23952           entries.push([b, operands]);
23953           operands = [];
23954           ++pos;
23955         } else {
23956           operands.push(parseOperand());
23957         }
23958       }
23959       return entries;
23960     },
23961     parseIndex: function CFFParser_parseIndex(pos) {
23962       var cffIndex = new CFFIndex();
23963       var bytes = this.bytes;
23964       var count = (bytes[pos++] << 8) | bytes[pos++];
23965       var offsets = [];
23966       var start = pos;
23967       var end = pos;
23968 
23969       if (count !== 0) {
23970         var offsetSize = bytes[pos++];
23971         // add 1 for offset to determine size of last object
23972         var startPos = pos + ((count + 1) * offsetSize) - 1;
23973 
23974         for (var i = 0, ii = count + 1; i < ii; ++i) {
23975           var offset = 0;
23976           for (var j = 0; j < offsetSize; ++j) {
23977             offset <<= 8;
23978             offset += bytes[pos++];
23979           }
23980           offsets.push(startPos + offset);
23981         }
23982         end = offsets[count];
23983       }
23984       for (var i = 0, ii = offsets.length - 1; i < ii; ++i) {
23985         var offsetStart = offsets[i];
23986         var offsetEnd = offsets[i + 1];
23987         cffIndex.add(bytes.subarray(offsetStart, offsetEnd));
23988       }
23989       return {obj: cffIndex, endPos: end};
23990     },
23991     parseNameIndex: function CFFParser_parseNameIndex(index) {
23992       var names = [];
23993       for (var i = 0, ii = index.count; i < ii; ++i) {
23994         var name = index.get(i);
23995         // OTS doesn't allow names to be over 127 characters.
23996         var length = Math.min(name.length, 127);
23997         var data = [];
23998         // OTS also only permits certain characters in the name.
23999         for (var j = 0; j < length; ++j) {
24000           var c = name[j];
24001           if (j === 0 && c === 0) {
24002             data[j] = c;
24003             continue;
24004           }
24005           if ((c < 33 || c > 126) || c === 91 /* [ */ || c === 93 /* ] */ ||
24006               c === 40 /* ( */ || c === 41 /* ) */ || c === 123 /* { */ ||
24007               c === 125 /* } */ || c === 60 /* < */ || c === 62 /* > */ ||
24008               c === 47 /* / */ || c === 37 /* % */) {
24009             data[j] = 95;
24010             continue;
24011           }
24012           data[j] = c;
24013         }
24014         names.push(String.fromCharCode.apply(null, data));
24015       }
24016       return names;
24017     },
24018     parseStringIndex: function CFFParser_parseStringIndex(index) {
24019       var strings = new CFFStrings();
24020       for (var i = 0, ii = index.count; i < ii; ++i) {
24021         var data = index.get(i);
24022         strings.add(String.fromCharCode.apply(null, data));
24023       }
24024       return strings;
24025     },
24026     createDict: function CFFParser_createDict(Type, dict, strings) {
24027       var cffDict = new Type(strings);
24028       var types = cffDict.types;
24029 
24030       for (var i = 0, ii = dict.length; i < ii; ++i) {
24031         var pair = dict[i];
24032         var key = pair[0];
24033         var value = pair[1];
24034         cffDict.setByKey(key, value);
24035       }
24036       return cffDict;
24037     },
24038     parseCharStrings: function CFFParser_parseCharStrings(charStringOffset) {
24039       var charStrings = this.parseIndex(charStringOffset).obj;
24040       var seacs = [];
24041       var count = charStrings.count;
24042       for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
24043         var charstring = charStrings.get(i);
24044 
24045         var stackSize = 0;
24046         var stack = [];
24047         var undefStack = true;
24048         var hints = 0;
24049         var valid = true;
24050         var data = charstring;
24051         var length = data.length;
24052         for (var j = 0; j < length;) {
24053           var value = data[j++];
24054           var validationCommand = null;
24055           if (value == 12) {
24056             var q = data[j++];
24057             if (q === 0) {
24058               // The CFF specification state that the 'dotsection' command
24059               // (12, 0) is deprecated and treated as a no-op, but all Type2
24060               // charstrings processors should support them. Unfortunately
24061               // the font sanitizer don't. As a workaround the sequence (12, 0)
24062               // is replaced by a useless (0, hmoveto).
24063               data[j - 2] = 139;
24064               data[j - 1] = 22;
24065               stackSize = 0;
24066             } else {
24067               validationCommand = CharstringValidationData12[q];
24068             }
24069           } else if (value === 28) { // number (16 bit)
24070             stack[stackSize] = ((data[j] << 24) | (data[j + 1] << 16)) >> 16;
24071             j += 2;
24072             stackSize++;
24073           } else if (value == 14) {
24074             if (stackSize >= 4) {
24075               stackSize -= 4;
24076               if (SEAC_ANALYSIS_ENABLED) {
24077                 seacs[i] = stack.slice(stackSize, stackSize + 4);
24078                 valid = false;
24079               }
24080             }
24081           } else if (value >= 32 && value <= 246) {  // number
24082             stack[stackSize] = value - 139;
24083             stackSize++;
24084           } else if (value >= 247 && value <= 254) {  // number (+1 bytes)
24085             stack[stackSize] = value < 251 ?
24086               ((value - 247) << 8) + data[j] + 108 :
24087               -((value - 251) << 8) - data[j] - 108;
24088             j++;
24089             stackSize++;
24090           } else if (value == 255) {  // number (32 bit)
24091             stack[stackSize] = ((data[j] << 24) | (data[j + 1] << 16) |
24092               (data[j + 2] << 8) | data[j + 3]) / 65536;
24093             j += 4;
24094             stackSize++;
24095           } else if (value == 19 || value == 20) {
24096             hints += stackSize >> 1;
24097             j += (hints + 7) >> 3; // skipping right amount of hints flag data
24098             stackSize = 0;
24099           } else {
24100             validationCommand = CharstringValidationData[value];
24101           }
24102           if (validationCommand) {
24103             if (validationCommand.stem) {
24104               hints += stackSize >> 1;
24105             }
24106             if ('min' in validationCommand) {
24107               if (!undefStack && stackSize < validationCommand.min) {
24108                 warn('Not enough parameters for ' + validationCommand.id +
24109                      '; actual: ' + stackSize +
24110                      ', expected: ' + validationCommand.min);
24111                 valid = false;
24112                 break;
24113               }
24114             }
24115             if ('stackDelta' in validationCommand) {
24116               if ('stackFn' in validationCommand) {
24117                 validationCommand.stackFn(stack, stackSize);
24118               }
24119               stackSize += validationCommand.stackDelta;
24120             } else if (validationCommand.resetStack) {
24121               stackSize = 0;
24122               undefStack = false;
24123             } else if (validationCommand.undefStack) {
24124               stackSize = 0;
24125               undefStack = true;
24126             }
24127           }
24128         }
24129         if (!valid) {
24130           // resetting invalid charstring to single 'endchar'
24131           charStrings.set(i, new Uint8Array([14]));
24132         }
24133       }
24134       return { charStrings: charStrings, seacs: seacs };
24135     },
24136     emptyPrivateDictionary:
24137       function CFFParser_emptyPrivateDictionary(parentDict) {
24138       var privateDict = this.createDict(CFFPrivateDict, [],
24139                                         parentDict.strings);
24140       parentDict.setByKey(18, [0, 0]);
24141       parentDict.privateDict = privateDict;
24142     },
24143     parsePrivateDict: function CFFParser_parsePrivateDict(parentDict) {
24144       // no private dict, do nothing
24145       if (!parentDict.hasName('Private')) {
24146         this.emptyPrivateDictionary(parentDict);
24147         return;
24148       }
24149       var privateOffset = parentDict.getByName('Private');
24150       // make sure the params are formatted correctly
24151       if (!isArray(privateOffset) || privateOffset.length !== 2) {
24152         parentDict.removeByName('Private');
24153         return;
24154       }
24155       var size = privateOffset[0];
24156       var offset = privateOffset[1];
24157       // remove empty dicts or ones that refer to invalid location
24158       if (size === 0 || offset >= this.bytes.length) {
24159         this.emptyPrivateDictionary(parentDict);
24160         return;
24161       }
24162 
24163       var privateDictEnd = offset + size;
24164       var dictData = this.bytes.subarray(offset, privateDictEnd);
24165       var dict = this.parseDict(dictData);
24166       var privateDict = this.createDict(CFFPrivateDict, dict,
24167                                         parentDict.strings);
24168       parentDict.privateDict = privateDict;
24169 
24170       // Parse the Subrs index also since it's relative to the private dict.
24171       if (!privateDict.getByName('Subrs'))
24172         return;
24173       var subrsOffset = privateDict.getByName('Subrs');
24174       var relativeOffset = offset + subrsOffset;
24175       // Validate the offset.
24176       if (subrsOffset === 0 || relativeOffset >= this.bytes.length) {
24177         this.emptyPrivateDictionary(parentDict);
24178         return;
24179       }
24180       var subrsIndex = this.parseIndex(relativeOffset);
24181       privateDict.subrsIndex = subrsIndex.obj;
24182     },
24183     parseCharsets: function CFFParser_parseCharsets(pos, length, strings, cid) {
24184       if (pos === 0) {
24185         return new CFFCharset(true, CFFCharsetPredefinedTypes.ISO_ADOBE,
24186                               ISOAdobeCharset);
24187       } else if (pos == 1) {
24188         return new CFFCharset(true, CFFCharsetPredefinedTypes.EXPERT,
24189                               ExpertCharset);
24190       } else if (pos == 2) {
24191         return new CFFCharset(true, CFFCharsetPredefinedTypes.EXPERT_SUBSET,
24192                               ExpertSubsetCharset);
24193       }
24194 
24195       var bytes = this.bytes;
24196       var start = pos;
24197       var format = bytes[pos++];
24198       var charset = ['.notdef'];
24199 
24200       // subtract 1 for the .notdef glyph
24201       length -= 1;
24202 
24203       switch (format) {
24204         case 0:
24205           for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
24206             var id = (bytes[pos++] << 8) | bytes[pos++];
24207             charset.push(cid ? id : strings.get(id));
24208           }
24209           break;
24210         case 1:
24211           while (charset.length <= length) {
24212             var id = (bytes[pos++] << 8) | bytes[pos++];
24213             var count = bytes[pos++];
24214             for (var i = 0; i <= count; i++)
24215               charset.push(cid ? id++ : strings.get(id++));
24216           }
24217           break;
24218         case 2:
24219           while (charset.length <= length) {
24220             var id = (bytes[pos++] << 8) | bytes[pos++];
24221             var count = (bytes[pos++] << 8) | bytes[pos++];
24222             for (var i = 0; i <= count; i++)
24223               charset.push(cid ? id++ : strings.get(id++));
24224           }
24225           break;
24226         default:
24227           error('Unknown charset format');
24228       }
24229       // Raw won't be needed if we actually compile the charset.
24230       var end = pos;
24231       var raw = bytes.subarray(start, end);
24232 
24233       return new CFFCharset(false, format, charset, raw);
24234     },
24235     parseEncoding: function CFFParser_parseEncoding(pos,
24236                                                     properties,
24237                                                     strings,
24238                                                     charset) {
24239       var encoding = {};
24240       var bytes = this.bytes;
24241       var predefined = false;
24242       var hasSupplement = false;
24243       var format;
24244       var raw = null;
24245 
24246       function readSupplement() {
24247         var supplementsCount = bytes[pos++];
24248         for (var i = 0; i < supplementsCount; i++) {
24249           var code = bytes[pos++];
24250           var sid = (bytes[pos++] << 8) + (bytes[pos++] & 0xff);
24251           encoding[code] = properties.differences.indexOf(strings.get(sid));
24252         }
24253       }
24254 
24255       if (pos === 0 || pos == 1) {
24256         predefined = true;
24257         format = pos;
24258         var baseEncoding = pos ? Encodings.ExpertEncoding :
24259                                  Encodings.StandardEncoding;
24260         for (var i = 0, ii = charset.length; i < ii; i++) {
24261           var index = baseEncoding.indexOf(charset[i]);
24262           if (index != -1) {
24263             encoding[index] = i;
24264           }
24265         }
24266       } else {
24267         var dataStart = pos;
24268         var format = bytes[pos++];
24269         switch (format & 0x7f) {
24270           case 0:
24271             var glyphsCount = bytes[pos++];
24272             for (var i = 1; i <= glyphsCount; i++)
24273               encoding[bytes[pos++]] = i;
24274             break;
24275 
24276           case 1:
24277             var rangesCount = bytes[pos++];
24278             var gid = 1;
24279             for (var i = 0; i < rangesCount; i++) {
24280               var start = bytes[pos++];
24281               var left = bytes[pos++];
24282               for (var j = start; j <= start + left; j++)
24283                 encoding[j] = gid++;
24284             }
24285             break;
24286 
24287           default:
24288             error('Unknow encoding format: ' + format + ' in CFF');
24289             break;
24290         }
24291         var dataEnd = pos;
24292         if (format & 0x80) {
24293           // The font sanitizer does not support CFF encoding with a
24294           // supplement, since the encoding is not really used to map
24295           // between gid to glyph, let's overwrite what is declared in
24296           // the top dictionary to let the sanitizer think the font use
24297           // StandardEncoding, that's a lie but that's ok.
24298           bytes[dataStart] &= 0x7f;
24299           readSupplement();
24300           hasSupplement = true;
24301         }
24302         raw = bytes.subarray(dataStart, dataEnd);
24303       }
24304       format = format & 0x7f;
24305       return new CFFEncoding(predefined, format, encoding, raw);
24306     },
24307     parseFDSelect: function CFFParser_parseFDSelect(pos, length) {
24308       var start = pos;
24309       var bytes = this.bytes;
24310       var format = bytes[pos++];
24311       var fdSelect = [];
24312       switch (format) {
24313         case 0:
24314           for (var i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
24315             var id = bytes[pos++];
24316             fdSelect.push(id);
24317           }
24318           break;
24319         case 3:
24320           var rangesCount = (bytes[pos++] << 8) | bytes[pos++];
24321           for (var i = 0; i < rangesCount; ++i) {
24322             var first = (bytes[pos++] << 8) | bytes[pos++];
24323             var fdIndex = bytes[pos++];
24324             var next = (bytes[pos] << 8) | bytes[pos + 1];
24325             for (var j = first; j < next; ++j)
24326               fdSelect.push(fdIndex);
24327           }
24328           // Advance past the sentinel(next).
24329           pos += 2;
24330           break;
24331         default:
24332           error('Unknown fdselect format ' + format);
24333           break;
24334       }
24335       var end = pos;
24336       return new CFFFDSelect(fdSelect, bytes.subarray(start, end));
24337     }
24338   };
24339   return CFFParser;
24340 })();
24341 
24342 // Compact Font Format
24343 var CFF = (function CFFClosure() {
24344   function CFF() {
24345     this.header = null;
24346     this.names = [];
24347     this.topDict = null;
24348     this.strings = new CFFStrings();
24349     this.globalSubrIndex = null;
24350 
24351     // The following could really be per font, but since we only have one font
24352     // store them here.
24353     this.encoding = null;
24354     this.charset = null;
24355     this.charStrings = null;
24356     this.fdArray = [];
24357     this.fdSelect = null;
24358 
24359     this.isCIDFont = false;
24360   }
24361   return CFF;
24362 })();
24363 
24364 var CFFHeader = (function CFFHeaderClosure() {
24365   function CFFHeader(major, minor, hdrSize, offSize) {
24366     this.major = major;
24367     this.minor = minor;
24368     this.hdrSize = hdrSize;
24369     this.offSize = offSize;
24370   }
24371   return CFFHeader;
24372 })();
24373 
24374 var CFFStrings = (function CFFStringsClosure() {
24375   function CFFStrings() {
24376     this.strings = [];
24377   }
24378   CFFStrings.prototype = {
24379     get: function CFFStrings_get(index) {
24380       if (index >= 0 && index <= 390)
24381         return CFFStandardStrings[index];
24382       if (index - 391 <= this.strings.length)
24383         return this.strings[index - 391];
24384       return CFFStandardStrings[0];
24385     },
24386     add: function CFFStrings_add(value) {
24387       this.strings.push(value);
24388     },
24389     get count() {
24390       return this.strings.length;
24391     }
24392   };
24393   return CFFStrings;
24394 })();
24395 
24396 var CFFIndex = (function CFFIndexClosure() {
24397   function CFFIndex() {
24398     this.objects = [];
24399     this.length = 0;
24400   }
24401   CFFIndex.prototype = {
24402     add: function CFFIndex_add(data) {
24403       this.length += data.length;
24404       this.objects.push(data);
24405     },
24406     set: function CFFIndex_set(index, data) {
24407       this.length += data.length - this.objects[index].length;
24408       this.objects[index] = data;
24409     },
24410     get: function CFFIndex_get(index) {
24411       return this.objects[index];
24412     },
24413     get count() {
24414       return this.objects.length;
24415     }
24416   };
24417   return CFFIndex;
24418 })();
24419 
24420 var CFFDict = (function CFFDictClosure() {
24421   function CFFDict(tables, strings) {
24422     this.keyToNameMap = tables.keyToNameMap;
24423     this.nameToKeyMap = tables.nameToKeyMap;
24424     this.defaults = tables.defaults;
24425     this.types = tables.types;
24426     this.opcodes = tables.opcodes;
24427     this.order = tables.order;
24428     this.strings = strings;
24429     this.values = {};
24430   }
24431   CFFDict.prototype = {
24432     // value should always be an array
24433     setByKey: function CFFDict_setByKey(key, value) {
24434       if (!(key in this.keyToNameMap))
24435         return false;
24436       // ignore empty values
24437       if (value.length === 0)
24438         return true;
24439       var type = this.types[key];
24440       // remove the array wrapping these types of values
24441       if (type === 'num' || type === 'sid' || type === 'offset')
24442         value = value[0];
24443       this.values[key] = value;
24444       return true;
24445     },
24446     setByName: function CFFDict_setByName(name, value) {
24447       if (!(name in this.nameToKeyMap)) {
24448         error('Invalid dictionary name "' + name + '"');
24449       }
24450       this.values[this.nameToKeyMap[name]] = value;
24451     },
24452     hasName: function CFFDict_hasName(name) {
24453       return this.nameToKeyMap[name] in this.values;
24454     },
24455     getByName: function CFFDict_getByName(name) {
24456       if (!(name in this.nameToKeyMap))
24457         error('Invalid dictionary name "' + name + '"');
24458       var key = this.nameToKeyMap[name];
24459       if (!(key in this.values))
24460         return this.defaults[key];
24461       return this.values[key];
24462     },
24463     removeByName: function CFFDict_removeByName(name) {
24464       delete this.values[this.nameToKeyMap[name]];
24465     }
24466   };
24467   CFFDict.createTables = function CFFDict_createTables(layout) {
24468     var tables = {
24469       keyToNameMap: {},
24470       nameToKeyMap: {},
24471       defaults: {},
24472       types: {},
24473       opcodes: {},
24474       order: []
24475     };
24476     for (var i = 0, ii = layout.length; i < ii; ++i) {
24477       var entry = layout[i];
24478       var key = isArray(entry[0]) ? (entry[0][0] << 8) + entry[0][1] : entry[0];
24479       tables.keyToNameMap[key] = entry[1];
24480       tables.nameToKeyMap[entry[1]] = key;
24481       tables.types[key] = entry[2];
24482       tables.defaults[key] = entry[3];
24483       tables.opcodes[key] = isArray(entry[0]) ? entry[0] : [entry[0]];
24484       tables.order.push(key);
24485     }
24486     return tables;
24487   };
24488   return CFFDict;
24489 })();

24620 // Helper class to keep track of where an offset is within the data and helps
24621 // filling in that offset once it's known.
24622 var CFFOffsetTracker = (function CFFOffsetTrackerClosure() {
24623   function CFFOffsetTracker() {
24624     this.offsets = {};
24625   }
24626   CFFOffsetTracker.prototype = {
24627     isTracking: function CFFOffsetTracker_isTracking(key) {
24628       return key in this.offsets;
24629     },
24630     track: function CFFOffsetTracker_track(key, location) {
24631       if (key in this.offsets)
24632         error('Already tracking location of ' + key);
24633       this.offsets[key] = location;
24634     },
24635     offset: function CFFOffsetTracker_offset(value) {
24636       for (var key in this.offsets) {
24637         this.offsets[key] += value;
24638       }
24639     },
24640     setEntryLocation: function CFFOffsetTracker_setEntryLocation(key,
24641                                                                  values,
24642                                                                  output) {
24643       if (!(key in this.offsets))
24644         error('Not tracking location of ' + key);
24645       var data = output.data;
24646       var dataOffset = this.offsets[key];
24647       var size = 5;
24648       for (var i = 0, ii = values.length; i < ii; ++i) {
24649         var offset0 = i * size + dataOffset;
24650         var offset1 = offset0 + 1;
24651         var offset2 = offset0 + 2;
24652         var offset3 = offset0 + 3;
24653         var offset4 = offset0 + 4;
24654         // It's easy to screw up offsets so perform this sanity check.
24655         if (data[offset0] !== 0x1d || data[offset1] !== 0 ||
24656             data[offset2] !== 0 || data[offset3] !== 0 || data[offset4] !== 0)
24657           error('writing to an offset that is not empty');
24658         var value = values[i];
24659         data[offset0] = 0x1d;
24660         data[offset1] = (value >> 24) & 0xFF;
24661         data[offset2] = (value >> 16) & 0xFF;
24662         data[offset3] = (value >> 8) & 0xFF;
24663         data[offset4] = value & 0xFF;
24664       }
24665     }
24666   };
24667   return CFFOffsetTracker;
24668 })();
24669 
24670 // Takes a CFF and converts it to the binary representation.
24671 var CFFCompiler = (function CFFCompilerClosure() {
24672   function stringToArray(str) {
24673     var array = [];
24674     for (var i = 0, ii = str.length; i < ii; ++i)
24675       array[i] = str.charCodeAt(i);
24676 
24677     return array;
24678   }
24679   function CFFCompiler(cff) {
24680     this.cff = cff;
24681   }
24682   CFFCompiler.prototype = {
24683     compile: function CFFCompiler_compile() {
24684       var cff = this.cff;
24685       var output = {
24686         data: [],
24687         length: 0,
24688         add: function CFFCompiler_add(data) {
24689           this.data = this.data.concat(data);
24690           this.length = this.data.length;
24691         }
24692       };
24693 
24694       // Compile the five entries that must be in order.
24695       var header = this.compileHeader(cff.header);
24696       output.add(header);
24697 
24698       var nameIndex = this.compileNameIndex(cff.names);
24699       output.add(nameIndex);
24700 
24701       if (cff.isCIDFont) {
24702         // The spec is unclear on how font matrices should relate to each other
24703         // when there is one in the main top dict and the sub top dicts.
24704         // Windows handles this differently than linux and osx so we have to
24705         // normalize to work on all.
24706         // Rules based off of some mailing list discussions:
24707         // - If main font has a matrix and subfont doesn't, use the main matrix.
24708         // - If no main font matrix and there is a subfont matrix, use the
24709         //   subfont matrix.
24710         // - If both have matrices, concat together.
24711         // - If neither have matrices, use default.
24712         // To make this work on all platforms we move the top matrix into each
24713         // sub top dict and concat if necessary.
24714         if (cff.topDict.hasName('FontMatrix')) {
24715           var base = cff.topDict.getByName('FontMatrix');
24716           cff.topDict.removeByName('FontMatrix');
24717           for (var i = 0, ii = cff.fdArray.length; i < ii; i++) {
24718             var subDict = cff.fdArray[i];
24719             var matrix = base.slice(0);
24720             if (subDict.hasName('FontMatrix')) {
24721               matrix = Util.transform(matrix, subDict.getByName('FontMatrix'));
24722             }
24723             subDict.setByName('FontMatrix', matrix);
24724           }
24725         }
24726       }
24727 
24728       var compiled = this.compileTopDicts([cff.topDict],
24729                                           output.length,
24730                                           cff.isCIDFont);
24731       output.add(compiled.output);
24732       var topDictTracker = compiled.trackers[0];
24733 
24734       var stringIndex = this.compileStringIndex(cff.strings.strings);
24735       output.add(stringIndex);
24736 
24737       var globalSubrIndex = this.compileIndex(cff.globalSubrIndex);
24738       output.add(globalSubrIndex);
24739 
24740       // Now start on the other entries that have no specfic order.
24741       if (cff.encoding && cff.topDict.hasName('Encoding')) {
24742         if (cff.encoding.predefined) {
24743           topDictTracker.setEntryLocation('Encoding', [cff.encoding.format],
24744                                           output);
24745         } else {
24746           var encoding = this.compileEncoding(cff.encoding);
24747           topDictTracker.setEntryLocation('Encoding', [output.length], output);
24748           output.add(encoding);
24749         }
24750       }
24751 
24752       if (cff.charset && cff.topDict.hasName('charset')) {
24753         if (cff.charset.predefined) {
24754           topDictTracker.setEntryLocation('charset', [cff.charset.format],
24755                                           output);
24756         } else {
24757           var charset = this.compileCharset(cff.charset);
24758           topDictTracker.setEntryLocation('charset', [output.length], output);
24759           output.add(charset);
24760         }
24761       }
24762 
24763       var charStrings = this.compileCharStrings(cff.charStrings);
24764       topDictTracker.setEntryLocation('CharStrings', [output.length], output);
24765       output.add(charStrings);
24766 
24767       if (cff.isCIDFont) {
24768         // For some reason FDSelect must be in front of FDArray on windows. OSX
24769         // and linux don't seem to care.
24770         topDictTracker.setEntryLocation('FDSelect', [output.length], output);
24771         var fdSelect = this.compileFDSelect(cff.fdSelect.raw);
24772         output.add(fdSelect);
24773         // It is unclear if the sub font dictionary can have CID related
24774         // dictionary keys, but the sanitizer doesn't like them so remove them.
24775         var compiled = this.compileTopDicts(cff.fdArray, output.length, true);
24776         topDictTracker.setEntryLocation('FDArray', [output.length], output);
24777         output.add(compiled.output);
24778         var fontDictTrackers = compiled.trackers;
24779 
24780         this.compilePrivateDicts(cff.fdArray, fontDictTrackers, output);
24781       }
24782 
24783       this.compilePrivateDicts([cff.topDict], [topDictTracker], output);
24784 
24785       // If the font data ends with INDEX whose object data is zero-length,
24786       // the sanitizer will bail out. Add a dummy byte to avoid that.
24787       output.add([0]);
24788 
24789       return output.data;
24790     },
24791     encodeNumber: function CFFCompiler_encodeNumber(value) {
24792       if (parseFloat(value) == parseInt(value, 10) && !isNaN(value)) // isInt
24793         return this.encodeInteger(value);
24794       else
24795         return this.encodeFloat(value);
24796     },
24797     encodeFloat: function CFFCompiler_encodeFloat(num) {
24798       var value = num.toString();
24799 
24800       // rounding inaccurate doubles
24801       var m = /\.(\d*?)(?:9{5,20}|0{5,20})\d{0,2}(?:e(.+)|$)/.exec(value);
24802       if (m) {
24803         var epsilon = parseFloat('1e' + ((m[2] ? +m[2] : 0) + m[1].length));
24804         value = (Math.round(num * epsilon) / epsilon).toString();
24805       }
24806 
24807       var nibbles = '';
24808       for (var i = 0, ii = value.length; i < ii; ++i) {
24809         var a = value[i];
24810         if (a === 'e') {
24811           nibbles += value[++i] === '-' ? 'c' : 'b';
24812         } else if (a === '.') {
24813           nibbles += 'a';
24814         } else if (a === '-') {
24815           nibbles += 'e';
24816         } else {
24817           nibbles += a;
24818         }
24819       }
24820       nibbles += (nibbles.length & 1) ? 'f' : 'ff';
24821       var out = [30];
24822       for (var i = 0, ii = nibbles.length; i < ii; i += 2) {
24823         out.push(parseInt(nibbles.substr(i, 2), 16));
24824       }
24825       return out;
24826     },
24827     encodeInteger: function CFFCompiler_encodeInteger(value) {
24828       var code;
24829       if (value >= -107 && value <= 107) {
24830         code = [value + 139];
24831       } else if (value >= 108 && value <= 1131) {
24832         value = [value - 108];
24833         code = [(value >> 8) + 247, value & 0xFF];
24834       } else if (value >= -1131 && value <= -108) {
24835         value = -value - 108;
24836         code = [(value >> 8) + 251, value & 0xFF];
24837       } else if (value >= -32768 && value <= 32767) {
24838         code = [0x1c, (value >> 8) & 0xFF, value & 0xFF];
24839       } else {
24840         code = [0x1d,
24841                 (value >> 24) & 0xFF,
24842                 (value >> 16) & 0xFF,
24843                 (value >> 8) & 0xFF,
24844                  value & 0xFF];
24845       }
24846       return code;
24847     },
24848     compileHeader: function CFFCompiler_compileHeader(header) {
24849       return [
24850         header.major,
24851         header.minor,
24852         header.hdrSize,
24853         header.offSize
24854       ];
24855     },
24856     compileNameIndex: function CFFCompiler_compileNameIndex(names) {
24857       var nameIndex = new CFFIndex();
24858       for (var i = 0, ii = names.length; i < ii; ++i)
24859         nameIndex.add(stringToArray(names[i]));
24860       return this.compileIndex(nameIndex);
24861     },
24862     compileTopDicts: function CFFCompiler_compileTopDicts(dicts,
24863                                                           length,
24864                                                           removeCidKeys) {
24865       var fontDictTrackers = [];
24866       var fdArrayIndex = new CFFIndex();
24867       for (var i = 0, ii = dicts.length; i < ii; ++i) {
24868         var fontDict = dicts[i];
24869         if (removeCidKeys) {
24870           fontDict.removeByName('CIDFontVersion');
24871           fontDict.removeByName('CIDFontRevision');
24872           fontDict.removeByName('CIDFontType');
24873           fontDict.removeByName('CIDCount');
24874           fontDict.removeByName('UIDBase');
24875         }
24876         var fontDictTracker = new CFFOffsetTracker();
24877         var fontDictData = this.compileDict(fontDict, fontDictTracker);
24878         fontDictTrackers.push(fontDictTracker);
24879         fdArrayIndex.add(fontDictData);
24880         fontDictTracker.offset(length);
24881       }
24882       fdArrayIndex = this.compileIndex(fdArrayIndex, fontDictTrackers);
24883       return {
24884         trackers: fontDictTrackers,
24885         output: fdArrayIndex
24886       };
24887     },
24888     compilePrivateDicts: function CFFCompiler_compilePrivateDicts(dicts,
24889                                                                   trackers,
24890                                                                   output) {
24891       for (var i = 0, ii = dicts.length; i < ii; ++i) {
24892         var fontDict = dicts[i];
24893         assert(fontDict.privateDict && fontDict.hasName('Private'),
24894                'There must be an private dictionary.');
24895         var privateDict = fontDict.privateDict;
24896         var privateDictTracker = new CFFOffsetTracker();
24897         var privateDictData = this.compileDict(privateDict, privateDictTracker);
24898 
24899         var outputLength = output.length;
24900         privateDictTracker.offset(outputLength);
24901         if (!privateDictData.length) {
24902           // The private dictionary was empty, set the output length to zero to
24903           // ensure the offset length isn't out of bounds in the eyes of the
24904           // sanitizer.
24905           outputLength = 0;
24906         }
24907 
24908         trackers[i].setEntryLocation('Private',
24909                                      [privateDictData.length, outputLength],
24910                                      output);
24911         output.add(privateDictData);
24912 
24913         if (privateDict.subrsIndex && privateDict.hasName('Subrs')) {
24914           var subrs = this.compileIndex(privateDict.subrsIndex);
24915           privateDictTracker.setEntryLocation('Subrs', [privateDictData.length],
24916                                               output);
24917           output.add(subrs);
24918         }
24919       }
24920     },
24921     compileDict: function CFFCompiler_compileDict(dict, offsetTracker) {
24922       var out = [];
24923       // The dictionary keys must be in a certain order.
24924       var order = dict.order;
24925       for (var i = 0; i < order.length; ++i) {
24926         var key = order[i];
24927         if (!(key in dict.values))
24928           continue;
24929         var values = dict.values[key];
24930         var types = dict.types[key];
24931         if (!isArray(types)) types = [types];
24932         if (!isArray(values)) values = [values];
24933 
24934         // Remove any empty dict values.
24935         if (values.length === 0)
24936           continue;
24937 
24938         for (var j = 0, jj = types.length; j < jj; ++j) {
24939           var type = types[j];
24940           var value = values[j];
24941           switch (type) {
24942             case 'num':
24943             case 'sid':
24944               out = out.concat(this.encodeNumber(value));
24945               break;
24946             case 'offset':
24947               // For offsets we just insert a 32bit integer so we don't have to
24948               // deal with figuring out the length of the offset when it gets
24949               // replaced later on by the compiler.
24950               var name = dict.keyToNameMap[key];
24951               // Some offsets have the offset and the length, so just record the
24952               // position of the first one.
24953               if (!offsetTracker.isTracking(name))
24954                 offsetTracker.track(name, out.length);
24955               out = out.concat([0x1d, 0, 0, 0, 0]);
24956               break;
24957             case 'array':
24958             case 'delta':
24959               out = out.concat(this.encodeNumber(value));
24960               for (var k = 1, kk = values.length; k < kk; ++k)
24961                 out = out.concat(this.encodeNumber(values[k]));
24962               break;
24963             default:
24964               error('Unknown data type of ' + type);
24965               break;
24966           }
24967         }
24968         out = out.concat(dict.opcodes[key]);
24969       }
24970       return out;
24971     },
24972     compileStringIndex: function CFFCompiler_compileStringIndex(strings) {
24973       var stringIndex = new CFFIndex();
24974       for (var i = 0, ii = strings.length; i < ii; ++i)
24975         stringIndex.add(stringToArray(strings[i]));
24976       return this.compileIndex(stringIndex);
24977     },
24978     compileGlobalSubrIndex: function CFFCompiler_compileGlobalSubrIndex() {
24979       var globalSubrIndex = this.cff.globalSubrIndex;
24980       this.out.writeByteArray(this.compileIndex(globalSubrIndex));
24981     },
24982     compileCharStrings: function CFFCompiler_compileCharStrings(charStrings) {
24983       return this.compileIndex(charStrings);
24984     },
24985     compileCharset: function CFFCompiler_compileCharset(charset) {
24986       return this.compileTypedArray(charset.raw);
24987     },
24988     compileEncoding: function CFFCompiler_compileEncoding(encoding) {
24989       return this.compileTypedArray(encoding.raw);
24990     },
24991     compileFDSelect: function CFFCompiler_compileFDSelect(fdSelect) {
24992       return this.compileTypedArray(fdSelect);
24993     },
24994     compileTypedArray: function CFFCompiler_compileTypedArray(data) {
24995       var out = [];
24996       for (var i = 0, ii = data.length; i < ii; ++i)
24997         out[i] = data[i];
24998       return out;
24999     },
25000     compileIndex: function CFFCompiler_compileIndex(index, trackers) {
25001       trackers = trackers || [];
25002       var objects = index.objects;
25003       // First 2 bytes contains the number of objects contained into this index
25004       var count = objects.length;
25005 
25006       // If there is no object, just create an index. This technically
25007       // should just be [0, 0] but OTS has an issue with that.
25008       if (count === 0)
25009         return [0, 0, 0];
25010 
25011       var data = [(count >> 8) & 0xFF, count & 0xff];
25012 
25013       var lastOffset = 1;
25014       for (var i = 0; i < count; ++i)
25015         lastOffset += objects[i].length;
25016 
25017       var offsetSize;
25018       if (lastOffset < 0x100)
25019         offsetSize = 1;
25020       else if (lastOffset < 0x10000)
25021         offsetSize = 2;
25022       else if (lastOffset < 0x1000000)
25023         offsetSize = 3;
25024       else
25025         offsetSize = 4;
25026 
25027       // Next byte contains the offset size use to reference object in the file
25028       data.push(offsetSize);
25029 
25030       // Add another offset after this one because we need a new offset
25031       var relativeOffset = 1;
25032       for (var i = 0; i < count + 1; i++) {
25033         if (offsetSize === 1) {
25034           data.push(relativeOffset & 0xFF);
25035         } else if (offsetSize === 2) {
25036           data.push((relativeOffset >> 8) & 0xFF,
25037                      relativeOffset & 0xFF);
25038         } else if (offsetSize === 3) {
25039           data.push((relativeOffset >> 16) & 0xFF,
25040                     (relativeOffset >> 8) & 0xFF,
25041                      relativeOffset & 0xFF);
25042         } else {
25043           data.push((relativeOffset >>> 24) & 0xFF,
25044                     (relativeOffset >> 16) & 0xFF,
25045                     (relativeOffset >> 8) & 0xFF,
25046                      relativeOffset & 0xFF);
25047         }
25048 
25049         if (objects[i])
25050           relativeOffset += objects[i].length;
25051       }
25052       var offset = data.length;
25053 
25054       for (var i = 0; i < count; i++) {
25055         // Notify the tracker where the object will be offset in the data.
25056         if (trackers[i])
25057           trackers[i].offset(data.length);
25058         for (var j = 0, jj = objects[i].length; j < jj; j++)
25059           data.push(objects[i][j]);
25060       }
25061       return data;
25062     }
25063   };
25064   return CFFCompiler;
25065 })();

25083 
25084 var FontRendererFactory = (function FontRendererFactoryClosure() {
25085   function getLong(data, offset) {
25086     return (data[offset] << 24) | (data[offset + 1] << 16) |
25087            (data[offset + 2] << 8) | data[offset + 3];
25088   }
25089 
25090   function getUshort(data, offset) {
25091     return (data[offset] << 8) | data[offset + 1];
25092   }
25093 
25094   function parseCmap(data, start, end) {
25095     var offset = getUshort(data, start + 2) === 1 ? getLong(data, start + 8) :
25096                                                     getLong(data, start + 16);
25097     var format = getUshort(data, start + offset);
25098     if (format === 4) {
25099       var length = getUshort(data, start + offset + 2);
25100       var segCount = getUshort(data, start + offset + 6) >> 1;
25101       var p = start + offset + 14;
25102       var ranges = [];
25103       for (var i = 0; i < segCount; i++, p += 2) {
25104         ranges[i] = {end: getUshort(data, p)};
25105       }
25106       p += 2;
25107       for (var i = 0; i < segCount; i++, p += 2) {
25108         ranges[i].start = getUshort(data, p);
25109       }
25110       for (var i = 0; i < segCount; i++, p += 2) {
25111         ranges[i].idDelta = getUshort(data, p);
25112       }
25113       for (var i = 0; i < segCount; i++, p += 2) {
25114         var idOffset = getUshort(data, p);
25115         if (idOffset === 0) {
25116           continue;
25117         }
25118         ranges[i].ids = [];
25119         for (var j = 0, jj = ranges[i].end - ranges[i].start + 1; j < jj; j++) {
25120           ranges[i].ids[j] = getUshort(data, p + idOffset);
25121           idOffset += 2;
25122         }
25123       }
25124       return ranges;
25125     } else if (format === 12) {
25126       var length = getLong(data, start + offset + 4);
25127       var groups = getLong(data, start + offset + 12);
25128       var p = start + offset + 16;
25129       var ranges = [];
25130       for (var i = 0; i < groups; i++) {
25131         ranges.push({
25132           start: getLong(data, p),
25133           end: getLong(data, p + 4),
25134           idDelta: getLong(data, p + 8) - getLong(data, p)
25135         });
25136         p += 12;
25137       }
25138       return ranges;
25139     }
25140     error('not supported cmap: ' + format);
25141   }
25142 
25143   function parseCff(data, start, end) {
25144     var properties = {};
25145     var parser = new CFFParser(
25146       new Stream(data, start, end - start), properties);
25147     var cff = parser.parse();
25148     return {
25149       glyphs: cff.charStrings.objects,
25150       subrs: cff.topDict.privateDict && cff.topDict.privateDict.subrsIndex &&
25151              cff.topDict.privateDict.subrsIndex.objects,
25152       gsubrs: cff.globalSubrIndex && cff.globalSubrIndex.objects
25153     };
25154   }
25155 
25156   function parseGlyfTable(glyf, loca, isGlyphLocationsLong) {
25157     var itemSize, itemDecode;
25158     if (isGlyphLocationsLong) {
25159       itemSize = 4;
25160       itemDecode = function fontItemDecodeLong(data, offset) {
25161         return (data[offset] << 24) | (data[offset + 1] << 16) |
25162                (data[offset + 2] << 8) | data[offset + 3];
25163       };
25164     } else {
25165       itemSize = 2;
25166       itemDecode = function fontItemDecode(data, offset) {
25167         return (data[offset] << 9) | (data[offset + 1] << 1);
25168       };
25169     }
25170     var glyphs = [];
25171     var startOffset = itemDecode(loca, 0);
25172     for (var j = itemSize; j < loca.length; j += itemSize) {
25173       var endOffset = itemDecode(loca, j);
25174       glyphs.push(glyf.subarray(startOffset, endOffset));
25175       startOffset = endOffset;
25176     }
25177     return glyphs;
25178   }
25179 
25180   function lookupCmap(ranges, unicode) {
25181     var code = unicode.charCodeAt(0);
25182     var l = 0, r = ranges.length - 1;
25183     while (l < r) {
25184       var c = (l + r + 1) >> 1;
25185       if (code < ranges[c].start) {
25186         r = c - 1;
25187       } else {
25188         l = c;
25189       }
25190     }
25191     if (ranges[l].start <= code && code <= ranges[l].end) {
25192       return (ranges[l].idDelta + (ranges[l].ids ?
25193         ranges[l].ids[code - ranges[l].start] : code)) & 0xFFFF;
25194     }
25195     return 0;
25196   }
25197 
25198   function compileGlyf(code, js, font) {
25199     function moveTo(x, y) {
25200       js.push('c.moveTo(' + x + ',' + y + ');');
25201     }
25202     function lineTo(x, y) {
25203       js.push('c.lineTo(' + x + ',' + y + ');');
25204     }
25205     function quadraticCurveTo(xa, ya, x, y) {
25206       js.push('c.quadraticCurveTo(' + xa + ',' + ya + ',' +
25207                                    x + ',' + y + ');');
25208     }
25209 
25210     var i = 0;
25211     var numberOfContours = ((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) >> 16;
25212     var xMin = ((code[i + 2] << 24) | (code[i + 3] << 16)) >> 16;
25213     var yMin = ((code[i + 4] << 24) | (code[i + 5] << 16)) >> 16;
25214     var xMax = ((code[i + 6] << 24) | (code[i + 7] << 16)) >> 16;
25215     var yMax = ((code[i + 8] << 24) | (code[i + 9] << 16)) >> 16;
25216     i += 10;
25217     if (numberOfContours < 0) {
25218       // composite glyph
25219       var x = 0, y = 0;
25220       do {
25221         var flags = (code[i] << 8) | code[i + 1];
25222         var glyphIndex = (code[i + 2] << 8) | code[i + 3];
25223         i += 4;
25224         var arg1, arg2;
25225         if ((flags & 0x01)) {
25226           arg1 = ((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) >> 16;
25227           arg2 = ((code[i + 2] << 24) | (code[i + 3] << 16)) >> 16;
25228           i += 4;
25229         } else {
25230           arg1 = code[i++]; arg2 = code[i++];
25231         }
25232         if ((flags & 0x02)) {
25233            x = arg1;
25234            y = arg2;
25235         } else {
25236            x = 0; y = 0; // TODO "they are points" ?
25237         }
25238         var scaleX = 1, scaleY = 1, scale01 = 0, scale10 = 0;
25239         if ((flags & 0x08)) {
25240           scaleX =
25241           scaleY = ((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) / 1073741824;
25242           i += 2;
25243         } else if ((flags & 0x40)) {
25244           scaleX = ((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) / 1073741824;
25245           scaleY = ((code[i + 2] << 24) | (code[i + 3] << 16)) / 1073741824;
25246           i += 4;
25247         } else if ((flags & 0x80)) {
25248           scaleX = ((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) / 1073741824;
25249           scale01 = ((code[i + 2] << 24) | (code[i + 3] << 16)) / 1073741824;
25250           scale10 = ((code[i + 4] << 24) | (code[i + 5] << 16)) / 1073741824;
25251           scaleY = ((code[i + 6] << 24) | (code[i + 7] << 16)) / 1073741824;
25252           i += 8;
25253         }
25254         var subglyph = font.glyphs[glyphIndex];
25255         if (subglyph) {
25256           js.push('c.save();');
25257           js.push('c.transform(' + scaleX + ',' + scale01 + ',' +
25258                   scale10 + ',' + scaleY + ',' + x + ',' + y + ');');
25259           compileGlyf(subglyph, js, font);
25260           js.push('c.restore();');
25261         }
25262       } while ((flags & 0x20));
25263     } else {
25264       // simple glyph
25265       var endPtsOfContours = [];
25266       for (var j = 0; j < numberOfContours; j++) {
25267         endPtsOfContours.push((code[i] << 8) | code[i + 1]);
25268         i += 2;
25269       }
25270       var instructionLength = (code[i] << 8) | code[i + 1];
25271       i += 2 + instructionLength; // skipping the instructions
25272       var numberOfPoints = endPtsOfContours[endPtsOfContours.length - 1] + 1;
25273       var points = [];
25274       while (points.length < numberOfPoints) {
25275         var flags = code[i++], repeat = 1;
25276         if ((flags & 0x08)) {
25277           repeat += code[i++];
25278         }
25279         while (repeat-- > 0) {
25280           points.push({flags: flags});
25281         }
25282       }
25283       var x = 0, y = 0;
25284       for (var j = 0; j < numberOfPoints; j++) {
25285         switch (points[j].flags & 0x12) {
25286           case 0x00:
25287             x += ((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) >> 16;
25288             i += 2;
25289             break;
25290           case 0x02:
25291             x -= code[i++];
25292             break;
25293           case 0x12:
25294             x += code[i++];
25295             break;
25296         }
25297         points[j].x = x;
25298       }
25299       for (var j = 0; j < numberOfPoints; j++) {
25300         switch (points[j].flags & 0x24) {
25301           case 0x00:
25302             y += ((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) >> 16;
25303             i += 2;
25304             break;
25305           case 0x04:
25306             y -= code[i++];
25307             break;
25308           case 0x24:
25309             y += code[i++];
25310             break;
25311         }
25312         points[j].y = y;
25313       }
25314 
25315       var startPoint = 0;
25316       for (var i = 0; i < numberOfContours; i++) {
25317         var endPoint = endPtsOfContours[i];
25318         // contours might have implicit points, which is located in the middle
25319         // between two neighboring off-curve points
25320         var contour = points.slice(startPoint, endPoint + 1);
25321         if ((contour[0].flags & 1)) {
25322           contour.push(contour[0]); // using start point at the contour end
25323         } else if ((contour[contour.length - 1].flags & 1)) {
25324           // first is off-curve point, trying to use one from the end
25325           contour.unshift(contour[contour.length - 1]);
25326         } else {
25327           // start and end are off-curve points, creating implicit one
25328           var p = {
25329             flags: 1,
25330             x: (contour[0].x + contour[contour.length - 1].x) / 2,
25331             y: (contour[0].y + contour[contour.length - 1].y) / 2
25332           };
25333           contour.unshift(p);
25334           contour.push(p);
25335         }
25336         moveTo(contour[0].x, contour[0].y);
25337         for (var j = 1, jj = contour.length; j < jj; j++) {
25338           if ((contour[j].flags & 1)) {
25339             lineTo(contour[j].x, contour[j].y);
25340           } else if ((contour[j + 1].flags & 1)){
25341             quadraticCurveTo(contour[j].x, contour[j].y,
25342                              contour[j + 1].x, contour[j + 1].y);
25343             j++;
25344           } else {
25345             quadraticCurveTo(contour[j].x, contour[j].y,
25346               (contour[j].x + contour[j + 1].x) / 2,
25347               (contour[j].y + contour[j + 1].y) / 2);
25348           }
25349         }
25350         startPoint = endPoint + 1;
25351       }
25352     }
25353   }
25354 
25355   function compileCharString(code, js, font) {
25356     var stack = [];
25357     var x = 0, y = 0;
25358     var stems = 0;
25359 
25360     function moveTo(x, y) {
25361       js.push('c.moveTo(' + x + ',' + y + ');');
25362     }
25363     function lineTo(x, y) {
25364       js.push('c.lineTo(' + x + ',' + y + ');');
25365     }
25366     function bezierCurveTo(x1, y1, x2, y2, x, y) {
25367       js.push('c.bezierCurveTo(' + x1 + ',' + y1 + ',' + x2 + ',' + y2 + ',' +
25368                                    x + ',' + y + ');');
25369     }
25370 
25371     function parse(code) {
25372       var i = 0;
25373       while (i < code.length) {
25374         var stackClean = false;
25375         var v = code[i++];
25376         switch (v) {
25377           case 1: // hstem
25378             stems += stack.length >> 1;
25379             stackClean = true;
25380             break;
25381           case 3: // vstem
25382             stems += stack.length >> 1;
25383             stackClean = true;
25384             break;
25385           case 4: // vmoveto
25386             y += stack.pop();
25387             moveTo(x, y);
25388             stackClean = true;
25389             break;
25390           case 5: // rlineto
25391             while (stack.length > 0) {
25392               x += stack.shift();
25393               y += stack.shift();
25394               lineTo(x, y);
25395             }
25396             break;
25397           case 6: // hlineto
25398             while (stack.length > 0) {
25399               x += stack.shift();
25400               lineTo(x, y);
25401               if (stack.length === 0) {
25402                 break;
25403               }
25404               y += stack.shift();
25405               lineTo(x, y);
25406             }
25407             break;
25408           case 7: // vlineto
25409             while (stack.length > 0) {
25410               y += stack.shift();
25411               lineTo(x, y);
25412               if (stack.length === 0) {
25413                 break;
25414               }
25415               x += stack.shift();
25416               lineTo(x, y);
25417             }
25418             break;
25419           case 8: // rrcurveto
25420             while (stack.length > 0) {
25421               var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y + stack.shift();
25422               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25423               x = xb + stack.shift(); y = yb + stack.shift();
25424               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25425             }
25426             break;
25427           case 10: // callsubr
25428             var n = stack.pop() + font.subrsBias;
25429             var subrCode = font.subrs[n];
25430             if (subrCode) {
25431               parse(subrCode);
25432             }
25433             break;
25434           case 11: // return
25435             return;
25436           case 12:
25437             v = code[i++];
25438             switch (v) {
25439               case 34: // flex
25440                 var xa = x + stack.shift();
25441                 var xb = xa + stack.shift(), y1 = y + stack.shift();
25442                 x = xb + stack.shift();
25443                 bezierCurveTo(xa, y, xb, y1, x, y1);
25444                 var xa = x + stack.shift();
25445                 var xb = xa + stack.shift();
25446                 x = xb + stack.shift();
25447                 bezierCurveTo(xa, y1, xb, y, x, y);
25448                 break;
25449               case 35: // flex
25450                 var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y + stack.shift();
25451                 var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25452                 x = xb + stack.shift(); y = yb + stack.shift();
25453                 bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25454                 var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y + stack.shift();
25455                 var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25456                 x = xb + stack.shift(); y = yb + stack.shift();
25457                 bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25458                 stack.pop(); // fd
25459                 break;
25460               case 36: // hflex1
25461                 var xa = x + stack.shift(), y1 = y + stack.shift();
25462                 var xb = xa + stack.shift(), y2 = y1 + stack.shift();
25463                 x = xb + stack.shift();
25464                 bezierCurveTo(xa, y1, xb, y2, x, y2);
25465                 var xa = x + stack.shift();
25466                 var xb = xa + stack.shift(), y3 = y2 + stack.shift();
25467                 x = xb + stack.shift();
25468                 bezierCurveTo(xa, y2, xb, y3, x, y);
25469                 break;
25470               case 37: // flex1
25471                 var x0 = x, y0 = y;
25472                 var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y + stack.shift();
25473                 var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25474                 x = xb + stack.shift(); y = yb + stack.shift();
25475                 bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25476                 var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y + stack.shift();
25477                 var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25478                 x = xb; y = yb;
25479                 if (Math.abs(x - x0) > Math.abs(y - y0))
25480                   x += stack.shift();
25481                 else
25482                   y += stack.shift();
25483                 bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25484                 break;
25485               default:
25486                 error('unknown operator: 12 ' + v);
25487             }
25488             break;
25489           case 14: // endchar
25490             if (stack.length >= 4) {
25491               var achar = stack.pop();
25492               var bchar = stack.pop();
25493               y = stack.pop();
25494               x = stack.pop();
25495               js.push('c.save();');
25496               js.push('c.translate('+ x + ',' + y + ');');
25497               var gid = lookupCmap(font.cmap, String.fromCharCode(
25498                 font.glyphNameMap[Encodings.StandardEncoding[achar]]));
25499               compileCharString(font.glyphs[gid], js, font);
25500               js.push('c.restore();');
25501 
25502               gid = lookupCmap(font.cmap, String.fromCharCode(
25503                 font.glyphNameMap[Encodings.StandardEncoding[bchar]]));
25504               compileCharString(font.glyphs[gid], js, font);
25505             }
25506             return;
25507           case 18: // hstemhm
25508             stems += stack.length >> 1;
25509             stackClean = true;
25510             break;
25511           case 19: // hintmask
25512             stems += stack.length >> 1;
25513             i += (stems + 7) >> 3;
25514             stackClean = true;
25515             break;
25516           case 20: // cntrmask
25517             stems += stack.length >> 1;
25518             i += (stems + 7) >> 3;
25519             stackClean = true;
25520             break;
25521           case 21: // rmoveto
25522             y += stack.pop();
25523             x += stack.pop();
25524             moveTo(x, y);
25525             stackClean = true;
25526             break;
25527           case 22: // hmoveto
25528             x += stack.pop();
25529             moveTo(x, y);
25530             stackClean = true;
25531             break;
25532           case 23: // vstemhm
25533             stems += stack.length >> 1;
25534             stackClean = true;
25535             break;
25536           case 24: // rcurveline
25537             while (stack.length > 2) {
25538               var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y + stack.shift();
25539               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25540               x = xb + stack.shift(); y = yb + stack.shift();
25541               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25542             }
25543             x += stack.shift();
25544             y += stack.shift();
25545             lineTo(x, y);
25546             break;
25547           case 25: // rlinecurve
25548             while (stack.length > 6) {
25549               x += stack.shift();
25550               y += stack.shift();
25551               lineTo(x, y);
25552             }
25553             var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y + stack.shift();
25554             var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25555             x = xb + stack.shift(); y = yb + stack.shift();
25556             bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25557             break;
25558           case 26: // vvcurveto
25559             if (stack.length % 2) {
25560               x += stack.shift();
25561             }
25562             while (stack.length > 0) {
25563               var xa = x, ya = y + stack.shift();
25564               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25565               x = xb; y = yb + stack.shift();
25566               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25567             }
25568             break;
25569           case 27: // hhcurveto
25570             if (stack.length % 2) {
25571               y += stack.shift();
25572             }
25573             while (stack.length > 0) {
25574               var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y;
25575               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25576               x = xb + stack.shift(); y = yb;
25577               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25578             }
25579             break;
25580           case 28:
25581             stack.push(((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16)) >> 16);
25582             i += 2;
25583             break;
25584           case 29: // callgsubr
25585             var n = stack.pop() + font.gsubrsBias;
25586             var subrCode = font.gsubrs[n];
25587             if (subrCode) {
25588               parse(subrCode);
25589             }
25590             break;
25591           case 30: // vhcurveto
25592             while (stack.length > 0) {
25593               var xa = x, ya = y + stack.shift();
25594               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25595               x = xb + stack.shift();
25596               y = yb + (stack.length === 1 ? stack.shift() : 0);
25597               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25598               if (stack.length === 0) {
25599                 break;
25600               }
25601 
25602               var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y;
25603               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25604               y = yb + stack.shift();
25605               x = xb + (stack.length === 1 ? stack.shift() : 0);
25606               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25607             }
25608             break;
25609           case 31: // hvcurveto
25610             while (stack.length > 0) {
25611               var xa = x + stack.shift(), ya = y;
25612               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25613               y = yb + stack.shift();
25614               x = xb + (stack.length === 1 ? stack.shift() : 0);
25615               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25616               if (stack.length === 0) {
25617                 break;
25618               }
25619 
25620               var xa = x, ya = y + stack.shift();
25621               var xb = xa + stack.shift(), yb = ya + stack.shift();
25622               x = xb + stack.shift();
25623               y = yb + (stack.length === 1 ? stack.shift() : 0);
25624               bezierCurveTo(xa, ya, xb, yb, x, y);
25625             }
25626             break;
25627           default:
25628             if (v < 32)
25629               error('unknown operator: ' + v);
25630             if (v < 247)
25631               stack.push(v - 139);
25632             else if (v < 251)
25633               stack.push((v - 247) * 256 + code[i++] + 108);
25634             else if (v < 255)
25635               stack.push(-(v - 251) * 256 - code[i++] - 108);
25636             else {
25637               stack.push(((code[i] << 24) | (code[i + 1] << 16) |
25638                          (code[i + 2] << 8) | code[i + 3]) / 65536);
25639               i += 4;
25640             }
25641             break;
25642         }
25643         if (stackClean) {
25644           stack.length = 0;
25645         }
25646       }
25647     }
25648     parse(code);
25649   }
25650 
25651   function TrueTypeCompiled(glyphs, cmap, fontMatrix) {
25652     this.glyphs = glyphs;
25653     this.cmap = cmap;
25654     this.fontMatrix = fontMatrix || [0.000488, 0, 0, 0.000488, 0, 0];
25655 
25656     this.compiledGlyphs = [];
25657   }
25658 
25659   var noop = function () {};
25660 
25661   TrueTypeCompiled.prototype = {
25662     getPathGenerator: function (unicode) {
25663       var gid = lookupCmap(this.cmap, unicode);
25664       var fn = this.compiledGlyphs[gid];
25665       if (!fn) {
25666         this.compiledGlyphs[gid] = fn = this.compileGlyph(this.glyphs[gid]);
25667       }
25668       return fn;
25669     },
25670     compileGlyph: function (code) {
25671       if (!code || code.length === 0 || code[0] === 14) {
25672         return noop;
25673       }
25674 
25675       var js = [];
25676       js.push('c.save();');
25677       js.push('c.transform(' + this.fontMatrix.join(',') + ');');
25678       js.push('c.scale(size, -size);');
25679 
25680       var stack = [], x = 0, y = 0;
25681       compileGlyf(code, js, this);
25682 
25683       js.push('c.restore();');
25684 
25685       /*jshint -W054 */
25686       return new Function('c', 'size', js.join('\n'));
25687     }
25688   };
25689 
25690   function Type2Compiled(cffInfo, cmap, fontMatrix, glyphNameMap) {
25691     this.glyphs = cffInfo.glyphs;
25692     this.gsubrs = cffInfo.gsubrs || [];
25693     this.subrs = cffInfo.subrs || [];
25694     this.cmap = cmap;
25695     this.glyphNameMap = glyphNameMap || GlyphsUnicode;
25696     this.fontMatrix = fontMatrix || [0.001, 0, 0, 0.001, 0, 0];
25697 
25698     this.compiledGlyphs = [];
25699     this.gsubrsBias = this.gsubrs.length < 1240 ? 107 :
25700                       this.gsubrs.length < 33900 ? 1131 : 32768;
25701     this.subrsBias = this.subrs.length < 1240 ? 107 :
25702                      this.subrs.length < 33900 ? 1131 : 32768;
25703   }
25704 
25705   Type2Compiled.prototype = {
25706     getPathGenerator: function (unicode) {
25707       var gid = lookupCmap(this.cmap, unicode);
25708       var fn = this.compiledGlyphs[gid];
25709       if (!fn) {
25710         this.compiledGlyphs[gid] = fn = this.compileGlyph(this.glyphs[gid]);
25711       }
25712       return fn;
25713     },
25714     compileGlyph: function (code) {
25715       if (!code || code.length === 0 || code[0] === 14) {
25716         return noop;
25717       }
25718 
25719       var js = [];
25720       js.push('c.save();');
25721       js.push('c.transform(' + this.fontMatrix.join(',') + ');');
25722       js.push('c.scale(size, -size);');
25723 
25724       var stack = [], x = 0, y = 0;
25725       compileCharString(code, js, this);
25726 
25727       js.push('c.restore();');
25728 
25729       /*jshint -W054 */
25730       return new Function('c', 'size', js.join('\n'));
25731     }
25732   };
25733 
25734   return {
25735     create: function FontRendererFactory_create(font) {
25736       var data = new Uint8Array(font.data);
25737       var cmap, glyf, loca, cff, indexToLocFormat, unitsPerEm;
25738       var numTables = getUshort(data, 4);
25739       for (var i = 0, p = 12; i < numTables; i++, p += 16) {
25740         var tag = String.fromCharCode.apply(null, data.subarray(p, p + 4));
25741         var offset = getLong(data, p + 8);
25742         var length = getLong(data, p + 12);
25743         switch (tag) {
25744           case 'cmap':
25745             cmap = parseCmap(data, offset, offset + length);
25746             break;
25747           case 'glyf':
25748             glyf = data.subarray(offset, offset + length);
25749             break;
25750           case 'loca':
25751             loca = data.subarray(offset, offset + length);
25752             break;
25753           case 'head':
25754             unitsPerEm = getUshort(data, offset + 18);
25755             indexToLocFormat = getUshort(data, offset + 50);
25756             break;
25757           case 'CFF ':
25758             cff = parseCff(data, offset, offset + length);
25759             break;
25760         }
25761       }
25762 
25763       if (glyf) {
25764         var fontMatrix = !unitsPerEm ? font.fontMatrix :
25765           [1 / unitsPerEm, 0, 0, 1 / unitsPerEm, 0, 0];
25766         return new TrueTypeCompiled(
25767           parseGlyfTable(glyf, loca, indexToLocFormat), cmap, fontMatrix);
25768       } else {
25769         return new Type2Compiled(cff, cmap, font.fontMatrix, font.glyphNameMap);
25770       }
25771     }
25772   };
25773 })();
