34906   function FlateStream(stream) {
34907     var bytes = stream.getBytes();
34908     var bytesPos = 0;
34909 
34910     this.dict = stream.dict;
34911     var cmf = bytes[bytesPos++];
34912     var flg = bytes[bytesPos++];
34913     if (cmf == -1 || flg == -1)
34914       error('Invalid header in flate stream: ' + cmf + ', ' + flg);
34915     if ((cmf & 0x0f) != 0x08)
34916       error('Unknown compression method in flate stream: ' + cmf + ', ' + flg);
34917     if ((((cmf << 8) + flg) % 31) !== 0)
34918       error('Bad FCHECK in flate stream: ' + cmf + ', ' + flg);
34919     if (flg & 0x20)
34920       error('FDICT bit set in flate stream: ' + cmf + ', ' + flg);
34921 
34922     this.bytes = bytes;
34923     this.bytesPos = bytesPos;
34924 
34925     this.codeSize = 0;
34926     this.codeBuf = 0;
34927 
34928     DecodeStream.call(this);
34929   }
34930 
34931   FlateStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
34932 
34933   FlateStream.prototype.getBits = function FlateStream_getBits(bits) {
34934     var codeSize = this.codeSize;
34935     var codeBuf = this.codeBuf;
34936     var bytes = this.bytes;
34937     var bytesPos = this.bytesPos;
34938 
34939     var b;
34940     while (codeSize < bits) {
34941       if (typeof (b = bytes[bytesPos++]) == 'undefined')
34942         error('Bad encoding in flate stream');
34943       codeBuf |= b << codeSize;
34944       codeSize += 8;
34945     }
34946     b = codeBuf & ((1 << bits) - 1);
34947     this.codeBuf = codeBuf >> bits;
34948     this.codeSize = codeSize -= bits;
34949     this.bytesPos = bytesPos;
34950     return b;
34951   };
34952 
34953   FlateStream.prototype.getCode = function FlateStream_getCode(table) {
34954     var codes = table[0];
34955     var maxLen = table[1];
34956     var codeSize = this.codeSize;
34957     var codeBuf = this.codeBuf;
34958     var bytes = this.bytes;
34959     var bytesPos = this.bytesPos;
34960 
34961     while (codeSize < maxLen) {
34962       var b;
34963       if (typeof (b = bytes[bytesPos++]) == 'undefined')
34964         error('Bad encoding in flate stream');
34965       codeBuf |= (b << codeSize);
34966       codeSize += 8;
34967     }
34968     var code = codes[codeBuf & ((1 << maxLen) - 1)];
34969     var codeLen = code >> 16;
34970     var codeVal = code & 0xffff;
34971     if (codeSize === 0 || codeSize < codeLen || codeLen === 0)
34972       error('Bad encoding in flate stream');
34973     this.codeBuf = (codeBuf >> codeLen);
34974     this.codeSize = (codeSize - codeLen);
34975     this.bytesPos = bytesPos;
34976     return codeVal;
34977   };
34978 
34979   FlateStream.prototype.generateHuffmanTable =
34980     function flateStreamGenerateHuffmanTable(lengths) {
34981     var n = lengths.length;
34982 
34983     // find max code length
34984     var maxLen = 0;
34985     for (var i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
34986       if (lengths[i] > maxLen)
34987         maxLen = lengths[i];
34988     }
34989 
34990     // build the table
34991     var size = 1 << maxLen;
34992     var codes = new Uint32Array(size);
34993     for (var len = 1, code = 0, skip = 2;
34994          len <= maxLen;
34995          ++len, code <<= 1, skip <<= 1) {
34996       for (var val = 0; val < n; ++val) {
34997         if (lengths[val] == len) {
34998           // bit-reverse the code
34999           var code2 = 0;
35000           var t = code;
35001           for (var i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
35002             code2 = (code2 << 1) | (t & 1);
35003             t >>= 1;
35004           }
35005 
35006           // fill the table entries
35007           for (var i = code2; i < size; i += skip)
35008             codes[i] = (len << 16) | val;
35009 
35010           ++code;
35011         }
35012       }
35013     }
35014 
35015     return [codes, maxLen];
35016   };
35017 
35018   FlateStream.prototype.readBlock = function FlateStream_readBlock() {
35019     // read block header
35020     var hdr = this.getBits(3);
35021     if (hdr & 1)
35022       this.eof = true;
35023     hdr >>= 1;
35024 
35025     if (hdr === 0) { // uncompressed block
35026       var bytes = this.bytes;
35027       var bytesPos = this.bytesPos;
35028       var b;
35029 
35030       if (typeof (b = bytes[bytesPos++]) == 'undefined')
35031         error('Bad block header in flate stream');
35032       var blockLen = b;
35033       if (typeof (b = bytes[bytesPos++]) == 'undefined')
35034         error('Bad block header in flate stream');
35035       blockLen |= (b << 8);
35036       if (typeof (b = bytes[bytesPos++]) == 'undefined')
35037         error('Bad block header in flate stream');
35038       var check = b;
35039       if (typeof (b = bytes[bytesPos++]) == 'undefined')
35040         error('Bad block header in flate stream');
35041       check |= (b << 8);
35042       if (check != (~blockLen & 0xffff) &&
35043           (blockLen !== 0 || check !== 0)) {
35044         // Ignoring error for bad "empty" block (see issue 1277)
35045         error('Bad uncompressed block length in flate stream');
35046       }
35047 
35048       this.codeBuf = 0;
35049       this.codeSize = 0;
35050 
35051       var bufferLength = this.bufferLength;
35052       var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + blockLen);
35053       var end = bufferLength + blockLen;
35054       this.bufferLength = end;
35055       for (var n = bufferLength; n < end; ++n) {
35056         if (typeof (b = bytes[bytesPos++]) == 'undefined') {
35057           this.eof = true;
35058           break;
35059         }
35060         buffer[n] = b;
35061       }
35062       this.bytesPos = bytesPos;
35063       return;
35064     }
35065 
35066     var litCodeTable;
35067     var distCodeTable;
35068     if (hdr == 1) { // compressed block, fixed codes
35069       litCodeTable = fixedLitCodeTab;
35070       distCodeTable = fixedDistCodeTab;
35071     } else if (hdr == 2) { // compressed block, dynamic codes
35072       var numLitCodes = this.getBits(5) + 257;
35073       var numDistCodes = this.getBits(5) + 1;
35074       var numCodeLenCodes = this.getBits(4) + 4;
35075 
35076       // build the code lengths code table
35077       var codeLenCodeLengths = new Uint8Array(codeLenCodeMap.length);
35078 
35079       for (var i = 0; i < numCodeLenCodes; ++i)
35080         codeLenCodeLengths[codeLenCodeMap[i]] = this.getBits(3);
35081       var codeLenCodeTab = this.generateHuffmanTable(codeLenCodeLengths);
35082 
35083       // build the literal and distance code tables
35084       var len = 0;
35085       var i = 0;
35086       var codes = numLitCodes + numDistCodes;
35087       var codeLengths = new Uint8Array(codes);
35088       while (i < codes) {
35089         var code = this.getCode(codeLenCodeTab);
35090         if (code == 16) {
35091           var bitsLength = 2, bitsOffset = 3, what = len;
35092         } else if (code == 17) {
35093           var bitsLength = 3, bitsOffset = 3, what = (len = 0);
35094         } else if (code == 18) {
35095           var bitsLength = 7, bitsOffset = 11, what = (len = 0);
35096         } else {
35097           codeLengths[i++] = len = code;
35098           continue;
35099         }
35100 
35101         var repeatLength = this.getBits(bitsLength) + bitsOffset;
35102         while (repeatLength-- > 0)
35103           codeLengths[i++] = what;
35104       }
35105 
35106       litCodeTable =
35107         this.generateHuffmanTable(codeLengths.subarray(0, numLitCodes));
35108       distCodeTable =
35109         this.generateHuffmanTable(codeLengths.subarray(numLitCodes, codes));
35110     } else {
35111       error('Unknown block type in flate stream');
35112     }
35113 
35114     var buffer = this.buffer;
35115     var limit = buffer ? buffer.length : 0;
35116     var pos = this.bufferLength;
35117     while (true) {
35118       var code1 = this.getCode(litCodeTable);
35119       if (code1 < 256) {
35120         if (pos + 1 >= limit) {
35121           buffer = this.ensureBuffer(pos + 1);
35122           limit = buffer.length;
35123         }
35124         buffer[pos++] = code1;
35125         continue;
35126       }
35127       if (code1 == 256) {
35128         this.bufferLength = pos;
35129         return;
35130       }
35131       code1 -= 257;
35132       code1 = lengthDecode[code1];
35133       var code2 = code1 >> 16;
35134       if (code2 > 0)
35135         code2 = this.getBits(code2);
35136       var len = (code1 & 0xffff) + code2;
35137       code1 = this.getCode(distCodeTable);
35138       code1 = distDecode[code1];
35139       code2 = code1 >> 16;
35140       if (code2 > 0)
35141         code2 = this.getBits(code2);
35142       var dist = (code1 & 0xffff) + code2;
35143       if (pos + len >= limit) {
35144         buffer = this.ensureBuffer(pos + len);
35145         limit = buffer.length;
35146       }
35147       for (var k = 0; k < len; ++k, ++pos)
35148         buffer[pos] = buffer[pos - dist];
35149     }
35150   };
35151 
35152   return FlateStream;
35153 })();
35154 
35155 var PredictorStream = (function PredictorStreamClosure() {
35156   function PredictorStream(str, params) {
35157     var predictor = this.predictor = params.get('Predictor') || 1;
35158 
35159     if (predictor <= 1)
35160       return str; // no prediction
35161     if (predictor !== 2 && (predictor < 10 || predictor > 15))
35162       error('Unsupported predictor: ' + predictor);
35163 
35164     if (predictor === 2)
35165       this.readBlock = this.readBlockTiff;
35166     else
35167       this.readBlock = this.readBlockPng;
35168 
35169     this.str = str;
35170     this.dict = str.dict;
35171 
35172     var colors = this.colors = params.get('Colors') || 1;
35173     var bits = this.bits = params.get('BitsPerComponent') || 8;
35174     var columns = this.columns = params.get('Columns') || 1;
35175 
35176     this.pixBytes = (colors * bits + 7) >> 3;
35177     this.rowBytes = (columns * colors * bits + 7) >> 3;
35178 
35179     DecodeStream.call(this);
35180     return this;
35181   }
35182 
35183   PredictorStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
35184 
35185   PredictorStream.prototype.readBlockTiff =
35186     function predictorStreamReadBlockTiff() {
35187     var rowBytes = this.rowBytes;
35188 
35189     var bufferLength = this.bufferLength;
35190     var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + rowBytes);
35191 
35192     var bits = this.bits;
35193     var colors = this.colors;
35194 
35195     var rawBytes = this.str.getBytes(rowBytes);
35196     this.eof = !rawBytes.length;
35197     if (this.eof) {
35198       return;
35199     }
35200 
35201     var inbuf = 0, outbuf = 0;
35202     var inbits = 0, outbits = 0;
35203     var pos = bufferLength;
35204 
35205     if (bits === 1) {
35206       for (var i = 0; i < rowBytes; ++i) {
35207         var c = rawBytes[i];
35208         inbuf = (inbuf << 8) | c;
35209         // bitwise addition is exclusive or
35210         // first shift inbuf and then add
35211         buffer[pos++] = (c ^ (inbuf >> colors)) & 0xFF;
35212         // truncate inbuf (assumes colors < 16)
35213         inbuf &= 0xFFFF;
35214       }
35215     } else if (bits === 8) {
35216       for (var i = 0; i < colors; ++i)
35217         buffer[pos++] = rawBytes[i];
35218       for (; i < rowBytes; ++i) {
35219         buffer[pos] = buffer[pos - colors] + rawBytes[i];
35220         pos++;
35221       }
35222     } else {
35223       var compArray = new Uint8Array(colors + 1);
35224       var bitMask = (1 << bits) - 1;
35225       var j = 0, k = bufferLength;
35226       var columns = this.columns;
35227       for (var i = 0; i < columns; ++i) {
35228         for (var kk = 0; kk < colors; ++kk) {
35229           if (inbits < bits) {
35230             inbuf = (inbuf << 8) | (rawBytes[j++] & 0xFF);
35231             inbits += 8;
35232           }
35233           compArray[kk] = (compArray[kk] +
35234                            (inbuf >> (inbits - bits))) & bitMask;
35235           inbits -= bits;
35236           outbuf = (outbuf << bits) | compArray[kk];
35237           outbits += bits;
35238           if (outbits >= 8) {
35239             buffer[k++] = (outbuf >> (outbits - 8)) & 0xFF;
35240             outbits -= 8;
35241           }
35242         }
35243       }
35244       if (outbits > 0) {
35245         buffer[k++] = (outbuf << (8 - outbits)) +
35246         (inbuf & ((1 << (8 - outbits)) - 1));
35247       }
35248     }
35249     this.bufferLength += rowBytes;
35250   };
35251 
35252   PredictorStream.prototype.readBlockPng =
35253     function predictorStreamReadBlockPng() {
35254 
35255     var rowBytes = this.rowBytes;
35256     var pixBytes = this.pixBytes;
35257 
35258     var predictor = this.str.getByte();
35259     var rawBytes = this.str.getBytes(rowBytes);
35260     this.eof = !rawBytes.length;
35261     if (this.eof) {
35262       return;
35263     }
35264 
35265     var bufferLength = this.bufferLength;
35266     var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + rowBytes);
35267 
35268     var prevRow = buffer.subarray(bufferLength - rowBytes, bufferLength);
35269     if (prevRow.length === 0)
35270       prevRow = new Uint8Array(rowBytes);
35271 
35272     var j = bufferLength;
35273     switch (predictor) {
35274       case 0:
35275         for (var i = 0; i < rowBytes; ++i)
35276           buffer[j++] = rawBytes[i];
35277         break;
35278       case 1:
35279         for (var i = 0; i < pixBytes; ++i)
35280           buffer[j++] = rawBytes[i];
35281         for (; i < rowBytes; ++i) {
35282           buffer[j] = (buffer[j - pixBytes] + rawBytes[i]) & 0xFF;
35283           j++;
35284         }
35285         break;
35286       case 2:
35287         for (var i = 0; i < rowBytes; ++i)
35288           buffer[j++] = (prevRow[i] + rawBytes[i]) & 0xFF;
35289         break;
35290       case 3:
35291         for (var i = 0; i < pixBytes; ++i)
35292           buffer[j++] = (prevRow[i] >> 1) + rawBytes[i];
35293         for (; i < rowBytes; ++i) {
35294           buffer[j] = (((prevRow[i] + buffer[j - pixBytes]) >> 1) +
35295                            rawBytes[i]) & 0xFF;
35296           j++;
35297         }
35298         break;
35299       case 4:
35300         // we need to save the up left pixels values. the simplest way
35301         // is to create a new buffer
35302         for (var i = 0; i < pixBytes; ++i) {
35303           var up = prevRow[i];
35304           var c = rawBytes[i];
35305           buffer[j++] = up + c;
35306         }
35307         for (; i < rowBytes; ++i) {
35308           var up = prevRow[i];
35309           var upLeft = prevRow[i - pixBytes];
35310           var left = buffer[j - pixBytes];
35311           var p = left + up - upLeft;
35312 
35313           var pa = p - left;
35314           if (pa < 0)
35315             pa = -pa;
35316           var pb = p - up;
35317           if (pb < 0)
35318             pb = -pb;
35319           var pc = p - upLeft;
35320           if (pc < 0)
35321             pc = -pc;
35322 
35323           var c = rawBytes[i];
35324           if (pa <= pb && pa <= pc)
35325             buffer[j++] = left + c;
35326           else if (pb <= pc)
35327             buffer[j++] = up + c;
35328           else
35329             buffer[j++] = upLeft + c;
35330         }
35331         break;
35332       default:
35333         error('Unsupported predictor: ' + predictor);
35334     }
35335     this.bufferLength += rowBytes;
35336   };
35337 
35338   return PredictorStream;
35339 })();

35407 var JpxStream = (function JpxStreamClosure() {

35415   JpxStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
35416 
35417   JpxStream.prototype.ensureBuffer = function JpxStream_ensureBuffer(req) {
35418     if (this.bufferLength)
35419       return;
35420 
35421     var jpxImage = new JpxImage();
35422     jpxImage.parse(this.bytes);
35423 
35424     var width = jpxImage.width;
35425     var height = jpxImage.height;
35426     var componentsCount = jpxImage.componentsCount;
35427     if (componentsCount != 1 && componentsCount != 3 && componentsCount != 4)
35428       error('JPX with ' + componentsCount + ' components is not supported');
35429 
35430     var data = new Uint8Array(width * height * componentsCount);
35431 
35432     for (var k = 0, kk = jpxImage.tiles.length; k < kk; k++) {
35433       var tileCompoments = jpxImage.tiles[k];
35434       var tileWidth = tileCompoments[0].width;
35435       var tileHeight = tileCompoments[0].height;
35436       var tileLeft = tileCompoments[0].left;
35437       var tileTop = tileCompoments[0].top;
35438 
35439       var dataPosition, sourcePosition, data0, data1, data2, data3, rowFeed;
35440       switch (componentsCount) {
35441         case 1:
35442           data0 = tileCompoments[0].items;
35443 
35444           dataPosition = width * tileTop + tileLeft;
35445           rowFeed = width - tileWidth;
35446           sourcePosition = 0;
35447           for (var j = 0; j < tileHeight; j++) {
35448             for (var i = 0; i < tileWidth; i++)
35449               data[dataPosition++] = data0[sourcePosition++];
35450             dataPosition += rowFeed;
35451           }
35452           break;
35453         case 3:
35454           data0 = tileCompoments[0].items;
35455           data1 = tileCompoments[1].items;
35456           data2 = tileCompoments[2].items;
35457 
35458           dataPosition = (width * tileTop + tileLeft) * 3;
35459           rowFeed = (width - tileWidth) * 3;
35460           sourcePosition = 0;
35461           for (var j = 0; j < tileHeight; j++) {
35462             for (var i = 0; i < tileWidth; i++) {
35463               data[dataPosition++] = data0[sourcePosition];
35464               data[dataPosition++] = data1[sourcePosition];
35465               data[dataPosition++] = data2[sourcePosition];
35466               sourcePosition++;
35467             }
35468             dataPosition += rowFeed;
35469           }
35470           break;
35471         case 4:
35472           data0 = tileCompoments[0].items;
35473           data1 = tileCompoments[1].items;
35474           data2 = tileCompoments[2].items;
35475           data3 = tileCompoments[3].items;
35476 
35477           dataPosition = (width * tileTop + tileLeft) * 4;
35478           rowFeed = (width - tileWidth) * 4;
35479           sourcePosition = 0;
35480           for (var j = 0; j < tileHeight; j++) {
35481             for (var i = 0; i < tileWidth; i++) {
35482               data[dataPosition++] = data0[sourcePosition];
35483               data[dataPosition++] = data1[sourcePosition];
35484               data[dataPosition++] = data2[sourcePosition];
35485               data[dataPosition++] = data3[sourcePosition];
35486               sourcePosition++;
35487             }
35488             dataPosition += rowFeed;
35489           }
35490           break;
35491       }
35492     }
35493 
35494     this.buffer = data;
35495     this.bufferLength = data.length;
35496     this.eof = true;
35497   };
35498 
35499   return JpxStream;

35506 var Jbig2Stream = (function Jbig2StreamClosure() {

35516   Jbig2Stream.prototype.ensureBuffer = function Jbig2Stream_ensureBuffer(req) {
35517     if (this.bufferLength)
35518       return;
35519 
35520     var jbig2Image = new Jbig2Image();
35521 
35522     var chunks = [], decodeParams = this.dict.get('DecodeParms');
35523     if (decodeParams && decodeParams.has('JBIG2Globals')) {

35544 var DecryptStream = (function DecryptStreamClosure() {
35545   function DecryptStream(str, decrypt) {
35546     this.str = str;
35547     this.dict = str.dict;
35548     this.decrypt = decrypt;
35549     this.nextChunk = null;
35550     this.initialized = false;
35551 
35552     DecodeStream.call(this);
35553   }
35554 
35555   var chunkSize = 512;
35556 
35557   DecryptStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
35558 
35559   DecryptStream.prototype.readBlock = function DecryptStream_readBlock() {
35560     var chunk;
35561     if (this.initialized) {
35562       chunk = this.nextChunk;
35563     } else {
35564       chunk = this.str.getBytes(chunkSize);
35565       this.initialized = true;
35566     }
35567     if (!chunk || chunk.length === 0) {
35568       this.eof = true;
35569       return;
35570     }
35571     this.nextChunk = this.str.getBytes(chunkSize);
35572     var hasMoreData = this.nextChunk && this.nextChunk.length > 0;
35573 
35574     var decrypt = this.decrypt;
35575     chunk = decrypt(chunk, !hasMoreData);
35576 
35577     var bufferLength = this.bufferLength;
35578     var i, n = chunk.length;
35579     var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + n);
35580     for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
35581       buffer[bufferLength++] = chunk[i];
35582     this.bufferLength = bufferLength;
35583   };
35584 
35585   return DecryptStream;
35586 })();

35588 var Ascii85Stream = (function Ascii85StreamClosure() {
35589   function Ascii85Stream(str) {
35590     this.str = str;
35591     this.dict = str.dict;
35592     this.input = new Uint8Array(5);
35593 
35594     DecodeStream.call(this);
35595   }
35596 
35597   Ascii85Stream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
35598 
35599   Ascii85Stream.prototype.readBlock = function Ascii85Stream_readBlock() {
35600     var TILDA_CHAR = 0x7E; // '~'
35601     var Z_LOWER_CHAR = 0x7A; // 'z'
35602     var EOF = -1;
35603 
35604     var str = this.str;
35605 
35606     var c = str.getByte();
35607     while (Lexer.isSpace(c)) {
35608       c = str.getByte();
35609     }
35610 
35611     if (c === EOF || c === TILDA_CHAR) {
35612       this.eof = true;
35613       return;
35614     }
35615 
35616     var bufferLength = this.bufferLength, buffer;
35617 
35618     // special code for z
35619     if (c == Z_LOWER_CHAR) {
35620       buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + 4);
35621       for (var i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
35622         buffer[bufferLength + i] = 0;
35623       this.bufferLength += 4;
35624     } else {
35625       var input = this.input;
35626       input[0] = c;
35627       for (var i = 1; i < 5; ++i) {
35628         c = str.getByte();
35629         while (Lexer.isSpace(c)) {
35630           c = str.getByte();
35631         }
35632 
35633         input[i] = c;
35634 
35635         if (c === EOF || c == TILDA_CHAR)
35636           break;
35637       }
35638       buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + i - 1);
35639       this.bufferLength += i - 1;
35640 
35641       // partial ending;
35642       if (i < 5) {
35643         for (; i < 5; ++i)
35644           input[i] = 0x21 + 84;
35645         this.eof = true;
35646       }
35647       var t = 0;
35648       for (var i = 0; i < 5; ++i)
35649         t = t * 85 + (input[i] - 0x21);
35650 
35651       for (var i = 3; i >= 0; --i) {
35652         buffer[bufferLength + i] = t & 0xFF;
35653         t >>= 8;
35654       }
35655     }
35656   };
35657 
35658   return Ascii85Stream;
35659 })();
35660 
35661 var AsciiHexStream = (function AsciiHexStreamClosure() {
35662   function AsciiHexStream(str) {
35663     this.str = str;
35664     this.dict = str.dict;
35665 
35666     this.firstDigit = -1;
35667 
35668     DecodeStream.call(this);
35669   }
35670 
35671   AsciiHexStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
35672 
35673   AsciiHexStream.prototype.readBlock = function AsciiHexStream_readBlock() {
35674     var UPSTREAM_BLOCK_SIZE = 8000;
35675     var bytes = this.str.getBytes(UPSTREAM_BLOCK_SIZE);
35676     if (!bytes.length) {
35677       this.eof = true;
35678       return;
35679     }
35680 
35681     var maxDecodeLength = (bytes.length + 1) >> 1;
35682     var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(this.bufferLength + maxDecodeLength);
35683     var bufferLength = this.bufferLength;
35684 
35685     var firstDigit = this.firstDigit;
35686     for (var i = 0, ii = bytes.length; i < ii; i++) {
35687       var ch = bytes[i], digit;
35688       if (ch >= 0x30 && ch <= 0x39) { // '0'-'9'
35689         digit = ch & 0x0F;
35690       } else if ((ch >= 0x41 && ch <= 0x46) || (ch >= 0x61 && ch <= 0x66)) {
35691         // 'A'-'Z', 'a'-'z'
35692         digit = (ch & 0x0F) + 9;
35693       } else if (ch === 0x3E) { // '>'
35694         this.eof = true;
35695         break;
35696       } else { // probably whitespace
35697         continue; // ignoring
35698       }
35699       if (firstDigit < 0) {
35700         firstDigit = digit;
35701       } else {
35702         buffer[bufferLength++] = (firstDigit << 4) | digit;
35703         firstDigit = -1;
35704       }
35705     }
35706     if (firstDigit >= 0 && this.eof) {
35707       // incomplete byte
35708       buffer[bufferLength++] = (firstDigit << 4);
35709       firstDigit = -1;
35710     }
35711     this.firstDigit = firstDigit;
35712     this.bufferLength = bufferLength;
35713   };
35714 
35715   return AsciiHexStream;
35716 })();
35717 
35718 var RunLengthStream = (function RunLengthStreamClosure() {
35719   function RunLengthStream(str) {
35720     this.str = str;
35721     this.dict = str.dict;
35722 
35723     DecodeStream.call(this);
35724   }
35725 
35726   RunLengthStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
35727 
35728   RunLengthStream.prototype.readBlock = function RunLengthStream_readBlock() {
35729     // The repeatHeader has following format. The first byte defines type of run
35730     // and amount of bytes to repeat/copy: n = 0 through 127 - copy next n bytes
35731     // (in addition to the second byte from the header), n = 129 through 255 -
35732     // duplicate the second byte from the header (257 - n) times, n = 128 - end.
35733     var repeatHeader = this.str.getBytes(2);
35734     if (!repeatHeader || repeatHeader.length < 2 || repeatHeader[0] == 128) {
35735       this.eof = true;
35736       return;
35737     }
35738 
35739     var bufferLength = this.bufferLength;
35740     var n = repeatHeader[0];
35741     if (n < 128) {
35742       // copy n bytes
35743       var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + n + 1);
35744       buffer[bufferLength++] = repeatHeader[1];
35745       if (n > 0) {
35746         var source = this.str.getBytes(n);
35747         buffer.set(source, bufferLength);
35748         bufferLength += n;
35749       }
35750     } else {
35751       n = 257 - n;
35752       var b = repeatHeader[1];
35753       var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(bufferLength + n + 1);
35754       for (var i = 0; i < n; i++)
35755         buffer[bufferLength++] = b;
35756     }
35757     this.bufferLength = bufferLength;
35758   };
35759 
35760   return RunLengthStream;
35761 })();

36191   function CCITTFaxStream(str, params) {
36192     this.str = str;
36193     this.dict = str.dict;
36194 
36195     params = params || new Dict();
36196 
36197     this.encoding = params.get('K') || 0;
36198     this.eoline = params.get('EndOfLine') || false;
36199     this.byteAlign = params.get('EncodedByteAlign') || false;
36200     this.columns = params.get('Columns') || 1728;
36201     this.rows = params.get('Rows') || 0;
36202     var eoblock = params.get('EndOfBlock');
36203     if (eoblock === null || eoblock === undefined)
36204       eoblock = true;
36205     this.eoblock = eoblock;
36206     this.black = params.get('BlackIs1') || false;
36207 
36208     this.codingLine = new Uint32Array(this.columns + 1);
36209     this.refLine = new Uint32Array(this.columns + 2);
36210 
36211     this.codingLine[0] = this.columns;
36212     this.codingPos = 0;
36213 
36214     this.row = 0;
36215     this.nextLine2D = this.encoding < 0;
36216     this.inputBits = 0;
36217     this.inputBuf = 0;
36218     this.outputBits = 0;
36219     this.buf = EOF;
36220 
36221     var code1;
36222     while ((code1 = this.lookBits(12)) === 0) {
36223       this.eatBits(1);
36224     }
36225     if (code1 == 1) {
36226       this.eatBits(12);
36227     }
36228     if (this.encoding > 0) {
36229       this.nextLine2D = !this.lookBits(1);
36230       this.eatBits(1);
36231     }
36232 
36233     DecodeStream.call(this);
36234   }
36235 
36236   CCITTFaxStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
36237 
36238   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.readBlock = function CCITTFaxStream_readBlock() {
36239     while (!this.eof) {
36240       var c = this.lookChar();
36241       this.buf = EOF;
36242       this.ensureBuffer(this.bufferLength + 1);
36243       this.buffer[this.bufferLength++] = c;
36244     }
36245   };
36246 
36247   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.addPixels =
36248     function ccittFaxStreamAddPixels(a1, blackPixels) {
36249     var codingLine = this.codingLine;
36250     var codingPos = this.codingPos;
36251 
36252     if (a1 > codingLine[codingPos]) {
36253       if (a1 > this.columns) {
36254         info('row is wrong length');
36255         this.err = true;
36256         a1 = this.columns;
36257       }
36258       if ((codingPos & 1) ^ blackPixels) {
36259         ++codingPos;
36260       }
36261 
36262       codingLine[codingPos] = a1;
36263     }
36264     this.codingPos = codingPos;
36265   };
36266 
36267   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.addPixelsNeg =
36268     function ccittFaxStreamAddPixelsNeg(a1, blackPixels) {
36269     var codingLine = this.codingLine;
36270     var codingPos = this.codingPos;
36271 
36272     if (a1 > codingLine[codingPos]) {
36273       if (a1 > this.columns) {
36274         info('row is wrong length');
36275         this.err = true;
36276         a1 = this.columns;
36277       }
36278       if ((codingPos & 1) ^ blackPixels)
36279         ++codingPos;
36280 
36281       codingLine[codingPos] = a1;
36282     } else if (a1 < codingLine[codingPos]) {
36283       if (a1 < 0) {
36284         info('invalid code');
36285         this.err = true;
36286         a1 = 0;
36287       }
36288       while (codingPos > 0 && a1 < codingLine[codingPos - 1])
36289         --codingPos;
36290       codingLine[codingPos] = a1;
36291     }
36292 
36293     this.codingPos = codingPos;
36294   };
36295 
36296   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.lookChar = function CCITTFaxStream_lookChar() {
36297     if (this.buf != EOF)
36298       return this.buf;
36299 
36300     var refLine = this.refLine;
36301     var codingLine = this.codingLine;
36302     var columns = this.columns;
36303 
36304     var refPos, blackPixels, bits;
36305 
36306     if (this.outputBits === 0) {
36307       if (this.eof)
36308         return null;
36309 
36310       this.err = false;
36311 
36312       var code1, code2, code3;
36313       if (this.nextLine2D) {
36314         for (var i = 0; codingLine[i] < columns; ++i)
36315           refLine[i] = codingLine[i];
36316 
36317         refLine[i++] = columns;
36318         refLine[i] = columns;
36319         codingLine[0] = 0;
36320         this.codingPos = 0;
36321         refPos = 0;
36322         blackPixels = 0;
36323 
36324         while (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36325           code1 = this.getTwoDimCode();
36326           switch (code1) {
36327             case twoDimPass:
36328               this.addPixels(refLine[refPos + 1], blackPixels);
36329               if (refLine[refPos + 1] < columns)
36330                 refPos += 2;
36331               break;
36332             case twoDimHoriz:
36333               code1 = code2 = 0;
36334               if (blackPixels) {
36335                 do {
36336                   code1 += (code3 = this.getBlackCode());
36337                 } while (code3 >= 64);
36338                 do {
36339                   code2 += (code3 = this.getWhiteCode());
36340                 } while (code3 >= 64);
36341               } else {
36342                 do {
36343                   code1 += (code3 = this.getWhiteCode());
36344                 } while (code3 >= 64);
36345                 do {
36346                   code2 += (code3 = this.getBlackCode());
36347                 } while (code3 >= 64);
36348               }
36349               this.addPixels(codingLine[this.codingPos] +
36350                              code1, blackPixels);
36351               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36352                 this.addPixels(codingLine[this.codingPos] + code2,
36353                                blackPixels ^ 1);
36354               }
36355               while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36356                      refLine[refPos] < columns) {
36357                 refPos += 2;
36358               }
36359               break;
36360             case twoDimVertR3:
36361               this.addPixels(refLine[refPos] + 3, blackPixels);
36362               blackPixels ^= 1;
36363               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36364                 ++refPos;
36365                 while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36366                        refLine[refPos] < columns)
36367                   refPos += 2;
36368               }
36369               break;
36370             case twoDimVertR2:
36371               this.addPixels(refLine[refPos] + 2, blackPixels);
36372               blackPixels ^= 1;
36373               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36374                 ++refPos;
36375                 while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36376                        refLine[refPos] < columns) {
36377                   refPos += 2;
36378                 }
36379               }
36380               break;
36381             case twoDimVertR1:
36382               this.addPixels(refLine[refPos] + 1, blackPixels);
36383               blackPixels ^= 1;
36384               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36385                 ++refPos;
36386                 while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36387                        refLine[refPos] < columns)
36388                   refPos += 2;
36389               }
36390               break;
36391             case twoDimVert0:
36392               this.addPixels(refLine[refPos], blackPixels);
36393               blackPixels ^= 1;
36394               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36395                 ++refPos;
36396                 while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36397                        refLine[refPos] < columns)
36398                   refPos += 2;
36399               }
36400               break;
36401             case twoDimVertL3:
36402               this.addPixelsNeg(refLine[refPos] - 3, blackPixels);
36403               blackPixels ^= 1;
36404               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36405                 if (refPos > 0)
36406                   --refPos;
36407                 else
36408                   ++refPos;
36409                 while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36410                        refLine[refPos] < columns)
36411                   refPos += 2;
36412               }
36413               break;
36414             case twoDimVertL2:
36415               this.addPixelsNeg(refLine[refPos] - 2, blackPixels);
36416               blackPixels ^= 1;
36417               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36418                 if (refPos > 0)
36419                   --refPos;
36420                 else
36421                   ++refPos;
36422                 while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36423                        refLine[refPos] < columns)
36424                   refPos += 2;
36425               }
36426               break;
36427             case twoDimVertL1:
36428               this.addPixelsNeg(refLine[refPos] - 1, blackPixels);
36429               blackPixels ^= 1;
36430               if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36431                 if (refPos > 0)
36432                   --refPos;
36433                 else
36434                   ++refPos;
36435 
36436                 while (refLine[refPos] <= codingLine[this.codingPos] &&
36437                        refLine[refPos] < columns)
36438                   refPos += 2;
36439               }
36440               break;
36441             case EOF:
36442               this.addPixels(columns, 0);
36443               this.eof = true;
36444               break;
36445             default:
36446               info('bad 2d code');
36447               this.addPixels(columns, 0);
36448               this.err = true;
36449           }
36450         }
36451       } else {
36452         codingLine[0] = 0;
36453         this.codingPos = 0;
36454         blackPixels = 0;
36455         while (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36456           code1 = 0;
36457           if (blackPixels) {
36458             do {
36459               code1 += (code3 = this.getBlackCode());
36460             } while (code3 >= 64);
36461           } else {
36462             do {
36463               code1 += (code3 = this.getWhiteCode());
36464             } while (code3 >= 64);
36465           }
36466           this.addPixels(codingLine[this.codingPos] + code1, blackPixels);
36467           blackPixels ^= 1;
36468         }
36469       }
36470 
36471       if (this.byteAlign)
36472         this.inputBits &= ~7;
36473 
36474       var gotEOL = false;
36475 
36476       if (!this.eoblock && this.row == this.rows - 1) {
36477         this.eof = true;
36478       } else {
36479         code1 = this.lookBits(12);
36480         while (code1 === 0) {
36481           this.eatBits(1);
36482           code1 = this.lookBits(12);
36483         }
36484         if (code1 == 1) {
36485           this.eatBits(12);
36486           gotEOL = true;
36487         } else if (code1 == EOF) {
36488           this.eof = true;
36489         }
36490       }
36491 
36492       if (!this.eof && this.encoding > 0) {
36493         this.nextLine2D = !this.lookBits(1);
36494         this.eatBits(1);
36495       }
36496 
36497       if (this.eoblock && gotEOL) {
36498         code1 = this.lookBits(12);
36499         if (code1 == 1) {
36500           this.eatBits(12);
36501           if (this.encoding > 0) {
36502             this.lookBits(1);
36503             this.eatBits(1);
36504           }
36505           if (this.encoding >= 0) {
36506             for (var i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
36507               code1 = this.lookBits(12);
36508               if (code1 != 1)
36509                 info('bad rtc code: ' + code1);
36510               this.eatBits(12);
36511               if (this.encoding > 0) {
36512                 this.lookBits(1);
36513                 this.eatBits(1);
36514               }
36515             }
36516           }
36517           this.eof = true;
36518         }
36519       } else if (this.err && this.eoline) {
36520         while (true) {
36521           code1 = this.lookBits(13);
36522           if (code1 == EOF) {
36523             this.eof = true;
36524             return null;
36525           }
36526           if ((code1 >> 1) == 1) {
36527             break;
36528           }
36529           this.eatBits(1);
36530         }
36531         this.eatBits(12);
36532         if (this.encoding > 0) {
36533           this.eatBits(1);
36534           this.nextLine2D = !(code1 & 1);
36535         }
36536       }
36537 
36538       if (codingLine[0] > 0)
36539         this.outputBits = codingLine[this.codingPos = 0];
36540       else
36541         this.outputBits = codingLine[this.codingPos = 1];
36542       this.row++;
36543     }
36544 
36545     if (this.outputBits >= 8) {
36546       this.buf = (this.codingPos & 1) ? 0 : 0xFF;
36547       this.outputBits -= 8;
36548       if (this.outputBits === 0 && codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36549         this.codingPos++;
36550         this.outputBits = (codingLine[this.codingPos] -
36551                            codingLine[this.codingPos - 1]);
36552       }
36553     } else {
36554       var bits = 8;
36555       this.buf = 0;
36556       do {
36557         if (this.outputBits > bits) {
36558           this.buf <<= bits;
36559           if (!(this.codingPos & 1)) {
36560             this.buf |= 0xFF >> (8 - bits);
36561           }
36562           this.outputBits -= bits;
36563           bits = 0;
36564         } else {
36565           this.buf <<= this.outputBits;
36566           if (!(this.codingPos & 1)) {
36567             this.buf |= 0xFF >> (8 - this.outputBits);
36568           }
36569           bits -= this.outputBits;
36570           this.outputBits = 0;
36571           if (codingLine[this.codingPos] < columns) {
36572             this.codingPos++;
36573             this.outputBits = (codingLine[this.codingPos] -
36574                                codingLine[this.codingPos - 1]);
36575           } else if (bits > 0) {
36576             this.buf <<= bits;
36577             bits = 0;
36578           }
36579         }
36580       } while (bits);
36581     }
36582     if (this.black) {
36583       this.buf ^= 0xFF;
36584     }
36585     return this.buf;
36586   };
36587 
36588   // This functions returns the code found from the table.
36589   // The start and end parameters set the boundaries for searching the table.
36590   // The limit parameter is optional. Function returns an array with three
36591   // values. The first array element indicates whether a valid code is being
36592   // returned. The second array element is the actual code. The third array
36593   // element indicates whether EOF was reached.
36594   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.findTableCode =
36595     function ccittFaxStreamFindTableCode(start, end, table, limit) {
36596 
36597     var limitValue = limit || 0;
36598     for (var i = start; i <= end; ++i) {
36599       var code = this.lookBits(i);
36600       if (code == EOF)
36601         return [true, 1, false];
36602       if (i < end)
36603         code <<= end - i;
36604       if (!limitValue || code >= limitValue) {
36605         var p = table[code - limitValue];
36606         if (p[0] == i) {
36607           this.eatBits(i);
36608           return [true, p[1], true];
36609         }
36610       }
36611     }
36612     return [false, 0, false];
36613   };
36614 
36615   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.getTwoDimCode =
36616     function ccittFaxStreamGetTwoDimCode() {
36617 
36618     var code = 0;
36619     var p;
36620     if (this.eoblock) {
36621       code = this.lookBits(7);
36622       p = twoDimTable[code];
36623       if (p && p[0] > 0) {
36624         this.eatBits(p[0]);
36625         return p[1];
36626       }
36627     } else {
36628       var result = this.findTableCode(1, 7, twoDimTable);
36629       if (result[0] && result[2])
36630         return result[1];
36631     }
36632     info('Bad two dim code');
36633     return EOF;
36634   };
36635 
36636   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.getWhiteCode =
36637     function ccittFaxStreamGetWhiteCode() {
36638 
36639     var code = 0;
36640     var p;
36641     var n;
36642     if (this.eoblock) {
36643       code = this.lookBits(12);
36644       if (code == EOF)
36645         return 1;
36646 
36647       if ((code >> 5) === 0)
36648         p = whiteTable1[code];
36649       else
36650         p = whiteTable2[code >> 3];
36651 
36652       if (p[0] > 0) {
36653         this.eatBits(p[0]);
36654         return p[1];
36655       }
36656     } else {
36657       var result = this.findTableCode(1, 9, whiteTable2);
36658       if (result[0])
36659         return result[1];
36660 
36661       result = this.findTableCode(11, 12, whiteTable1);
36662       if (result[0])
36663         return result[1];
36664     }
36665     info('bad white code');
36666     this.eatBits(1);
36667     return 1;
36668   };
36669 
36670   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.getBlackCode =
36671     function ccittFaxStreamGetBlackCode() {
36672 
36673     var code, p;
36674     if (this.eoblock) {
36675       code = this.lookBits(13);
36676       if (code == EOF)
36677         return 1;
36678       if ((code >> 7) === 0)
36679         p = blackTable1[code];
36680       else if ((code >> 9) === 0 && (code >> 7) !== 0)
36681         p = blackTable2[(code >> 1) - 64];
36682       else
36683         p = blackTable3[code >> 7];
36684 
36685       if (p[0] > 0) {
36686         this.eatBits(p[0]);
36687         return p[1];
36688       }
36689     } else {
36690       var result = this.findTableCode(2, 6, blackTable3);
36691       if (result[0])
36692         return result[1];
36693 
36694       result = this.findTableCode(7, 12, blackTable2, 64);
36695       if (result[0])
36696         return result[1];
36697 
36698       result = this.findTableCode(10, 13, blackTable1);
36699       if (result[0])
36700         return result[1];
36701     }
36702     info('bad black code');
36703     this.eatBits(1);
36704     return 1;
36705   };
36706 
36707   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.lookBits = function CCITTFaxStream_lookBits(n) {
36708     var c;
36709     while (this.inputBits < n) {
36710       if ((c = this.str.getByte()) === -1) {
36711         if (this.inputBits === 0)
36712           return EOF;
36713         return ((this.inputBuf << (n - this.inputBits)) &
36714                 (0xFFFF >> (16 - n)));
36715       }
36716       this.inputBuf = (this.inputBuf << 8) + c;
36717       this.inputBits += 8;
36718     }
36719     return (this.inputBuf >> (this.inputBits - n)) & (0xFFFF >> (16 - n));
36720   };
36721 
36722   CCITTFaxStream.prototype.eatBits = function CCITTFaxStream_eatBits(n) {
36723     if ((this.inputBits -= n) < 0)
36724       this.inputBits = 0;
36725   };
36726 
36727   return CCITTFaxStream;
36728 })();
36729 
36730 var LZWStream = (function LZWStreamClosure() {
36731   function LZWStream(str, earlyChange) {
36732     this.str = str;
36733     this.dict = str.dict;
36734     this.cachedData = 0;
36735     this.bitsCached = 0;
36736 
36737     var maxLzwDictionarySize = 4096;
36738     var lzwState = {
36739       earlyChange: earlyChange,
36740       codeLength: 9,
36741       nextCode: 258,
36742       dictionaryValues: new Uint8Array(maxLzwDictionarySize),
36743       dictionaryLengths: new Uint16Array(maxLzwDictionarySize),
36744       dictionaryPrevCodes: new Uint16Array(maxLzwDictionarySize),
36745       currentSequence: new Uint8Array(maxLzwDictionarySize),
36746       currentSequenceLength: 0
36747     };
36748     for (var i = 0; i < 256; ++i) {
36749       lzwState.dictionaryValues[i] = i;
36750       lzwState.dictionaryLengths[i] = 1;
36751     }
36752     this.lzwState = lzwState;
36753 
36754     DecodeStream.call(this);
36755   }
36756 
36757   LZWStream.prototype = Object.create(DecodeStream.prototype);
36758 
36759   LZWStream.prototype.readBits = function LZWStream_readBits(n) {
36760     var bitsCached = this.bitsCached;
36761     var cachedData = this.cachedData;
36762     while (bitsCached < n) {
36763       var c = this.str.getByte();
36764       if (c === -1) {
36765         this.eof = true;
36766         return null;
36767       }
36768       cachedData = (cachedData << 8) | c;
36769       bitsCached += 8;
36770     }
36771     this.bitsCached = (bitsCached -= n);
36772     this.cachedData = cachedData;
36773     this.lastCode = null;
36774     return (cachedData >>> bitsCached) & ((1 << n) - 1);
36775   };
36776 
36777   LZWStream.prototype.readBlock = function LZWStream_readBlock() {
36778     var blockSize = 512;
36779     var estimatedDecodedSize = blockSize * 2, decodedSizeDelta = blockSize;
36780     var i, j, q;
36781 
36782     var lzwState = this.lzwState;
36783     if (!lzwState)
36784       return; // eof was found
36785 
36786     var earlyChange = lzwState.earlyChange;
36787     var nextCode = lzwState.nextCode;
36788     var dictionaryValues = lzwState.dictionaryValues;
36789     var dictionaryLengths = lzwState.dictionaryLengths;
36790     var dictionaryPrevCodes = lzwState.dictionaryPrevCodes;
36791     var codeLength = lzwState.codeLength;
36792     var prevCode = lzwState.prevCode;
36793     var currentSequence = lzwState.currentSequence;
36794     var currentSequenceLength = lzwState.currentSequenceLength;
36795 
36796     var decodedLength = 0;
36797     var currentBufferLength = this.bufferLength;
36798     var buffer = this.ensureBuffer(this.bufferLength + estimatedDecodedSize);
36799 
36800     for (i = 0; i < blockSize; i++) {
36801       var code = this.readBits(codeLength);
36802       var hasPrev = currentSequenceLength > 0;
36803       if (code < 256) {
36804         currentSequence[0] = code;
36805         currentSequenceLength = 1;
36806       } else if (code >= 258) {
36807         if (code < nextCode) {
36808           currentSequenceLength = dictionaryLengths[code];
36809           for (j = currentSequenceLength - 1, q = code; j >= 0; j--) {
36810             currentSequence[j] = dictionaryValues[q];
36811             q = dictionaryPrevCodes[q];
36812           }
36813         } else {
36814           currentSequence[currentSequenceLength++] = currentSequence[0];
36815         }
36816       } else if (code == 256) {
36817         codeLength = 9;
36818         nextCode = 258;
36819         currentSequenceLength = 0;
36820         continue;
36821       } else {
36822         this.eof = true;
36823         delete this.lzwState;
36824         break;
36825       }
36826 
36827       if (hasPrev) {
36828         dictionaryPrevCodes[nextCode] = prevCode;
36829         dictionaryLengths[nextCode] = dictionaryLengths[prevCode] + 1;
36830         dictionaryValues[nextCode] = currentSequence[0];
36831         nextCode++;
36832         codeLength = (nextCode + earlyChange) & (nextCode + earlyChange - 1) ?
36833           codeLength : Math.min(Math.log(nextCode + earlyChange) /
36834           0.6931471805599453 + 1, 12) | 0;
36835       }
36836       prevCode = code;
36837 
36838       decodedLength += currentSequenceLength;
36839       if (estimatedDecodedSize < decodedLength) {
36840         do {
36841           estimatedDecodedSize += decodedSizeDelta;
36842         } while (estimatedDecodedSize < decodedLength);
36843         buffer = this.ensureBuffer(this.bufferLength + estimatedDecodedSize);
36844       }
36845       for (j = 0; j < currentSequenceLength; j++)
36846         buffer[currentBufferLength++] = currentSequence[j];
36847     }
36848     lzwState.nextCode = nextCode;
36849     lzwState.codeLength = codeLength;
36850     lzwState.prevCode = prevCode;
36851     lzwState.currentSequenceLength = currentSequenceLength;
36852 
36853     this.bufferLength = currentBufferLength;
36854   };
36855 
36856   return LZWStream;
36857 })();
36858 
36859 var NullStream = (function NullStreamClosure() {

36861     Stream.call(this, new Uint8Array(0));
36862   }
36863 
36864   NullStream.prototype = Stream.prototype;
36865 
36866   return NullStream;
36867 })();

36869 
36870 function MessageHandler(name, comObj) {
36871   this.name = name;
36872   this.comObj = comObj;
36873   this.callbackIndex = 1;
36874   var callbacks = this.callbacks = {};
36875   var ah = this.actionHandler = {};
36876 
36877   ah['console_log'] = [function ahConsoleLog(data) {
36878     log.apply(null, data);
36879   }];
36880   // If there's no console available, console_error in the
36881   // action handler will do nothing.
36882   if ('console' in globalScope) {
36883     ah['console_error'] = [function ahConsoleError(data) {
36884       globalScope['console'].error.apply(null, data);
36885     }];
36886   } else {
36887     ah['console_error'] = [function ahConsoleError(data) {
36888       log.apply(null, data);
36889     }];
36890   }
36891   ah['_warn'] = [function ah_Warn(data) {
36892     warn(data);
36893   }];
36894 
36895   comObj.onmessage = function messageHandlerComObjOnMessage(event) {
36896     var data = event.data;
36897     if (data.isReply) {
36898       var callbackId = data.callbackId;
36899       if (data.callbackId in callbacks) {
36900         var callback = callbacks[callbackId];
36901         delete callbacks[callbackId];
36902         callback(data.data);
36903       } else {
36904         error('Cannot resolve callback ' + callbackId);
36905       }
36906     } else if (data.action in ah) {
36907       var action = ah[data.action];
36908       if (data.callbackId) {
36909         var promise = new Promise();
36910         promise.then(function(resolvedData) {
36911           comObj.postMessage({
36912             isReply: true,
36913             callbackId: data.callbackId,
36914             data: resolvedData
36915           });
36916         });
36917         action[0].call(action[1], data.data, promise);
36918       } else {
36919         action[0].call(action[1], data.data);
36920       }
36921     } else {
36922       error('Unkown action from worker: ' + data.action);
36923     }
36924   };
36925 }
36926 
36927 MessageHandler.prototype = {
36928   on: function messageHandlerOn(actionName, handler, scope) {
36929     var ah = this.actionHandler;
36930     if (ah[actionName]) {
36931       error('There is already an actionName called "' + actionName + '"');
36932     }
36933     ah[actionName] = [handler, scope];
36934   },
36941   send: function messageHandlerSend(actionName, data, callback) {
36942     var message = {
36943       action: actionName,
36944       data: data
36945     };
36946     if (callback) {
36947       var callbackId = this.callbackIndex++;
36948       this.callbacks[callbackId] = callback;
36949       message.callbackId = callbackId;
36950     }
36951     this.comObj.postMessage(message);
36952   }
36953 };
36954 
36955 var WorkerMessageHandler = {
36956   setup: function wphSetup(handler) {
36957     var pdfManager;
36958 
36959     function loadDocument(recoveryMode) {
36960       var loadDocumentPromise = new Promise();
36961 
36962       var parseSuccess = function parseSuccess() {
36963         var numPagesPromise = pdfManager.ensureModel('numPages');
36964         var fingerprintPromise = pdfManager.ensureModel('fingerprint');
36965         var outlinePromise = pdfManager.ensureCatalog('documentOutline');
36966         var infoPromise = pdfManager.ensureModel('documentInfo');
36967         var metadataPromise = pdfManager.ensureCatalog('metadata');
36968         var encryptedPromise = pdfManager.ensureXRef('encrypt');
36969         var javaScriptPromise = pdfManager.ensureCatalog('javaScript');
36970         Promise.all([numPagesPromise, fingerprintPromise, outlinePromise,
36971           infoPromise, metadataPromise, encryptedPromise,
36972           javaScriptPromise]).then(
36973             function onDocReady(results) {
36974 
36975           var doc = {
36976             numPages: results[0],
36977             fingerprint: results[1],
36978             outline: results[2],
36979             info: results[3],
36980             metadata: results[4],
36981             encrypted: !!results[5],
36982             javaScript: results[6]
36983           };
36984           loadDocumentPromise.resolve(doc);
36985         },
36986         parseFailure);
36987       };
36988 
36989       var parseFailure = function parseFailure(e) {
36990         loadDocumentPromise.reject(e);
36991       };
36992 
36993       pdfManager.ensureModel('checkHeader', []).then(function() {
36994         pdfManager.ensureModel('parseStartXRef', []).then(function() {
36995           pdfManager.ensureModel('parse', [recoveryMode]).then(
36996               parseSuccess, parseFailure);
36997         }, parseFailure);
36998       }, parseFailure);
36999 
37000       return loadDocumentPromise;
37001     }
37002 
37003     function getPdfManager(data) {
37004       var pdfManagerPromise = new Promise();
37005 
37006       var source = data.source;
37007       var disableRange = data.disableRange;
37008       if (source.data) {
37009         try {
37010           pdfManager = new LocalPdfManager(source.data, source.password);
37011           pdfManagerPromise.resolve();
37012         } catch (ex) {
37013           pdfManagerPromise.reject(ex);
37014         }
37015         return pdfManagerPromise;
37016       } else if (source.chunkedViewerLoading) {
37017         try {
37018           pdfManager = new NetworkPdfManager(source, handler);
37019           pdfManagerPromise.resolve();
37020         } catch (ex) {
37021           pdfManagerPromise.reject(ex);
37022         }
37023         return pdfManagerPromise;
37024       }
37025 
37026       var networkManager = new NetworkManager(source.url, {
37027         httpHeaders: source.httpHeaders
37028       });
37029       var fullRequestXhrId = networkManager.requestFull({
37030         onHeadersReceived: function onHeadersReceived() {
37031           if (disableRange) {
37032             return;
37033           }
37034 
37035           var fullRequestXhr = networkManager.getRequestXhr(fullRequestXhrId);
37036           if (fullRequestXhr.getResponseHeader('Accept-Ranges') !== 'bytes') {
37037             return;
37038           }
37039 
37040           var contentEncoding =
37041             fullRequestXhr.getResponseHeader('Content-Encoding') || 'identity';
37042           if (contentEncoding !== 'identity') {
37043             return;
37044           }
37045 
37046           var length = fullRequestXhr.getResponseHeader('Content-Length');
37047           length = parseInt(length, 10);
37048           if (!isInt(length)) {
37049             return;
37050           }
37051 
37052           // NOTE: by cancelling the full request, and then issuing range
37053           // requests, there will be an issue for sites where you can only
37054           // request the pdf once. However, if this is the case, then the
37055           // server should not be returning that it can support range requests.
37056           networkManager.abortRequest(fullRequestXhrId);
37057 
37058           source.length = length;
37059           try {
37060             pdfManager = new NetworkPdfManager(source, handler);
37061             pdfManagerPromise.resolve(pdfManager);
37062           } catch (ex) {
37063             pdfManagerPromise.reject(ex);
37064           }
37065         },
37066 
37067         onDone: function onDone(args) {
37068           // the data is array, instantiating directly from it
37069           try {
37070             pdfManager = new LocalPdfManager(args.chunk, source.password);
37071             pdfManagerPromise.resolve();
37072           } catch (ex) {
37073             pdfManagerPromise.reject(ex);
37074           }
37075         },
37076 
37077         onError: function onError(status) {
37078           if (status == 404) {
37079             var exception = new MissingPDFException( 'Missing PDF "' +
37080                 source.url + '".');
37081             handler.send('MissingPDF', { exception: exception });
37082           } else {
37083             handler.send('DocError', 'Unexpected server response (' +
37084                 status + ') while retrieving PDF "' +
37085                 source.url + '".');
37086           }
37087         },
37088 
37089         onProgress: function onProgress(evt) {
37090           handler.send('DocProgress', {
37091             loaded: evt.loaded,
37092             total: evt.lengthComputable ? evt.total : void(0)
37093           });
37094         }
37095       });
37096 
37097       return pdfManagerPromise;
37098     }
37099 
37100     handler.on('test', function wphSetupTest(data) {
37101       // check if Uint8Array can be sent to worker
37102       if (!(data instanceof Uint8Array)) {
37103         handler.send('test', false);
37104         return;
37105       }
37106       // check if the response property is supported by xhr
37107       var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
37108       var responseExists = 'response' in xhr;
37109       // check if the property is actually implemented
37110       try {
37111         var dummy = xhr.responseType;
37112       } catch (e) {
37113         responseExists = false;
37114       }
37115       if (!responseExists) {
37116         handler.send('test', false);
37117         return;
37118       }
37119       handler.send('test', true);
37120     });
37121 
37122     handler.on('GetDocRequest', function wphSetupDoc(data) {
37123 
37124       var onSuccess = function(doc) {
37125         handler.send('GetDoc', { pdfInfo: doc });
37126         pdfManager.ensureModel('traversePages', []).then(null, onFailure);
37127       };
37128 
37129       var onFailure = function(e) {
37130         if (e instanceof PasswordException) {
37131           if (e.code === PasswordResponses.NEED_PASSWORD) {
37132             handler.send('NeedPassword', {
37133               exception: e
37134             });
37135           } else if (e.code === PasswordResponses.INCORRECT_PASSWORD) {
37136             handler.send('IncorrectPassword', {
37137               exception: e
37138             });
37139           }
37140         } else if (e instanceof InvalidPDFException) {
37141           handler.send('InvalidPDF', {
37142             exception: e
37143           });
37144         } else if (e instanceof MissingPDFException) {
37145           handler.send('MissingPDF', {
37146             exception: e
37147           });
37148         } else {
37149           handler.send('UnknownError', {
37150             exception: new UnknownErrorException(e.message, e.toString())
37151           });
37152         }
37153       };
37154 
37155       PDFJS.maxImageSize = data.maxImageSize === undefined ?
37156                            -1 : data.maxImageSize;
37157 
37158       getPdfManager(data).then(function pdfManagerReady() {
37159         loadDocument(false).then(onSuccess, function loadFailure(ex) {
37160           // Try again with recoveryMode == true
37161           if (!(ex instanceof XRefParseException)) {
37162             if (ex instanceof PasswordException) {
37163               // after password exception prepare to receive a new password
37164               // to repeat loading
37165               pdfManager.passwordChangedPromise = new Promise();
37166               pdfManager.passwordChangedPromise.then(pdfManagerReady);
37167             }
37168 
37169             onFailure(ex);
37170             return;
37171           }
37172 
37173           pdfManager.requestLoadedStream();
37174           pdfManager.onLoadedStream().then(function() {
37175             loadDocument(true).then(onSuccess, onFailure);
37176           });
37177         }, onFailure);
37178       }, onFailure);
37179     });
37180 
37181     handler.on('GetPageRequest', function wphSetupGetPage(data) {
37182       var pageIndex = data.pageIndex;
37183       pdfManager.getPage(pageIndex).then(function(page) {
37184         var rotatePromise = pdfManager.ensure(page, 'rotate');
37185         var refPromise = pdfManager.ensure(page, 'ref');
37186         var viewPromise = pdfManager.ensure(page, 'view');
37187 
37188         Promise.all([rotatePromise, refPromise, viewPromise]).then(
37189             function(results) {
37190           var page = {
37191             pageIndex: data.pageIndex,
37192             rotate: results[0],
37193             ref: results[1],
37194             view: results[2]
37195           };
37196 
37197           handler.send('GetPage', { pageInfo: page });
37198         });
37199       });
37200     });
37201 
37202     handler.on('GetDestinations',
37203       function wphSetupGetDestinations(data, promise) {
37204         pdfManager.ensureCatalog('destinations').then(function(destinations) {
37205           promise.resolve(destinations);
37206         });
37207       }
37208     );
37209 
37210     handler.on('GetData', function wphSetupGetData(data, promise) {
37211       pdfManager.requestLoadedStream();
37212       pdfManager.onLoadedStream().then(function(stream) {
37213         promise.resolve(stream.bytes);
37214       });
37215     });
37216 
37217     handler.on('DataLoaded', function wphSetupDataLoaded(data, promise) {
37218       pdfManager.onLoadedStream().then(function(stream) {
37219         promise.resolve({ length: stream.bytes.byteLength });
37220       });
37221     });

37223     handler.on('UpdatePassword', function wphSetupUpdatePassword(data) {
37224       pdfManager.updatePassword(data);
37225     });
37226 
37227     handler.on('GetAnnotationsRequest', function wphSetupGetAnnotations(data) {
37228       pdfManager.getPage(data.pageIndex).then(function(page) {
37229         pdfManager.ensure(page, 'getAnnotationsData', []).then(
37230           function(annotationsData) {
37231             handler.send('GetAnnotations', {
37232               pageIndex: data.pageIndex,
37233               annotations: annotationsData
37234             });
37235           }
37236         );
37237       });

37239 
37240     handler.on('RenderPageRequest', function wphSetupRenderPage(data) {
37241       pdfManager.getPage(data.pageIndex).then(function(page) {
37242 
37243         var pageNum = data.pageIndex + 1;
37244         var start = Date.now();
37245         // Pre compile the pdf page and fetch the fonts/images.
37246         page.getOperatorList(handler).then(function(opListData) {
37247 
37248           var operatorList = opListData.queue;
37249           var dependency = Object.keys(opListData.dependencies);
37250 
37251           // The following code does quite the same as
37252           // Page.prototype.startRendering, but stops at one point and sends the
37253           // result back to the main thread.
37254 
37255           log('page=%d - getOperatorList: time=%dms, len=%d', pageNum,
37256               Date.now() - start, operatorList.fnArray.length);
37257 
37258           // Filter the dependecies for fonts.
37259           var fonts = {};
37260           for (var i = 0, ii = dependency.length; i < ii; i++) {
37261             var dep = dependency[i];
37262             if (dep.indexOf('g_font_') === 0) {
37263               fonts[dep] = true;
37264             }
37265           }
37266           handler.send('RenderPage', {
37267             pageIndex: data.pageIndex,
37268             operatorList: operatorList,
37269             depFonts: Object.keys(fonts)
37270           });
37271         }, function(e) {
37272 
37273           var minimumStackMessage =
37274               'worker.js: while trying to getPage() and getOperatorList()';
37275 
37276           var wrappedException;
37277 
37278           // Turn the error into an obj that can be serialized
37279           if (typeof e === 'string') {
37280             wrappedException = {
37281               message: e,
37282               stack: minimumStackMessage
37283             };
37284           } else if (typeof e === 'object') {
37285             wrappedException = {
37286               message: e.message || e.toString(),
37287               stack: e.stack || minimumStackMessage
37288             };
37289           } else {
37290             wrappedException = {
37291               message: 'Unknown exception type: ' + (typeof e),
37292               stack: minimumStackMessage
37293             };
37294           }
37295 
37296           handler.send('PageError', {
37297             pageNum: pageNum,
37298             error: wrappedException
37299           });
37300         });
37301       });
37302     }, this);
37303 
37304     handler.on('GetTextContent', function wphExtractText(data, promise) {
37305       pdfManager.getPage(data.pageIndex).then(function(page) {
37306         var pageNum = data.pageIndex + 1;
37307         var start = Date.now();
37308         page.extractTextContent().then(function(textContent) {
37309           promise.resolve(textContent);
37310           log('text indexing: page=%d - time=%dms', pageNum,
37311               Date.now() - start);
37312         }, function (e) {
37313           // Skip errored pages
37314           promise.reject(e);
37315         });
37316       });
37317     });
37318 
37319     handler.on('Terminate', function wphTerminate(data, promise) {
37320       pdfManager.streamManager.networkManager.abortAllRequests();
37321       promise.resolve();
37322     });
37323   }
37324 };

37335   },
37336 
37337   error: function error() {
37338     var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
37339     globalScope.postMessage({
37340       action: 'console_error',
37341       data: args
37342     });
37343     throw 'pdf.js execution error';
37344   },
37345 
37346   time: function time(name) {
37347     consoleTimer[name] = Date.now();
37348   },
37349 
37350   timeEnd: function timeEnd(name) {
37351     var time = consoleTimer[name];
37352     if (!time) {
37353       error('Unkown timer name ' + name);
37354     }
37355     this.log('Timer:', name, Date.now() - time);
37356   }
37357 };
37358 
37359 // Worker thread?
37360 if (typeof window === 'undefined') {
37361   globalScope.console = workerConsole;
37362 
37363   // Add a logger so we can pass warnings on to the main thread, errors will
37364   // throw an exception which will be forwarded on automatically.
37365   PDFJS.LogManager.addLogger({
37366     warn: function(msg) {
37367       globalScope.postMessage({
37368         action: '_warn',
37369         data: msg
37370       });
37371     }
37372   });
37373 
37374   var handler = new MessageHandler('worker_processor', this);
37375   WorkerMessageHandler.setup(handler);
37376 }
