39305     function ArithmeticDecoder(data, start, end) {
39306       this.data = data;
39307       this.bp = start;
39308       this.dataEnd = end;
39309 
39310       this.chigh = data[start];
39311       this.clow = 0;
39312 
39313       this.byteIn();
39314 
39315       this.chigh = ((this.chigh << 7) & 0xFFFF) | ((this.clow >> 9) & 0x7F);
39316       this.clow = (this.clow << 7) & 0xFFFF;
39317       this.ct -= 7;
39318       this.a = 0x8000;
39319     }
39320 
39321     ArithmeticDecoder.prototype = {
39322       byteIn: function ArithmeticDecoder_byteIn() {
39323         var data = this.data;
39324         var bp = this.bp;
39325         if (data[bp] == 0xFF) {
39326           var b1 = data[bp + 1];
39327           if (b1 > 0x8F) {
39328             this.clow += 0xFF00;
39329             this.ct = 8;
39330           } else {
39331             bp++;
39332             this.clow += (data[bp] << 9);
39333             this.ct = 7;
39334             this.bp = bp;
39335           }
39336         } else {
39337           bp++;
39338           this.clow += bp < this.dataEnd ? (data[bp] << 8) : 0xFF00;
39339           this.ct = 8;
39340           this.bp = bp;
39341         }
39342         if (this.clow > 0xFFFF) {
39343           this.chigh += (this.clow >> 16);
39344           this.clow &= 0xFFFF;
39345         }
39346       },
39347       readBit: function ArithmeticDecoder_readBit(cx) {
39348         var qeIcx = QeTable[cx.index].qe;
39349         this.a -= qeIcx;
39350 
39351         if (this.chigh < qeIcx) {
39352           var d = this.exchangeLps(cx);
39353           this.renormD();
39354           return d;
39355         } else {
39356           this.chigh -= qeIcx;
39357           if ((this.a & 0x8000) === 0) {
39358             var d = this.exchangeMps(cx);
39359             this.renormD();
39360             return d;
39361           } else {
39362             return cx.mps;
39363           }
39364         }
39365       },
39366       renormD: function ArithmeticDecoder_renormD() {
39367         do {
39368           if (this.ct === 0)
39369             this.byteIn();
39370 
39371           this.a <<= 1;
39372           this.chigh = ((this.chigh << 1) & 0xFFFF) | ((this.clow >> 15) & 1);
39373           this.clow = (this.clow << 1) & 0xFFFF;
39374           this.ct--;
39375         } while ((this.a & 0x8000) === 0);
39376       },
39377       exchangeMps: function ArithmeticDecoder_exchangeMps(cx) {
39378         var d;
39379         var qeTableIcx = QeTable[cx.index];
39380         if (this.a < qeTableIcx.qe) {
39381           d = 1 - cx.mps;
39382 
39383           if (qeTableIcx.switchFlag == 1) {
39384             cx.mps = 1 - cx.mps;
39385           }
39386           cx.index = qeTableIcx.nlps;
39387         } else {
39388           d = cx.mps;
39389           cx.index = qeTableIcx.nmps;
39390         }
39391         return d;
39392       },
39393       exchangeLps: function ArithmeticDecoder_exchangeLps(cx) {
39394         var d;
39395         var qeTableIcx = QeTable[cx.index];
39396         if (this.a < qeTableIcx.qe) {
39397           this.a = qeTableIcx.qe;
39398           d = cx.mps;
39399           cx.index = qeTableIcx.nmps;
39400         } else {
39401           this.a = qeTableIcx.qe;
39402           d = 1 - cx.mps;
39403 
39404           if (qeTableIcx.switchFlag == 1) {
39405             cx.mps = 1 - cx.mps;
39406           }
39407           cx.index = qeTableIcx.nlps;
39408         }
39409         return d;
39410       }
39411     };
39412 
39413     return ArithmeticDecoder;
39414   })();

39444   // Annex A. Arithmetic Integer Decoding Procedure
39445   // A.2 Procedure for decoding values
39446   function decodeInteger(contextCache, procedure, decoder) {
39447     var contexts = contextCache.getContexts(procedure);
39448 
39449     var prev = 1;
39450     var state = 1, v = 0, s;
39451     var toRead = 32, offset = 4436; // defaults for state 7
39452     while (state) {
39453       var cx = contexts[prev];
39454       if (!cx)
39455         contexts[prev] = cx = {index: 0, mps: 0};
39456       var bit = decoder.readBit(cx);
39457       prev = prev < 256 ? (prev << 1) | bit :
39458         (((prev << 1) | bit) & 511) | 256;
39459       switch (state) {
39460         case 1:
39461           s = !!bit;
39462           break;
39463         case 2:
39464           if (bit) break;
39465           state = 7;
39466           toRead = 2;
39467           offset = 0;
39468           break;
39469         case 3:
39470           if (bit) break;
39471           state = 7;
39472           toRead = 4;
39473           offset = 4;
39474           break;
39475         case 4:
39476           if (bit) break;
39477           state = 7;
39478           toRead = 6;
39479           offset = 20;
39480           break;
39481         case 5:
39482           if (bit) break;
39483           state = 7;
39484           toRead = 8;
39485           offset = 84;
39486           break;
39487         case 6:
39488           if (bit) break;
39489           state = 7;
39490           toRead = 12;
39491           offset = 340;
39492           break;
39493         default:
39494           v = v * 2 + bit;
39495           if (--toRead === 0)
39496             state = 0;
39497           continue;
39498       }
39499       state++;
39500     }
39501     v += offset;
39502     return !s ? v : v > 0 ? -v : null;
39503   }
39504 
39505   // A.3 The IAID decoding procedure
39506   function decodeIAID(contextCache, decoder, codeLength) {
39507     var contexts = contextCache.getContexts('IAID');
39508 
39509     var prev = 1;
39510     for (var i = 0; i < codeLength; i++) {
39511       var cx = contexts[prev];
39512       if (!cx)
39513         contexts[prev] = cx = {index: 0, mps: 0};
39514       var bit = decoder.readBit(cx);
39515       prev = (prev * 2) + bit;
39516     }
39517     if (codeLength < 31)
39518       return prev & ((1 << codeLength) - 1);
39519     else
39520       return prev - Math.pow(2, codeLength);
39521   }

39560     {
39561       coding: [{x: -1, y: -1}, {x: 0, y: -1}, {x: 1, y: -1}, {x: -1, y: 0}],
39562       reference: [{x: 0, y: -1}, {x: -1, y: 0}, {x: 0, y: 0}, {x: 1, y: 0},
39563                   {x: 0, y: 1}, {x: 1, y: 1}]
39564     }
39565   ];
39566 
39567   var ReusedContexts = [
39568     0x1CD3, // '00111001101' (template) + '0011' (at),
39569     0x079A, // '001111001101' + '0',
39570     0x00E3, // '001110001' + '1',
39571     0x018B  // '011000101' + '1'
39572   ];
39573 
39574   var RefinementReusedContexts = [
39575     0x0020, // '000' + '0' (coding) + '00010000' + '0' (reference)
39576     0x0008  // '0000' + '001000'
39577   ];
39578 
39579   function log2(x) {
39580     var n = 1, i = 0;
39581     while (x > n) {
39582       n <<= 1;
39583       i++;
39584     }
39585     return i;
39586   }
39587 
39588   function readInt32(data, start) {
39589     return (data[start] << 24) | (data[start + 1] << 16) |
39590            (data[start + 2] << 8) | data[start + 3];
39591   }
39592 
39593   function readUint32(data, start) {
39594     var value = readInt32(data, start);
39595     return value & 0x80000000 ? (value + 4294967296) : value;
39596   }
39597 
39598   function readUint16(data, start) {
39599     return (data[start] << 8) | data[start + 1];
39600   }
39601 
39602   function readInt8(data, start) {
39603     return (data[start] << 24) >> 24;
39604   }
39605 
39606   // 6.2 Generic Region Decoding Procedure
39607   function decodeBitmap(mmr, width, height, templateIndex, prediction, skip, at,
39608                         decodingContext) {
39609     if (mmr)
39610       error('JBIG2 error: MMR encoding is not supported');
39611 
39612     var useskip = !!skip;
39613     var template = CodingTemplates[templateIndex].concat(at);
39614     var templateLength = template.length;
39615     var templateX = new Int32Array(templateLength);
39616     var templateY = new Int32Array(templateLength);
39617     for (var k = 0; k < templateLength; k++) {
39618       templateX[k] = template[k].x;
39619       templateY[k] = template[k].y;
39620     }
39621 
39622     var pseudoPixelContext = ReusedContexts[templateIndex];
39623     var bitmap = [];
39624 
39625     var decoder = decodingContext.decoder;
39626     var contexts = decodingContext.contextCache.getContexts('GB');
39627 
39628     var ltp = 0;
39629     for (var i = 0; i < height; i++) {
39630       if (prediction) {
39631         var cx = contexts[pseudoPixelContext];
39632         if (!cx)
39633           contexts[pseudoPixelContext] = cx = {index: 0, mps: 0};
39634         var sltp = decoder.readBit(cx);
39635         ltp ^= sltp;
39636       }
39637       if (ltp) {
39638         bitmap.push(bitmap[bitmap.length - 1]); // duplicate previous row
39639         continue;
39640       }
39641       var row = new Uint8Array(width);
39642       bitmap.push(row);
39643       for (var j = 0; j < width; j++) {
39644         if (useskip && skip[i][j]) {
39645           row[j] = 0;
39646           continue;
39647         }
39648         var contextLabel = 0;
39649         for (var k = 0; k < templateLength; k++) {
39650           var i0 = i + templateY[k], j0 = j + templateX[k];
39651           if (i0 < 0 || j0 < 0 || j0 >= width)
39652             contextLabel <<= 1; // out of bound pixel
39653           else
39654             contextLabel = (contextLabel << 1) | bitmap[i0][j0];
39655         }
39656         var cx = contexts[contextLabel];
39657         if (!cx)
39658           contexts[contextLabel] = cx = {index: 0, mps: 0};
39659         var pixel = decoder.readBit(cx);
39660         row[j] = pixel;
39661       }
39662     }
39663     return bitmap;
39664   }
39665 
39666   // 6.3.2 Generic Refinement Region Decoding Procedure
39667   function decodeRefinement(width, height, templateIndex, referenceBitmap,
39668                             offsetX, offsetY, prediction, at,
39669                             decodingContext) {
39670     var codingTemplate = RefinementTemplates[templateIndex].coding;
39671     if (templateIndex === 0)
39672       codingTemplate = codingTemplate.concat([at[0]]);
39673     var codingTemplateLength = codingTemplate.length;
39674     var codingTemplateX = new Int32Array(codingTemplateLength);
39675     var codingTemplateY = new Int32Array(codingTemplateLength);
39676     for (var k = 0; k < codingTemplateLength; k++) {
39677       codingTemplateX[k] = codingTemplate[k].x;
39678       codingTemplateY[k] = codingTemplate[k].y;
39679     }
39680     var referenceTemplate = RefinementTemplates[templateIndex].reference;
39681     if (templateIndex === 0)
39682       referenceTemplate = referenceTemplate.concat([at[1]]);
39683     var referenceTemplateLength = referenceTemplate.length;
39684     var referenceTemplateX = new Int32Array(referenceTemplateLength);
39685     var referenceTemplateY = new Int32Array(referenceTemplateLength);
39686     for (var k = 0; k < referenceTemplateLength; k++) {
39687       referenceTemplateX[k] = referenceTemplate[k].x;
39688       referenceTemplateY[k] = referenceTemplate[k].y;
39689     }
39690     var referenceWidth = referenceBitmap[0].length;
39691     var referenceHeight = referenceBitmap.length;
39692 
39693     var pseudoPixelContext = RefinementReusedContexts[templateIndex];
39694     var bitmap = [];
39695 
39696     var decoder = decodingContext.decoder;
39697     var contexts = decodingContext.contextCache.getContexts('GR');
39698 
39699     var ltp = 0;
39700     for (var i = 0; i < height; i++) {
39701       if (prediction) {
39702         var cx = contexts[pseudoPixelContext];
39703         if (!cx)
39704           contexts[pseudoPixelContext] = cx = {index: 0, mps: 0};
39705         var sltp = decoder.readBit(cx);
39706         ltp ^= sltp;
39707       }
39708       var row = new Uint8Array(width);
39709       bitmap.push(row);
39710       for (var j = 0; j < width; j++) {
39711         if (ltp)
39712           error('JBIG2 error: prediction is not supported');
39713 
39714         var contextLabel = 0;
39715         for (var k = 0; k < codingTemplateLength; k++) {
39716           var i0 = i + codingTemplateY[k], j0 = j + codingTemplateX[k];
39717           if (i0 < 0 || j0 < 0 || j0 >= width)
39718             contextLabel <<= 1; // out of bound pixel
39719           else
39720             contextLabel = (contextLabel << 1) | bitmap[i0][j0];
39721         }
39722         for (var k = 0; k < referenceTemplateLength; k++) {
39723           var i0 = i + referenceTemplateY[k] + offsetY;
39724           var j0 = j + referenceTemplateX[k] + offsetX;
39725           if (i0 < 0 || i0 >= referenceHeight || j0 < 0 || j0 >= referenceWidth)
39726             contextLabel <<= 1; // out of bound pixel
39727           else
39728             contextLabel = (contextLabel << 1) | referenceBitmap[i0][j0];
39729         }
39730         var cx = contexts[contextLabel];
39731         if (!cx)
39732           contexts[contextLabel] = cx = {index: 0, mps: 0};
39733         var pixel = decoder.readBit(cx);
39734         row[j] = pixel;
39735       }
39736     }
39737 
39738     return bitmap;
39739   }
39740 
39741   // 6.5.5 Decoding the symbol dictionary
39742   function decodeSymbolDictionary(huffman, refinement, symbols,
39743                                   numberOfNewSymbols, numberOfExportedSymbols,
39744                                   huffmanTables, templateIndex, at,
39745                                   refinementTemplateIndex, refinementAt,
39746                                   decodingContext) {
39747     if (huffman)
39748       error('JBIG2 error: huffman is not supported');
39749 
39750     var newSymbols = [];
39751     var currentHeight = 0;
39752     var symbolCodeLength = log2(symbols.length + numberOfNewSymbols);
39753 
39754     var decoder = decodingContext.decoder;
39755     var contextCache = decodingContext.contextCache;
39756 
39757     while (newSymbols.length < numberOfNewSymbols) {
39758       var deltaHeight = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IADH', decoder); // 6.5.6
39759       currentHeight += deltaHeight;
39760       var currentWidth = 0;
39761       var totalWidth = 0;
39762       while (true) {
39763         var deltaWidth = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IADW', decoder); // 6.5.7
39764         if (deltaWidth === null)
39765           break; // OOB
39766         currentWidth += deltaWidth;
39767         totalWidth += currentWidth;
39768         var bitmap;
39769         if (refinement) {
39770           // 6.5.8.2 Refinement/aggregate-coded symbol bitmap
39771           var numberOfInstances = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IAAI', decoder);
39772           if (numberOfInstances > 1)
39773             error('JBIG2 error: number of instances > 1 is not supported');
39774           var symbolId = decodeIAID(contextCache, decoder, symbolCodeLength);
39775           var rdx = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IARDX', decoder); // 6.4.11.3
39776           var rdy = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IARDY', decoder); // 6.4.11.4
39777           var symbol = symbolId < symbols.length ? symbols[symbolId] :
39778             newSymbols[symbolId - symbols.length];
39779           bitmap = decodeRefinement(currentWidth, currentHeight,
39780             refinementTemplateIndex, symbol, rdx, rdy, false, refinementAt,
39781             decodingContext);
39782         } else {
39783           // 6.5.8.1 Direct-coded symbol bitmap
39784           bitmap = decodeBitmap(false, currentWidth, currentHeight,
39785             templateIndex, false, null, at, decodingContext);
39786         }
39787         newSymbols.push(bitmap);
39788       }
39789     }
39790     // 6.5.10 Exported symbols
39791     var exportedSymbols = [];
39792     var flags = [], currentFlag = false;
39793     var totalSymbolsLength = symbols.length + numberOfNewSymbols;
39794     while (flags.length < totalSymbolsLength) {
39795       var runLength = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IAEX', decoder);
39796       while (runLength--)
39797         flags.push(currentFlag);
39798       currentFlag = !currentFlag;
39799     }
39800     for (var i = 0, ii = symbols.length; i < ii; i++)
39801       if (flags[i]) exportedSymbols.push(symbols[i]);
39802     for (var j = 0; j < numberOfNewSymbols; i++, j++)
39803       if (flags[i]) exportedSymbols.push(newSymbols[j]);
39804     return exportedSymbols;
39805   }
39806 
39807   function decodeTextRegion(huffman, refinement, width, height,
39808                             defaultPixelValue, numberOfSymbolInstances,
39809                             stripSize, inputSymbols, symbolCodeLength,
39810                             transposed, dsOffset, referenceCorner,
39811                             combinationOperator, huffmanTables,
39812                             refinementTemplateIndex, refinementAt,
39813                             decodingContext) {
39814     if (huffman)
39815       error('JBIG2 error: huffman is not supported');
39816 
39817     // Prepare bitmap
39818     var bitmap = [];
39819     for (var i = 0; i < height; i++) {
39820       var row = new Uint8Array(width);
39821       if (defaultPixelValue) {
39822         for (var j = 0; j < width; j++)
39823           row[j] = defaultPixelValue;
39824       }
39825       bitmap.push(row);
39826     }
39827 
39828     var decoder = decodingContext.decoder;
39829     var contextCache = decodingContext.contextCache;
39830 
39831     if (transposed)
39832       error('JBIG2 error: transposed is not supported');
39833 
39834     var stripT = -decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IADT', decoder); // 6.4.6
39835     var firstS = 0;
39836     var i = 0;
39837     while (i < numberOfSymbolInstances) {
39838       var deltaT = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IADT', decoder); // 6.4.6
39839       stripT += deltaT;
39840 
39841       var deltaFirstS = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IAFS', decoder); // 6.4.7
39842       firstS += deltaFirstS;
39843       var currentS = firstS;
39844       do {
39845         var currentT = stripSize == 1 ? 0 :
39846           decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IAIT', decoder); // 6.4.9
39847         var t = stripSize * stripT + currentT;
39848         var symbolId = decodeIAID(contextCache, decoder, symbolCodeLength);
39849         var applyRefinement = refinement &&
39850           decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IARI', decoder);
39851         var symbolBitmap = inputSymbols[symbolId];
39852         var symbolWidth = symbolBitmap[0].length;
39853         var symbolHeight = symbolBitmap.length;
39854         if (applyRefinement) {
39855           var rdw = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IARDW', decoder); // 6.4.11.1
39856           var rdh = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IARDH', decoder); // 6.4.11.2
39857           var rdx = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IARDX', decoder); // 6.4.11.3
39858           var rdy = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IARDY', decoder); // 6.4.11.4
39859           symbolWidth += rdw;
39860           symbolHeight += rdh;
39861           symbolBitmap = decodeRefinement(symbolWidth, symbolHeight,
39862             refinementTemplateIndex, symbolBitmap, (rdw >> 1) + rdx,
39863             (rdh >> 1) + rdy, false, refinementAt,
39864             decodingContext);
39865         }
39866         var offsetT = t - ((referenceCorner & 1) ? 0 : symbolHeight);
39867         var offsetS = currentS - ((referenceCorner & 2) ? symbolWidth : 0);
39868         for (var t2 = 0; t2 < symbolHeight; t2++) {
39869           var row = bitmap[offsetT + t2];
39870           if (!row) continue;
39871           var symbolRow = symbolBitmap[t2];
39872           switch (combinationOperator) {
39873             case 0: // OR
39874               for (var s2 = 0; s2 < symbolWidth; s2++)
39875                 row[offsetS + s2] |= symbolRow[s2];
39876               break;
39877             case 2: // XOR
39878               for (var s2 = 0; s2 < symbolWidth; s2++)
39879                 row[offsetS + s2] ^= symbolRow[s2];
39880               break;
39881             default:
39882               error('JBIG2 error: operator ' + combinationOperator +
39883                     ' is not supported');
39884           }
39885         }
39886 
39887         currentS += symbolWidth - 1;
39888         i++;
39889 
39890         var deltaS = decodeInteger(contextCache, 'IADS', decoder); // 6.4.8
39891         if (deltaS === null)
39892           break; // OOB
39893         currentS += deltaS + dsOffset;
39894       } while (true);
39895     }
39896     return bitmap;
39897   }
39898 
39899   function readSegmentHeader(data, start) {
39900     var segmentHeader = {};
39901     segmentHeader.number = readUint32(data, start);
39902     var flags = data[start + 4];
39903     var segmentType = flags & 0x3F;
39904     if (!SegmentTypes[segmentType])
39905       error('JBIG2 error: invalid segment type: ' + segmentType);
39906     segmentHeader.type = segmentType;
39907     segmentHeader.typeName = SegmentTypes[segmentType];
39908     segmentHeader.deferredNonRetain = !!(flags & 0x80);
39909     var pageAssociationFieldSize = !!(flags & 0x40);
39910     var referredFlags = data[start + 5];
39911     var referredToCount = (referredFlags >> 5) & 7;
39912     var retainBits = [referredFlags & 31];
39913     var position = start + 6;
39914     if (referredFlags == 7) {
39915       referredToCount = readInt32(data, position - 1) & 0x1FFFFFFF;
39916       position += 3;
39917       var bytes = (referredToCount + 7) >> 3;
39918       retainBits[0] = data[position++];
39919       while (--bytes > 0) {
39920         retainBits.push(data[position++]);
39921       }
39922     } else if (referredFlags == 5 || referredFlags == 6)
39923       error('JBIG2 error: invalid referred-to flags');
39924     segmentHeader.retainBits = retainBits;
39925     var referredToSegmentNumberSize = segmentHeader.number <= 256 ? 1 :
39926       segmentHeader.number <= 65536 ? 2 : 4;
39927     var referredTo = [];
39928     for (var i = 0; i < referredToCount; i++) {
39929       var number = referredToSegmentNumberSize == 1 ? data[position] :
39930         referredToSegmentNumberSize == 2 ? readUint16(data, position) :
39931         readUint32(data, position);
39932       referredTo.push(number);
39933       position += referredToSegmentNumberSize;
39934     }
39935     segmentHeader.referredTo = referredTo;
39936     if (!pageAssociationFieldSize)
39937       segmentHeader.pageAssociation = data[position++];
39938     else {
39939       segmentHeader.pageAssociation = readUint32(data, position);
39940       position += 4;
39941     }
39942     segmentHeader.length = readUint32(data, position);
39943     position += 4;
39944     if (segmentHeader.length == 0xFFFFFFFF) {
39945       // 7.2.7 Segment data length, unknown segment length
39946       if (segmentType === 38) { // ImmediateGenericRegion
39947         var genericRegionInfo = readRegionSegmentInformation(data, position);
39948         var genericRegionSegmentFlags = data[position +
39949           RegionSegmentInformationFieldLength];
39950         var genericRegionMmr = !!(genericRegionSegmentFlags & 1);
39951         // searching for the segment end
39952         var searchPatternLength = 6;
39953         var searchPattern = new Uint8Array(searchPatternLength);
39954         if (!genericRegionMmr) {
39955           searchPattern[0] = 0xFF;
39956           searchPattern[1] = 0xAC;
39957         }
39958         searchPattern[2] = (genericRegionInfo.height >>> 24) & 0xFF;
39959         searchPattern[3] = (genericRegionInfo.height >> 16) & 0xFF;
39960         searchPattern[4] = (genericRegionInfo.height >> 8) & 0xFF;
39961         searchPattern[5] = genericRegionInfo.height & 0xFF;
39962         for (var i = position, ii = data.length; i < ii; i++) {
39963           var j = 0;
39964           while (j < searchPatternLength && searchPattern[j] === data[i + j]) {
39965             j++;
39966           }
39967           if (j == searchPatternLength) {
39968             segmentHeader.length = i + searchPatternLength;
39969             break;
39970           }
39971         }
39972         if (segmentHeader.length == 0xFFFFFFFF) {
39973           error('JBIG2 error: segment end was not found');
39974         }
39975       } else {
39976         error('JBIG2 error: invalid unknown segment length');
39977       }
39978     }
39979     segmentHeader.headerEnd = position;
39980     return segmentHeader;
39981   }
39982 
39983   function readSegments(header, data, start, end) {
39984     var segments = [];
39985     var position = start;
39986     while (position < end) {
39987       var segmentHeader = readSegmentHeader(data, position);
39988       position = segmentHeader.headerEnd;
39989       var segment = {
39990         header: segmentHeader,
39991         data: data
39992       };
39993       if (!header.randomAccess) {
39994         segment.start = position;
39995         position += segmentHeader.length;
39996         segment.end = position;
39997       }
39998       segments.push(segment);
39999       if (segmentHeader.type == 51)
40000         break; // end of file is found
40001     }
40002     if (header.randomAccess) {
40003       for (var i = 0, ii = segments.length; i < ii; i++) {
40004         segments[i].start = position;
40005         position += segments[i].header.length;
40006         segments[i].end = position;
40007       }
40008     }
40009     return segments;
40010   }
40011 
40012   // 7.4.1 Region segment information field
40013   function readRegionSegmentInformation(data, start) {
40014     return {
40015       width: readUint32(data, start),
40016       height: readUint32(data, start + 4),
40017       x: readUint32(data, start + 8),
40018       y: readUint32(data, start + 12),
40019       combinationOperator: data[start + 16] & 7
40020     };
40021   }
40022   var RegionSegmentInformationFieldLength = 17;
40023 
40024   function processSegment(segment, visitor) {
40025     var header = segment.header;
40026 
40027     var data = segment.data, position = segment.start, end = segment.end;
40028     var args;
40029     switch (header.type) {
40030       case 0: // SymbolDictionary
40031         // 7.4.2 Symbol dictionary segment syntax
40032         var dictionary = {};
40033         var dictionaryFlags = readUint16(data, position); // 7.4.2.1.1
40034         dictionary.huffman = !!(dictionaryFlags & 1);
40035         dictionary.refinement = !!(dictionaryFlags & 2);
40036         dictionary.huffmanDHSelector = (dictionaryFlags >> 2) & 3;
40037         dictionary.huffmanDWSelector = (dictionaryFlags >> 4) & 3;
40038         dictionary.bitmapSizeSelector = (dictionaryFlags >> 6) & 1;
40039         dictionary.aggregationInstancesSelector = (dictionaryFlags >> 7) & 1;
40040         dictionary.bitmapCodingContextUsed = !!(dictionaryFlags & 256);
40041         dictionary.bitmapCodingContextRetained = !!(dictionaryFlags & 512);
40042         dictionary.template = (dictionaryFlags >> 10) & 3;
40043         dictionary.refinementTemplate = (dictionaryFlags >> 12) & 1;
40044         position += 2;
40045         if (!dictionary.huffman) {
40046           var atLength = dictionary.template === 0 ? 4 : 1;
40047           var at = [];
40048           for (var i = 0; i < atLength; i++) {
40049             at.push({
40050               x: readInt8(data, position),
40051               y: readInt8(data, position + 1)
40052             });
40053             position += 2;
40054           }
40055           dictionary.at = at;
40056         }
40057         if (dictionary.refinement && !dictionary.refinementTemplate) {
40058           var at = [];
40059           for (var i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
40060             at.push({
40061               x: readInt8(data, position),
40062               y: readInt8(data, position + 1)
40063             });
40064             position += 2;
40065           }
40066           dictionary.refinementAt = at;
40067         }
40068         dictionary.numberOfExportedSymbols = readUint32(data, position);
40069         position += 4;
40070         dictionary.numberOfNewSymbols = readUint32(data, position);
40071         position += 4;
40072         args = [dictionary, header.number, header.referredTo,
40073                 data, position, end];
40074         break;
40075       case 6: // ImmediateTextRegion
40076       case 7: // ImmediateLosslessTextRegion
40077         var textRegion = {};
40078         textRegion.info = readRegionSegmentInformation(data, position);
40079         position += RegionSegmentInformationFieldLength;
40080         var textRegionSegmentFlags = readUint16(data, position);
40081         position += 2;
40082         textRegion.huffman = !!(textRegionSegmentFlags & 1);
40083         textRegion.refinement = !!(textRegionSegmentFlags & 2);
40084         textRegion.stripSize = 1 << ((textRegionSegmentFlags >> 2) & 3);
40085         textRegion.referenceCorner = (textRegionSegmentFlags >> 4) & 3;
40086         textRegion.transposed = !!(textRegionSegmentFlags & 64);
40087         textRegion.combinationOperator = (textRegionSegmentFlags >> 7) & 3;
40088         textRegion.defaultPixelValue = (textRegionSegmentFlags >> 9) & 1;
40089         textRegion.dsOffset = (textRegionSegmentFlags << 17) >> 27;
40090         textRegion.refinementTemplate = (textRegionSegmentFlags >> 15) & 1;
40091         if (textRegion.huffman) {
40092           var textRegionHuffmanFlags = readUint16(data, position);
40093           position += 2;
40094           textRegion.huffmanFS = (textRegionHuffmanFlags) & 3;
40095           textRegion.huffmanDS = (textRegionHuffmanFlags >> 2) & 3;
40096           textRegion.huffmanDT = (textRegionHuffmanFlags >> 4) & 3;
40097           textRegion.huffmanRefinementDW = (textRegionHuffmanFlags >> 6) & 3;
40098           textRegion.huffmanRefinementDH = (textRegionHuffmanFlags >> 8) & 3;
40099           textRegion.huffmanRefinementDX = (textRegionHuffmanFlags >> 10) & 3;
40100           textRegion.huffmanRefinementDY = (textRegionHuffmanFlags >> 12) & 3;
40101           textRegion.huffmanRefinementSizeSelector =
40102             !!(textRegionHuffmanFlags & 14);
40103         }
40104         if (textRegion.refinement && !textRegion.refinementTemplate) {
40105           var at = [];
40106           for (var i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
40107             at.push({
40108               x: readInt8(data, position),
40109               y: readInt8(data, position + 1)
40110             });
40111             position += 2;
40112           }
40113           textRegion.refinementAt = at;
40114         }
40115         textRegion.numberOfSymbolInstances = readUint32(data, position);
40116         position += 4;
40117         // TODO 7.4.3.1.7 Symbol ID Huffman table decoding
40118         if (textRegion.huffman)
40119           error('JBIG2 error: huffman is not supported');
40120         args = [textRegion, header.referredTo, data, position, end];
40121         break;
40122       case 38: // ImmediateGenericRegion
40123       case 39: // ImmediateLosslessGenericRegion
40124         var genericRegion = {};
40125         genericRegion.info = readRegionSegmentInformation(data, position);
40126         position += RegionSegmentInformationFieldLength;
40127         var genericRegionSegmentFlags = data[position++];
40128         genericRegion.mmr = !!(genericRegionSegmentFlags & 1);
40129         genericRegion.template = (genericRegionSegmentFlags >> 1) & 3;
40130         genericRegion.prediction = !!(genericRegionSegmentFlags & 8);
40131         if (!genericRegion.mmr) {
40132           var atLength = genericRegion.template === 0 ? 4 : 1;
40133           var at = [];
40134           for (var i = 0; i < atLength; i++) {
40135             at.push({
40136               x: readInt8(data, position),
40137               y: readInt8(data, position + 1)
40138             });
40139             position += 2;
40140           }
40141           genericRegion.at = at;
40142         }
40143         args = [genericRegion, data, position, end];
40144         break;
40145       case 48: // PageInformation
40146         var pageInfo = {
40147           width: readUint32(data, position),
40148           height: readUint32(data, position + 4),
40149           resolutionX: readUint32(data, position + 8),
40150           resolutionY: readUint32(data, position + 12)
40151         };
40152         if (pageInfo.height == 0xFFFFFFFF)
40153           delete pageInfo.height;
40154         var pageSegmentFlags = data[position + 16];
40155         var pageStripingInformatiom = readUint16(data, position + 17);
40156         pageInfo.lossless = !!(pageSegmentFlags & 1);
40157         pageInfo.refinement = !!(pageSegmentFlags & 2);
40158         pageInfo.defaultPixelValue = (pageSegmentFlags >> 2) & 1;
40159         pageInfo.combinationOperator = (pageSegmentFlags >> 3) & 3;
40160         pageInfo.requiresBuffer = !!(pageSegmentFlags & 32);
40161         pageInfo.combinationOperatorOverride = !!(pageSegmentFlags & 64);
40162         args = [pageInfo];
40163         break;
40164       case 49: // EndOfPage
40165         break;
40166       case 50: // EndOfStripe
40167         break;
40168       case 51: // EndOfFile
40169         break;
40170       default:
40171         error('JBIG2 error: segment type ' + header.typeName + '(' +
40172               header.type + ') is not implemented');
40173     }
40174     var callbackName = 'on' + header.typeName;
40175     if (callbackName in visitor)
40176       visitor[callbackName].apply(visitor, args);
40177   }
40178 
40179   function processSegments(segments, visitor) {
40180     for (var i = 0, ii = segments.length; i < ii; i++)
40181       processSegment(segments[i], visitor);
40182   }
40183 
40184   function parseJbig2(data, start, end) {
40185     var position = start;
40186     if (data[position] != 0x97 || data[position + 1] != 0x4A ||
40187         data[position + 2] != 0x42 || data[position + 3] != 0x32 ||
40188         data[position + 4] != 0x0D || data[position + 5] != 0x0A ||
40189         data[position + 6] != 0x1A || data[position + 7] != 0x0A)
40190       error('JBIG2 error: invalid header');
40191     var header = {};
40192     position += 8;
40193     var flags = data[position++];
40194     header.randomAccess = !(flags & 1);
40195     if (!(flags & 2)) {
40196       header.numberOfPages = readUint32(data, position);
40197       position += 4;
40198     }
40199     var segments = readSegments(header, data, position, end);
40200     error('Not implemented');
40201     // processSegments(segments, new SimpleSegmentVisitor());
40202   }
40203 
40204   function parseJbig2Chunks(chunks) {
40205     var visitor = new SimpleSegmentVisitor();
40206     for (var i = 0, ii = chunks.length; i < ii; i++) {
40207       var chunk = chunks[i];
40208       var segments = readSegments({}, chunk.data, chunk.start, chunk.end);
40209       processSegments(segments, visitor);
40210     }
40211     return visitor.buffer;
40212   }
40213 
40214   function SimpleSegmentVisitor() {}
40215 
40216   SimpleSegmentVisitor.prototype = {
40217     onPageInformation: function SimpleSegmentVisitor_onPageInformation(info) {
40218       this.currentPageInfo = info;
40219       var rowSize = (info.width + 7) >> 3;
40220       var buffer = new Uint8Array(rowSize * info.height);
40221       var fill = info.defaultPixelValue ? 0xFF : 0;
40222       for (var i = 0, ii = buffer.length; i < ii; i++)
40223         buffer[i] = fill;
40224       this.buffer = buffer;
40225     },
40226     drawBitmap: function SimpleSegmentVisitor_drawBitmap(regionInfo, bitmap) {
40227       var pageInfo = this.currentPageInfo;
40228       var width = regionInfo.width, height = regionInfo.height;
40229       var rowSize = (pageInfo.width + 7) >> 3;
40230       var combinationOperator = pageInfo.combinationOperatorOverride ?
40231         regionInfo.combinationOperator : pageInfo.combinationOperator;
40232       var buffer = this.buffer;
40233       for (var i = 0; i < height; i++) {
40234         var mask = 128 >> (regionInfo.x & 7);
40235         var offset = (i + regionInfo.y) * rowSize + (regionInfo.x >> 3);
40236         switch (combinationOperator) {
40237           case 0: // OR
40238             for (var j = 0; j < width; j++) {
40239               buffer[offset] |= bitmap[i][j] ? mask : 0;
40240               mask >>= 1;
40241               if (!mask) {
40242                 mask = 128;
40243                 offset++;
40244               }
40245             }
40246             break;
40247           case 2: // XOR
40248             for (var j = 0; j < width; j++) {
40249               buffer[offset] ^= bitmap[i][j] ? mask : 0;
40250               mask >>= 1;
40251               if (!mask) {
40252                 mask = 128;
40253                 offset++;
40254               }
40255             }
40256             break;
40257           default:
40258             error('JBIG2 error: operator ' + combinationOperator +
40259                   ' is not supported');
40260         }
40261       }
40262     },
40263     onImmediateGenericRegion:
40264       function SimpleSegmentVisitor_onImmediateGenericRegion(region, data,
40265                                                              start, end) {
40266       var regionInfo = region.info;
40267       var decodingContext = new DecodingContext(data, start, end);
40268       var bitmap = decodeBitmap(region.mmr, regionInfo.width, regionInfo.height,
40269                                 region.template, region.prediction, null,
40270                                 region.at, decodingContext);
40271       this.drawBitmap(regionInfo, bitmap);
40272     },
40273     onImmediateLosslessGenericRegion:
40274       function SimpleSegmentVisitor_onImmediateLosslessGenericRegion() {
40275       this.onImmediateGenericRegion.apply(this, arguments);
40276     },
40277     onSymbolDictionary:
40278       function SimpleSegmentVisitor_onSymbolDictionary(dictionary,
40279                                                        currentSegment,
40280                                                        referredSegments,
40281                                                        data, start, end) {
40282       var huffmanTables;
40283       if (dictionary.huffman)
40284         error('JBIG2 error: huffman is not supported');
40285 
40286       // Combines exported symbols from all referred segments
40287       var symbols = this.symbols;
40288       if (!symbols)
40289         this.symbols = symbols = {};
40290 
40291       var inputSymbols = [];
40292       for (var i = 0, ii = referredSegments.length; i < ii; i++)
40293         inputSymbols = inputSymbols.concat(symbols[referredSegments[i]]);
40294 
40295       var decodingContext = new DecodingContext(data, start, end);
40296       symbols[currentSegment] = decodeSymbolDictionary(dictionary.huffman,
40297         dictionary.refinement, inputSymbols, dictionary.numberOfNewSymbols,
40298         dictionary.numberOfExportedSymbols, huffmanTables,
40299         dictionary.template, dictionary.at,
40300         dictionary.refinementTemplate, dictionary.refinementAt,
40301         decodingContext);
40302     },
40303     onImmediateTextRegion:
40304       function SimpleSegmentVisitor_onImmediateTextRegion(region,
40305                                                           referredSegments,
40306                                                           data, start, end) {
40307       var regionInfo = region.info;
40308       var huffmanTables;
40309 
40310       // Combines exported symbols from all referred segments
40311       var symbols = this.symbols;
40312       var inputSymbols = [];
40313       for (var i = 0, ii = referredSegments.length; i < ii; i++)
40314         inputSymbols = inputSymbols.concat(symbols[referredSegments[i]]);
40315       var symbolCodeLength = log2(inputSymbols.length);
40316 
40317       var decodingContext = new DecodingContext(data, start, end);
40318       var bitmap = decodeTextRegion(region.huffman, region.refinement,
40319         regionInfo.width, regionInfo.height, region.defaultPixelValue,
40320         region.numberOfSymbolInstances, region.stripSize, inputSymbols,
40321         symbolCodeLength, region.transposed, region.dsOffset,
40322         region.referenceCorner, region.combinationOperator, huffmanTables,
40323         region.refinementTemplate, region.refinementAt, decodingContext);
40324       this.drawBitmap(regionInfo, bitmap);
40325     },
40326     onImmediateLosslessTextRegion:
40327       function SimpleSegmentVisitor_onImmediateLosslessTextRegion() {
40328         this.onImmediateTextRegion.apply(this, arguments);
40329     }
40330   };

40336       return parseJbig2Chunks(chunks);
40337     }
40338   };

40340   return Jbig2Image;

40394   function isOdd(i) {
40395     return (i & 1) !== 0;
40396   }
40397 
40398   function isEven(i) {
40399     return (i & 1) === 0;
40400   }
40401 
40402   function findUnequal(arr, start, value) {
40403     var j;
40404     for (var j = start, jj = arr.length; j < jj; ++j) {
40405       if (arr[j] != value)
40406         return j;
40407     }
40408     return j;
40409   }
40410 
40411   function setValues(arr, start, end, value) {
40412     for (var j = start; j < end; ++j) {
40413       arr[j] = value;
40414     }
40415   }
40416 
40417   function reverseValues(arr, start, end) {
40418     for (var i = start, j = end - 1; i < j; ++i, --j) {
40419       var temp = arr[i];
40420       arr[i] = arr[j];
40421       arr[j] = temp;
40422     }
40423   }
40424 
40425   function mirrorGlyphs(c) {
40426     /*
40427      # BidiMirroring-1.txt
40428      0028; 0029 # LEFT PARENTHESIS
40429      0029; 0028 # RIGHT PARENTHESIS
40430      003C; 003E # LESS-THAN SIGN
40431      003E; 003C # GREATER-THAN SIGN
40432      005B; 005D # LEFT SQUARE BRACKET
40433      005D; 005B # RIGHT SQUARE BRACKET
40434      007B; 007D # LEFT CURLY BRACKET
40435      007D; 007B # RIGHT CURLY BRACKET
40436      00AB; 00BB # LEFT-POINTING DOUBLE ANGLE QUOTATION MARK
40437      00BB; 00AB # RIGHT-POINTING DOUBLE ANGLE QUOTATION MARK
40438      */
40439     switch (c) {
40440       case '(':
40441         return ')';
40442       case ')':
40443         return '(';
40444       case '<':
40445         return '>';
40446       case '>':
40447         return '<';
40448       case ']':
40449         return '[';
40450       case '[':
40451         return ']';
40452       case '}':
40453         return '{';
40454       case '{':
40455         return '}';
40456       case '\u00AB':
40457         return '\u00BB';
40458       case '\u00BB':
40459         return '\u00AB';
40460       default:
40461         return c;
40462     }
40463   }
40464 
40465   function BidiResult(str, isLTR, vertical) {
40466     this.str = str;
40467     this.dir = vertical ? 'ttb' : isLTR ? 'ltr' : 'rtl';
40468   }
40469 
40470   function bidi(str, startLevel, vertical) {
40471     var isLTR = true;
40472     var strLength = str.length;
40473     if (strLength === 0 || vertical)
40474       return new BidiResult(str, isLTR, vertical);
40475 
40476     // get types, fill arrays
40477 
40478     var chars = [];
40479     var types = [];
40480     var oldtypes = [];
40481     var numBidi = 0;
40482 
40483     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40484       chars[i] = str.charAt(i);
40485 
40486       var charCode = str.charCodeAt(i);
40487       var charType = 'L';
40488       if (charCode <= 0x00ff)
40489         charType = baseTypes[charCode];
40490       else if (0x0590 <= charCode && charCode <= 0x05f4)
40491         charType = 'R';
40492       else if (0x0600 <= charCode && charCode <= 0x06ff)
40493         charType = arabicTypes[charCode & 0xff];
40494       else if (0x0700 <= charCode && charCode <= 0x08AC)
40495         charType = 'AL';
40496 
40497       if (charType == 'R' || charType == 'AL' || charType == 'AN')
40498         numBidi++;
40499 
40500       oldtypes[i] = types[i] = charType;
40501     }
40502 
40503     // detect the bidi method
40504     //  if there are no rtl characters then no bidi needed
40505     //  if less than 30% chars are rtl then string is primarily ltr
40506     //  if more than 30% chars are rtl then string is primarily rtl
40507     if (numBidi === 0) {
40508       isLTR = true;
40509       return new BidiResult(str, isLTR);
40510     }
40511 
40512     if (startLevel == -1) {
40513       if ((strLength / numBidi) < 0.3) {
40514         isLTR = true;
40515         startLevel = 0;
40516       } else {
40517         isLTR = false;
40518         startLevel = 1;
40519       }
40520     }
40521 
40522     var levels = [];
40523 
40524     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40525       levels[i] = startLevel;
40526     }
40527 
40528     /*
40529      X1-X10: skip most of this, since we are NOT doing the embeddings.
40530      */
40531 
40532     var e = isOdd(startLevel) ? 'R' : 'L';
40533     var sor = e;
40534     var eor = sor;
40535 
40536     /*
40537      W1. Examine each non-spacing mark (NSM) in the level run, and change the
40538      type of the NSM to the type of the previous character. If the NSM is at the
40539      start of the level run, it will get the type of sor.
40540      */
40541 
40542     var lastType = sor;
40543     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40544       if (types[i] == 'NSM')
40545         types[i] = lastType;
40546       else
40547         lastType = types[i];
40548     }
40549 
40550     /*
40551      W2. Search backwards from each instance of a European number until the
40552      first strong type (R, L, AL, or sor) is found.  If an AL is found, change
40553      the type of the European number to Arabic number.
40554      */
40555 
40556     var lastType = sor;
40557     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40558       var t = types[i];
40559       if (t == 'EN')
40560         types[i] = (lastType == 'AL') ? 'AN' : 'EN';
40561       else if (t == 'R' || t == 'L' || t == 'AL')
40562         lastType = t;
40563     }
40564 
40565     /*
40566      W3. Change all ALs to R.
40567      */
40568 
40569     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40570       var t = types[i];
40571       if (t == 'AL')
40572         types[i] = 'R';
40573     }
40574 
40575     /*
40576      W4. A single European separator between two European numbers changes to a
40577      European number. A single common separator between two numbers of the same
40578      type changes to that type:
40579      */
40580 
40581     for (var i = 1; i < strLength - 1; ++i) {
40582       if (types[i] == 'ES' && types[i - 1] == 'EN' && types[i + 1] == 'EN')
40583         types[i] = 'EN';
40584       if (types[i] == 'CS' && (types[i - 1] == 'EN' || types[i - 1] == 'AN') &&
40585           types[i + 1] == types[i - 1])
40586         types[i] = types[i - 1];
40587     }
40588 
40589     /*
40590      W5. A sequence of European terminators adjacent to European numbers changes
40591      to all European numbers:
40592      */
40593 
40594     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40595       if (types[i] == 'EN') {
40596         // do before
40597         for (var j = i - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
40598           if (types[j] != 'ET')
40599             break;
40600           types[j] = 'EN';
40601         }
40602         // do after
40603         for (var j = i + 1; j < strLength; --j) {
40604           if (types[j] != 'ET')
40605             break;
40606           types[j] = 'EN';
40607         }
40608       }
40609     }
40610 
40611     /*
40612      W6. Otherwise, separators and terminators change to Other Neutral:
40613      */
40614 
40615     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40616       var t = types[i];
40617       if (t == 'WS' || t == 'ES' || t == 'ET' || t == 'CS')
40618         types[i] = 'ON';
40619     }
40620 
40621     /*
40622      W7. Search backwards from each instance of a European number until the
40623      first strong type (R, L, or sor) is found. If an L is found,  then change
40624      the type of the European number to L.
40625      */
40626 
40627     var lastType = sor;
40628     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40629       var t = types[i];
40630       if (t == 'EN')
40631         types[i] = (lastType == 'L') ? 'L' : 'EN';
40632       else if (t == 'R' || t == 'L')
40633         lastType = t;
40634     }
40635 
40636     /*
40637      N1. A sequence of neutrals takes the direction of the surrounding strong
40638      text if the text on both sides has the same direction. European and Arabic
40639      numbers are treated as though they were R. Start-of-level-run (sor) and
40640      end-of-level-run (eor) are used at level run boundaries.
40641      */
40642 
40643     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40644       if (types[i] == 'ON') {
40645         var end = findUnequal(types, i + 1, 'ON');
40646         var before = sor;
40647         if (i > 0)
40648           before = types[i - 1];
40649         var after = eor;
40650         if (end + 1 < strLength)
40651           after = types[end + 1];
40652         if (before != 'L')
40653           before = 'R';
40654         if (after != 'L')
40655           after = 'R';
40656         if (before == after)
40657           setValues(types, i, end, before);
40658         i = end - 1; // reset to end (-1 so next iteration is ok)
40659       }
40660     }
40661 
40662     /*
40663      N2. Any remaining neutrals take the embedding direction.
40664      */
40665 
40666     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40667       if (types[i] == 'ON')
40668         types[i] = e;
40669     }
40670 
40671     /*
40672      I1. For all characters with an even (left-to-right) embedding direction,
40673      those of type R go up one level and those of type AN or EN go up two
40674      levels.
40675      I2. For all characters with an odd (right-to-left) embedding direction,
40676      those of type L, EN or AN go up one level.
40677      */
40678 
40679     for (var i = 0; i < strLength; ++i) {
40680       var t = types[i];
40681       if (isEven(levels[i])) {
40682         if (t == 'R') {
40683           levels[i] += 1;
40684         } else if (t == 'AN' || t == 'EN') {
40685           levels[i] += 2;
40686         }
40687       } else { // isOdd, so
40688         if (t == 'L' || t == 'AN' || t == 'EN') {
40689           levels[i] += 1;
40690         }
40691       }
40692     }
40693 
40694     /*
40695      L1. On each line, reset the embedding level of the following characters to
40696      the paragraph embedding level:
40697 
40698      segment separators,
40699      paragraph separators,
40700      any sequence of whitespace characters preceding a segment separator or
40701      paragraph separator, and any sequence of white space characters at the end
40702      of the line.
40703      */
40704 
40705     // don't bother as text is only single line
40706 
40707     /*
40708      L2. From the highest level found in the text to the lowest odd level on
40709      each line, reverse any contiguous sequence of characters that are at that
40710      level or higher.
40711      */
40712 
40713     // find highest level & lowest odd level
40714 
40715     var highestLevel = -1;
40716     var lowestOddLevel = 99;
40717     for (var i = 0, ii = levels.length; i < ii; ++i) {
40718       var level = levels[i];
40719       if (highestLevel < level)
40720         highestLevel = level;
40721       if (lowestOddLevel > level && isOdd(level))
40722         lowestOddLevel = level;
40723     }
40724 
40725     // now reverse between those limits
40726 
40727     for (var level = highestLevel; level >= lowestOddLevel; --level) {
40728       // find segments to reverse
40729       var start = -1;
40730       for (var i = 0, ii = levels.length; i < ii; ++i) {
40731         if (levels[i] < level) {
40732           if (start >= 0) {
40733             reverseValues(chars, start, i);
40734             start = -1;
40735           }
40736         } else if (start < 0) {
40737           start = i;
40738         }
40739       }
40740       if (start >= 0) {
40741         reverseValues(chars, start, levels.length);
40742       }
40743     }
40744 
40745     /*
40746      L3. Combining marks applied to a right-to-left base character will at this
40747      point precede their base character. If the rendering engine expects them to
40748      follow the base characters in the final display process, then the ordering
40749      of the marks and the base character must be reversed.
40750      */
40751 
40752     // don't bother for now
40753 
40754     /*
40755      L4. A character that possesses the mirrored property as specified by
40756      Section 4.7, Mirrored, must be depicted by a mirrored glyph if the resolved
40757      directionality of that character is R.
40758      */
40759 
40760     // don't mirror as characters are already mirrored in the pdf
40761 
40762     // Finally, return string
40763 
40764     var result = '';
40765     for (var i = 0, ii = chars.length; i < ii; ++i) {
40766       var ch = chars[i];
40767       if (ch != '<' && ch != '>')
40768         result += ch;
40769     }
40770 
40771     return new BidiResult(result, isLTR);
40772   }
40773 
40774   return bidi;
40775 })();
40776

40779 var Metadata = PDFJS.Metadata = (function MetadataClosure() {
40780   function fixMetadata(meta) {
40781     return meta.replace(/>\\376\\377([^<]+)/g, function(all, codes) {
40782       var bytes = codes.replace(/\\([0-3])([0-7])([0-7])/g,
40783                                 function(code, d1, d2, d3) {
40784         return String.fromCharCode(d1 * 64 + d2 * 8 + d3 * 1);
40785       });
40786       var chars = '';
40787       for (var i = 0; i < bytes.length; i += 2) {
40788         var code = bytes.charCodeAt(i) * 256 + bytes.charCodeAt(i + 1);
40789         chars += code >= 32 && code < 127 && code != 60 && code != 62 &&
40790           code != 38 && false ? String.fromCharCode(code) :
40791           '&#x' + (0x10000 + code).toString(16).substring(1) + ';';
40792       }
40793       return '>' + chars;
40794     });
40795   }
40796 
40797   function Metadata(meta) {
40798     if (typeof meta === 'string') {
40799       // Ghostscript produces invalid metadata
40800       meta = fixMetadata(meta);
40801 
40802       var parser = new DOMParser();
40803       meta = parser.parseFromString(meta, 'application/xml');
40804     } else if (!(meta instanceof Document)) {
40805       error('Metadata: Invalid metadata object');
40806     }
40807 
40808     this.metaDocument = meta;
40809     this.metadata = {};
40810     this.parse();
40811   }
40812 
40813   Metadata.prototype = {
40814     parse: function Metadata_parse() {
40815       var doc = this.metaDocument;
40816       var rdf = doc.documentElement;
40817 
40818       if (rdf.nodeName.toLowerCase() !== 'rdf:rdf') { // Wrapped in <xmpmeta>
40819         rdf = rdf.firstChild;
40820         while (rdf && rdf.nodeName.toLowerCase() !== 'rdf:rdf')
40821           rdf = rdf.nextSibling;
40822       }
40823 
40824       var nodeName = (rdf) ? rdf.nodeName.toLowerCase() : null;
40825       if (!rdf || nodeName !== 'rdf:rdf' || !rdf.hasChildNodes())
40826         return;
40827 
40828       var children = rdf.childNodes, desc, entry, name, i, ii, length, iLength;
40829 
40830       for (i = 0, length = children.length; i < length; i++) {
40831         desc = children[i];
40832         if (desc.nodeName.toLowerCase() !== 'rdf:description')
40833           continue;
40834 
40835         for (ii = 0, iLength = desc.childNodes.length; ii < iLength; ii++) {
40836           if (desc.childNodes[ii].nodeName.toLowerCase() !== '#text') {
40837             entry = desc.childNodes[ii];
40838             name = entry.nodeName.toLowerCase();
40839             this.metadata[name] = entry.textContent.trim();
40840           }
40841         }
40842       }
40843     },
40844 
40845     get: function Metadata_get(name) {
40846       return this.metadata[name] || null;
40847     },
40848 
40849     has: function Metadata_has(name) {
40850       return typeof this.metadata[name] !== 'undefined';
40851     }
40852   };
40853 
40854   return Metadata;
40855 })();
